(91, 'barbara g', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1036285279-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Ambience lover', 'Great food, ambience and service( served well by Charles)!‚Ä¶....................................‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..........', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(92, 'Kerith L', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1036138842-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'A lovely meal!', 'Delicious fresh food! The lamb shank was our favorite! Also enjoyed the harvest salad and Tuscan bean soup.  Lovely atmosphere. Dennis Onunga waited on us - 5 stars for him!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(93, 'Yevi O', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1035993512-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great food, great service!', 'Very good restaurant and nice location in the Village market. I was served by Onunga who was very professional and friendly. Very good man! The food was fabulous and well presented. Such a welcome break after a hectic morning!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(94, 'Passport32427177290', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1035361268-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'A perfect afternoon with amazing service', 'I had the best experience at Harvest Restaurant. The atmosphere was calm and beautiful, and the food was delicious and perfectly prepared. I was served by Iggy, who was kind, attentive, and made sure everything was just right. The team made us feel welcome from the moment we arrived. It‚Äôs definitely a place I‚Äôd recommend for anyone looking to enjoy a relaxed and memorable meal in Nairobi. I‚Äôll be coming back soon.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(95, 'Ingrid Rose', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1035356721-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Superb!!!', 'The service was excellent. Always ready to attend to customers\' concerns. Thank you Bernice and Chef Moha for a job well done.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(96, 'ann m', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1034475048-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great Ambiance and Delicious Food!', 'My friend and I had a wonderful time at the Harvest restaurant.Our waiter Kiarie definitely stood out! He was exceptionally friendly, offered great food and drink suggestions, and handled everything with such professionalism.kudos to the chef for a delicious meal and thank you to the Harvest team for making our experience memorable!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(97, 'Cherop C', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1034364737-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'My dinning experience at Harvest', 'Loved dinning at the Harvest Restaurant. The food was amazing, never had such amazing Roasted Pork Belly. Our server, Mr. Onunga was such a delight, polite and very professional. The ambience and the crown of it all, the saxophonist who played some of my favourite old gems made my visit to this restaurant heavenly. Definitely going back!!!!! ü§ó', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(98, 'M Gitau', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1033524794-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Nice Service', 'The hotel experience was good, but it was amplified by our Server Grace, who had so much grace and patience. And even helped us our with recommendations', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(99, 'Angel G', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1033524505-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Exceptional Service', 'Great experience. Grace was exceptional, attentive, gave great advice on the food. Overall amazing service and dining.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(100, 'JustKevo', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1032529315-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Good food and great service.', 'The portions were generous, the food was tasty, and the service was superb. We were celebrating a friend\'s 50th, and the team at the Harvester accommodated our plans. Special thanks to our server, Iggy Masingu.  He was attentive to our many demands and dealt with us professionally, with patience and a smile.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(101, 'Phylis k', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1031557240-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Dinner at Harvest', 'Went to Harvest for dinner.The entrance was warm and we got a nice seat.Our server was Higgy who offered exceptional service..he gave us really good recommendations for both food and drinks.He also checked on us after every course asking us if we were enjoying our meal.He is also really funny omg!\nWe really enjoyed our food and drinks..the ambience the service.To wrap.it up everything was A1.I would highly recommend the restaurant and Higgy of course!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(102, 'Reuben M', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1031485618-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Birthday Lunch with Family', 'We were warmly received by the hostess Stellamaris . She took time to explain the menu to us very professionally. \nHyginius, our host, was patient with us as we deliberate on what to order. We were spolit for choices but he guided us skillfully.\nThe food was amazing and the cheese cake was delicious.  Amazing love from the team leaders Mercy and Gibson who constantly checked on us. We will definitely be back. Thank you for making my daugters birthday memorable.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(103, 'Sara Nzilani Mu... M', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1031146258-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Best steak house in town', 'The steaks here are to die for.\nChef got them as we like them, tender and juicy. Service was impeccable,Kiarie and Harrison made our evening even better. Drinks were on point. Kudos harvest!!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(104, 'Explore09059149031', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1031122839-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Efficient team! Food was yummy', 'We had an excellent experience, and a big part of that was thanks to Christina. From the moment we were seated, she was attentive, friendly, and incredibly professional. \n\nShe and the team, took the time to explain and answer all our questions with a smile, and made great recommendations that we ended up loving\n\nWhat really stood out was their timing‚Äîdrinks and food arrived promptly, and they checked in just the right amount without being intrusive. It\'s rare to find service this smooth and genuine.\n\nThank you for making our day a success.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(105, 'Mwalo M', 'Limuru Road The Village Market, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Harvest Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15213862-r1031073248-Harvest_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great service', 'Great service from \nFaith ndea.. You wouldn\'t know she\'s a trainee ‚ò∫Ô∏è\n\nI love the tea at harvest and the service is smooth and warm\n\nHappy to come back again', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(106, 'Maryann Mathenge', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r1031335135-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Incredible!', 'I took my family to Hob House to celebrate my son‚Äôs 23rd birthday, and honestly, it was *magical*! üéâ Even though it was a last-minute plan, the dinner delivery absolutely blew us away ‚Äî every single dish was packed with flavor and so much love. The chef truly outdid himself and made our night unforgettable. üë®‚Äçüç≥üî•\n\nWe devoured some amazing dishes:\n\n* **Zaatar Manoushe** ‚Äî warm Lebanese flatbread with zaatar (a herby mix of thyme, sumac & sesame seeds). Simple but SO good! ü´ìüåø\n* **Armenian Lahmbajine** ‚Äî like Armenian pizza, thin bread topped with juicy minced meat & spices. Comfort food at its best. üçïüçñ\n* **Falafel Salad** ‚Äî crispy falafel balls on fresh greens, crunchy and fresh, the perfect balance. ü•ó‚ú®\n* **Lebanese Trio of Dips** ‚Äî creamy hummus, smoky baba ghanoush, and tangy labneh ‚Äî all absolute flavor bombs! üòçüßÜ\n* **Shish Taouk** ‚Äî juicy, garlicky grilled chicken skewers that were pure smoky heaven. üç¢üí•\n* **Lamb Harira** ‚Äî rich, slow-cooked lamb stew, warm and full of comforting spices ‚Äî like a big cozy hug in a bowl. üç≤‚ù§Ô∏è\n\nAnd of course, wine to toast the night ü•Çüç∑. What really made the celebration extra special was when the Hob House team surprised my son by singing *Happy Birthday* to him  the love and joy in that moment was everything. üé∂üéÇü•≥\n\nI‚Äôm at Hob House at least once a month, and honestly, every visit is a fresh, amazing experience. So much love for this place it really feels like home every time. If you haven‚Äôt been yet, do yourself a favor and go! You won‚Äôt regret it. üíØüôå', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"delivery_takeout\"]'),
(107, 'Mzungubabe', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r1026594384-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely garden restaurant', 'A quiet oasis set in lush gardens. Tasty food, although I enjoyed the starters and dessert more than the main course, which was overly spicy.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(108, 'Rebeca P', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r1022597900-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Delicious dinner off the beaten path', 'We went for dinner at the recommendation of a friend of a friend. It is in a surprising location, and well worth the effort to find one‚Äôs way to it. Beautiful patio and delicious food with wonderful variety! Service was very friendly and prompt. Would definitely return!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(109, 'H Fisher', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r989432363-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'A beautiful, comfortable oasis with an amazing restaurant', 'A beautiful, comfortable, oasis just outside the centre of Nairobi. The garden is beautiful, so peaceful, and the food is amazing. The staff are very friendly and professional. We stay three nights and ate supper here twice. Breakfasts in the garden were a delicious treat as was the picnic breakfast they packed for us when we had to leave early, and so generous. The flavours of the evening meals were outstanding. A lovely place to stay with an exceptional restaurant and a commitment to sustainability and sourcing organic ingredients.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(110, 'Donna', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r986603416-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'An Oasis of the Levant on the Kenyan Coast', 'The new Hob House in Malindi is a welcome addition to the coast, adding much-needed diversity to the food scene. It is an oasis on the coast offering superb serenity in a verdant garden. The service is impeccable, and the food is delectable and fresh, transporting one to the Levant. Kelly, the owner and manager, is straight from the source and brings Lebanon to us with her flair for decor, exquisite taste, and talent for offering genuinely authentic food. It has become my favorite hob (love) house for a relaxing lunch and great company as Kelly is the \"hostess with the mostess.\"', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(111, 'africanman_840', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r950110017-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', '2nd visit but disappointed.', 'I went to the branch at Riverside Drive for the second time. The food was alright but there was a major problem because half of the drinks and some dishes on the menu were missing.\nFurthermore, the service was nothing special.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(112, 'Jonathan Abi Gerges', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r939516893-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Food and Love that are bound together.', 'Walking into this restaurant, you‚Äôre wrapped in a hug of warmth and coziness that feels like coming home. The place is lit softly, decorated with love, making every corner inviting and every meal feel like a family gathering. \n\nBut the real heart-stealer is their Koussa. This dish, a playful twist on a Lebanese classic, carries the warmth of tradition with a spark of something new. \n\nKelly, the owner, makes you feel seen, with smiles that welcome you back even if it‚Äôs your first time.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(113, 'Copperline G', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r939410877-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Unprofessional staff and infrastructure', 'Awful, unfriendly and very slow servers. The lights went of 2 times during the diner. And they only opend til 10:30 instead of the described 23:00. food was okay. Wouldnt recommend this place to anyone.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(114, 'Sudeshan R', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r916578790-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'An elegant oasis', 'What a delightful evening at this gem of a place that feels off the beaten track and yet is not inaccessible. The warm welcome from the owner of this establishment coupled with the friendly staff added to the warm ambience. Our meals were delicious - and the milky rose drink was sublime. Highly recommended for an elegant evening seated among the trees', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(115, 'Moreno', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r910079281-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'New opening in Malindi, Kenya!', 'After many days eating dull Italian food in Malindi, we had the best libanese experience ever. Kelly lead us by the hand on an amazing taste journey. Staff is very courteous and the venue itself is just amazing. Highly recommended!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(116, 'GlobetrottingSwede', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r905391080-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Good restaurant, average lodging', 'We stayed for 3 nights while visiting Nairobi. The rooms are a bit run down and where probably at their peak 20 years ago.\n\nIt seems that the main business is the restaurant, which is busy with groups every day. Food is tasty Lebanese and Mediterranean.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(117, 'Avni', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r891629959-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Best Lebanese food with a warm family welcome ', 'Dinner on 6th May  with family whilst visiting Nairobi.\nTruly amazing place, food was delicious and to blessed with the company of Kelly at our table sharing her wonderful and interesting stories. Thank you Kelly for making us feel part of your family.\nGreat finish to our penultimate day in Kenya.\nA special note for the best apple pie ever!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(118, 'Siddharth Patel', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r874006091-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Blown Away by the best Lebanese Food!', 'Where do I start?\nThe vibes, the food, the service, the personal touch by the owner = BRILLIANT!\nThe best and most authentic Lebanese food in Nairobi!\nIt was my first time at the restaurant, and it exceeded all my expectations.\nI will definitely be going to this place a lot more now!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(119, 'RichWilx', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r871429607-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Unforgettable.  An absolute delight.', 'A hidden delight, tucked away on Kinanda Road, we were told that this restaurant has been here for over 7 years. \n\nEntering the colonial style house, you pass though a small gift shop featuring local products and crafts and are led through veranda dining areas into the garden where each table is uniquely nestled under the trees.  Colourful birds flutter around the trees and rest on the parasols that shade you from the sun:\n\nEach table has comfortable, cushioned, garden style seats and is laid out with delicate blue silk napkins.  A small tray of condiments sits on the table.\n\nThe effect is relaxing.  Lost is the sense that you are in Nairobi.  Rather, you could be nestled in the tranquil gardens of a home on the Litani river.\n\nYou will spend time here.  Each dish is prepared from scratch and nothing is rushed.  Perfumed seasonings are the order of the day here and, if you arrive hungry, your nose will be titillated with the scents coming from the kitchen while you wait.\n\nThe dishes live up to the surroundings, delicate flavours , beautifully prepared, are delivered in every mouthful. \n\nDesserts were not treated with any less respect.  Every element from pastry to sauce were homemade, delicious, and memorable.\n\nThis may well be my favourite restaurant in Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"delivery_takeout\"]'),
(120, 'mbuckanoff', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r865354782-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Five star food.  Five star setting.  Five star service', 'Off the beaten path but very much worth the trip.  I wish we were there with more than two people so we could try more food.   But highly recommend the mezze sampler.   And they now have a limited wine list which was a bonus', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(121, 'Yusuf Reja', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r865253019-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'The best experience I have had in Nairobi', 'Absolutely lovely place to stay and dine.  The best place I have every stayed and dine in Kenya.  Beautiful garden, clean and cozy rooms, it feels like home, excellent customer services, polite and professional staffs, quite responsive and accommodating; delusions food.  The host Kelly and Peter are lovely couple and always ready to help.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(122, 'Andrea', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r863671991-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'One of the best food experiences in Nairobi', 'Absolutely gorgeous garden with a variety of plants and birds to watch as you enjoy the fantastic tasty food this reatuarant has to offer! Highly recommended, we will be back for sure.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(123, 'Marijana E', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r861564837-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Beautiful setting and friendly service', 'I absolutely loved the beautiful garden setting  with flowers and greenery surrounding you. Also each table is secluded so you can enjoy some privacy whilst dining. Unfortunately I didn‚Äôt like the food so much. I have had Lebanese cuisine a few times before so it wasn‚Äôt my first time, but this time it just lacked something. If it had been my first time to try it I would probably not attempt to try it a second time.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(124, 'hcb81', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r839351889-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'Great Lebanese food', 'Really enjoyed our meal here. It‚Äôs a beautiful garden setting. The inside areas are really well designed. The food was fresh, delicious and very authentic. Will return', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(125, 'Moiz H', 'Kinanda Road Kitisuru, Nairobi 00621 Kenya', 'Hob House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12394465-r821019394-Hob_House-Nairobi.html', 'A unique experience!', 'Visited hob house with the family last night. The service we received was excellent. Food was also very different, very unique and very delicious. The atmosphere was very chic. The string lights and all the paintings gave off a very rustic vibe. The waiters however need to be a little more informative on how to help first time visitors. Overall a pleasant Saturday night for my family. Highly recommend Hob House be visited by all at least once, we surely will be visiting again.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(126, 'Jamaldin O', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r973514363-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Drug peddlers everywhere ‚Ä¶ disgusted by this place to be honest', 'If you are looking for Weed and Cocain , this is the kind of establishment you go to . Today on 11th October was too much drug usage', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(127, 'Offshore Canuck', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r964606564-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Fantastic Live Music great atmosphere', 'Great Vibe and Live Music.  Weekends rock but weekdays are slow as one would expect with the work week.\n\nI avoided the line ups by going early.\n\nAte a burger from Mama\'s (sp) very tasty I must admit.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(128, 'Helena P', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r962040004-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Very nice!', 'Had a burger in my own. The staff was very nice. They have a bit screen playing sports, which was nice when being alone! Will come back for some drinks.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(129, 'Brian', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r958720488-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Cool vibes / great bar', 'Attending a live musical performance of MaKadem!   He played for three hours straight - amazing!!!   cool vibes, great staff an excellent bar options.   This is the place to chill in Westlands.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"events_entertainment\"]'),
(130, 'richj65', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r951546861-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'The good place to get a meal and socialize. ', 'The atmosphere is pleasant, and there are a multitude of things to do before going upstairs to the disco. I suggest that you sit back and get something to eat while taking in the vibe.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\"]'),
(131, 'Safe Adventures and Expeditions', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r946406797-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Vibrant Night at The Alchemist Bar, Nairobi', 'Located on Parklands Road, The Alchemist Bar offers an unforgettable night of music and drinks.\n\nThe atmosphere is vibrant, with stylish d√©cor and cozy outdoor seating.\n\nMusic is eclectic and keeps the dance floor lively.\n\nDrinks are varied and expertly crafted.\n\nThe sense of community adds to the experience.\n\nOverall, The Alchemist Bar delivers an exceptional night out.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(132, 'Floicy A', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r941133566-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Very nice bar ', 'Nice place, good vibes, good drinks. Good people.  Enough security. Fairly clean toilets. I love it a lot . I\'ll definitely be going back', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(133, 'YoJat', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r920184435-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'A nice place for drinks, good vibe', 'Great place for a casual night for drinks, relaxed, good music, chill vibe.\n\nGood cocktails, happy hour price is good but the hours are in the afternoon not evening which is silly.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(134, 'DD S', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r919632349-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Tasty refreshing cocktails,  chilled rooftop bar vibes and good music!', 'Tasty refreshing cocktails and this cool bar also has happy hour :-) There\'s also some great music inc. some classic rnb and hip tracks thrown in. The live DJ set adds to the atmosphere, and there is a good mix of people, chilled rooftop bar vibes and tasty drinks! Excellent choice to catch up with friends or date night ;-) The staff are really friendly and the service was on point. We will be coming again when next in Nairobi for sure!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(135, 'JNelsonRedSoxFan', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r910159052-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Best cocktails in Nairobi', 'Having tried several of the places in Nairobi, Alchemist stands out as my favorite among pretty tough competition.  The huge subdivided venue has something for everyone, but I found my home in the upstairs lounge where they make proper whiskey sours and old fashioned.  ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(136, 'Nora T', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r909872381-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Letting in Minors', 'Absolutely horrible. They don‚Äôt check ID‚Äôs properly, and are inconsistent when letting people in. Multiple minors have been let in (specifically girls), who can easily get inappropriately approached by older men. Meanwhile people over the age of 18 are held back, which are people who are adults; allowed to legally drink according to the Kenyan Law, and who can give consent. This is despicable, and they need to put a new reasonable system in place! ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(137, 'Lonelynomad', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r830477957-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Just Electric!', 'The place is simply lively throughout. The food and the drinks all are at par with the ambience and the music and fun in this club!! They also have a saloon on the 1st deck... The juggling, drinks and the food all are just just amazing!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(138, 'Aditya M', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r823016537-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Active and fun', 'The place has the vibe ...it has energy and is fun ... a cool hangout . The burger shacks had good juicy fresh burgers . Music is good , the place is divided in sections and has corners with interesting stories.  will be back . Definately recommended .  \n  ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(139, 'Mahaut', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r796483154-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Bar sympa ', 'L‚Äôambiance de l‚ÄôAlchemist est g√©niale, avec diff√©rents DJ qui font danser tout le monde. Les prix sont raisonnables mais les cocktails ne sont pas vraiment bons... Cependant le vin et les bi√®res sont bons. Le cadre est tr√®s agr√©ables, les canap√©s sont confortables et vous rencontrez facilement de nouvelles personnes. \nJe recommande ce lieu si vous voulez passer une bonne soir√©e entre amis. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\"]'),
(140, 'Capellanus', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r783705605-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'The Best Bar in Westlands', 'The Alchemist is a great place to spend a few hours and worth the repeat visits.  Set up in a courtyard among large trees and plants, it really gives you an great outdoor feel, enjoying the sun and breeze in comfort.\n\nThe bar has access to a few food vendors, all of whom will visit your table with a menu and take your order.  Spanish tapas, pizza, wings and one of the best burger experiences in Nairobi are all there.  \n\nThe Happy Hour runs from 1pm to 6pm and the prices cannot be beat.  Weekends get rather busy late afternoon, so come early to grab your favourite spot; but there is usually lots of room upstairs.\n\nA must see.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(141, 'Marija J', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r735374273-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Nice place', 'I love this place because I ate there best deep fried bananas :) I enjoyed bars and few nice shops, really good place to take a break.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(142, 'Janelle J', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r734663211-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Night at the Alchemist', 'I went here for my last night in Nairobi. The popular African pop group Elani was the live music for the evening. There are food trucks and vendors when you first enter the bar. Waitstaff was a bit rude but the veggie burger was tasty. Visit the Alchemist for a taste of Nairobi nightlife! ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(143, 'Whitney', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r723165558-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Great spot on a Friday night !', 'It a great place to go for the evening or at night!There are 3 bars and 3 food trucks all in one compound. We got there around 7 and first ate dinner and chilled. The Mexican food truck had good vegetarian tacos although they are spicy which they didn‚Äôt tell us when we ordered. The Kenyan chicken burger at the burger food truck was excellent! One of the best burgers we have had in Kenya!  Overall the place has great customer service! You can sit anywhere in the compound and services from all the food trucks will  come to your table and you order from them. We went on a Friday and around 9 the Dj starts playing and the place turns into a club so you can hit the dance floor. It was a great evening ! ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(144, 'TheTaskin', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r717398219-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Nairbo‚Äôs hottest chilling spot', 'Nairobi, with its security issues, still has some fantastic places. \nThe alchemist has 3 bars and 3 food carts inside a compound. Nice place with fun cocktails n bears. They also do great burgers. \nWe went to Mulberry which is on level 2. I had really good old fashioned ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(145, 'Besa', 'Parklands Road Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'The Alchemist Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10290440-r715730978-The_Alchemist_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'Be sure you check your bill', 'Awful food from the German Sausage place. Cold und not cooked. After complaining about it you will still get the full bill. \nThe Alchemist Bar waiters a ripping you off and you better check your bill and at what time the happy hour starts. And if you complain you will be called a liar. I‚Äôm was going there for more than a year now, but the quality and service is going down. This is also including the hygiene. ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(146, 'Mercy K', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r734720132-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Pathetic customer service', 'Visited Spurs Eagle at Eka hotel Mombasa road on 26th December 2019. Placed our order,had starter and some dawa as we wait. After one hour our meal was yet to be served. Following up on the order no one seemed to concerned about it,they were like \"wait you will be served\" after how long? 2-3 hours? Is that when we shall eat? I visited the place hungry,left the place angry.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(147, 'Takashi Y', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r731221346-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Eka Hotel„Å´ÂÆøÊ≥ä„Åó„Å¶„ÅÑ„ÅüÂ§ú„Å´Âà©Áî®„Åó„Åæ„Åó„Åü„ÄÇ', 'Eka Hotel„Å´ÂÆøÊ≥ä„Åó„Å¶„ÅÑ„ÅüÂ§ú„Å´Âà©Áî®„Åó„Åæ„Åó„Åü„ÄÇ\n„ÉÅ„Çß„Éº„É≥Â∫ó„ÅÆÂÆâÂÆöÊÑü„Åå„Çä„Çπ„ÉÜ„ÉºÔøΩÔøΩ„ÇíÈ£ü„Åπ„Åü„ÅÑ„Å™„ÇâÊâãËªΩ„Å´Âà©Áî®Âá∫Êù•„ÄÅ‰æ°Ê†º„ÇÇ„É™„Éº„Ç∫„Éä„Éñ„É´„Å™„ÅÆ„Åß„Åä„Çπ„Çπ„É°„Åß„Åô„ÄÇÂ§ú„ÅØ11ÊôÇ„Åæ„ÅßÂñ∂Ê•≠„Åó„Å¶„Åä„ÇäÂ§úÈÅÖ„Åè„Å™„Å£„Å¶„ÇÇOK„Åß„Åô„ÄÇ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(148, 'Livono', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r726781649-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Disappointed lunch ', 'We were off for lunch today and we thought lets do this place at Eka Hotel. When we arrived the place was not busy at all and it was poorly lit. We came to be told there was no power( understandable. Being inside Eka one would expect to have a standby generator. I ordered for a latte and my partner a milk shake. The waitress told ua we wont get the latte in 10 minutes as they sort power. So we ordered their famous pork ribs, spinach, ugali and onion rings. The place was virtually empty and we thought quick service right? Well wrong. 20 minutes later no latte and no shake. Upon asking whats up, my partner was brought the \'shake\' which was actually 2 scoops of ice cream and orio planted on top. Not a milk shake as you would expect. Further asking if our food was ready we were told it hasnt been prepared and our guess was right due to power( yet music was playing which i was told doesnt use powerüôÑüôÑüôÑ). So we decided to have the ice cream and pay for it and leave now that we wont have the meal. Which in record few minutes we were brought the ribs but not as per the standard and with wrong accompaniments.A different group had come after us and got their meals before us yet they had same order like us. On sharing the same thoughts to the team it became a needless excuses session.  Disappointed and without any communication on the progress of our meals we had to leave and cancel what was otherwise meant to be an excited lunch session. Hopefully next time with power on i will still get to enjoy their pork ribs with my spinach and ugali(which dont need electricity  to cook). ', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(149, '40701', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r726533384-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Very nice restaurant', 'This is a very nice restaurant attached to the Eka Hotel.\n serving great steaks and burgers and the onion bits are to die for.\nWe found it a little noisy but still enjoyed our food', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(150, 'Christian', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r724930743-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Average food', 'We BBO ribs and a so called NY cut steak with chips and fried onions. The ribs was ok but the steak was never a NY cut and the meat quality was average. The chips and onion rings were just a little warm and not crispy at all. Service was very good and friendly. The competitor next door has a better meat quality.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(151, '982rodneyl', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r724486564-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Good food, good beer, good service', 'Located right in Eka Hotel. We had dinner while overnighting prior to leaving on a 2 week Safari. We had Hanging kebob and calamari, both were excellent washed down with Tusker beer. Friendly efficient service. The only disconcerting thing was the North American Indian motif and decorations - we thought we had made a wrong turn and were in Arizona instead of Kenya!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(152, 'Corinne Berneman', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r698936282-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent beef', 'I received excellent service and advice on which type of meat to choose. I had no idea there were so many varieties!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(153, 'Susan A', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r676591602-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Great food', 'As a traveling American, it was interesting to see a steakhouse in Nairobi.  The food was great and the staff were friendly and helpful.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(154, '365GT4-BB', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r670716835-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Êù•„Å¶ËâØ„Åã„Å£„Åü„Å®ÂÆüÊÑü„Åó„Åæ„Åô„ÄÇ', 'EKA„Éõ„ÉÜ„É´„ÅÆ‰∏≠„Å´„ÅÇ„Çã„Çπ„ÉÜ„Éº„Ç≠„Éè„Ç¶„Çπ„Åß„Åô„ÄÇÂ∫óÂÜÖ„ÅØ„ÄÅÂåóÁ±≥„Å´„Çà„Åè„ÅÇ„Çã„Çπ„ÉÜ„Éº„Ç≠„Éè„Ç¶„Çπ„Å®„Éï„Ç°„Éü„É¨„Çπ„ÇíÂêà„Çè„Åõ„ÅüÊßò„Å™Èõ∞Âõ≤Ê∞ó„Åß„Åô„ÄÇ‰ªäÂõû„Ç™„Éº„ÉÄ„Éº„Åó„Åü„ÅÆ„ÅØ„Éä„ÉÅ„Éß„Çπ„Åß„Åó„Åü„ÅåÁæéÂë≥„Åó„ÅèÈ†Ç„Åç„Åæ„Åó„Åü„ÄÇ„Åó„Åã„Åó„ÄÅÁ¥†Êô¥„Çâ„Åó„ÅÑ„ÅÆ„ÅØÊñôÁêÜ„ÇÇ„Åù„ÅÜ„Åß„Åô„Åå„ÄÅ„Çπ„Çø„ÉÉ„Éï„ÅÆÁöÜ„Åï„Çì„ÅÆÂØæÂøú„Åß„Åô„Å≠\nÊù•„Å¶„Çà„Åã„Å£„Åü„Å®ÂÆüÊÑü„Åó„Åæ„Åô„ÄÇ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(155, 'AamirSK', 'Eka Hotel, Mombasa Road, Highway Estate, Nairobi 00623 Kenya', 'Soaring Eagle Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4020263-r658102941-Soaring_Eagle_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Greats steaks ', 'Amazing steaks as always at the Spurs the quality and quantity is always good and satisfying \nnever go wrong with the cheddar melt though i had ordered the 300grms but dint seem like it \nThe chicken strips and cheesy prawns we had as a starter was very nice \nService was good the staff every smiling and as the one who initially served us had ended her shift came to inform us and also handed us to her colleague \nIt was a good dining experience ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(156, 'Marco S', 'Dagoretti Karen Hub, Nairobi Kenya', 'La Cascina', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10140471-r997254092-La_Cascina-Nairobi.html', 'Lunch at La Cascina', 'We found this restaurant at the mall, at the end of a safari, on the way back to Nairobi. It\'s amazing and well handled. I recommend the calamari with shrimps, very well done.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"overall_experience\"]'),
(157, 'Expat Kate', 'Dagoretti Karen Hub, Nairobi Kenya', 'La Cascina', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10140471-r996595513-La_Cascina-Nairobi.html', 'Great Cheesecake', 'Scouting for a good cheesecake in Nairobi hasn‚Äôt been easy. \n\nLast week I approved of @harvestrestaurant_  classic New York Classic Cheesecake and this week I am happy to share that I approve of La Cascina\'s Strawberry Cheesecake.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(158, 'christine a', 'Dagoretti Karen Hub, Nairobi Kenya', 'La Cascina', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10140471-r986367689-La_Cascina-Nairobi.html', 'Pathetic customer care and  services', 'Service was 0/10.   The waiters kept ignoring us. They brought our order in rounds and simple things like ice came to us after waiting for like 40 minutes. What was most annoying was the lack of responsiveness and total dis regard for customer care. Wouldn\'t recommend  at all.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(159, 'Venture49511725949', 'Dagoretti Karen Hub, Nairobi Kenya', 'La Cascina', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10140471-r980306094-La_Cascina-Nairobi.html', 'Truly Awful', 'We came here in a downpour so it wasn\'t planned and we will never return. Honestly the worst Italian restaurant I have ever been to. And I have worked in and eaten in many. The Caprese salad was unrecognisable as such... solid chunks of rubbery mozarella and chunks, rather than slices, of unripe tomatoes served with an afterthought of roasted vegetables. The wine by the glass was overpriced and dreadful. The lasagne looked like burnt sh*t on a plate. The top layer was dry bolognese and the b√©chamel below looked like there was \"plastic\" sliced cheese in it. Indescribably bad. If I was the Italian owner of this restaurant I would be embarrassed', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\"]'),
(160, 'Esther M', 'Dagoretti Karen Hub, Nairobi Kenya', 'La Cascina', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10140471-r972746107-La_Cascina-Nairobi.html', '4/10', 'Visited there yesterday,was surprised to get all male waiters! Don\'t know what\'s up with that.The service was a solid 1/10,they were happy to serve the more fairer(white) people in the restaurant,I had to wait too long for just an iced coffee.\nThe pizza was okay,I expected better for an Italian restaurant The ice cream was good.Overall I would give it 4/10,just for the ice cream', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(161, 'Arpit Bansal', 'Dagoretti Karen Hub, Nairobi Kenya', 'La Cascina', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10140471-r912606374-La_Cascina-Nairobi.html', 'Good Italian experience', 'Good food, vegetarian friendly menu as well. Italian food is authentic and reasonably priced. Overall a good value for money', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]');
