(440, 'Road26400339602', '154 James Gichuru Road, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The Other Room Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d21236043-r1018707938-The_Other_Room_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'True Gem', 'This is that rare instance where I was moved to stop what I was doing to render a review in real time.  Still sitting at the table, having just completed my meal, I can\'t hold back my excitement regarding my experience at Social House-The Other Room.  I live in Southern California, the land of salads, but I can safely say I just had the best Chicken Cobb Salad of my lifetime!  This fantastic meal was only rivaled by the all-around fantastic service I received upon entry. There were three staffers however who went above and beyond the standards of first rate service.  Donella, the manager, led the way as an amazing floor general, checking in and making sure all culinary needs were being met.  Elizabeth followed up with a great smile and warm hospitality.  And my server Maurine was fantastic in her own right keeping me abreast of all menu options and providing swift delivery of food/beverages with steady follow-up.  The vibe here is highly comfortable yet uber classy.  I\'m an instant fan, and so too shall you be once you give this gem location the shot it deserves!  Which is to say:  I enthusiastically recommend!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(441, 'Freida F', '154 James Gichuru Road, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The Other Room Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d21236043-r1017624997-The_Other_Room_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'The Social housing is perfect for intimate events.', 'The Social housing is perfect for intimate events and general hangouts. It\'s very ambient and the staff are exceptionally attentive, a special mention to Purity. I\'d recommend the place to anyone looking to enjoy an afternoon or evening with friends and family.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(442, 'Discover07181750483', '154 James Gichuru Road, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The Other Room Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d21236043-r1017619604-The_Other_Room_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Lunch @ The Social House', 'Purity\nElizabeth\nChef Panda & Annibal\nJanet.\nAmazing guest experience from the above staff. The wild mushroom & butternut risotto was creamy and very tasty', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(443, 'Mbugua K', '154 James Gichuru Road, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The Other Room Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d21236043-r1017619590-The_Other_Room_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Wines of South Africa at The Social House üç∑', 'I came to The Social House for a corporate event hosted at the house. It was a beautiful luncheon filled delicious food, lovely wone & great company.\n\nChef Annibal & Chef David aka Panda came up with a wonderful pairing with wines curated by the best sommelier around, Janet K!\n\nThe service and warm smiles by the hostesses Koki & Elizabeth made me feel right at home. From the moment I walked in to the moment I sat down, they were with me every step of the way.\n\nAnd the ever professional Purity was the best of them all. She was so attentive with her service and all my questions were addressed.\n\nHere\'s to more moments at The Social House üç∑ ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
