(510, 'Antonino M', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r656964153-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Ottimo cibo servizio lento', 'Mi avevano parlato tanto bene del locale che in effetti √® molto bello e con ottima musica e belle cameriere. Il cibo era buono ma il servizio lasciava a desiderare', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(511, 'Ivy G', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r643004377-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Lost Glory!', 'It\'s so sad to see what has Become of que pasa. It\'s once extensive menu now only has meat platter and grossly underwhelming pizzas.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(512, 'Dr Rob G', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r636216567-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Good pizza - amidst chaos', 'Very nice pizza, but be prepared for haphazard service, especially if you are in a group. Anywhere attempting to be a restaurant, takeaway and sports bar at the same time is going to run into difficulties. Takeaway orders were being prepared in the middle of our large order - which meant half of us had well finished before others in our party had been served. The staff were hard working but running about like headless chickens ! No sign of any effective management or attempt at organisation', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(513, 'Yuriy B', 'Arwings Kodhek Nairobi Hospital, Doctors Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Daily Cafe & Bistro - Argwings Kodhek', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23402266-r971505696-The_Daily_Cafe_Bistro_Argwings_Kodhek-Nairobi.html', 'A beautiful caf√© with delicious food', 'Interestingly, this caf√© is located on the grounds of a hospital. Don‚Äôt hesitate to visit ‚Äî the place is both elegant and simple, offering tasty and diverse food.\n\nWe came for dinner and ordered soup, rice, fish fingers, a burger, and a couple of desserts. The reserved and polite waitstaff took our order, and the kitchen swiftly prepared everything. All the dishes were fantastically delicious!\n\nThe caf√©\'s interior is unpretentious and classically simple, which makes the visit all the more pleasant. White tones, wooden accents, plenty of lighting, two verandas, and a large kitchen that you can peek into through glass, along with a wonderful playlist, including some good old classics. The atmosphere here is just delightful!\n\nWe decided we‚Äôll definitely come back many times.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(514, 'Linda R', 'Arwings Kodhek Nairobi Hospital, Doctors Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Daily Cafe & Bistro - Argwings Kodhek', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23402266-r921572103-The_Daily_Cafe_Bistro_Argwings_Kodhek-Nairobi.html', 'Quick bite after appointment ', 'The service is horrible, the servers are standing around and forget half your order, pity it has so much potential, the disinterest  is so obvious', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\"]'),
(515, 'Ianfung', 'Arwings Kodhek Nairobi Hospital, Doctors Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Daily Cafe & Bistro - Argwings Kodhek', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23402266-r902518421-The_Daily_Cafe_Bistro_Argwings_Kodhek-Nairobi.html', 'TERRIBLE FOOD AND SERVICE', 'went to their branch at sarit centre for a simple meal. how was it? ordered a simple steak recommended by the waitress and waited for 1 hour for food to arrive! it was not busy since most customers were eating cakes / ice cream etc. anyway steak arrived and taste so bad! it is the worst meal i had for many years', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(516, 'Tabby', 'Arwings Kodhek Nairobi Hospital, Doctors Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Daily Cafe & Bistro - Argwings Kodhek', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23402266-r876588800-The_Daily_Cafe_Bistro_Argwings_Kodhek-Nairobi.html', 'Poor service', 'The server took an hour before even noticing that I was there despite me trying to call them multiple times. The food took almost another hour to be served yet it was a slow day. Extremely poor service.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(517, 'Joseph N M', 'Arwings Kodhek Nairobi Hospital, Doctors Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Daily Cafe & Bistro - Argwings Kodhek', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23402266-r862578858-The_Daily_Cafe_Bistro_Argwings_Kodhek-Nairobi.html', 'Serving Broken rice in high class restaurant', 'Ordered chicken in coconut source. A cool 1500.\n\nchicken very sweet.\n\nRice tasteless and made of lowest grade of rice ...broken rice .\n\nAn insult to our intelligence', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\"]'),
(518, 'Lucy K', 'Arwings Kodhek Nairobi Hospital, Doctors Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Daily Cafe & Bistro - Argwings Kodhek', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23402266-r843513110-The_Daily_Cafe_Bistro_Argwings_Kodhek-Nairobi.html', 'Poor service', 'Been meaning to sample this  \"gem\" housed within Nairobi hospital. Tried it today, Sunday when there were minimal customers.  Poor service - an apple pie took 30 minutes to serve!!', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(519, 'Mzungubabe', 'Arwings Kodhek Nairobi Hospital, Doctors Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Daily Cafe & Bistro - Argwings Kodhek', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23402266-r805998958-The_Daily_Cafe_Bistro_Argwings_Kodhek-Nairobi.html', 'Extensive menu', 'This is a cafe based at the Nairobi hospital doctors plaza. Has a nice outdoor seating area and an interesting menu. I had pizza which was very good. Great place to grab a bite after a hospital appointment.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(520, 'Titanjones', 'Lavington Corner Mall, James Gichuru Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Amazonia Bistro', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27106802-r1018787702-Amazonia_Bistro-Nairobi.html', 'I love the chicken, very savory', 'Really cool vibes very green and peaceful. The music was great. Definitely see myself coming here as a date spot. Gladys was my server and was very attentive and  provided great service. I had an old-fashioned cocktail  and it was delicious\n\nThe standout item was the chicken, it was very savory and cooked perfectly. Beef samosa as appetizer was yummy as well. It was my first time visiting this restaurant and I will definitely be back next time I come to Kenya on vacation!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(521, 'MARIA SUNDA', 'Lavington Corner Mall, James Gichuru Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Amazonia Bistro', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27106802-r1006536982-Amazonia_Bistro-Nairobi.html', 'If you‚Äôre a foodie like me, you‚Äôll love this place! The menu has a fantastic selection of dishes, and we loved everything we tri', 'Hands down!!! Food was excellent,  Ambiance was cozy and welcoming, and Service was extremely good. I can\'t wait to be back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(522, 'Kharcy', 'Lavington Corner Mall, James Gichuru Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Amazonia Bistro', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27106802-r966573329-Amazonia_Bistro-Nairobi.html', 'Customer service is good and they don\'t keep their customers waiting ', 'It\'s a nice place..... plus the ambience üòçdecided to quench my thirst so I ordered a milkshake and the quality was top notch we\'ll definitely be back again', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(523, 'Allan M', 'Lavington Corner Mall, James Gichuru Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Amazonia Bistro', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27106802-r964915226-Amazonia_Bistro-Nairobi.html', 'My experience at Amazonia Bistro was fantastic I went on Thirsty Thursday and tried their \"Amazonia Obsession\" cocktail.', 'Amazonia Bistro offers a vibrant, jungle-inspired dining experience. I visited on Thirsty Thursday and tried their signature \"Amazonia Obsession\" cocktail‚Äîa refreshing mix of tropical fruits and rum. It was the perfect drink to unwind with. The atmosphere is lively, with lush greenery and fun decor that makes you feel like you\'re in the heart of the Amazonia. The service was friendly and quick, adding to the enjoyable evening. Prices are reasonable, especially with the Thursday drink specials. A great place to relax and enjoy unique flavors', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(524, 'Jack B', 'Lavington Corner Mall, James Gichuru Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Amazonia Bistro', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27106802-r951411765-Amazonia_Bistro-Nairobi.html', 'Bill Padding', 'Had a terrible experience at Amazonia.  The waitress issued thew wrong bill and insisted that I pay it.  After a long dispute they brought the right bill. Always ask for receipt every step of the way.  I will not go back to Amazonia', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(525, 'Kui K', 'Lavington Corner Mall, James Gichuru Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Amazonia Bistro', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27106802-r934818016-Amazonia_Bistro-Nairobi.html', 'Mildly disappointing', 'Went to try out this new place for lunch. It\'s rather small so when the rains forced some people inside, it was a tight squeeze around the tables.\n\nThe service was good and the staff are very attentive - we were served by Jackline and she was very efficient.\n\nThe food is reasonably priced but average. Among us we had the snapper, steak, and stuffed chicken and none of the dishes were special. The menu states that the fish comes with salsa verde and a caper sauce but it came with a basic tartare sauce and olive oil.\n\nI\'d recommend the place for drinks and vibes.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(526, 'Brittany_11_10', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r1013627869-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Great setting, slow service', 'If you\'re looking for a casual place where your kid/s can run around (in a safe, grassy place) while you wait (and wait, and wait) for the food to come out, this is your restaurant. \n\nThe main pro to Shamba is all its outdoor space, including its little sandbox area and tires for littles to play in/on (the slides looked in need of an update, but there were a couple tykes seemingly enjoying them), and they have painting for kids as well. It\'s just a lovely environment, especially (see above) while waiting for food. Thankfully, we didn\'t seem to wait as long as some other reviewers apparently did, so our experience overall was fine. \n\nThe food was fine. Nothing to write home about, but we didn\'t have any complaints. The servers were friendly enough, and the prices were fair for the quality and quantity of food (and the location/environment).\n\nIf you\'re looking for out-of-this-world food and/or speedy service, I\'d go elsewhere. But if you want to enjoy a casual meal outside where your kid/s can roam and play around, it\'s worth checking out. Our toddler had a fun time, and we\'ll most certainly be back.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(527, 'Linda K', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r1010616737-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'A horrible bout of food poisoning...', 'I went to Shamba cafe with my parents for an early dinner back in February. We loved the environment and whole shamba theme and were looking forward to a great meal experience. All was going well under my mum found a metal piece in her steak that was the size of a staple. Had she swallowed it, I can\'t even begin to imagine how horribly that would have gone. We shared this with the waitress and she called a gentleman who came over and apologized, explaining to us that it may have been a bristle from the brush that they use to clean the grill. That was rather disturbing to hear but we offered grace to them. They did not take my mums food back to replace it with a different dish and we still paid full price for the meal. We thought our issue with the food ended there but we were sorely mistaken.\n\nThe following morning, my dad called me to alert me that my mum was feeling ill and needed to be taken to the hospital. This was a surprise to me because she was totally fine the previous day when we met for dinner and Dad and I did not have any issues given that we ate a different dish from hers. I rushed home and from the symptoms she described to me, it sounded like she had a horrible bout of food poisoning. It got so bad, she even passed out while in the bathroom. I took her to the hospital and she ended up admitted there for four days. Thank God she is better now but it was a dreadful experience to say the least.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(528, 'Sunshine20797733347', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r1000487713-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'A disappointment', 'The seating was wonderful and calm. Unfortunately the food was sub standard - hash browns are best avoided. The sourdough toast was the highlight. The coffee came in a carafe and stone cold before breakfast arrived.\nThe waitress tried her best to compensate', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(529, 'Tana W', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r986722219-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Diana is a rockstar', 'Diana was an incredible server! Our whole experience was made by her help and hospitality. We got drinks and dessert and she helped us with several modifications. Thank you, Diana!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(530, 'Makena W', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r968867413-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Poor experience in Shamba cafe', 'I visited Shamba cafe today at around lunchtime and it‚Äôs a usual place I go with my family due to the cozy atmosphere and the open land of the view of the green fields. It has been a place a visit frequently with my family but this time around it was very disappointing considering the place has so much potential.\n\nHowever they were some few things that fell short.  Unfortunately we arrive they is no host to approach us and we stood waiting for minimum 30 minutes. The service being slower than we expected we finished our drinks before the food came and the food took 2 hours. Which we ordered there weekend special a meat platter which was supposed to have variety of different meats but only 2 types of meat which were just dunked in bbq sauce and considering we have ordered that previously and it was good was just a big disappointment! In addition half the meat was raw and inedible which was very frustrating!\n\nI believe that Shamba cafe has a lot to offer, but perhaps some attention to timing and guest experience and lastly communication in the kitchen would improve the experience and quality of food. I‚Äôm hoping to give it another try in future,hoping this issues are resolved because truly the ambiance is truly inviting.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(531, 'Rayheb', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r922462851-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Shamba-olic', 'Shamba is the Ryanair of the Nairobi food scene. If there was any other option for desperate parents looking for a safe open space for their kids to dash around in whilst getting slowly sozzled, they would take it...\n\nDon\'t expect to get the food you ordered. Don\'t expect to get it fast (a 2 hour wait is not abnormal). Do have an open mind to never getting your food at all. \n\nShamba\'s reputation for the above precedes itself. It is a joke that keeps on giving. And yet we keep on strapping ourselves in for another go at it, as there really is little other option when the clock ticks 3 and the kids are wild. \n\nToday, five meals came one after the other over a 2-hour period. One we definitely didn\'t order, three others were wrong to some degree. Friends on other tables exchanged glances confirming the same. \'A mess up in the kitchen\'. Same old. Might as well torch the order pads and count us in for some brunch roulette. We were angry, we complained, it achieves nothing, we laughed, we paid, we left, we will come again.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(532, 'Liz S', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r921940189-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Great food, lovely surrounds', 'Visited Shamba for lunch twice and loved it. Great menu range, lovely surroundings, friendly and competent staff, and we all loved the food. The food takes a bit longer to come than I\'m used to but that was the same for most restaurants I went to in Nairobi.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(533, 'Rakhee J', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r919297546-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Pathetic service and the worst attitude from the lady staff', 'Need more tables outside and maintenance in the garden. Service from staff depends on their moods (racist service esp from the lady waitresses). They can decide to ignore and make u run after them or give you good service if their moods are good. Too pricy.\nAfter not being given a good table the waitress actually had the guts to tell us we will give you maasai shawls and u can sit on the floor and eat. Do they forget their salaries come from having customers around? Where they going to charge us less by giving us the place on the ground????', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(534, 'Pooja P', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r919255964-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Given alcohol when requesting a non alcoholic drink due to breastfeeding', 'I requested a non alcoholic drink because I am breastfeeding. The drink arrived wrong once and the next was alcoholic!! Our server got 4 drinks out of a table of 5 wrong and we had to return them.\n\nWorst service in Nairobi!!!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(535, 'Dora W', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r912750688-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Great service from Walter', 'The area is really beautiful and ideal if you have children. We came on a day that they seemed to be under staffed but Walter our server went above and beyond to ensure that we didn\'t notice that they were under staffed. The food was good but Walter\'s service was really the star of the show especially in Nairobi, service like that is hard to find.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(536, 'Shelina H', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r911407775-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'BAD SERVICE', 'I have been here a few times with family hoping that every new time we go, the service will get better! Unfortunately, I must say after a few times of visiting, food is nice but most definitely not worth the wait. To wait an hour for breakfast when it‚Äôs just eggs is absolutely ridiculous. Every time we have gone, I have called in advance and asked if it‚Äôs busy and whether the food will take long and always i am told food will take less than 20 minutes. When you ask for anything the waitresses look at you like as if you are disturbing them and that it‚Äôs a crime to even ask them for anything. They messed up our meals bringing us sausages when we asked them to cancel the sausage order after finding out the sausages are not halal! To wait for over an hour for mistakes in the food is absolutely madness and super frustrating. Having. The kids were tired and cranky by the time our food came so our whole experience I must say every time we have come is 1/10 despite the food being okay. Please improve your staff waiters/waitresses (they shouldn‚Äôt be grumpy if they want to work they should work happily or not bother!) \n\nDon‚Äôt think we will be coming back for a very very long time!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(537, 'Carol W', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r889030349-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Good ', 'The location is beautiful and unique. The food was great but the service was very slow, luckily I was with friends and we kept each other entertained as we waited.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(538, 'Mr P', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r887323732-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent ambience, service, and food could improve ', 'Unbeatable ambience with the large farmhouse feel and airy setting. Service sometimes seems a bit harried with frazzled servers, making it difficult to get attention sometimes. The salads are great. The barbecued meats can be a tad bland, but that\'s nit picking. Overall, it\'s worth a visit or two especially on live band nights', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(539, 'Maureen K', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r885170426-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Not the best service, food and prices ', 'The location and ambience was great but that is all to offer. The staff were not helpful, knowledgeable of the menu, they seemed so busy to assist us with anything. \nWe thought the food would makes us forget everything but it was just as bad and the prices are not friendly. ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(540, 'vivek0210', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r884695167-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Informal fine dining restaurant in Nairobi ', 'Shamba is a fine dining restaurant serving excellent Western, European and Pizzas.\n\nIt\'s a very large open air restaurant having multiple zones for customers to choose.\n\nGreat food, well trained staff and open air ambience makes dining an experience worth remembering ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(541, 'SussexSarah2014', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r877622274-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Love this place!', 'We go to Shamba regularly as it\'s consistently good in terms of food, drinks, service and the big shady garden setting is unbeatable. The additional things like organic farmers markets on a Wednesday & Saturday, the fabulous shop with local and regeneratively produced foods, gifts and other lovely things, the herb/plant shop and the recycling station, also draw us in time after time. We had a big brunch party there in January which was fantastic as well and super easy to organise. Definitely a place to come when in Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(542, 'Tino C', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r874469482-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Il posto molto gradevole, cucina mediocre, shop pretenzioso', 'La posizione e l‚Äôambiente sono molto gradevoli, direi incantevoli,  ideali per un pasto riposante. Purtroppo il cibo √® mediocre. La pizza margherita (1100 scellini circa 8-9 euro) sottile, ma senza sapore; gli zoodles con i prawns (1550 scellini, circa 12/13 euro) discreti, il caff√® espresso (150 scellini, 1 euro e rotti) da dimenticare. Eppure in altri locali, il caff√® lo preparano bene. Infine, il negozietto di generi vari √® caro, pretenzioso, indirizzato, evidentemente, agli espatriati che si fanno abbindolare dall ecologicamente corretto!', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\"]'),
(543, 'SRN', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r866137525-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Very Disappointing', 'Was there for a baby shower. Shock on us the bill came with an additional charge of Kes.20k as venue fee! During the booking of the venue, Manager informed us that only additional charge is corkage fee for the cake. Manager and Director tried to justify that they needed to get additional staff because we were a large group yet service was very very slow! They took so long to serve the kids we had to complain for them to speed up. Doesn\'t make sense to charge additional amounts yet we have spent alot of money there and the service is very slow. Very disappointed customer!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(544, 'AvdV80', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r864513281-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent lunch!', 'Came in for first time lunch experience. Shamba is a indoor/outdoor restaurant with a small store as annex. Great outdoor area which makes it family friendly for sure.\n\nWe were kind off in a rush so did not spend a lot of time looking at all the details of the restaurant (will definately do that during a future visit). Waitress was very friendly and made sure our order was in quickly. Great service on that area!\n\nWe opted for Leo\'s original prociutto and the sweet potato burger. The food came out quickly and was of great quality. Excellent job on the fries also. The accompanying drinks were good.\n\nWe had our lunch at the porch / outdoor area overlooking the garden. This brings a really nice relaxing atmosphere. This i really enjoyed.\n\nCompliments on the service, food and restaurant in general! Will definately come back in the future.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(545, 'Gillian S', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r858857966-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Focussed on the customer', 'Lunched here on 4th September with family and friends.  Although we had made a reservation for a large group some four days in advance, on arrival we found the intended table for us still had a very large group not yet finished with their meal.  The owner, Michelle, seated us at the bar and at seats nearby and took our drinks orders herself ensuring we were all comfortable as we waited for the group to finish up and leave.  Whilst this took some time, it was not an issue as we were well looked after.  The food here is very fresh, very reasonably priced and the staff offer exemplary service.  As soon as we were seated our waiter brought us some complementary starters from the owner as way of her apology for the chaos and our having to wait.  This was well appreciated as it is not normal practice in a Kenyan restaurant.  We had several young children with our group who were well entertained, served their meals very quickly and treated with courtesy.  My first time here, but guaranteed I will be back.... well done Michelle and your fantastic staff.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(546, 'niall f', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r990255956-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Beware the cocktails', 'I would be very careful when selecting a cocktail and make sure you know and more importantly see what goes into it. Best advice in one word \"AVOID\"', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\"]'),
(547, 'Mishya k', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r947085610-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Sexual harassment by Tom and Dorcas security and when I refused they started to forcefully Push me out..Sex is  not focd', 'Dorcas and Tom at the security were harassing me without a reason , they started pushing me without a reason. I paid my bill and yet they were busy hurting me .The security guy Tom was trying to sexually harass me and when I refused he started to force me out', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(548, 'reenmm', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r893675580-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Food below par', 'Went for Sunday brunch at Brew Westlands. The food is below par tbh, wide variety but only thing that tasted fresh and tasty were the waffles that were made as you wait. Service is very slow and they seemed overwhelmed. Only go if you are into bottomless gin cocktails which also served quite slow considering the offer ends at 5', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(549, 'Linda', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r830923101-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'VERY UNDERWHELMING FOOD', 'Went to this place hungry and ready to indulge only for us to be served with very tasteless platter. Tried to talk to the supervisor only for him to give us cake. Very bad customer service on top of the very bad meal.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(550, 'JG_137', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r827813765-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Didn\'t enjoy the burger, beer pretty mediocre', 'Had a burger which arrived absolutely drowned in too much sickly BBQ sauce. The meat didn\'t taste of much. And the patty seemed kind of dry and just warm, not hot and juicy like it had been freshly grilled? Had a couple signature beers and they were disappointing. Definitely not living up to the descriptions on the menu at all. Wouldn\'t order them again, don\'t think I\'ll go back.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(551, 'Stephan', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r803961825-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Sch√∂ner, letzter Abend', 'Wir waren an einem Donnerstag Abend dort, unser letzter Abend in Kenia. Der Service war sehr aufmerksam und unsere Bestellungen kamen alle z√ºgig. Wir hatten als Starter die Chicken Bits und als Hauptgericht die Surf and Turf Platte. Das Essen war frisch und kam hei√ü aus der K√ºche. Alles sehr lecker. Auch das Bier war beachtenswert. Ich hatte einen dunklen Bock welches einem deutschen in nichts nachstand. Wir werden mit Sicherheit wiederkommen.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(552, 'BRUNOMOMBASA', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r750007044-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'NICE PLACE TO HANG OUT AND EAT GOOD STEAKS', 'The place was quiet for a Thursday evening, we got all the attention from a friendly and competent service. Steaks are fantastic, other meals also very good. The advertised home made Bernaise sauce, unfortunately by far no Bernaise at all.\nOverall a good experiance and good food at medium to high price.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]');
INSERT INTO `restaurant_reviews` (`id`, `author_name`, `place_address`, `place_name`, `review_url`, `review_title`, `review_text`, `review_rating`, `location`, `created_at`, `predicted_sentiment`, `predicted_aspects`) VALUES
(553, 'Stavros C', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r748520069-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Brunch? Oh yes indeed!!!', 'We went for brunch on a Sunday, and I may surprisingly admit that these guys have done a wonderful job of putting everything together in a winner takes it all atmosphere!\n\nFood, drinks, service, ambiance,  music, you name it, they provided and provided with superior professionalism! Head chef Dennis was amazing, so was our waitress Nancy who kept coming again and again for refills...\n\nOh yes, we will be back, and I hear that nights are also a full blast treat!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(554, 'Barbara S', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r742745680-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Different locations, good beer, and build your own burger', 'I like Brew Bistro. The food is ok, the beer is well cooled and the craft beers are great to taste. The atmosphere is relaxed and service usually good. The \'build your own burger\' initiative is great although they did forget a few things on mine. And if you go to the Westlands branch on the weekend, be ready to dance. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(555, 'SaxbyHawk', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r740152718-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Tranquilla...', '...serata tra amici molto tranquilla... un locale molto particolare..sorround ad alto volume per sentire bene la partita nelle varie tv all interno del locale.. filetto di manzo con varie salse cotto in modo magistrale con contorno di patate  veramente molto buone... un servizio al tavolo impeccabile grazie all\'impegno di Nancy una ragazza sempre con il sorriso e con una delicatezza professionale unica. Un birra nera fredda al punto giusto che scendeva molto  bene... rapporto qualit√† prezzo ottimo...consigliato ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(556, 'M728FWericb', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r738942308-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'SUPERB SERVICE ', 'This restaurant is in a class of it\'s own \nThe waiters are attentive, fast and always smiling \nThe food and drinks are amazing and  value for money. \nThe ambience is good and the place is very clean \nI highly recommend this place and definitely will be back ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(557, 'Marc S', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r736021573-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Well managed at peak times', 'New Year‚Äôs Eve party place was rocking but despite this place was kept clean secure and with swift service.\nDrinks pricey but not ridiculously friendly team and management\nHighly recommended', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(558, 'santa', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r732853914-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'SUNDAY EVENING', 'Don\'t let your sundays be boring.  If you are looking for a sunday afternoon and evening out,  this is one of the best places to be. They have great offers for brunch, and if you are a, freshly brewed beer and barbeque person,  then this is it.  Unlimited barbeque and beer at very good prices. Good music at very nice volume thus you can have a good conversation. And if you are a sports person,  that is catered for too with their TVs even at the balcony.  They have heaters to keep you warm if it gets too cold.   Trust me,  this is it', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(559, 'mrmarutiak', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r730475187-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Good Microbrew beer', 'Nice bar with decent bar food.  Very popular location for late night music.  Beer was good but not spectacular.  Advertises roof top view but cannot see any of the city - bar is only on the second floor', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(560, 'Sean4476', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r721715083-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Beer tastes flat', 'I went to Brew Bistro fives years ago and recently returned. I don\'t remember being impressed then and I still am not. I came only for the beer. I tried the flight of 5 beers and was not compelled to order a full beer of any of the options. The music is bit loud for a chilled Sunday, too. The outdoor seating was nice and it is always good when an area is trying to craft different types of beers. I don\'t think I would return.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(561, 'Lizzy', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r718218433-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Good cocktails', 'Have been to brew bistro several times and always its a new experience. From the band nights to DJs its just mind blowing.\nWe had our cocktails at the bar and there was this guy Oscar full of life and recommendations. Definitely going back.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(562, 'Weeney R', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r707349895-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent and professional service! ', 'Third time at the brew bistro lounge, westlands. Super occupied considering it‚Äôs a Friday. had one guy, Peter, as our server, courteous, friendly and professional! With every sense of these words! Made us feel well taken care of and we were strangers to him! And I believe the customers next to us felt the same as they kept shaking hands and others even hugging him... I mean he had the time to go around the tables to ask if we were okay. This guy is exceptional! Felt very welcome like never before and I mean it! Anyway the bistro is a cool place if you are here on vacation and looking to have a good time! Music is awesome as well, all round ! Residents love it too, but for the first time I LOVED the service ...Will def come back and even recommend friends. My night is made. ‚ù§Ô∏è', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(563, 'Angela n', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r702267907-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Horrible service..', 'Been visiting brew bistro for years then took a hiatus. Came back today and got extremely horrible treatment form a Lewis who was the manager. Started off with lots of attitude from him, then gave us a wrong bill, and then proceeded to shout at us when we complained. I am completely out off by the customer service. Do better.Thank you Mose for helping us..', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(564, 'The One and Only', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r695294893-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Nice atmosphere!', 'One of the beef burgers was awesome (the one that costs 1200).\nThe place is great for hanging out with friends.\n', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(565, 'cesare', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r688832076-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Bell\' ambiente', 'Ottimo locale, il cibo √® veramente ottimo, ottima anche l\'ambiente e ottima la scelta della musica dal vivo.....\nSpettacolare la vista dal 11 piano ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(566, 'KeduKudzi', 'Vineyard - Ridgeways, Kiambu Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Vineyard', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23754697-r877480505-The_Vineyard-Nairobi.html', 'Great mood', 'Amazing mood go on Wednesday evenings for food drinks great company and live music. They keep the crowd engaged and you will be entertained', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(567, 'Loise', 'Vineyard - Ridgeways, Kiambu Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Vineyard', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23754697-r865639510-The_Vineyard-Nairobi.html', 'Friends hang out', 'The place is accessible, right on the road. It‚Äôs easy to spot \n\nThe food was amazing, had goat wet fry (Kenyan specialty) \n\nWould definitely come back', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(568, 'David W', 'Vineyard - Ridgeways, Kiambu Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Vineyard', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23754697-r827310752-The_Vineyard-Nairobi.html', 'Vibes at Ridgeways', 'Awesome ambience, expansive grounds, just the right vibe for a night out or chilled daytime brunch....Highly recommended!!!ü§ó', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(569, 'mary n', '69 Camellia Close, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nicks Donuts', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d32229259-r1003576458-Nicks_Donuts-Nairobi.html', 'Total treat', 'Make sure to stop by Nick‚Äôs Donuts and honestly, once you‚Äôve had one, you‚Äôll find yourself coming back again and again. They‚Äôre just that good, fresh, soft, and impossible to resist. You\'ve been warned!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(570, 'Warren H', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r631489285-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Awesome place', 'Awesome Pizza. For someone who travels alot. This is one of the best pizza s I have ever had. The services was spot on!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(571, 'Anja P', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r630296002-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Miss', 'As a lot of restaurants in Nairobi, it\'s a \'hit or miss\'. We\'ve had a few \'hits\' here, but today we went for take out pizza, which was definitely a very big miss.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(572, 'Frank Ganda', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r624764265-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'AMAZING PIZZAS IN KAREN', 'This is Probably the best chill-out spot in Karen shopping centre. \nIt\'s unique and very trendy. Their cocktails are great but their PIZZAS are some of the best in Nairobi. \nThe service is prompt and good \nBest best best', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(573, 'miloux', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r620484241-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Fun and tasty dinner', 'Que Pasa is the \"local\" for Karen, Kenya and we could see why. Friendly, competent service, good drinks, excellent thin-crust pizza. Monday you get three pizzas for the price of two. This is the place to go if you want to be with real locals and not just tourists! ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(574, 'Brian A', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r610185387-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Great Ambience, Food & Music', 'The music on a Friday and Saturday evening just gets you dancing and in the mood with the in house DJ. The meat platter is a serious fit for 2 and sorts out the pre drinks ritual with a cold draft Heineken, while the meat lovers pizza is just superb. Great service by Anita, Edward, Martin and the whole team. Definitely worth the visit.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(575, 'DismasMokua', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r610161645-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Awesome', 'Top of the range hospitality. Hospitality staff trained for custom services and one feels comfortable and happy. The pizzas are tantalizing.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(576, 'Muriithi N', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r589810933-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Good time ', 'We had excellent service from Zaina. The red snapper and vol au vent  was impeccable.\nWe got to watch Nigeria vs Iceland. It was so much fun ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(577, 'Eric M', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r586457378-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Great Food and music', 'In Karen on a Friday or Saturday? Que Pasa is the place to be at. Amazing music, wonderful crowd and great food and finger bitings.\n\nLove the place and the atmosphere. Wonderful wait staff, crowd and just general feel.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(578, 'jameyponte', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r583537924-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'place gets better each time i visit and the PIZZA', 'Great experience almost every time - fair prices for a mid to high end place and service just keeps getting better.  The best I have seen in Kenya by far.  Love the pizza per I am on a budget so I can eat great pizza and be in a space that is well designed with trained and happy staff.  what a joy to find in Kenya.   \n\nTo the staff- congrats and keep up the great effort.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(579, 'Carl G', 'Karen Shopping Centre, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Que Pasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3767853-r582537842-Que_Pasa-Nairobi.html', 'Chill spot', 'Karen doesn\'t have that many spots to just sit and chill. I\'m impartial to liquor and these guys know how to do it well. Introduced to one of the stronger shots I\'ve had in a while. Don\'t know if it\'s just me but I got a little banana undertone from it, not mad at it. Super difficult name but tasty and potent drink. I\'m a repeat customer and will be keeping it that way üëå', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(580, 'jokiwitraveller', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r855053471-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent food, service and setting', 'My husband and I went here for lunch with friends on Thursday 18 August. We sat out in the beautiful spacious garden and a lovely waitress came to take our drinks order straight away. My glass of bubbles was large, cold and went down a treat! \n\nWe ordered our food and enjoyed relaxing and sipping our drinks. One friend had the snapper which was amazing, another had the delicious feta, coriander stuffed chicken, my husband enjoyed the spare ribs and I had the double burger in lettuce wrap (as I am gluten free) with salad and guacamole - made to perfection! \n\nI cannot believe the other poor reviews because for us, we all came away saying how wonderful our lunch was and that we cannot wait to return! The waitress and male waiter served us with huge smiles and nothing was too much trouble for them. Keep up the good work! \n\nLastly, I bought some of the strawberry jam from the shop which is the best I have tasted. \nSee you soon Shamba Cafe.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(581, 'BonVoyager87', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r848255838-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Delicious', 'I really enjoyed my meal here and the there is no denying the setting is gorgeous and design of the restaurant was well conceived. It was not my choice to go here but it wasn\'t my night to pick the restaurant so my travel companion picked it based on recommendations from friends. I wasn\'t disappointed in my meal at all, I just had been looking forward to more authentic East African cuisine and restaurant experiences. This was American through and through. It was nice, just don\'t go here if you\'re playing tourist and want the Kenyan experience. If you\'re homesick, by all means, it\'s a great place!', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(582, 'Antonella S', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r848063180-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Poor', 'Was out with friends and family. The owner of the restaurant approached my elderly parents and decided to introduce her to her friends and her elderly mother. Upon her doing so, I caught her introducing my mother, ( who has dementia), and whilst introducing her, twirling her finger round and round next to her eye, so as to indicate that my mother is mad. \nThis is how they treat elderly paying customers. It‚Äôs absolutely disgusting and disrespectful. \nFurthermore on an earlier visit to the restaurant with friends, it was specified that the dish ordered would not be pork. My friends don‚Äôt eat pork because of custom and religion. The restaurant served them pork. Again, poor and disrespectful.\nThe food served in this restaurant is also average .', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(583, 'Jeet', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r846526106-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Awful awful awful', 'Went there to do some work and have a coffee. Was told to leave because I was not adding any value to the restaurant by being there. Also keeping in mind I was the only person there. \nStaff rude with no manners. Avoid at all cost.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(584, 'standardfamily474', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r846289834-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'very good breakfast', 'Business trip, came here early with colleagues for breakfast (staurday). Only 2 tables seated so service was fast. Shakshuka with breakfast sausage patties was very good. Coffee was excellent (espresso). Staff very professional and friendly. Nice shop and Small Saturday market worth a look with friendly people. Not cheap but would come back.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\"]'),
(585, 'Marci P', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r842209808-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Shamba‚Ä¶The place to be!', 'Shamba served as our back yard and one of go-tos for our 3 months spent in Laresho Crescent!  Not sure how we would have survived without it! Great assortment of food from juices, to bowls to delicious pizzas. Beautiful outdoor spaces for families to hang, play and kids kids can have room to roam. Bring your recycling, shop in the store for bakery items and so much more. \nIf you‚Äôre lucky enough to be in the area around the holidays, Michelle put on an amazing Christmas show with choral groups, gingerbread house decorating, an auction, and festive decorations! I can hardly wait to go back again. \nThank you for bringing Shamba into the world and for sharing it with us.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(586, 'Bella', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r840029929-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Always happy here!', 'The owner Michelle and the staff are extremely friendly and helpful, the food has never disappointed us, it is bright in colours and the menu offers a great variety of dishes including vegetarian/vegan/gluten free.\nThe location is beautiful, surrounded by many trees and the farmer‚Äôs market has fresh vegetables.\nEvery time we go to the Shamba we are joyful and relaxed, thankful to be surrounded by that calming atmosphere that makes us feel so very at ease.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(587, 'JG_137', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r834012584-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'For desserts, beer, pizza or ambience, it\'s okay', 'Good beer, nice ambience, attractive setting. Service can be slow, but not unbearable.\n\nI like the desserts. Spectacular ice cream. Generally though the food is average or disappointing. For instance, the Vietnamese Salad is mainly chopped kale, pumpkin seeds, carrots and egg noodles. No herbs and no Vietnamese flavouring... This is pretty typical of the menu, which looks and sounds good, and is priced a little high, but then the dishes just don\'t taste delicious. The pizzas are okay.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(588, 'Robert C', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r826191776-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely location, shame about the service.', 'Service is extremely slow. Quality of food is not bad, it just takes a long time to receive it. \nThere is some suggestion that the staff are discriminatory. As a Caucasian couple I can assure you the service is equally as bad, regardless of skin tone.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(589, 'YvanoTP', 'Loresho Ridge, Nairobi Kenya', 'Shamba', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17345977-r826047913-Shamba-Nairobi.html', 'Great open area and pizza', 'Came over with a friend over December and as you can imagine it was quite packed. But we were still able to get a table. I loved their pizza!!\nOverall : great family ambiance but can get packed at times', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(590, 'Marvin B', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r1036460655-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'A Deeply Disappointing Family Experience ‚Äî Avoid if You Expect Respectful Service', 'We were really looking forward to trying Rivercafe, but sadly our experience was far from pleasant. As a family carrying a baby, we were stunned when we were refused proper seating. Hospitality should be welcoming ‚Äî not discriminatory ‚Äî especially in 2025.\n\nOur server, Virginia, made things worse. She rushed our ordering process and seemed visibly irritated by our presence. It‚Äôs never a good feeling when you‚Äôre made to feel like a burden.\n\nThen came the final frustration: part of our breakfast order was changed without any communication. They had run out of toast, and instead of informing us or offering options, they simply served an alternative without asking. Such disregard for customer preference and basic courtesy is unacceptable.\n\nWe left feeling deeply disappointed and uncomfortable. There are plenty of restaurants that treat guests with dignity and respect ‚Äî unfortunately, Rivercafe isn‚Äôt one of them.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(591, 'Judy', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r1026196105-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Worst service in Nairobi', 'The worst service, food was cold, supervisor was rude, they got the order wrong with no apologies. I used to be a fan of this place, never again.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(592, 'Francine S', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r942245551-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Dining in Karura Forest at the River Cafe - An experience', 'Very cozy restaurant in Karura Forest, had a bit of a wait as it was brunch time, the experience was pleasant despite the wait.  The manager was busy on the floor assisting staff to ensure empty tables were cleaned and the seating of waiting guests.\n\nHad a drink at the bar with my friend and the drinks were fresh I had pineapple mint and my friend had freshly squeezed orange juice while we waited.  Once seated we were quickly served and we both went for that omelette, very tasty filled with spinach, I loooooooveee that omelette experience, overall service delivery was excellent.\n\nPicked up a few things from the shop there, shower gel made of natural plants and some locally made pickles.\n\nWas bitten by an insect but hey I am in the forest.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"delivery_takeout\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(593, 'PuzzleSolver855', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r892670908-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Good menu options, good service, clean bathrooms', 'We had hiked the trail and were ready for lunch.  This was the perfect option.  It was a cool day so the open style restaurant was suitable and quite attractive.  My husband said his hamburger tasted odd but it may have been just different from what he is used to.  They take Visa which is important so we aren\'t carrying around tons of cash.  I would go again!', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(594, 'Mr P', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r887324100-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Could improve, seems to have declined somewhat', 'The setting is unmatched with Karura Forest, providing an excellent backdrop for dining, albeit a bit windy on occasion. On our last visit, it seemed the staff were a bit overwhelmed by numbers with our reservation being mixed up. However, the hostess was gracious and apologetic. The food overall seems to be on a steady decline, but the service was great (despite the initial hiccup). I wouldn\'t strike it off our list and will still recommend it ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(595, 'Christine M', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r878467018-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Tasteless Food, below par service', 'They have run down this place. It used to have decent food. Had the worst burger I have ever had there recently. My friends burger was also so bad. The meat tasted like it was going bad.\n\nNo hand washing stations. You have to wash hands in the toilet.\n\nWould not eat here again.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(596, 'Ireri', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r876181455-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'PATHETIC SERVICE', 'The service is PATHETIC, HORRIBLE AND DISGUSTING.I\'m not even going to hide it but the staff that works there is RACIST(YES R A C I S T). I sat there for an hour waiting to be served but nobody served me,they only tended to the white folks that were there.\nWe\'re in 2023 why is this still happening?.My review may not matter but may you treat someone else the way you treated me and get cancelled for it.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(597, 'Maria', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r871506127-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Sumptuous Meal in Green Heaven ', 'The location and ambience is absolutely beautiful üòç The warm welcome at the entrance by Joyce set the mood for our first visit The menu can only be accessed by a qr code and it is well set makes it easy to choose with its specific variety of dishes The pasta,  chicken BLT  and beef burger choices were our favourite Absolutely tasty deeeelish and finger-licking mmh mmmh mmmmh The excellent customer service by Joyce who was also assisted by Kennedy was a big plus Thank You. We will definitely be back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(598, 'Kelvin M', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r867317362-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Racist service?', 'The waiters ignored me and catered to the white patrons. Not saying it‚Äôs racist but it sure smells like it.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[]'),
(599, 'Holzwurm1', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r858340839-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'H√§lt nicht was versprochen wird ', 'Zun√§chst einmal muss erw√§hnt werden, dass man um zum Caf√© oder besser Restaurant zu kommen einen Eintritt f√ºr den Park bezahlen muss.\nDort angekommen kann es an Wochenenden passieren, dass man auf einen freien Tisch warten muss, also besser vorher reservieren. \nHat man einen Tisch, dann muss man mittels QR-Code die Speisekarte scannen.  Dabei wird man feststellen, dass die Preise sehr hoch sind.\nWenn dann das bestellte Gericht kommt wird man feststellen, dass es sehr klein ist und somit die Preise v√∂llig √ºberteuert sind. \nDementsprechend trifft man sehr viele Ausl√§nder, haupts√§chlich Diplomaten und Angestellte der Botschaften. Diesen scheinen die √ºberzogenen Preise nichts auszumachen, denn es wird √ºppig bestellt.  Die Qualit√§t ist obendrein nur durchschnittlich. Ich hatte einen Caesars Salad mit Avocado bestellt, das Dressing war durchschnittlich ohne Pep, als K√§se wurde ein Hauch von Parmesanchips verwendet. Was ein Anchovis im Salat zu suchen hatte konnte mir der Kellner auch nicht erkl√§ren.  Die Avocadost√ºckchen entsprachen etwa einer halben Avocado.  Daf√ºr sind dann noch 1.600 Kes zum heutigen Kurs etwa 13,90‚Ç¨ zu bezahlen. Das war der Salat auch an diesem Standort definitiv nicht wert.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(600, 'jannus', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r838317436-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Terrible customer service, expensive food which is ok, nice setting ', 'I arrived, restaurant was empty. Staff could not be less interested in customer if they tried. It appeared like they hated their jobs. Won\'t be back again. Nairobi has lots of place, which might not be in the same setting but where you are not treated like trash.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(601, 'Azad XORTO B', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r838076616-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Sch√∂ne Umgebung', 'Sehr sch√∂ne Umgebung und leckeres Essen, leider sind die Gerichte zu teuer. Der Wald gibt dem Ganzen seine Ruhe.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(602, 'Maureen W.', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r836757097-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Overpriced and mediocre meals üôÉ', 'First time having a watery milkshake. The shake was served with a spoon üòÑüòÅ because the waiter said \"no plastics allowed in Karura\" (talk about stating the obviously obvious)  Mentioned there\'s paper straws nowadays and lots of environmentally-conscious restaurants are using them. \n\nLong story short, ended up drinking it from the glass cause it was that watery. Felt ripped off, cause I was hoping to enjoy a milkshake after my run. Guess I\'ll stick to running and having home-made milkshakes.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(603, 'Departure611865', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r832813252-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Food poor', 'Food was very poor, no sauces and high prices. Cannot recommend and would not eat here again. Waiter was also not very friendly', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(604, 'AABCtravel', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r831735404-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'BOOKING IS ESSENTIAL', 'Following an exercising walk or run around the fabulous Karura Forest a meal here is a just reward.  The food is very good, the service is proactive and friendly and the ambiance is restful.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(605, 'Swale Woki', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r831727388-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Terrible Service', 'The restaurant needs to invest in training their waiters/waitresses to equip them for hospitable and friendly service. They seem unbothered with customers, predominantly blacks, and are somewhat rude.\n\nMy experience there was less than stellar, from the waiter forgetting half of our order to  being spoken to audaciously by one of the male waiters.\n\nI will not be coming back here, ever due to their services and quite frankly their overpriced bland food.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(606, 'cornishventurer', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r823208027-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely family lunch location', 'Had lunch here after a lovely walk through the forest. The staff were attentive, friendly & efficient. The food was lovely just as we ordered tons of flavour & very generous portion size. We loved that even though they were very busy so a small wait on food they sent the children‚Äôs meals early such a brilliant & appreciated touch. Would definitely recommend a walk to the waterfall then lunch in this cafe.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(607, 'Traveling Chopsticks', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r819720784-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Cool Restaurant in the middle of the forest', 'Went to Karura the first time and stumbled upon this restaurant. It was packed and we didn\'t have reservations but we lucked out with one of the cocktail tables freeing up (and better view in my opinion) so wait was minimal but looked like reservations would be recommended. Brunch was nice and the menu was random fusion but as the other reviews have said, it\'s overpriced and the food is quite average. The service was pretty horrible where we didn\'t see our waiter that often, Though the place was packed due to midday rush, surely this isn\'t their first Sunday brunch and should\'ve been staffed properly.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(608, 'Nikki L', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r786581300-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Incredible ambience, high prices', 'One of a kind forest cafe. Surrounded by lovely Karura forest, you can watch monkeys from your seat. A good place to work from with decent wifi. The bread and butter dessert was rich and delicious. The burger was mediocre to poor. The prices are very high for Nairobi.The service was kind and attentive.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(609, 'medolinel', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r785400435-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Lunch visit', 'The staff should be be orinted on provision of equitable services to all.  My husband and I visited for lunch during the recent lockdown, order lunch to as we should. As we intended eating at the picnic site we requested  to borrow the utensils (fork and knife) the server declined though this was not applied to all costumers, with a statement \"you can use your fingers to eat\" This Information should be provided at the entrance so the customer can choose  what to do!  \nWe paid for the meal but I did not eat it.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(610, 'Tiffany Raleigh', 'Lonrho House Standard St, Nairobi Kenya', 'Cafe AMKA', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25398977-r1036523951-Cafe_AMKA-Nairobi.html', 'BEAUTIFUL RESTAURANT, TERRIBLE STAFF.', 'The restaurant has such beautiful ambience, and it‚Äôs a shame that the staff doesn‚Äôt reflect or complement it. \n\nWe got there and ordered, only to wait for over an hour for our food & drinks. The staff was drinking at the bar, ignoring our signals when we tried to follow up on what was making the food take so long. \n\nThe bill took ages to come, and when it did, our orders were captured wrong - I reckon because they were drunk - and this we found unacceptable & disrespectful. There‚Äôs no way we shall be returning, after such disrespect!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
