(632, 'Neil S', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r658664246-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Good place to unwind or watch football', 'Noisy place but quite fun and have a larger range of beers than most places. The food was very much pub food but although unhealthy it was good. They have a quiet area tucked away which we appreciated while eating. ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(633, 'munr', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r656589561-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Noisy lounge, but also good things', 'Me and a colleague went here for some beers and food. A band was playing. They were loud. If it was a concert it would be fine, but it seemed it was just live music to entertain the visitors. The music was good, but when you go out you would probably like to keep a conversation going. We literally had to yell to each other to be heard. After a while we resorted to chatting on Whatsapp. \n\nThe employees had a hard time taking our orders. The music was loud, and if this was the regular level of sound I also suspect they must have some damage to their ears.\n\nDamage to the ears could not explain why my patatas bravas were not cooked. They were rock hard. I sent them back.\n\nThe service from the waiters was excellent. All smiles and attentive. Bouncer as well. He helped me with the internet password.\n\nWe finnished our food and left after an hour. If they had not tried to damage my ears I could forgive them the lousy patatas bravas. I will probably not be back.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(634, 'Alexi.', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r654146036-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Corruption, harassment,rogue staff', 'What was once an excellent establishment, has completely become jeopardised,\n\nBrew bistro Westlands, (A corrupt free zone sign needs to be placed)\n\nIt starts with security,\nIt is a good thing for security to know one,\nBut it comes with the unexpected,\n\nThe second time you run into them,\nBy this time one becomes a money token,\n\nNot only do they put force on it,\nInsist on it,\n\nBut even while inside, one of them even came to me for his tip,\n\nThe harassment didn\'t stop there, what I offered, which to be honest if I was completely sober I wouldn\'t have given into,\n\nThis particular bouncer expected more,\n\nIt didn\'t stop there,\n\nI went downstairs to pick up my friends,\nOn my way up,\nI was once again targeted by a different security personnel\n\nWithin one night,\nI had at this time tipped two security personnels\n\nThe dilemma didn\'t stop there,\n\nThe brew staff as I now understand,\nHave their own way of marking someone,\n\nFrom a polite asking or rather  referring to a different server when it\'s very busy,\n\nAll boundaries are broken,\nIt seems \"you become friends\"\n\nAnd so all together, I ended up tipping five staff members within a one night,\n\nOur specific, server, this one he wasn\'t even content in his tip,\n\nNot only did he get argumentative but demanded more and made sure he got more,\n\nSomething is so terribly wrong somewhere,\n\nWords cannot even articulate the events of the corruption scenes, harassment of staff over tips, greed,\n\nThe fact that one has to deal with broken staff boundaries,\n\nIt really is so unfortunate given that there drinks and food are exceptional and the atmosphere according to me is accommodating,\n\nOne thing for sure though,\n\nIt is time to move on from Brew bistro', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(635, 'maria o', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r642368351-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Place to be if you love to party', 'Its a local joint in Nairobi, that offers a laid back interesting party scene.\nThey have both wonderful cocktails and food.\n', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(636, 'N3iriso', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r636249069-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Great Atmosphere', 'It is a tradition to have a good night out for me, especially in Nairobi. we went there on a Monday and they were open, all staff engaged and courteous and ready to help. \ni really like the music and the sliders are great! this place is not a miss if you pass by westie', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(637, 'jennifernyambare', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r635233596-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Hanging out @ Brew bistro ngong rd', 'After work or touring nairobi,unwind at the brew bistro. Loving the happy hour(5-7pm) buy one get one free drink.loving their own brewed beer, chuikolsh,temstrout, simpils and nyatipa.\nThe music selection is also amazingüòçüëå', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(638, 'Hasan S', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r631108302-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'Nice busy happening place', 'Had dinner there with office colleagues. It\'s a good place to wind down after a busy day. The place is quite energetic and fun.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(639, 'Chantelle P', 'Piedmont Plaza 671 Ngong Road, Nairobi Kenya', 'Brew Bistro & Lounge', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d2269080-r624221141-Brew_Bistro_Lounge-Nairobi.html', 'My favorite lounge in Nairobi', 'I\'ve been a regular Brew Bistro customer for around 6 years now. Used to frequent the Ngong Rd branch every Friday with my friends. My favorite branch is the Westlands one.\n\nTheir ambiance is a solid 4/5. Food 4/5. Cocktails and drinks 4/5. Service 3/5. Why I have service a low rating is because sometimes the staff can be a bit rude. Also, when the place gets packed, service slows down.\n\nOther than that, Brew Bistro is a great place to enjoy a weekend out with friends or a nice brunch with family. It\'s a must visit if you come to Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
