(665, 'Curious_TravellerKE', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r767758671-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'friends\' catch up ', 'Very few lunch dinner choices; mostly breakfast options. That said; enjoyed every bit of my thai beef salad; washed down with a cold glass of ginger ale. The decor and ambience fell below expectations.  ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(666, 'Michael R', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r748318376-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Perfect breakfast/brunch/lunch', 'Perfect breakfast/brunch/lunch restaurant for your Karura Forest visit.  (Or even if you don‚Äôt do the forest bit). We rode a bunch of trails and then stopped here for lunch. The venue is really nice with a large seating area covered by a very high roof, open on all sides, so it really feels like you are still connected with nature. Nice menu selection. Apparently the steaks are excellent, but I chose the bacon and cheese burger which was pretty good. This is NOT a dinner place as I believe it closes quite early to not disturb the wildlife.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(667, 'Gill d', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r739824298-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely menu in a great location', 'A great place to grab a drink or meal as part of your day out in Karura forest.  Good to book ahead as it can get really busy.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(668, 'chotinita', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r735333038-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Restaurant in the forest', 'This is a restaurant within the Karura forest, located in the Round area of Nairobi. It has about 15-tables, a safari type of ambience, and nice views of the surrounding forest. There is usually a good breeze from the open -sides, which is pleasant on hot days. \nThe food is below mediocre, very expensive, service is reasonable, but one can be kept waiting for some time. Our food looked unappetising, the fish was under-cooked, the chicken was dry and chewy. I would be reluctant to come here for a meal, though a coffee and snack, while enjoying the surrounds may be more satisfactory.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(669, 'Kenyan Traveller', 'Karura Forest at Amani Gardens, Off Limuru Road, opposite Belgian Embassy, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'The River Cafe - Karura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10806639-r732440620-The_River_Cafe_Karura-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent restaurant in the middle of the forest', 'A beautiful place in the middle of the forest where one can spend the whole afternoon sipping coffee and staring into the forest. So very relaxing.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(670, 'Dominique B', 'Lonrho House Standard St, Nairobi Kenya', 'Cafe AMKA', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25398977-r969715701-Cafe_AMKA-Nairobi.html', 'AMKA, the soul of Nairobi', 'Ma visite au caf√© AMKA a √©t√© une v√©ritable r√©v√©lation ! Gr√¢ce au talent exceptionnel du meilleur des barista, Kennedy Owino et son √©quipe, j‚Äôai d√©couvert la magie du caf√© et le monde du th√©. Chaque tasse vibrait comme une m√©lodie, et les infusions aux saveurs uniques avec des racines inexplor√©es, chantaient en parfaite harmonie. AMKA est bien plus qu‚Äôun simple caf√©, c‚Äôest une exp√©rience...... Nairobi a un incontournable, et je n‚Äôai qu‚Äôune h√¢te : y retourner tr√®s bient√¥t pour revivre cette aventure sensorielle inoubliable !\"', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(671, 'Kimberly F', 'Lonrho House Standard St, Nairobi Kenya', 'Cafe AMKA', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25398977-r969592714-Cafe_AMKA-Nairobi.html', 'The best birthday destination', 'This place is terrific and the service is excellent. I would highly recommend it for surprise birthdays and small events with friends, colleagues and family', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(672, 'Vivian W', 'Lonrho House Standard St, Nairobi Kenya', 'Cafe AMKA', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25398977-r969585843-Cafe_AMKA-Nairobi.html', 'Brain power', 'The staffs are kind and caring, and trust them to hook you up with the best drinks. Mr Kennedy ( waiter) is sure to provide you with the best pairing when it comes to dessert o. \nI\'m safe to say that I have found my chill spot üòú.\nTill next time, Amka Cafe', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(673, 'violet k', 'Lonrho House Standard St, Nairobi Kenya', 'Cafe AMKA', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25398977-r968705766-Cafe_AMKA-Nairobi.html', 'A Delightful and Enchanting Tea Experience at Amka!', 'My friends and I stumbled upon Caf√© Amka by chance, and what a serendipitous find it was! We were warmly recommended to try their herbal infusions and special dawas by the head barista, Kennedy Owino, and I must say, it was an enchanting journey from the first sip.\n\nAs someone who doesn‚Äôt typically gravitate toward tea or coffee, I didn‚Äôt expect to be so thoroughly captivated. Yet, I left Caf√© Amka a true convert.\n\nWe began our tasting with the Relaxing Orange Rooibos, which was simply divine. Next up was the Nairobi Nector‚Äîa vibrant infusion of yerba mate, lemongrass, pineapple, hibiscus, and mint. The flavors still dance on my palate as I write this, even a day later.\n\nThen came Brain Power, which completely blew me away. Each element of the infusion hit different parts of my palate in perfect harmony, without any one flavor overpowering the others.\n\nOur final infusion was the Queen Koi, and oh, what a finale it was! With its blend of yerba mate, coconut, ginger, pineapple, chamomile, mint, and lemongrass, we were left in awe, unable to decide which tea was the best‚Äîthey were all exceptional.\n\nWhile we savored these remarkable teas, we also learned so much about the history of Caf√© Amka. It‚Äôs far from your ordinary cafe. Every ingredient is carefully selected, with the barista team curating the menu themselves. Herbs like yerba mate are sourced from indigenous communities in Argentina, and their cacao is exclusively ceremonial-grade and single-origin. Speaking of cacao, we sampled the Nutmeg Cacao‚Äîrich, creamy, and utterly luxurious, yet light on the tongue. It was perfection in a cup.\n\nThis cafe completely exceeded our expectations. What started as a brief meet-up with friends turned into two hours of savoring every sip and soaking in the experience.\n\nI cannot recommend this tea experience enough‚Äîit should be on everyone‚Äôs bucket list when visiting Nairobi‚Äôs CBD. I‚Äôm already looking forward to my next visit, where I‚Äôll be sure to indulge in their pastries and, of course, more of their exceptional teas! A huge thank you to Kennedy and the entire team‚Äîwe‚Äôll be talking about this experience for a very long time.\n\nP.S. They also serve amazing coffee, and they‚Äôve won awards for it too. Coffee lovers, this one‚Äôs for you!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(674, 'Winnie c', 'Lonrho House Standard St, Nairobi Kenya', 'Cafe AMKA', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25398977-r968702612-Cafe_AMKA-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden Gem in Nairobi CBD', 'The ambience was great, the books and couch to read was a great touch to everything . \nService from Muringo was awesome she gave us awesome recommendations that we are happy we took...the speciality dawas are now my absolute favorite.üòä', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
