(740, 'Paradise13541392385', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r976465338-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'I was a nervous hell meeting my partners parents together. I had to do it at Ezo!', 'My Booking Experience \n\nMy journey begins with making a reservation at the esteemed Ezo Restaurant. After perusing the menu, social media and reviews, I made an online reservation on 21st October 2024, booking a table for four persons. The time of arrival was supposed to be at 7pm. Which after making the reservation, a message popped-up that the manager will reach out to confirm the reservation.  I did not receive a call or message from the manager at the time of the booking that notwithstanding, my partner was able to follow-up the next day and I received my confirmation via text. \n\nOn Arrival\n\nThe evening ambience is quite good I was very casual in dressing, but I quickly leant my dress code was a little out of place. I should have worn formal or smart casual. In short, the place is too nice for a college jacket, Nike, Chinos and a Polo shirt. Our waiter Immaculate led my partner and I to our table. The initial table met my standards. The waiter was able to do a coat check for my partner and I. We were immediately provided with our menu and an immaculate pieces of chop sticks signaling that we will definitely be treated in an elegant fashion. After a quick glance of the room and placing our drink orders, my partner requested for a change of table/sitting. My partner preferred to have a table with the least distractions. We were pleasantly led to a different table which was even better than the former. \n\nThe Drinks & Starters.\n\nI will focus on my order. I really liked the prices and the list of drinks for the picking. Being a consumer of finer things and with a well-informed pallet, I avoided liquor for the reason I was meeting my partners parents, and I had a long day at work so drinking was not the best idea. So, I opted for an Earl Grey. Its tea I drank so often while in Europe. It is black tea served with bergamot oil and honey. \n\nFor my starter, I had Miso soup, tofu, wakame, enoki mushrooms.  This is the best soup in my opinion I have had the whole year. I might just go back and have this alone and by myself. \n\nMains.\n\nI had made the wrong choice. Let me explain! Red Snapper Katsu with Passion Fruit-Dashi Sauce, Asparagus and Green Beans with a side of baked potatoes. This is going to be alittle disappointing. \n\nPassion Fruit does not pair well with Dashi Sauce and the perfectly cooked Red Snapper! There was something awful about that pairing. I could barely finish my sauce. I tried taking the sauce alone, I paired it with the fish, with the green beans and it was just not working. \n\nI would have ordinarily sent the plate back but, I really liked the Snapper, and I did not want it to go back. Secondly, I like my green beans with a little more seasoned. \n\nAs for the baked potatoes.. I will give it a 5/10. Nothing special about it. \n\nBy this time, I was literally full to the brim. I had no room for desert at this point. But what I can say is that, I think their menu is very interesting. I will be visiting this place at least once a month.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"events_entertainment\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(741, 'Gennadii Bukhalovskii', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r976464624-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'It‚Äôs worth visiting for sure.', 'It is the awesome place to get a well cooked meal. The staff is perfectly trained and attentive. The atmosphere is very friendly and the background music is excellent.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(742, 'Robert P', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r975192324-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'A very disappointing dinner', 'Had dinner with a friend at Ezo and was thoroughly disappointed, particularly with the service.  We ordered an appetiser and main meal.  The waiter forgot the appetiser completely and only brought the main meal.  He apologised and asked if we still wanted the appetiser and we said no.  He then brought the wet wipes to clean our hands, after the main meal was delivered and we had started eating.\n\nThe manager did come by to see how we liked our meal and we told her how disappointed we were.  She asked if there was anything she could do but we said no there wasn\'t she could do at that time.\n\nThe food itself was tasty but the portions were very small and any vegetables, potatoes or rice were all at an additional cost.\n\nThe prices were clearly in the upper end for any restaurant.  So combined with the poor service, I would certainly not recommend this restaurant.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
