(777, 'Samuel M', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r715461897-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Love the African Touch', 'It was a nice experience being in Havana Bar and restaurant...especially being served by Liz Wangare ...the service was superB from her...will be there again and again. üôÉüôÉ zippie and Sam', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(778, 'Steven T', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r678221608-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Great atmosphere good food and friendly service', 'This is a friendly cosmopolitan bar ,it accommodates local workers, tourists and business people from around the world.  \n\nLoved the casual atmosphere and felt like I was getting real value for money.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(779, 'llansford', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r662242747-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Confused ambiance and lackluster experience', 'Maybe we went at an off-hour or maybe we aren\'t the target audience, but after reading rave reviews of this place we were incredibly disappointed. It was too dark, very quiet (like, we were the only ones there), and seems to be set up as a \"safe\" and easy restaurant for tourists. The Havana theme wasn\'t quite working--other than a few themed drinks and a Cuban flag, the country/western music, friend Euro-centric cuisine, and strange decor just weren\'t working for a cohesive or pleasant ambiance. This is the only place on the entire trip where we didn\'t experience warmth from people, and I got the impression maybe it wasn\'t the workers\' fault. We initially stopped in for dinner & drinks, but soon decided to down our Tuskers quickly and head elsewhere. The Alchemist ended up being an impressive and super fun alternative and was just around the corner.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(780, 'Cyrill S', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r655614193-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'feines Essen, k√ºhles Bier und \"Leichte Damen\"', 'Ich kann das Restaurant nur empfehlen: sehr gutes Essen, freundliches Personal, anst√§ndige Preise, ideale Lage in einem belebten Quartier, als Alleinreisender macht man nat√ºrlich auch schnell Bekanntschaft mit den Damen, was aber kein Problem ist, da sie weder aufdringlich noch aggressiv sind, sondern einfach nett...', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(781, 'blind.spot', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r654259142-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'essen + musik', 'das havana ist sowohl restaurant , als auch bar . es gibt eine vielzahl von unterschiedlichen speisen aus den unterschiedlichsten gegenden , aber nicht kubanisch , dazu manchmal livemusik/dj . ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\"]'),
(782, 'Friedwald S', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r652030254-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Great place to eat and cocktails', 'Big SURPRISE, excellent place to enjoy a fine dinner at modest prices.\nGreat atmosphere, perfect place to hang out. Interesting Africa art.\nTruly enjoyed the visit, like to highlight the kitchen again, almost at Michelin star level !\nWill go again during my next visit to Nairobi', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(783, 'July Fireworks', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r636733515-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Just OK.', 'The seevice was pretty good. The waitress was nice. It\'s a bar but you get a private area for eating. Ciban Style!! The Tilapia Fillet was exceptionally good though . Definitely worth every penny.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(784, 'Trisingh', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r622711660-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'One of the place travelers must try. ', 'Brillant place, good food, nice music which is not too loud.\nOverall nice place to have good food, talks and nice music.. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(785, 'Gardrr', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r616508215-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Good food and great atmosphere ', 'Don\'t get tricked from the little dodgy look from the outside. They serve good food in the restaurant and have all types of drinks in the bar. Plays r&b and have a smoking friendly bar upstairs. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(786, 'Juma C', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1031661960-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'Hospitality at it best', 'Nice hospitality from the staff.. especially Morine K and Virginia excellent welcoming and the food was tasty and yummy', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(787, 'Shirley R', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1031016907-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'See you soon.', 'I had the pleasure of being served by Mercy M. during my visit to Serena hotel and I genuinely can‚Äôt say enough good things. From the moment we were seated, Mercy made us feel welcomed, cared for, and completely at ease. Her warmth, attention to detail, and ability to anticipate our needs without ever hovering was the kind of 5-star service you don‚Äôt forget.\nShe was knowledgeable about the menu, offered thoughtful recommendations, and her timing was impeccable throughout the evening. You could tell she truly cared about our experience  and she elevated it beyond just a meal into something really special.\nThank you, Mercy, for your kindness and professionalism. You‚Äôre a gem, and I hope the hotel knows how lucky they are to have you!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(788, 'rnelsen', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1030624681-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent Service & Beautiful Setting', 'Specialty coffees were delicious. Nice variety of food on the buffet. Servers were exceptionally friendly & service was excellent.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(789, 'Voyage699084', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1030440500-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'EXCEEDED EXPECTATION', 'It was lovely,everything on point, Mary M,gave us excellent service,pleasant and very prompt.\nLocation -Convinient\nAtmosphere- Very welcoming\nFood- Spoilt for Choice\nService - Excellent \nValue - Worth the amount \nWait Time - Promptness', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(790, 'douvel t', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1030340292-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'A Beautiful day', 'The delicate care and attention had me feeling so loved. The food was so good as always. Special thanks to Joseph, Raphael and James. Serena will always have my heart.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(791, 'HARRIET ADHIAMB... O', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1030339987-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely', 'A 10/10 experience really attentive staff, great food and the ambience is cozy \nRaphael and James  were excellent \nI definitely enjoyed', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(792, 'Nomad13556779813', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1029891725-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent food and service', 'I really enjoyed the Sunday Brunch. Both the food and service was excellent\nMost especially the prawns they were delicious üòã . I would also like to recognise David.S who took care of us and Victor who kept on checking on us\nThe band was also lovely', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(793, 'Janet N', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1029879134-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'Our meals at cafe Maghreb', 'The food selection was very complete at their buffet. The staff were friendly and accommodating. It is a beautiful restaurant and hotel. I would definitely recommend', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(794, 'lesleydrane', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1029258858-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'My  husband very happy', 'Foods excellent very large portions \nThe waitress was very attentive Eunice happy and couldn‚Äôt do enough for us also suggested dishes', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(795, 'Faith N', 'Nairobi Serena Hotel Processional Way, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Cafe Maghreb', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1972492-r1029251614-Cafe_Maghreb-Nairobi.html', 'Above expected dinner', 'I reached the hostess desk and there was no one standing by the door as usual. \nJoseph came and apologise to us and escorted us to the table of our choise.\nWith his kindness he did a very good introduction of himself and the buffet. He provided us a unique hot towel in a hospitality way  \" Excuse me madam , a hot towel for you please\" while smiling. \nHe then served a very nice mushroom soup with bread which we enjoyed.\nThe buffet food was amazing and above my expectation. Nairobi Serena is above 5*.  Joseph was presentable with quick service and good listening skills by repeating our beverage orders and being attentive to us.\nI realised all staff are organised when a lady in black suit approaches our table and excused herself to clear the emty plate.\nI will be back oneday  for another Family dinner.ü•∞ü•∞ü•∞üòçü•∞ü•∞ü•∞', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(796, 'JULIET A', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r972495939-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Want some luxury experience, Visit EZO!', 'Luxury set up! Loved it! And their top chef has a Michelin Star! We were served at a private dining area. \n\nStaff were really amazing!!!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(797, 'Nelly Nzisa', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r972495695-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Their food is great.Their sushi is unmatched -minimalist, delicate and unforgettable  .The  ambience is also üíØ !', 'Their food is great.Their sushi is unmatched -minimalist, delicate and unforgettable  .The  ambience is also üíØ !\nIt‚Äôs also the only restuarant with a Michelin starred chef !', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(798, 'Tanya O', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r972405939-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Nice memories of visiting EZO restaurant', 'Cool place! Everything at EZO was great!  The staff is very attentive and friendly and the croissant with salmon , WOW!!!!!\n The cozy atmosphere and amazing flavor left the warmest impressions. \nMy only regret is that I was not there in the evening when they have parties and my favorite DJs play!\nI give it 5 stars and recommend it !', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(799, 'Artem e', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r972402838-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'extrardinary', 'Ezo Restaurant in Nairobi is highly recommended for those seeking an authentic Japanese dining experience. The restaurant combines modern and traditional Japanese aesthetics, creating a welcoming atmosphere ideal for various dining occasions.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(800, 'holidaylover55', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r967796388-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'NAIROBI‚ÄôS FINEST', 'My last review related to EZO was far from complementary. That said after last night all is forgotten. On arrival one has to pass through a metal detector and security check , then one enters the restaurant , \nThe decor is minimal and subtle, in the background you have house music to set the ambiance. Our waitress was friendly and the service was on point. The restaurant has an extensive wine list we opted for a Vergelegen Sauvignon Blanc. For starters we had the Various Nigiri. Eel , Tuna and Salmon. All excellent . I have tried most sushi establishments in Nairobi and this was the best I have had in Nairobi . We then moved onto a portion of Pork Dumplings , again excellent. For mains we had the Red Snapper served with mixed vegetables and the Duck breast served with spinach and mash accompanied with a reduction. Again top notch. For dessert we decided to share a dessert. Coconut ice cream with a lemon foam and meringue. The perfect finish to our dinner. The food I had last night was amazing and was world class. I highly recommend you try EZO.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(801, 'Alexey A', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r956653707-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Outstanding food quality for Kenya', 'Absolutely the best restaurant in Kenya.  At Michelin level. I didn\'t think I could find such a high standard of food in Kenya.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(802, 'Expat Kate', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r954652587-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great Food but too overpriced', 'EZO Restaurant is Kenya‚Äôs first Neo-Japanese restaurant, led by a Michelin Stared Chef. Located on the second floor of Stellato Mall, (42 Muthithi Rd ), Westlands. \nThe restaurant offers a fine dining experience ( high quality food , service , comfort ) that I have experienced in very few places across Nairobi. If you‚Äôre tired of the same old meals you‚Äôve had over and over, then come check out EZO restaurant for something different. You will not regret it. \n\nBE PREPARED TO OPEN YOUR WALLET üí≥ üíµ. The restaurant is priceyü´£ü§Ø. \nüìù Our orders:\n- - - - - -\n‚Ä¢ Dry age tenderloin beef with mushroom sauce and pak Choi [ Ksh3100 / $10 / ‚Ç¨9 ] \n‚Ä¢ Chicken katsu, rice, yuzu curd [ Ksh1950 / $14 / ‚Ç¨15 ] \n‚Ä¢ Tonkotsu ramen, pork chashu, wheat noodles, egg [ Ksh1900 / $14 / ‚Ç¨13 ] \n‚Ä¢ Udon, chicken broth, egg, chicken roll [ Ksh1650 / $13 / ‚Ç¨12 ] \n‚Ä¢ Hot chocolate cake, caramel ice cream and ginger mousse [ Ksh900 / $7 / ‚Ç¨6 ] \n- - - - -\n ü§î My only critics are; \n1) The menu is small and limited ( catering mostly for adults and not so much for any child below the ages of 6 years ) ;\n2) The portions are very small ( they could be a bit more generous ), both in terms of mains and accompaniments. \n\n Aside from that , it is so great to have another quality restaurant option in Nairobi! ‚Ä¶ We will definitely be back to try out some of the other dishes that the restaurant has to offer. \n\nThe tables are limited , so it is best to call ahead and making a reservation.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(803, 'holidaylover55', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r948049844-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Worst Experience in my Life', 'I had heard about this new restaurant in Nairobi and was excited to give it a try. \nWhen I heard Chef Evgeny Vikentev was doing a Russian Dinner I was super excited Price 25 000 KES with wine pairing. I had missed Evgeny when he did a pop up in Dubai. I was advised that I had to make a 100 % prepayment to book. \nSo on Sunday 21 April I took a drive to Ezo to make my prepayment. As I stepped out of the lift I was greeted by Emily the hostess and escorted to a table so that see could organize the payment. Great polite friendly service. A gentleman then arrived , ignored me and was more focused on communicating with my girlfriend. 3 times I said to excuse me it think you should be speaking to me I made the booking and am the one paying. Finally when he turned around he asked me what is my problem. I asked him for his name he refused . I explained to him his behavior was most rude. I asked him a few more times for his name before I left he refused. On leaving Emily was most apologetic and apologized on his behalf. I told her she had done nothing wrong. That afternoon I did some research and found the name of the rude gentleman it is Mr Hillary  Okello ( Food & Beverage Manger ) . I was so upset that on Monday I tried to reach out to someone senior at Ezo. I was contacted by a Mr Emil. We had a talk he told me it was all a big misunderstanding, and that I should still come to the event. It is now Wednesday 4 days later , my girlfriend remains upset as do I. In all my years of going to restaurants including the famous El Bulli in Spain have I ever been treated like this. Sorry Ezo team you can bring Michelin Chefs to Kenya but if your team does not know how to treat your customers you will not succeed in this industry.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(804, 'Joy M', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r946772777-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Subpar Food', 'It was an extremely disappointing fine dining experience. Despite the limited menu, the food quality was poor. While I understand that fine dining restaurants prioritise quality and flavour over quantity, this fell way off the mark. The meals we ordered were underwhelming and lacked diversity, flavours were basic and overall combinations just not it. On a positive note, the background music was good.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(805, 'Jens C', 'Stellato Mall, 42, Muthithi Road 2nd Floor, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ezo Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d27128080-r945608291-Ezo_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'New and exciting experience in Nairobi', 'Excellent food with a wide and varied selection of Asian fusion food. Recommend for a new dining experience in Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(806, 'wanja', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1029225848-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Food contamination', 'We ended up having a very bad food contamination infection after consuming their salad and beef steak. Avoid !\nThe customer service was so poor , it was raining and the roof at the outdoor terrace was leaking  and water started pouring on us . They were just stairing at us instead of helping us to move tables. Can‚Äôt go back . Can‚Äôt eat at CJs again', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(807, 'Bounce B', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1027329129-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Ensalada', 'I love this particular branch of CJ\'s. I have been here for breakfast, lunch and early dinner. What do I love about it compared to the one halfway across town at Village Market? This one is not crowded and they have more attention to detail. The village market one gave me salted bacon and the place was overflowing. Honestly, of a place is full, do the New York thing of waiting. Waterfront is value for money. \nAll CJ\'s have large portions I am never finish coz it\'s like a double portion! They always pack a doggy bag.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"delivery_takeout\"]'),
(808, 'Elizabeth M', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1022490980-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'The place smells good and the service is quick! Yummy, filling plates üçΩ üòã', 'They receive you at the entrance like they prayed for you to come üòÑ  so warm and kind... the food service doesn\'t take too much time\n\nWhen you ask for an extra lettuce as seen on the menu they don\'t hesitate to bring.  Crowded yes but bearable! Especially lunch time\nMaybe mid morning would be a litu quieter üòâ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(809, 'Judi O', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1021095718-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Superb dining experience', 'The food was spectacular. The service was amazing. The servers Sharon & Abigail M were superb waitresses. After we ordered the food which was cooked perfectly, it arrived at our table after a short wait. Anything we requested was delivered with a happy attitude. The manager Abhishek made sure everything ran smoothly.  All in all - 10 out of 10.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(810, 'Angela L', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1019550089-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', '', 'Abhishek has offered great service today. He is professional and empathetic. Quite excellent at his work. CJs restaurant in Karen is top notch.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(811, 'Valary S', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1014185786-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Brunch', 'The mananger Mr.Abhishek at the waterfront branch was kind and on stand by for assistance.The servers are kind  and the food was amezing', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(812, 'Shalom N', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1014015901-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing Brunch Time at CJs!', 'Excellent service from Manager Abhishek and Server Brenda at the Karen Waterfront CJs, good food, super service and they both went out of our way to make this experience amazing.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(813, 'Alice M', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1011319850-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Karen Waterfront', 'Excellent services from Manager Abhishek. He accommodated our requests graciously and kept us well served. Highly recommended üëå \n\nThe food portions are generous, fresh and tasty.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(814, 'Lox', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r1011225997-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Good food at a good price', 'Food is plentiful, served quickly, very reasonably priced and of good quality.\nStaff is varied, many are excellent, while others need to be told several times what you want; water at room temperature seems a particularly difficult concept.\nMy only gripe is that the rice served with a [chipotle] salad is often icey cold and that romaine lettuce has unappetizing big stalks, might be better to use thinly sliced iceberg lettuce.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(815, 'GLR HILLS HOTEL H', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r998743567-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'EXCEPTIONAL FOOD, OUTSTANDING SERVICE', 'We have been in January 2025 for a wildlife project and had an amazing experience at CJs restaurant. The food was absolutely delicious, fresh, and full of flavor. Every dish was prepared to perfection, and the presentation was spot on.\nThe entire team provided excellent service friendly, attentive and always making sure we are comfortable. A special mention to Manager Bipin, who went above beyond to ensure we had a great time. His professionalism and warm hospitality made all the difference.\nHighly recommend this place and will definitely be coming back.  \n\nThanks CJs and Team.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(816, 'Hamza S', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r968692984-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Bad customer service', 'This was by far the worst dining experience I‚Äôve ever had, and honestly, I can‚Äôt even believe how badly I was treated. From the moment I walked in, it was clear that customer service was the last thing on anyone\'s mind. After waiting for a good 10 minutes just to get a table, they finally seated me, but then, without so much as a word or explanation, they abruptly moved me. I hadn\'t even had a chance to order! No one bothered to ask if I was comfortable, if I had been helped, or even acknowledge my presence beyond shuffling me around like I didn‚Äôt matter. The lack of basic courtesy was staggering, and I felt completely disrespected.\n\nTo make matters worse, no one apologized or explained why they moved me. It was as if I was an inconvenience to them for simply being there. I‚Äôve never been treated this poorly in any restaurant. The staff clearly has no understanding of how to handle customers, and frankly, it was insulting. It‚Äôs shocking that a place like this is even in business with such horrendous customer service. After waiting around like a fool, hoping someone would finally take my order or at least acknowledge what had happened, I had enough.\n\nI left and went right next door to Kuku, where‚Äîwithin less than a minute‚ÄîI was seated, greeted with a smile, and had my order taken. The stark contrast in how I was treated at Kuku compared to the first restaurant was mind-blowing. It just shows how bad the service was at the first place. I will never go back there, and I would advise anyone thinking about visiting to steer clear. It was a complete waste of time, and frankly, they don‚Äôt deserve anyone‚Äôs business with the way they treat customers. Absolutely shameful!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(817, 'Massimo G', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r963417205-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Bella sorpresa', 'Nel centro commerciale nella zona tranquilla del Karen, posto tranquillo con men√π vario. Personale disponibile prezzi modici', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(818, 'Liam B', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r961581618-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Very good food', 'I have gone to Cjs many times and I always love it. They are very consistent with everything on their menu. I would recommend their tacos. The service is very fast as well. If you are in Nairobi I would recommend cjs.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(819, 'Brianna K', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r945832754-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Best service ever', 'The service was amazing my sisters food took less than one minute to be on the and the food was delicious I definitely recommend', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(820, 'Jeremiah Kibanya', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r945679151-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Refreshing Waterfront Dining', 'CJ‚Äôs is really more than a brand: It consistently gives you that excellent combination you would be looking for in a restaurant, whether you patronize solo, with friends, family or for business meetings. I have experienced all these, celebrated many family birthdays and other special occasions, and they truly live up to their unique standard and quality.\n\nTheir service is warm and personalized, their food is fresh, in delicious and generous portions; a truly great value for money. The ambiance is relaxing, with the water frontage. There will be a family, or two, or ten, celebrating something over a cake, and staff momentarily turn into a choir that belts out celebratory vibes, cheering the whole floor.\n\nCJ‚Äôs  will remain a No. 1 choice for my family and l, for those memorable meals and moments. Ms Philomena promptly took our order and served the delicious meal for the family. The team is doing a really Excellent job, led by their able manager, Mr Bipin,  Keep it up!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(821, 'Happiness595830', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r925427129-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Cafe with a difference', 'Great location where I can work, relax, have my coffee and a snack and have a view over the lake. Staff are very friendly and efficient. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(822, 'Marion N', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r913291785-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Honest review ', 'Ambience is good,  food is great and customer care is exceptional,  courtesy of one Judy who served us well.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(823, 'Risper M', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r913289057-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'CJ\'s review', 'Definitely would recommend to other people. Has great food, ambience and customer service. Judy was exceptional while attending to us and the food didn\'t take too long to arrive.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
