(826, 'KJain', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r1022758686-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'The best cakes / desserts in Nairobi!!!', 'Been to the Le Grenier twice for desserts and coffee and loved it!!! All that we ate was delicious & perfectly baked. \nLemon tart, salted caramel tart, brownie with ice-cream, macchiato, earl grey tea, and we picked up the orange tea cake.\nEven the cakes ordered for my birthday were absolutely   delicious. We ordered g√¢teau √† l‚Äôorange et au chocolat (orange chocolate)  & g√¢teau √† la mousse de chocolat noir (all chocolate).', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\"]'),
(827, 'Philippe C', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r1003138668-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'So disappointing!', 'We used to go to Petit Grenier at Riverside, though this was quite far from us. We were so excited to have a new outlet opening next to us in Mwanzi market. We have now come several times and it is a real disappointment for having breakfast there.\nWe first came about 6 weeks ago and lots of items missing on the menu, the service was slow and careless. We came back 3 weeks later, the food court was busy but again lack of attention from the staff which we called twice, got the answer - we are coming. WE did not want to wait further and left to go to Sugar Bowl nearby. Last week, we came again, service was poor and again no attention, still half of the items missing on the menu.  We also picked pastries for lunch and unfortunately, these were not fresh especially the eclairs and macarons - not crispy at all but soggy. As it is 2 mins drive, we were here again today , different team but same type of service. Manager walks in with hands in the pockets!! We ordered pain perdu from teh menu and for a French patisserie/bistro it is a real disaster. The brioche bread has only been passed so briefly into the egg mixuture rather than soaking in it and the panfried. Being a typical dish in France, it is really a shame for Petit Grenier to serve this so badly The rest of the food (salmon sandwich and a chicken salad) were OK. This is so disappointing as the outlet in Riverside used to be good! we will have to switch back to Sugarbowl', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(828, 'lindah', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r964878804-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Perfect', 'Perfect breakfast! The bread is the best! Staff are so friendly! The sweet sausage was so yummy!!! Definitely going back\nThe pastry section is heavenly', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(829, 'Dorcas M', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r958846246-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing food, poor service', 'Honestly, I would give Le Grenier 10 stars if only their service matched the quality of their food :-(\n\nI\'ve been patronising this cafe since 2020 and usually recommend it to anyone with ears, but if there\'s something that I\'ve consistently experienced regardless of time of day, number of patrons etc is really shockingly slow service. Plenty of times I\'ve had to get up and go to the counter to place my order because the waiters/waitresses (who are lovely) are huddled talking instead of paying attention to customers. \n\nToday was especially disappointing because I was in a hurry and had just enough time for a quick bite in between meetings, but it took ages for a waiter to take my order, then to inform me that they had run out of plain croissants and there was a fresh batch baking in the over that would be ready in a few minutes, then to inform me that the croissants had backfired in the oven and another batch would take another 2 hours to bake. \n\nI had to then change my order and still had to chase it up as staff members just stood idly...this is disappointing.\n\nLe Grenier has the best pastries I\'ve ever tasted in the world and definitely the best hot chocolate on the continent. If they improve their service standards, they will be the best to ever do it.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(830, 'Muna M', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r901157866-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Easy breakfast spot in Nairobi ', 'Easy breakfast spot in the hubbub of Nairobi! Good food and better service. Coffee however you want - and very good, iced or cold brew on those hot days. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(831, 'Matvl', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r888383473-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Fab spot', 'This is a great spot. Fantastic pastries, great coffee and a good menu: we enjoyed everything we had. Service and staff were great - it was a hot and we‚Äôll certainly be back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(832, 'Mr P', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r887767842-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Great pastries ', 'Perhaps the only true French bakery in Nairobi. Excellent pastries, the coffee is also great, the one small nitpick perhaps is missing attention to detail around the drinks but other than that a great spot for brunch and/or a light meal ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(833, 'holidaylover55', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r885123533-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Bakery Heaven', 'This must be the best Bakery in Nairobi. They offer a vast selection of breads including sour dough types. Then they have bread rolls plus croissants , quiche plus an incredible selection of pastries. The coffee and juices are also top notch. All the items are avaible to eat in or for take away. \nThey have in door plus out door dinning. The staff are always friendly and well trained. One thing I must mention it is a cashless zone. So remeber to bring your bank card or M-PESA. On negative thing to mention on my visit was the torn seats in one part of the establishment. Get it fixed .\nWill be back. This is a fantastic Sunday brunch venue.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(834, 'Charlotte Beauvoisin Diary of a Muzungu', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r878645575-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'It didn\'t disappoint üòã', 'I Googled \"best places for brunch in Nairobi\" and up came the recommendation for Nairobi\'s best croissant ü•ê\nIt didn\'t disappoint üòã\nIt was extremely hard to opt for a plain croissant with mouthwatering almond and chocolate ones on display.\nHam and cheese baguette perfectly, tastily French!\nMostly great service tho at times I had to call someone over (it wasn\'t all that busy).\nOverall, highly recommended.\nNot much to see from the outside as the restaurant is in ground floor of a modern block, which is accessed by a non-descript but secure parking area.\n\n#foodie #diaryofamuzungu #eastafricatraveldirectory', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(835, 'LeanneHeinrichs', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r848597447-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Superior desserts', 'Recently visited this coffee shop on a couple of different trips to Nairobi.  Must say their desserts, in particular the tarts and croissants, taste as good as they look!  The lemon tart has the perfect amount of sweet vs. tart flavour and the salted caramel is equally as delicious.  Note they only accept m-pesa or cc.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(836, 'Anne M', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r837312289-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'So disappointed. Do not order food.', 'Was a regular here  before Covid. Wow. Food is so disappointing . Ordered some eggs with the truffle oil and mushrooms. It was pitiful. The portion was so small with the thinnest slice of bread. Someone from the party order avo and toast with baby spinach. They got served lettuce and we were told they don\'t serve spinach any more. The third meal was a massive stodgy piece of bread with chicken and not a green leaf in sight. \nSafe to say not coming back here except for the pastries.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(837, 'Kui K', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r815688660-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Food Quality Standards Have Dropped', 'I remember LGP when it opened and the meals were great! Last two times I have visited, the sandwiches have been mediocre, served with a pitiful side of lettuce in the name of a salad. Very disappointing and a waste of money. Because one pays for their meal and drinks before service, no one comes after to confirm if the meal is good. I guess since you have already paid, no one cares?\n\nService is slow and I waited 10 minutes for cutlery before I walked up to a different waiter to ask them for it.\n\nTheir pastries and desserts are still very good so made a note to self not to bother with anything else on their menu. Not worth it especially when Barista & Co is just up the road.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(838, 'Stephanie', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r815647955-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Extremely poor service ', 'The food is still relatively good. Standard for food has gone down from the last time I came. However the service today was absolutely atrocious. It took more then 30 mins to receive food that was already made. I had to make several trips to the counter to continously ask and the only answer I got was \"its coming\". Please improve the service. ', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(839, 'Ali b', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r814671269-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Saturday Breakfast 1 hr  order', 'This is the first review I placing since Internet started. \n\nSo disappointed with the service nowadays at LGAP. \nWe ordered breakfast not only the orde came wrong but 1 hour later. We don\'t need to beg for services. The excuse from the manager was we lack manpower. This is Kenya. \nKindly improve your willingness to sell so that I can be motivated to improve my willingness to pay and come back. \n\nThis is the last time I am visiting this place again.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(840, 'Stephanie', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r809967228-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing pastries ', 'The food here is amazing. The pastries are so delectable its addictive. The only thing is that maybe the coffee is a bit bitter but apart from the fantastic. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\"]'),
(841, 'NurseMama25', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r799644733-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Goodness', 'Beautiful French bakery with so many delights. Took tea masala, hot chocolate, and a scrumptious almond croissant. Only negative was understanding their ordering system. There is no table service to take an order but if dining in, they will bring the order once placed at the counter. No cash accepted; credit card or Moses only.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]');
