(842, 'Jackie M', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r781086187-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Dismal Service', 'Having being here before, I expected great service and even better food. On arrival, we seated ourselves and had to wait a while before realising that it was self service. We made our way to the counter, ordered, went back to our table. We didn\'t know what to expect as there was only no waiter in sight to offer guidelines on how long our food & drinks would take, and whether they would be served to us or not because we saw a couple of customers walk to the service area to pick their own orders. After about 15 minutes of no service, we collected our drinks from the service counter, and another 10 min later, one waiter surfaced, bearing our food. Definitely not going back for a sit down meal. Restricting my visits to purchase assorted pasties only. Grossly disappointed!!!', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(843, 'Anne H', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r778943064-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Wonderful food', 'The Mille Feuille was perhaps the very best Mille Feuille I have ever eaten--including in France! Very nice, airy setting too.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(844, 'Amanda', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r774374753-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Lack of Covid-19 measures and overpriced.', 'The chocolate pastry and caramel tart  I ordered were very tasty but definitely overpriced. \nI was very shocked and disappointed at the lack of cleanliness and hygiene considering the current situation. No hand washing unit or temperature check, let alone sanitiser upon entering the venue. \nEverything is self service which is understandable, but there is no wiping of tables before or after guests leave. No signage about needing to distance or wash your hands. \nVery unimpressed with the lack of hygine here and this was confusing as every other venue in Nairobi are following the cleanliness rules to the utmost level.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(845, 'Ca R', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r750374396-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'gutes essen in gem√ºtlicher umgebung', 'Die b√§ckerei bietet nicht nur Teigwaren sondern hat auch eine sch√∂ne Speisekarte mit Salaten und warmen Mahlzeiten.\nman kann gem√ºtlich drau√üen sitzen. \nSehr nettes Personal und angemessene Preise', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(846, 'Besa', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r609264012-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Surprisingly good', 'The place looks a bit strange from the outside and even from the inside it is not the most prettiest place but the food was really good. The service speed could improve a little. A place to recommend. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(847, 'Nate D', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r603176815-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Havana...one the best hidden secrets in Westlands', 'Havana doesn\'t appear to be much from the outside, but inside you will find a hidden gem serving some of the best food in Westlands/Nairobi. The warm glow from the orange walls, accented by dim lighting, combined with friendly staff and most importantly...some of the best food in Nairobi makes Havana one of the top five restaurants in the area. They have biweekly specials, allowing the chef to showcase his skill. The bacon double cheeseburger is probably the best burger in town, and when coupled with crispy homemade onion rings makes for delicious meal. Havana does Taco Tuesdays as well...the pork and fish are my favourites. They also provide complimentary chips and guacamole, but you need to request it immediately, as they make the chips fresh for each order. Expect loud music on the weekends, and service staff can be a bit slow at times, but the consistency of the food is what makes Havana stand out from comparable restaurants in Nairobi. Nine out of ten times, Havana meets my expectations...an unusually high ratio for Nairobi. The value for money is also excellent.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(848, 'LikeFully', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r588056199-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Looks like a hole from outside, but is warm and friendly inside', 'I went here on a Friday night after a long week in Nairobi. It looks really dodgy when you look in from the street, but inside it is warm and friendly. The restaurant part is very retro cool with interesting paintings on the wall. I had grilled tilapia with a coconut chili sauce which was very nice. My dining partners enjoyed their meals. \n\nService is a little on the slow side, but if you want a nice, chilled place to relax and have a quiet conversation this is a good option. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(849, 'Ben', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r574095600-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Small but always busy.', 'Been coming here on and off for a number of years. It\'s a good place to catch up with friends. The staff are friendly the atmosphere is always booming. There are a lot of hookers but after you make it clear you\'re not interested they do leave you alone.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(850, 'ericmaci', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r568473172-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Superb!', 'The bars on the windows outside might make you pause but, believe me, once you step inside the Havana Bar you immediately feel a warmth and vibe that instantly relaxes you. The bar is small but cozy with minimal lighting and great tunes from speakers that don\'t kill your ears or the conversation. Past the bar there\'s a partititon wall that takes you into the restaurant where small tables in nooks and comfy booths offer untimate dining, great service and damn good prices. We had coktails, an awesome rare beef bruschetta which blew us away and red snapper mains accompanied by butternut squash and black pudding(!) Oh, and a decent bottle of Sauv Blanc. Couldn\'t fault it one bit. Excellent throughout. If you\'re in nairobi make sure you go.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(851, 'Richard O', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r566110603-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Tex-mex de bon go√ªt.', 'Bar tr√®s sympatique avec un menu int√©ressant qui offre, entre autres, une cuisine tex-mex. C\'est un endroit absolument d√©contract√© o√π on a le go√ªt d\'aller perdre son temps.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(852, 'Colman O', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r558472829-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Good service and atmosphere', 'From the title you might be expecting something uniquely Cuban. In fact, although the bar has that atmosphere, the food is a mix of Mexican, thai and various western styles. Starters and mains are excellent. I especially recommend the pork belly. I had dessert there once (sticky toffee pudding) and it was disappointing. But overall great value and good atmosphere.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(853, 'Anne D', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r551924610-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Great', 'Totally loved the food,The chef was on point,The staff were friendly especially the lady in specs.Definitely coming back for more.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(854, 'Zer0oo', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r548867862-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'The place to get the \"Nairobi\" experience', 'The place where the locals and foreigners mix, I have heard. And here I was, observing it first hand while eating Mexican food and sipping on Mojitos. \nFor start, food itself is not bad at all- their Fajitas were good and cocktails drinkable (even  Espresso Martini which came as a vodka and a shot of espresso on a side). \nStaff were nice and more often helpful than too busy to attend. \nHowever, the number of local young women, who are  obviously not here to eat Fajitas and rate them on TripAdviser, can be overwhelming on a busy night. \nIf you can enjoy your dinner while siting next to a table with local young women and grossly older white men trying to flirt with them, then all is good. \nI find this place more enjoyable with a bigger group of people, and certainly with more cocktails. \nThe ambience is great, though. It seems like a lot of people enjoying themselves here. And great fun can be had, especially for foreigners with extra cash to spare.\nI guess this is a Nairobi experience in some way, and not to be missed for those like night life buzz.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(855, 'Worldtraveller', 'Woodvale Grove, Nairobi Kenya', 'Havana Bar & Restaurante', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1143745-r540874705-Havana_Bar_Restaurante-Nairobi.html', 'Well......I guess if you have nowhere else to go', 'I live very close to Havana and have eaten there on a large number of occasions over the past 4 years. This place is mid-range price which is it\'s best feature as there is a limited choice for mid-price in Westlands. The food itself is generally acceptable however I have had to send inedible food to the kitchen on a few occasions. Maybe this was on an evening with the \'wrong\' chef.  \n\nThe never ending problem with Havanas is the poor management and table service. The waiting staff are either overloaded and forgetful or bored and bewildered. Either way it is very likely that you will get frustrated one way or another. When problems arise I have had to request intervention from Supervisor / Manager which has always been a total waste of time. On a few occasions I have been told bare-faced lies about why things aren\'t working properly, packaged in a totally indifferent attitude to the customer. This is particularly unacceptable.. \n\nI go back as it is the \'least worst\' eating option in the area. It is not worth a special trip, I recommend you find somewhere where your custom is valued rather than tolerated. If you go for a restaurant costing a couple of dollars more you will have a better chance of receiving what is reasonable to expect when eating out. \n\nOh yes, of course this is basically a Nairobi bar so it would be unfair to negatively comment on the loitering hookers, evening where the music is ridiculously loud, or the fact that the dining area is next to the toilet so there is a procession of people wandering through the dining tables from the bar to relieve themselves!  Oh, and once there was a rat running around which is not unheard of in Nairobi so I can\'t flag that as a negative aspect.\n\nHopefully we will get some more local competition before too long, In the meanwhile, if you have nowhere else to go you\'ll need to endure the Havana \'experience\'.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(856, 'Lina C', 'Hh Towers, Kenyatta Avenue, Nairobi 2nd Floor, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Tribal Roots Grill & Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25261434-r981712216-Tribal_Roots_Grill_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'An amazing dining experience', 'The food was absolutely delicious, and the staff was incredibly friendly, offering exceptional and attentive service. I will definitely be returning!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(857, 'Amanda R', 'Hh Towers, Kenyatta Avenue, Nairobi 2nd Floor, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Tribal Roots Grill & Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25261434-r981710675-Tribal_Roots_Grill_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Best restaurant in Nairobi', 'Tribal Roots Grill & Caf√© is my favorite restaurant in Nairobi. The food, service, and location are exceptional. If you visit, you must try their platters, they\'re incredible!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(858, 'Omar Y', 'Hh Towers, Kenyatta Avenue, Nairobi 2nd Floor, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Tribal Roots Grill & Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d25261434-r882222611-Tribal_Roots_Grill_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great food, atmosphere and people! ', 'I went for lunch once and also hosted a friends birthday dinner there. It was great! \n\nThe owner Fatima is an absolute sweetheart and made every possible accommodation to meet our needs. \n\nPrices are super affordable but nothing compares with the food. If you haven‚Äôt been to this new joint, I‚Äôd highly recommend. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(859, 'Expat Kate', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r1001830442-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Not the best baked cheesecake but definitely good cocktails', 'Personally I prefer no-baked cheesecakes to baked cheesecakes, however, I will never miss out on an opportunity to order a baked cheesecake if it is available at the restaurant. \n\nA good cheesecake (whether baked or no-baked) is a good concept for a great dessert. It is one of my favorite desserts. \n\nIt is a real pity that the burnt baked cheesecake had a bland-artificial taste. There‚Äôs nothing to write home about this dessert. I‚Äôm extremely disappointed. The unmistakably caramelized top of a typical burnt baked cheesecake didn‚Äôt come through. The top was burnt and tasteless, period. \n\nIt‚Äôs the first time that I am served an Apple Crumble without a base. An Apple Crumble typically has a base. The Apple cuts were thick and tough, gooey and the entire dessert was clumpy and simply not enjoyable at all. That filling of tender, cinnamon laced apples topped with a nubbly crunchy, golden topping was nonexistent. \n\nThey need a much better recipe for both desserts. \n\nThat said, despite the food being terrible, the customer service was great and the cocktails were good enough to make the experience worthwhile. \n\nI have now locked in my fourth best cocktail bar in Nairobi. I recommend you try their Aperol Spritz, Vineyard Basil Spritz and Cosmopolitan.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(860, 'Fit P', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r995976420-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'RUDE STAFF !', 'Terrible experience because of the rude staff. They charged our card twice and refused to refund ! Upon signing a form, they refused to pick our calls the days prior. Not to mention, they were not apologetic.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(861, 'Sebastian T', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r995261923-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Great jewel in Nairobi, great service, amazing food, top notch wines and a fantastic wine cellar.  I will come again', 'What an incredible gem in Nairobi.  From the design of the restaurant to the exquisite food choices, to the music, to the staff, everything was fantastic', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(862, 'Mario M', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r981258648-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'I will be back...definitely!!!', 'The place is amazing, well designed, good service, excellent choice of wines. The food is good (slightly on a sweet side for my taste). I like the menu with wine pairing.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(863, 'schey3', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r978905896-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Tolle Kombi - Weinladen mit tollem Restaurant / frische regionale K√ºche mit Pfiff', 'Tolle Kombi  Weinladen und Top Restaurant\nVegane / Vegetarische / Fleisch / Fisch / Desserts\nWine Pairing\nFreundlicher Service\nTop K√ºchenleistung\nEin tolles Restaurant um einen sch√∂nen Abend mit der Familie oder Freunden zu verbringen. Es gibt einen ChefTable mit Blick in die K√ºche f√ºr 12 G√§ste.\nInhaberin kommt aus Italien. Das gesamte Konzept ist super und wird von den G√§sten gut angenommen.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(864, 'AitchX', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r971536269-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Small portions and extras charged ', 'Sadly this place fell way short of our expectations, firstly the dishes did not include any starch or veg which were all extra making what seems like decent prices, expensive. Then when they arrived the portions were very small. The smallest flammkuche I have ever seen!\nTo top it all, we were not able to pay with cash, which no one had mentioned when we booked or arrived! This made for an embarrassing situation which the maitre \'d washed her hands of saying there was nothing she could do! \nClearly they don\'t care about customer service and are only interested in fleecing customers for as much as they can. No apology was offered! ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(865, 'Arnie-Mc', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r968840689-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Could be better', 'Sometimes it‚Äôs the little things that make a big difference. The setting is great and has a nice feel to the place. Food is ok but I would not say great. I would go back but not to eat the food! As they have a great wine selection but of course at a premium priceü§î. Not sure on what their policy is on giving bread for the Chicken livers as it seems disproportionate and then they try to charge if you want more bread‚Ä¶the waiters are all over the place and seem not to have any designated table to serve but then we had to get the Manager to intervene to get the extra bread we had asked for. The side dishes are charged separate, so what you think is a fair price for the main dish then becomes OTT if you add the French fries and veg. Overall lots of room for improvement.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(866, 'sylvia c', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r967694535-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'I need ice EVERYWHERE', 'Every once in a blue moon, you meet a chef and staff who are genuinely dedicated to their craft. Chef Misha has an understanding of taste, texture and flavour that has me enamoured of her. The staff understand exactly what great service is.  The wine selection is a sommeliers dream. My belly is full, my heart is content and I need ice everywhere. I indulged like a fool and while my knees appear to have disappeared I\'m THE BETTER for having gone. Will publish post icing. Go! Go! Go! Ask for Chef Misha!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(867, 'Buongiorno Ele', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r967675428-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Cucina moderna e ottimi vini a Nairobi!', 'Ottimo locale per una cena e un ottimo vino a Nairobo! Il ristorante propone una cucina moderna e una buona carta dei vini. La location √® bellissima e l‚Äôatmosfera √® giovane e accogliente cos√¨ come il servizio. Siamo tornati due sere consecutive per poter provare tutti i piatti che ci incuriosivano.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(868, 'Massimo G', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r963353584-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Ottimo per qualit√† e ambiente', 'Nel tranquillo quartiere Karen, un bel ristorante raffinato e accogliente con ottimi piatti. Ottimo il filetto per esempio e gli accostamenti dei vini proposti. Ottimo il triple chocolat!\nPersonale molto disponibile. \nIdeale per coppie o per serate senza non caotiche.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(869, 'Jasmine A', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r960039137-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Date night', 'Lovely spot for a date night. You arrive at the car park of the building it\'s in and it\'s hard to believe that such a cozy space exists just a few meters away. The decor is really pretty with lots of plants and the stone bricks give it a homely feel. The service was excellent and Steve did a great job of recommending dishes and wine. The wine was excellent. The steak was very good. My only criticism would be that some of the dishes were served cold (the chips, wedges and baked camembert) which was a shame because the taste of the food was very good otherwise.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(870, 'Erling √ò', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r954894903-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Super food and wine with excellent service!', 'The restaurant is great for having a nice time with friends or a business dinner.  \nExcellent selection of wine from all over the world.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(871, 'Jules', 'MPC9+C67, Karen Plains Rd, Nairobi Next To Rhino House, Karen, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cave A Manger', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d26842108-r949207405-Cave_A_Manger-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'All rounded! Homely & Lovely!', 'If you are looking for a lovely setting with plants, surrounded by wine, sumptuous meal and excellent customer service, this is the place to go to in Karen. I would like to mention Steve, who always extending such warmth and hospitality while serving. \n\nAlways a revisit for me.\n\nTip: Plan ahead and make a reservation as the place can get busy.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(872, 'sdmmb', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r748444494-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Enjoyable lunch.  Good choice', 'Enjoyable lunch.  Good choice of soups, salads and sandwiches.  Excellent coffees.  Would be good also for brunch. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(873, 'Monica G', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r747242293-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'A Tasteful Experience', 'This is one of the finest bakery cum cafe in Nairobi. I simply loved the experience of being there with cool breeze blowing past and the refreshing delectable cup of coffee with the awesome choice of desserts. I even bought a range of croissants for my next morning breakfast and they were lovely, flaky layers of satisfaction.\nThe best coffee I have had in a long time and the Apple tart surpasses the taste and presentation to an ooomph level.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(874, 'ecemuratoglan', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r744499334-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Good service, and great pastry', 'It is a very consistent place with its service and taste. Though it is a bit pricey, but I find it normal in Nairobi standards. The pastry is really well done. I suggest Le Grenier a Pain for lunch if you have a bit more than an hour to spend for lunch.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(875, 'Madhulika L', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r742317809-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Superbe!', 'We went to this wonderfully Gallic caf√© for lunch one afternoon. It‚Äôs housed in a spacious, uncluttered hall with huge windows overlooking a terrace (where there are some tables as well). Inside, as you enter, the display counters on the right are filled with glorious-looking croissants, puffs, cake slices, macarons, √©clairs, tarts and more. But this isn‚Äôt all that the caf√© offers: they also do a range of breakfast dishes, soups, salads, sandwiches, quiches, desserts, teas, coffees and non-caffeinated beverages.\n\nWhile my husband and I examined the menu (conveniently on place mats), our daughter was given her own place mat‚Äîa children‚Äôs one, which came with puzzles, images to be coloured, and so on. It kept her well occupied while we chose our order. This is what we ate, and my impression of each of the dishes:\n\nSalade de poulet a l‚Äôorange: Pieces of cooked chicken, mixed greens, shaved fennel, orange  segments and pine nuts, tossed with a honey mustard dressing that also had grated orange zest in it. A huge bowlful, and delicious. \n\nMini ficelle bacon et oignons: Shaped rather like a large elliptical roll, this was a bread stuffed with plenty of bacon and caramelized red onions. The proportion of bread to filling was perfect, and the large helping of mixed greens with vinaigrette that accompanied it was a great foil for the carbs, meat and fat of the ficelle.\n\nToast a l‚Äôavocat: Smashed avocado on toast, amped up. The toast was a beautifully crisp length cut from a long loaf, covered with a very generous quantity of smashed avocado, and topped with a fried egg, sunny side up. On the side was a large helping of mixed leaves, very lightly dressed. Delicious. \n\nSalted caramel tart: About three inches across, the pastry very light and short, and the caramel a very good balance between sweet, bitter and salty. \n\nLemon tart: Excellent, the lemon curd was really lemony and lovely. \n\nWe loved our meal here so much that we bought two things to take away:\n\nAlmond croissant, buttery and flaky and with a luscious filling of frangipane. Not too much, not too little, not too sweet. \n\nPassionfruit macaron: Lovely: the filling had a fabulous flavour of fresh passionfruit, and the macaron was light and mildly chewy. \n\nThe food was superb, and given that we paid just KSH 5120 (which also included two lemonades), good value for money. Service was overall good, but there was some delay in billing, since their billing machine wasn‚Äôt working, and it took our waitress a long time to calculate and make out a bill by hand. In the process, our takeaway order got a bit mixed up: we‚Äôd ordered a lemon macaron, but discovered we‚Äôd been given a passionfruit one only once we got back home. \n\nStill, definitely worth a visit.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(876, 'The_Egyptian_Couple', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r737991997-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Exquisite!', 'One thing no one can dispute is that this place doesn\'t cut corners when it comes to quality of ingredients. When they didn\'t have right chocolate for 4 months, they didn\'t offer Pain au Chocolat for 4 months! Moreover, the quality of their pastries is very consistent and is as good as it gets in Nairobi (can compete in Europe easily). We\'ve been regulars to this place from day one and we shall continue to do the same so long as Nairobi is home!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(877, 'Hitan P', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r737520503-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing Pastries', 'The pastries are mouth-watering but the cappuccino is not up to park had higher expectations from them. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(878, 'Emily993', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r734262525-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Fantastique!', 'Delightful modern french cafe and bakery with a great menu! We tried the pastries and breakfast dishes. Also great customer service from waiters', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(879, 'SushilBaguant', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r719701624-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Lunch with Sam Munda', 'Nice french cuisine in an excellent settings close to the centre in Westlands. I had the Avocado on toast and Fresh Juice. Price is value for money, portion good. Service a bit slow. Highly recommend the restaurant for business lunch.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(880, 'Gretchen Sanders', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r716106429-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Wow, just wow!', 'The caf√© is large with various types of seating-sofas, arm chairs, chairs and tables.\nAs we entered my friend directed me to the display of cakes, pastries and breads.It was wonderful! Works of art!\nThe staff are friendly and efficient. The menu was quite varied and the the price was reasonable. The coffee was hot and good. My croissant to die for!\nI couldn\'t leave without buying pastries to take home. They, were almost too beautiful to eat but eat we did! Divine!\nParking is ample and secure. It is wheelchair accessible. A must visit.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(881, 'robbieM1955', '9 Riverside Building, Riverside Drive, Nairobi Kenya', 'Le Grenier a Pain Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d11832098-r715552626-Le_Grenier_a_Pain_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Good breakfast', 'Went here for breakfast. Croissants and danish are great. My son and I had eggs which were good. My wife had the French toast which she said was amazing. Service was fine from the male waiter. The security into the property and building is amazingly secure which makes you feel very safe.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(882, 'TeresaHanda', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r1037036284-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely Lunch with great mixture of middle east & Japanese cuisine', 'Went with Friends for lunch after attending and Art Show! Reserved a table in two locations garden or inside Incase of rain! Very accommodating! Very well landscaped with large airy Makuti roofed Veranda and a small out door dining areas in the  garden as well as lovely indoor dining! Lighting was poor on the veranda where we sat! Music needed to be turned down a little!  Service was very quick and efficient receiving our order quicky! Along with assistance! Food was delicious üòã ! Desserts need a bit of work but mine was a blue berry cheesecake delicious!', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(883, 'Shemina S', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r998258142-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Phoenician', 'Clear signage.\nGreat ambience. \nAmazing variety on the menus, both food and drinks. \nGreat service from Wilson. \nYummy desserts üç® \n', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(884, 'Karina A', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r956858404-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Best Place in Nairobi', 'This spot is great! Heard they just made renovations and the place looks absolutely amazing! Hands down the best restaurant in Nairobi to have a drink and eat good food! Totally recommend! Also the managers are extremely welcoming and nice', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(885, 'Mzungubabe', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r890407491-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Lebanese and Japanese restaurant', 'The mezze selection here is excellent, with lots of vegetarian options. Slightly on the expensive side, but delicious and the service was very friendly.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(886, 'Nat', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r886479201-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Inexusable.', 'I only go to Phonenician if I\'m with friends who INSIST on going. The quality of food is substandard with insanely high prices. Butbtonihtb was the last straw- I ordered baklava and can not BELIEVE that a Lebanese restaurant would serve these disgusting dry nuggets of cral as baklava. SHAMEFUL!!!!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\"]'),
(887, 'Riya V', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r877433731-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Insect found in food', 'I recently dined at a restaurant and was extremely disappointed with my experience. While enjoying my noodles dish, I made the unpleasant discovery of a disgusting insect lurking in my food. This not only ruined my meal, but also made me question the hygiene and cleanliness of the kitchen. The lack of attention to detail in ensuring a safe and enjoyable dining experience is unacceptable. I will never return to this establishment and would not recommend it to anyone looking for a satisfying meal. This experience was truly repulsive and has left a bad taste in my mouth.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(888, 'Raluca B', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r818777398-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Disappointing and overpriced', 'Went there for lunch, and the atmosphere was sad. Poor service, average food (awful mashed, good fish, really unimpressive okra), totally overpriced. The playground is poorly maintained.\nI\'ve been there before for dinner and it\'s better (the lights were cosy at night, plus it is easier to spot issues with furniture, in the kitchen, etc, also it used to be more lively).', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(889, 'M&S Travels', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r808278825-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Good veg sushi', 'We always get sushi take-away when we come to nairobi from here. They make great veg sushi and make options. The quality is good and fresh.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(890, 'N&S', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r783419422-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Very poor delivery service. Rude manager called, ? Joseph', 'Ordered a pizza delivery, received a cold smashed up pizza. Upon calling the restaurant, the manager proceeded to unapologetically blame the delivery company and call me arrogant for making a complaint.\n\nRestaurants should equally bear the responsibility for a poorly delivered and handled product. This is a paid service, I expected better service and food.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(891, 'Ca R', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r750311384-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'gutes essen in gem√ºtlicher umgebung', 'sehr ruhig gelegen mit √ºberdachter terrasse. man kann sich gut unterhalten. gro√üe speisekarte mit gro√üer auswahl.\nleider war das personal nicht sonderlich freundlich und engagiert.\ndas essen kam leider mit sehr gro√üem abstand obwohl das restaurant nicht sehr besucht war.\nder brownie im nachtisch war verbrannt ansonsten war das essen gut', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(892, 'Monica G', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r741516178-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'A refreshing restaurant', 'The Phoenician holds the charm of taking you away from the hustle and bustle of the city while being within the city. The quiet space among the noisy surroundings makes a great meal time where one can concentrate on food, fresh air and the classic ambiance.\n\nThe food is delicious and service excellent.A good selection available for vegetarians as well.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(893, 'Srikanta P', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r727591579-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent ambiance', 'Its a nice one. Well presented. Lebanese and Japanese food. Good service from staffs. Ample space. Good seating arrangements, Quite place. Everyone will enjoy.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(894, 'tetedoeuf', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r695347197-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'To be avoided', 'I normally don\'t write a review when I can\'t give at least 3 stars. But this was so disappointing that I can\'t resist.. it\'s difficult to describe. When I see all those 4 and 5 stars I\'m wondering whether I came the wrong night or people don\'t know their food. Sushi was bad and not fresh. Rubber. Catering Sushi. The Lebanese dish was it really Lebanese? Eatable but not tasty. Okay, out of 100 plates on the menu you might find a good plate, but I wouldn\'t try the lobster here.. Service is average, not proffessionnel, but not rude.. Just useless.. And when it comes to the pretentious high prices that they practice, I would have expected clean naps and all that goes with it... Anyway, the mostly Indian customers that were there that night seemed to be satisfied. But for  Lebanese and Japanese food, go somewhere else. You can only find better in Nairobi. ', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(895, 'Vasco Da', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r688035937-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Food is great', 'The location of restaurant is a quiet. I ordered both middle eastern and  Japanese sushi, the taste was really good and quantity was also decent.\n\nI think the ambiance was cosy but still can improve on overall looks.\n\nStaff can be more polite and attentive to the customers, they made me wait long, were slow and unresponsive.\n\nOverall a good restaurant with wide menu and tasty food.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(896, 'SMP1943', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r686337413-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Superb cuisine in gracious ambiance', 'On a cloudy June afternoon, we had ordered a multicuisine meal - a combination of Japanese Sushi, Italian Pizza and Lebanese Falafal. Each dish was delicious, beautifully presented and graciously served.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(897, 'John in Nairobi', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r683843577-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent Middle Eastern food in a pleasant setting', 'Excellent Middle Eastern food in a pleasant setting. Not the easiest for Uber driver to find, but worth the trip.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(898, 'Astelz', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r679040711-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Comfortable eat out', 'A good selection of Lebanese and Japanese cuisine. Food is well prepare and very well presented.\n\nWe were there over lunch time and not too busy.\n\nAmbiance was good and layout with garden and kids area is good.\n\nPrice is on the high side but quality is definitely there.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(899, 'Momaina', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r656828573-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Terrible terrible food', 'I recently visited this restaurant. It has a lovely setting and was coupled with a very pleasant waiter. Unfortunately, the food wasn\'t as great as the service. \nHad the worst steak this year. It also tasted like it had been refrigerated for very long. The side salad was good, but nothing exceptional. Even after sending back the food barely touched, they were unapologetic and quickly brought the bill as if to chase us away.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(900, 'Rima', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r648993948-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Relaxed, good food and away from the hipster crowd :)', 'Being a frequent Nairobi visitor - had never to the the Phoenician. Smack bang in the middle of Westlands, but on a side street away from the hustle and bustle. Wish I had come before. Always  wary of a restaurant claiming to do number of different cuisines - Lebanese and Japanese - in this case. Surprisingly good, no pretentions - and came away feeling like we had a pleasant evening - food was good, authentic to both cuisines. Would go back in heart beat. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(901, 'RajenBull', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r648339363-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent food and service ', 'Had a lovely lunch at The Phoenician. Had the hummous and tzatziki and the chicken cubes. The food was extremely tasty and the sides of garlic and chilli were just yum. Will definitely return. Good service. Nice atmosphere too.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(902, 'Barbara M', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r901462858-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Lunch was a blast!', 'Loved the ambience and the food but what made our afternoon even better was Magdalene, who served us so well! She was patient and offered advice when needed. She went over and beyond to make sure we were comfortable. Thank you Magdalene! ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
