(906, 'Sarah N', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r894281744-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Great Service,  great food', 'Great Service,  great food selection, amazing food and drinks. Thanks for making my sisters birthday so memorable.  Kudos to Nyambura and the team serving 15 people of different ages ain\'t no mean feat. Thanks for meal suggestions all enjoyed their meals.  The food portions were just right. Price is pocket friendly. Your team was always available to us.  Thanks CJs team for the birthday surprise song. Thanks to Steve Jogo for helping us with the reservations,  planning and making sure we were as comfortable as possible. Definitely coming back.  Satisfied client.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(907, 'Benjamin M', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r893906565-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Great service', 'I really loved the service here , the ambiance was so nice .\nThanks to Ndumia and Eunice for the good service and hospitality.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(908, 'lawrence m', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r893906166-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Exceptional service ', 'I had an amazing time at the restaurant. The wait staff especially Eunice was very lovely. The portions are big, you get value for your money ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(909, 'melissa L', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r893370663-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent.', 'A good spot to go with friends and family.The service was quick courtesy of our waiter Faith who ensured we enjoyed our meals and had the best service.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(910, 'Violet M', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r893187528-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Good ', 'Exhalent service given by Faith she is so friendly a warm welcoming the food was delicious üòã coming back again ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(911, 'Chrispo N', 'Karen Road The Waterfront Mall, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'CJ\'s Waterfront', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23196295-r893182366-CJ_s_Waterfront-Nairobi.html', 'Wonderful ', 'The service is extremely beyond my expectations,,warm welcoming given by Faith she has a big heart would be visiting again ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(912, '', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r625345181-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', '‰∏çÈîôÁöÑÈ§êÂéÖ', 'È§êÂéÖ‰∏ªË¶ÅÊòØÈªéÂ∑¥Â´©ÂíåÊó•È§êÔºå‰ΩÜÊòØÊÄªÁöÑÊÑüËßâÊòØÊó•È§êÁõ∏ÂΩì‰∏çÈîôÔºåÈ£üÊùêÊñ∞È≤úÔºåÂë≥ÈÅìÂèØÂè£ÔºåÊé®Ëçê„ÄÇÈ§êÂéÖÈáåÊúâÂÑøÁ´•Ê∏∏‰πêÂú∫ÊâÄÔºåÂ≠©Â≠êÂèØ‰ª•ÊîæÂøÉÁöÑÂéªÁé©ËÄçÔºåÊÑüËßâÂæàË¥¥ÂøÉ„ÄÇÂÅúËΩ¶Âú∫‰πüÂæàÂ§ßÔºåÂºÄËΩ¶ÂéªÈùûÂ∏∏ÂêàÈÄÇ„ÄÇ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(913, 'Victor M', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r624487903-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Delicious food, friendly service ', 'Mr. Peter Muriithi efficiently walked us to our table and quickly brought out the menus for our family dinner. I was very impressed with the general layout of the restaurant, the furnishings looked and did feel cosy. There is also an outside sitting place where one can get to see their pizza being made as well as a Japanese sushi bar. A nice kids\' play area is adjacent to this.\n\nBack to the evening\'s business; we ordered hummus for starters and some drinks including Lebanese coffee. I asked for Peter\'s recommendation if a typical Lebanese dish which came to be Shish Taouk (grilled marinated cubes of boneless chicken served with garlic sauce with choice if rice, chips, baked or mashed potatoes). It was really tasty. My wife ordered mixed grill and she enjoyed it. Our daughter had salami pizza and she said it was good. And of course, I love Lebanese bread which landed on the table as complimentary. The quality of the food was great and good value for money. The bill for 3 people came to KES 6,199 (around US$ 61) which I think is very reasonable for Nairobi. The co-owner of the restaurant, Mr. Tawk, came in to say bye and find out how the dining had been. All in all, we had a great time in an awesome place with friendly staff. Thanks Peter, thanks Mr. Tawk.\n\nWe hope to come again (with our son in tow)!!!\n', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(914, 'Beryl', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r620137849-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Friends birthday celebration', 'First time going to the restaurant. Don‚Äôt know why I took me soo long. \n\nIt was my colleague birthday and with a couple of friends. \n\nThe food and ambiance was great. \n\nThe service was great as well. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(915, 'Al K', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r588971056-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Order the moose au Chocolat. I‚Äôm serious!', 'The food was amazing, the ambience was excellent, the wait staff were considerate and left us alone just the right way...\n\nBut the highlight of the evening was the Moose au Chocolat. Seriously, order some!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(916, 'Monica G', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r588755306-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'A palatable blend', 'The phoenician has the warmth of being in a closed in atmosphere yet one can enjoy the open air ambience. The service is good and food of course as usual excellent. We enjoyed the sips of hot Japanese Tea along with the Japanese starters and followed it up with main course from the Lebanese selection on the menu.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(917, 'Muntazir S', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r587050871-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Price WOOOOW', 'The price is high for the food however Japanese food is good amazing to say. However the Lebanese food is rubbish leaving in the Arab world I think this was not upto par \n\nI would go there for the starters and Japanese but nothing else and pricing mama mia ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(918, 'HmanG', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r584981597-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Overpriced average food', 'Went over for a bithday dinner. The sushi was average. Japanese was too salty - when we commented, we were told they would inform the chef only, I had to insist they do something about the dish. The food was way wayy over priced. Quality was mediocre at best. One of those restaurants you wonder why you hadn\'t been to for a while then realize  why immidiately after each time.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(919, 'hootymcg', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r582388384-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Lebanese and sushi ', 'Visited for diner, chose Lebanese mixed me e between us, food was very good and plentiful. Beware of the garlic sauce if you are on a date.. It\'s lovely but Very pungent.. Lol\nCocktails were lovely too and prices are very reasonable.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(920, 'Manuella', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r572331389-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing Lunch at the Phoenicien with a big group', 'My extended family was visiting us from Dubai, along with the children, we were a total of 6 adults and 6 kids. They stayed for two weeks so we had plenty of time to visit all the fun places and they tried all of our favorite restaurants:Talisman, Zen Garden, Carnivore, Hemingway\'s, Open House, Seven, Purdy arms, Tapas Ceviche.\nBeing a big group it is difficult to accommodate us and please both adults and children.\nI have to say that our loveliest experience was our lunch at the Phoenician on Sunday. When we arrived, our table was ready perfectly located overlooking the play area.Our waiter Peter was very welcoming and experienced, he recommended the best vegetarian Lebanese appetizers that came with plenty of pita bread and various dips: Hommos, Baba ghannouj, Falafel, Fattouche Tabbouleh and divine spinach and cheese pastries,pickles garlic and chili.... For the kids, he recommended pizzas and grilled deboned chicken with rice, which the kids loved. Some of us ordered a few sushi rolls which were perfect: the fish freshness, the perfectly sized roll bites, the stickiness of the rice, the generous pickled ginger portions. I highly recommend one of their signature dishes which is the sashimi salmon salad, its delicious. Wine was flowing, kids were playing in the play area, the live music was lovely. The patrons were there and they came to say hello and check if everything was ok, lovely touch. We had a great afternoon at the Phoenician in Westlands, great food, lovely atmosphere on sundays, but what did it for me was the super attentive and PROMPT service  (im the frustrated one at restaurants always asking for water cutlery napkins). I definitely recommend it especially for big groups. book in advance it was full when we arrived.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(921, 'Thelma', 'Matundu Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Phoenician', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d7239363-r566744290-The_Phoenician-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely dinner nights in Nairobi ', 'I have always loved this restaurant. Whether it‚Äôs an intimate dinner with a loved one or some family dinner, we have always had a great time here. The food is good. A variety to choose from the menu and it‚Äôs all been delicious. I love their falafels. \nWith family we always go for a carafe of wine and it‚Äôs good to get the night going. They even have a kids play area if you happen to go there with your young ones. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(922, 'Natalie. S', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r775847880-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'Superb Grounds for intimate Weddings!', 'My husband and I got married at Valencia Gardens, Riara Road. Our occasion took place in October 2020, with all the uncertainty around us. When we came to the management and staff at Valencia with our ideas they took it on with the utmost professionalism and seriousness, they wanted to bring our vision to life. The staff on the ground are professional and have years of experience in hosting events. They were all very responsive to our queries and quick to provide solutions. The food selection was incredible and our guest really enjoyed the variety.  The venue was exactly what we were looking for in terms of atmosphere, scenery and food. It gave us the experience of a home away from home which is what we wanted our guest to feel. Overall, at a time like this, the venue played a huge part in the success of our wedding and we are happy about how clean they kept the place. Thank you!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(923, 'Mev U', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r732059824-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'Valencia Gardens, Riara road', 'Very clean place, lovely ambience. Affordable food and drinks. They make the best mbuzi choma. Clean washrooms and the band that plays on Fridays (Weavers)is excellent. It would have been 5 stars except for the waiters getting our orders wrong, twice in one night.\nI‚Äôd definitely recommend Valencia( Riara road) on a Friday night.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(924, 'Mzungubabe', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r564514442-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'Pleasant outdoor lunch spot', 'This is a review of the main restaurant on Riara Road, not the one at the museum.  It has changed hands since the last time I came.  The food was OK but portion sizes were not as large as before and the choice is limited.  The layout of the tables is nice, each has it\'s own individual umbrella for shade.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(925, 'Entony K', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r556423881-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'VERY GOOD FOOD PRICES.', 'They have very good service, at fair prices for a middle class, there are no rooms available just for dining especially in the evenings, no swimming pool.Good for a weekend outs and their prices are fair chips goes for 120 and a bottle of soda is 100 and beer goes for 200.this is very fair.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(926, 'ALEXANDER P', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r554789062-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'Mediocre service and food', 'So, the National Museums of Kenya has two offerings for food, this and Vogue. I have had decent experiences with the few times I have been to Vogue. I have only been to Valencia once and I found it... disappointing. The server was not particularly welcoming, did not seem engaged when answering my colleagues\' question about the menu. The food was fairly pricey, especially considering what arrived. My vegetarian curry was adequate, but fairly bland. My colleague got a chicken dish and it looked like it had been left in a deep fryer. It was really dry and without much meat. Given the price range, I would expect a lot more from this offering. Also, considering the location, Valencia should really strive to be a strong option, but really just leaves it to Vogue.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(927, 'Adeyemi O', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r497811246-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'Casual', 'A good and lively spot for a mature crowd to hang out. In winter it could get quite chilled but fire places are provided to provide warmth. Menu is thin but always available,  drinks are very affordable and it\'s very private. In house music and DJ on weekends makes for good scenery. ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(928, 'isabelle n', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r456884587-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'An office farewell party', 'The place is ok . Has a lot of seating space and an outdoor bar. There\'s also music in the evening. They offer catering services for events.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(929, 'SimonF1950', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r450604380-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'Reasonable Food in Good Surroundings', 'The ambiance is \'good Kenyan style\' with sinks beside all outside tables - although roasting hot towels are brought before eating.\nThe food is \'reasonable\', although nothing to write home about.  I had chicken curry that had little or no spices in it, but was a superb flavour (chicken a little over-cooked) and my wife and friend had a whole Tilapia each, which were very small.\nVervet Monkeys and birds in the grounds, along with assorted cats, none of which bothered us while eating and were a joy to watch.\nThe service is a little slow, but pleasant and professional.\nWould we visit again?  Yes, it\'s very handy for Junction Mall and a change from the restaurants there.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(930, 'Toga Kings', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r359397741-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'great weekend afternoon spot', 'this is the lower museum restaurant.  I had pork chops, ugali, greens & beer.  To sit in the shade & quite away from the bustle of downtown Nairobi is a joy.  If the WIFI had worked I would have been happier.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\"]'),
(931, 'Guilfybear', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r328126029-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'Peaceful Location for.....?', 'Would recommend for the relatively tranquil location in heart of Nairobi.\n\nThe food however is tasteless and appears to be the same regardless of whether it is a in a sandwich or presented on a plate.\n\nService takes a while and is lacklustre ...generally a shame as potentially a gold mine if they could get the ingredients right.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(932, 'travellingzebra', 'Riara Road Inside the Kenya Nairobi Museum, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Valencia Gardens', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4101759-r302447607-Valencia_Gardens-Nairobi.html', 'Proper coffee.', 'Good sized coffee mug. Decent coffee. Only 140 ksh per mug.\nA large chocolate chip cookie(enough for 2) was 90ksh . It was clean , plenty of seating area, a smoking area and staff were friendly. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
