(1029, 'RovingCelt', 'Ngong Rd Adams Arcade Building, Nairobi Kenya', 'Java House', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d14006359-r829244002-Java_House-Nairobi.html', 'Variable customer service', 'We went here a few times for breakfast during our last trip to Kenya.  The first couple of times, the waiter was excellent, communicative and attentive.  Then a few trips where the different waiting-on staff were the complete opposite.  Requests for strong coffee were not passed on to those who made the coffee and when the person who seemed to be the manager intervened, it was no better.  Eggs did not come as requested.  \nOn one day, the waitress disappeared for a good while and could not pay till she reappeared.  We only returned after the initial poor experience as we\'d hoped the original waiter would be back.  I guess he got another job where customer service is important.  \nWe only returned once after we had had enough of the poor service, when we had no time to go elsewhere and the waitress was good: not as good as the first guy, but would have kept us coming back if it hadn\'t been for the others.  \nAside from that, when the order was correct, I was quite happy with the food and value for money.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
