(1083, 'heike', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1030999443-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Tolles Essen in wundersch√∂nem Ambiente', 'Tolles und sehr leckeres Essen ( der Reis hatte eine ganz feine Zimtnote) wundersch√∂nes Ambiente in herrlicher Natur und ein sehr zuvorkommender Service. Eric war einfach klasse und hat mit seiner Fr√∂hlichkeit f√ºr gute Laune gesorgt. Gerne wieder!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(1084, 'Travel46768602173', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1030689656-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Great Vibes!', 'I had such a wonderful experience here! The atmosphere was welcoming and relaxed, which made it a perfect place to spend time. The staff were incredibly friendly, attentive, and went out of their way to make sure everything was just right. The food was also really enjoyable ‚Äî fresh, well-prepared, and full of flavor. Altogether, it was such a pleasant visit, and I left feeling very satisfied. I would highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great service, a comfortable setting, and good food', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1085, 'Don M', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1029143436-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Don‚Äôt Miss Tamarind Brassiere', 'Headed back to the Tamarind Brassiere for the most amazing seafood cuisine offered in our city. Brought some of my dearest friends for a crab feast that was next to none. \nThe Crab Tempura was simply out of this world, followed by a Crab Claw starter with three dipping sauces which is always unreal. And the Chili Crab main course just knocked my socks off. This time I requested the Chef to dress the crab (out of the shell) and wow!!  Absolutely delicious! Followed by amazing deserts and coffee, we all agreed that the Tamarind Brassiere dining experience was one of the most memorable we‚Äôve ever shared together.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1086, 'Purity K', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1027069777-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Appalling Food, Worse Service,  Tamarind Hotels in Kenya ‚Äì A Warning from Personal Experience', 'I am Kenyan and had returned home after several years away. I chose Tamarind to reunite with friends and family, but the experience was terrible.\n\nThe food was inedible, overloaded with salt. Even the manager agreed after tasting it and promised to make it fresh. When it came back 20 minutes later, the stews were watered down and tasted like dishwater. By then, most of my family and friends had left in frustration.\n\nThe manager later offered complimentary coffee but disappeared and never returned. Another staff member, who smelled of alcohol, eventually brought the bill including charges for the ‚Äúcomplimentary‚Äù coffee. Despite our protests, and because I had left my card on file, I was charged in full for food that was inedible and coffee that had been offered as complimentary\n\nSince returning abroad, I have emailed both the hotel and headquarters multiple times, sharing receipts, but no one has responded. If this is how I was treated as a Kenyan who speaks the language, I can only imagine how you as a tourists would be treated.\n\nI later discovered many similar complaints about Tamarind. Based on my experience, I strongly advise avoiding this chain.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1087, 'Don M', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1020258726-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Incredible Crab', 'Best crab in Nairobi, without a doubt. \nBegan with a Crab Claw starter accompanied with three different dipping sauces, followed by Chilli Crab in the shell. \nAmazing dining experience. The service was impeccable. \nChef Hellen is tops! \nDon‚Äôt miss Tamarind Brasserie, by any means.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1088, 'Coastal43585758871', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1017094794-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'EXCEPETIONAL EXPERIENCE', 'Our experience at Tamarind Brasserie was amazing, from the top tier service to the amazing food. I will definitely be back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1089, 'Resort07292521572', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1013275258-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Lovely spot', 'Beautiful spot, delicious food, and Steve was a charming server. \n\nWe had Tuna Poke bowl and the Spinach and Chickpea Casserole - see photo. (there are many non-veg options as well).\n\nLoved this experience. \nDefinitely recommended.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1090, 'Rose Wambui M', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1009065898-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Great place, delicious food and impeccable service.', 'It was a delight having an event at Tamarind Brasserie. It is a beautiful venue with lush gardens. The food was amazing especially being for a large group. The service was personalized with great efficiency. Special thanks to Maryanne for catering to our needs as we planned and held the event. We shall definitely be back.Overall excellent and great value for money.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1091, 'charity m', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1008128018-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Kids birthday party lunch', 'I had a delightful experience! The food was exceptional, and beautifully presented. The charming garden setting made it a perfect spot for a kids birthday party. Service was top-notch, particularly from Antonio, who was attentive, friendly, and genuinely made our visit memorable. I highly recommend this restaurant for anyone looking to enjoy great food in a lovely ambience!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1092, 'amusolo l', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1008056872-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Exelllent', 'Every thing went well from parking reception and food was super good and the ground is ‚ù§Ô∏èmy children were able to have fun games and appreciate the time they spent and the service did a good job and the chef work was perfect it\'s place I can recommend for parties', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1093, 'Fabrice C', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1004082024-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'A Delightful Dining Experience at The Tamarind Brasserie ‚Äì Highly Recommended!', 'We recently hosted a dinner for 70 colleagues and participants from our cross-program event with Teach For All partners at The Tamarind Brasserie, and I must say‚Äîit was nothing short of spectacular!\n\nFrom the moment we stepped into their beautiful, spacious, and perfectly convening venue, we felt warmly welcomed and incredibly well taken care of. The team at Tamarind went above and beyond‚Äîstarting with a unique food tasting experience prior to the event, where we sampled generous portions of their delicious dishes and only paid for drinks. That alone was a standout service!\n\nOn the big night, everything ran smoothly and on time‚Äîwhich, if you‚Äôve ever organized an event of this size, you know is pure gold. The food was a wonderful blend of continental, local, and Asian cuisine‚Äîrich in flavor, perfectly portioned, and beautifully presented. From appetizers to dessert, every bite was a hit.\n\nA huge shoutout to Ms. Peace Ombura, who handled all the administrative coordination and payments with such professionalism and warmth, and to Ms. Maryanne and the entire service crew‚Äîfriendly, organized, spotless, and impressively fast. Our guests felt pampered and relaxed, and many wished we could stay longer just to soak in the atmosphere and the stunning view!\n\nThe reserved parking, the perfectly curated background music, and the smooth flow of service tied it all together. If you‚Äôre looking for a venue that combines elegance, great food, and impeccable service‚ÄîThe Tamarind Brasserie is it.\n\nTwo things to remember about Tamarind: they will be on time, and the place is simply beautiful.\n\nThank you for making our evening unforgettable!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"delivery_takeout\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1094, 'Seby S', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1004056378-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', '5/5', 'Best place... service is excellent \nFrom the reception to the bar marvelous \nThe buffet was top notch,got variety of options.\nLooking forward to staying here some time soon \n', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1095, 'Passenger50541983860', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1003940639-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Best First Birthday Party', 'Tamarind was the best place for us to host my daughter‚Äôs first birthday party! ü•≥ Peace welcomed us so warmly as we were venue hunting‚Ä¶ We were impressed by the food options and flexibility of having our own set up. On the day of the party, the staff were extremely accommodating, especially with the rains, and really cared for us. The food was also great‚Ä¶ I would highly recommend!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1096, 'Wa_Nganga', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1003811473-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Good food, exquisite grounds - Where memories are made!', 'The indoor-outdoor spaces coupled with Peace\'s warm welcome to the property convinced me to go with Tamarind Brasserie for my dad\'s 70th. The meals, facilities and the lush grounds are the cherry on top if you are looking for a convenient event venue. Peace is a star and she held my hand all through the preparations. Thank you as well to Joel, Antonio and Maryann for helping us with the set-up.\nI had a few hiccups, which were addressed promptly and I would recommend Tamarind Brasserie in a heartbeat. The property is amazing, the staff are hospitable, and Peace and the chef who makes the beets x apple x carrots salad definitely deserve a raise! üòÉ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1097, 'Vigilance A', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1003071051-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Excellent Hosts!', 'I sincerely express my gratitude to Tamarind Karen  team for hosting us and allowing us to film in their premises. \n\nIt was smooth and we really had a good time. \n\nMuch appreciation', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(1098, 'Entumoto s', '165 Ngong Road Next To St Christopher\'s School, Karen, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'Tamarind Brasserie', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d24915583-r1002359251-Tamarind_Brasserie-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Exceptional Venue for a Memorable Event!', 'Entumoto Safari Camp, hosted a cocktail and dinner event for tour agents at Tamarind Brasserie on April 4, 2025, which was an absolute success! From the seamless planning to the flawless execution, the team exceeded our expectations in every way.\n\nFood & Drinks ‚Äì The selected menu with delicious canap√©s, flavorful main courses, and expertly crafted cocktails  impressed all our guests.\n\nElegant Ambiance ‚Äì The stylish yet welcoming atmosphere set the perfect tone for networking and celebration.\n\nOutstanding Service ‚Äì The staff was attentive, professional, and went above and beyond to ensure everything ran smoothly.\n\nA special thanks to the guest relation, Peace Ombura, and the entire team for their dedication. Our tour agents left raving about the experience, and we couldn‚Äôt have asked for a better venue.\n\nHighly recommended for private events‚Äîwe‚Äôll definitely be back!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1099, 'Ms C', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r1000151440-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Amazing food', 'I just had the spiciest mutton biryani I‚Äôve had in my life!!!! Made me sweat! I loved it. Chef gave me exactly what I asked for (but forgot to include the mint sauce in my package) . The food, ambience and service was amazing. Will definitely be coming backüòç', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1100, 'Lox', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r958358583-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'C - at best', 'There are only a few tables inside and lighting there is unpleasantly bright, so we sat outside on a cold evening. A few jikos would have been nice. There were many diners, so we had to sit at a table for six with wobbly furniture and flickering disco lights all around. No table cloths, no heated plates, no cloth napkins, only two sauces on the table and the masala pappadams were served cold.\nThe chili garlic paneer was delicious, but all other dishes were utterly bland and chicken dishes had the cheaper, dark meat. Nans and roti good, service too, but for fragant, well-balanced Indian food, you better go elsewhere.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1101, 'el_andresiko', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r930950143-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Buena experiencia!', 'Excelente atenci√≥n: personal muy atento. Pedimos variedad de platos y todos estaban muy buenos. Las vistas desde la terraza son bonitas porque hay un parque delante, todo muy verde de la vegetaci√≥n. Los precios me parecieron correctos', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[]'),
(1102, 'Dakshdeep Singh S', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r925566329-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Nothing less than restaurant in India ', 'Loved the food here.\nYou won\'t miss India. Particularly liked fish tikka, dal makhni and paneer kadai.\n\nAnd rotis ofcourse ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(1103, 'Getrude M', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r921688381-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'I really loved the services offered the tasty food and the ambience of the place, keep up. ', 'I have heard of Mayura before and i decided to give it a trial for a lunch date with my friends at the entrance we were  received by  Flora such a pleasant girl, she greeted us and showed us a place to sit, she asked  if we were comfy  of which we were ,she gave us a  menu and even went ahead on recommending what would be suitable and enjoyable to us and trust me the food was so delicious ,after all this , she did not stop there but she kept checking  on us to know whether we were okay , thank you so much Flora   for making us feel at home i would highly recommend anyone to  The Mayura   Karen for their best services and tasty food,,, i can\'t  wait to go  back again.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1104, 'Aditya', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r918210001-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Tasty food and courteous service in this vegetarian friendly restaurant.', 'We are vegetarians visiting from India. \n\nWe ordered Aloo Tikki starter and dal tadka and paneer tikka masala for the main course. \n\nWe found the food to be good. Credit to the Indian chef Mr Rana and his team.\n\nAlso try the masala lassi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(1105, 'AnitaAjai', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r914202332-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Awesome food thanks Mukesh Rana', 'we went for lunch, even though it was past our booked time, the friendly staff treated us so well, they were so courteous. the food was awesome, thanks to chef Mukesh Rana.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(1106, 'africanman_840', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r914013753-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Tasty meal,calm ambience', 'I was here for lunch and all I can say is that their food was so good and well seasoned. The service was excellent and there is very lovely outdoor sitting space. This restaurant is a good value. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1107, 'Climber56056380542', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r907717280-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Best staff at the reception', 'Magdalena, the girl at the reception at Mayura is the best person ever! She was so very kind and when we decided that we did not feel like eating Indian ( we are Indians) and wanted to go to another place, she dropped us off to the other place which was not very safe to walk alone to. Just that gesture alone makes me want to go back to Mayura to dine and definitely will next time we are there. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1108, 'Rozafa', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r849584387-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Nice restaurant, reasonable food', 'The food was good but my chicken Tika masala was not spicy enough as I wanted, although I emphasized that I want extra spicy. The wine list was rather poor. All in all it was a pleasant evening. The waiter was nice.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(1109, 'Ravinder S', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r847492775-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Great kebabs', 'Really wanted kebabs with naans as we missed out on visiting Nargis! The Mayura did not disappoint! Ambiance was lovely, located in The Hub, Karen. Service was prompt and staff were friendly. Will definitely try the wider menu next time.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1110, 'africanman_840', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r825319265-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Superb Indian Food', 'I ate again at the Mayura restaurant for the first time in months. The food was just awesome. I had prawns which were so delicious.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1111, 'BiggsySnr', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r823337270-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Good Indian Food', 'We were spending an extended holiday in Africa and I saw this restaurant when visiting the Hub and decided to visit.\n\nThe Lamb bhuna was first class.  Much better than I have back in the UK.  Dal makani was pretty good too.  My other half had a chicken korma which was ok - probably on a par with the one\'s she has in the UK - but I had to stop her from digging into mine.\n\nPortion size was good.\n\nI would definitely eat here again.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1112, 'Naveen Vishwakarma', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r821075745-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Take away quantity portion was not supplied in full.', 'Be careful with the takeaway orders as they supply less quantity in compared to what they serve in the Restaurant.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"portion_size\", \"delivery_takeout\"]'),
(1113, 'Irene M', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r814398547-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Dining Experience', 'I had dinner at The Mayura in Karen at The Hub with my husband last night. They have this mutton cooked in cashewnut sauce that was so tender and tasty it blew my mind. The fried rice and the roti were excellently done. We got very nice vegetable salad on the side and a free glass of red wine. The service was amazing too. It was a fantastic experience. I highly recommend this restaurant.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1114, 'africanman_840', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r800233406-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Tasty Indian food', 'Great place to have Indian meals in Nairobi. The quality of the food was great and the service was good though the wait time was a bit long. For those who are allergic to smoke, I would recommend sitting inside instead of outside. This is one restaurant I cant recommend highly enough. It has an extensive menu of both vegetarian and non-vegetarian menu.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1115, 'nfriesen1', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r789093178-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Best Indian Food in Nairobi!', 'Mayura is incredible and the best Indian food I‚Äôve ever had outside of India. They have a great menu and both the food and service are incredible. We absolutely love Mayura! Highly recommend the Tandoori Prawns appetizer!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1116, 'Sachin G', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r750063365-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Mayur visit', 'Had a limited selection of vegetarian foods but whatever was available was very good and service was impressive. Prices are also fair enough', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1117, 'sdmmb', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r748441035-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Excellent Indian food.  ', 'Excellent Indian food.  The okra was superb as were all the meat dishes.  Service high quality, setting nice and value for money.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(1118, 'William G', 'The Hub, Karen, Nairobi 24815 Kenya', 'The Mayura', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g12559418-d11949016-r717545652-The_Mayura-Karen_Nairobi.html', 'Indian prawn lunch', 'Ordered the prawn Malabar‚Äô with Phulka‚Äô and a Coke Zero.   It was early so the restaurant was empty so excellent service with friendly waiters and waitresses.   Free salad served to nibble on with three sauces.   The phulka‚Äô was a small thin roti very tasty and light which was served instead of the Romani roti which I suspected they only served for dinner.   Overall a good pleasant experience so recommended. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1119, 'dLbuffin', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r989732212-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Not to Miss in Nairobi', 'We had a large group of 30 and were accommodated in a room. The food was fantastic and the service was great, given the large size of our group. The space is gorgeous and worth a walk around.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1120, 'Marrs Ericos Tours', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r989465353-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', '\"Safari to Sensation: A Perfect Dinner at Talisman\"After an amazing safari, we ended the day with a flawless dining experience a', 'After an exhilarating day on safari, we capped off our adventure with a dinner reservation at Talisman. The moment we walked in, the impeccable service swept us off our feet‚Äîswift, seamless, and utterly welcoming. The ambiance was enchanting, setting the perfect tone for the evening. Then came the food: a symphony of flavors that danced on our palates, each dish more divine than the last. Every bite told a story of culinary mastery, leaving us savoring the magic long after the plates were cleared. It was more than dinner‚Äîit was an unforgettable experience that crowned our day with perfection.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1121, 'RAHUL K', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r987337520-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'TALISMAN - AVERAGE FOOD BUT GOOD VIBE', 'Restaurant was fine nice atmosphere buzzing away good vibe no doubt.But sorry to say food was very average.This was boxing day and they were open only till afternoon so it seems waiters etc were in a kind of hurry to serve and finish off.Okay so lets get down to the food vibe.French Fries - not a difficult dish to serve nice thin crispy fries.They had it all wrong - they were oily and limb and not fresh .Next was my sushi starter - sorry to say average - the topping was suppose to be crunchy it wasn\'t and the sushi was not as fresh as it should be.The wine was a good selection so no problems there. Next comes my sweet dish an orange  pannecotta yes it was very nice but for the price a bit small. i ordered some veggies on the side - sorry good restaurants dont  just serve you boiled veggies and dump it on the plate.There is a way to serve good vegetables that make it tasty - like sauty with a bit of onions and garlic with a little white sauce add a little parmesan cheese as a topping make it interesting for gods sake.Anyway good luck....', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1122, 'Johnson O', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r986704756-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Love the food and service from Gladys', 'This spot is beautiful for dinner and meetings place. I love the ambience and the greenery. The food is amazing and the service', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1123, 'Adam Kipruto A', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r986691769-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', '10 star restaurant', 'Gladys is the best waitress around! Give her a promotion! Best food in Nairobi! Don\'t go anywhere else! Chilli beef and mushroom pasta fantastic', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(1124, 'Susan M', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r986683724-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Personable, cheerful service and great set up for lunch/ dinner', 'Talisman is great for good food, good service by Gladys and the team and amazing cocktails. I‚Äôd recommend it for anyone who wants international service and Kenyan quality ingredients cooked into creative sumptuous dishes.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1125, 'Kjgtrr2017', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r986443266-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Unique Atmosphere & Good Food Worth a Visit', 'Very unique building with a large outdoor seating area and several smaller covered areas. Beautiful original art is worth walking around to view. Service was very good and we all enjoyed our meals - cauliflower soup very good, Beef Carpaccio, Butternut Ravioli, and Swahili Fish Curry were all enjoyed. Love the little heaters. Definitely worth a visit while in Nairobi.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1126, 'Tim C', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r982569291-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great experience', 'Lovely venue and attentive service.  The food was very good and we enjoyed some excellent cocktails.  It was a busy restaurant that was running smoothly and we had a very enjoyable experience', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1127, 'MNKE', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r981501994-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Food poisoning and extremely rude customer service', 'My husband ordered Prawn Tempura starter and found a chunk of fiber/hair/? Inside it!\nWe called the waiter who took it immediately and as we were disgusted we cancelled our main course immediately and requested for the bill.\nImagine the prawn tempura was charged!!!as well as my glass of untouched red wine(1000+ kes)  for the main course!!!!\nWe were then obliged to fight for the prawns to be removed from the bill. \n\nNo consideration of what happened at the time of payment. \nIt‚Äôs our worst experience of food poisoning and extremely rude customer service.\nUnfortunately we had no time to take a picture of what we found.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1128, 'Jo A', '320 Ngong Road Karen, Nairobi Kenya', 'The Talisman Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1059634-r979257212-The_Talisman_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Fabulous decor/environment - excellent service & great food', 'Fabulous environment and great vibe: lively, cosy, fantastic service (thank you Bolton) and surrounded by great art works', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1129, 'Fenwick O', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r857829206-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'Dinner', 'Amazing customer service experience from Antony. Very pleased with his reception towards us and timely attendance to us.\nThe food is delicious and will definitely come back.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1130, 'Makena D', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r854792763-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'Contemptible treatment ', 'Went to this place on Wednesday night at around 945pm. Before we could even catch our breath we were informed the kitchen would be closing in five minutes. No worries, we order our food and it arrives quickly.Extremely fatty barely edible goat meat. As we near the end of our meal,the lights start to be switched off . I look at the time 1052.Then some man tells us \"thank you for visiting, we are closed now\".We start to laugh as this is totally ridiculous as we are still not finished drinking our tea. I mean ,they switch all the lights off!! So we are now sitting in the dark! It was still not 11 pm and even if it was how do you treat the customer in this complete and total contempt. Never going back and would never recommend it . There are so many other places with great food and customer respect.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]');
