(1131, 'Cynthia T', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r852373595-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'Review', 'We had an wzing time.The portions are very generous we had to takeaway.Our waiter Vincent was very kind and assisted us with understanding the menu...he was also very fast and quick to respond to us .Overall 10/10 experience .Would highly reccommend and come back', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1132, 'Elham fuad', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r846488128-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'Restaurant', 'Food was so delicious and the service was amazing üòç\nExcellent service from Cyrus! Definitely coming back again', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(1133, 'Shera201', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r845302524-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'Perpetually poor service and arrogant management', 'There is a table at Ankloe that is always reserved for the manager (who is never there) or used by the manager\'s friends. (Ankole PR person - please do not bother defending this or lying about it. Me and some of your repeat customers constantly complain about this). Ankole\'s absent manager and friends get higher priority than other paying customers, who can sit in the restaurant for two or three hours with that and other \"reserved\" tables. This restaurant has the most ridiculous and insulting \"reservation policy.\" (The reviewer who called them arrogant is right.)\n\nThe service deteriorated completely when it opened the Kitisuru branch and pulled the best staff. I\'ve watched this mess, complains about it to staff and a manager; it is hopeless so do not bother complaining. The staff there are mostly not friendly, and I wonder if it is them or the management or both?\n\nDon\'t buy the chicken wings. You\'ll get the tiniest wings you\'ve ever seen for more than Ksh 160 a piece with hardly any flesh. The food is otherwise decent, but the poor service levels and bad management have led to me and three friends independently choosing to no longer be customers.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1134, 'Jitaditya M', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r841527991-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'Arrogance ', 'Wouldn\'t let us sit where we wanted though the place was empty all throughout our visit ,saying they were  reserved. Food was average. Arrogance. Wouldn\'t recommend it. ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1135, 'Nkosi', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r841006327-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'An honest restaurant will give you a genuine experience!!', 'I had lunch there on Saturday May 28th with a friend. I left the restaurant and got to my friend\'s place 30mins later only to realise I left my Pouch bag with passport, money and all  ID and credit cards on the back of my chair!!\n\n.You can imagine how I held my head when I realized...\" My stuff is gone\" ...I feared to think. I called my friend and she called Ankole Grill fast. Management said they had my bag safe and secure and would only release it if I personally came. In 20mins I was back there and was asked to take a seat in the office upstairs while my bag was brought to me. It was stapled In a brown bag and opened in my presence. I was asked to confirm that everything was there and indeed it All was!!\n\nI want to thank Arnold manger, Jerry security, Fred Security and Zody another manager for their prompt management of the situation to avoid a potential disaster for me... it is so refreshing to think staff are honest like that. Why not go back another time. I had one of their veggie options and I think the pesto pizza with mushrooms made me probably forget my bag. That and the white cap \"facing Mount Kenya\".\n\nGood work guys and keep up the standard!\n\nEdwin', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1136, 'Nel', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r840962560-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'ANKOLE 100%', 'Had a beautiful time at ankole in kilimani.The services of Anthony were top notch,the professionalism amazing.My experience was to die for.Ankole all the way..\nWill definitely come back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"overall_experience\"]'),
(1137, 'Fatema I', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r838754224-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'The place to be !', 'Had a wonderfull time in a wonderful place with wonderful people. The mal was excellent we had rib eye n the amazing mushroom spicy soup.  ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1138, 'beachbummer75', 'Galana Road Ground Floor, Senteu Plaza, Nairobi Kenya', 'Ankole Grill Kilimani', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12626874-r838716264-Ankole_Grill_Kilimani-Nairobi.html', 'Restaurant offering a nice garden setting for food and drinks', 'Husband decided to bring me here for wedding anniversary celebration - we had evening drinks before ordering lamb samosas. He took grilled beef while I had chicken with rice\nThe food portions were huge, meats were well cooked and flavourful \n\nOnly comment I had was I don‚Äôt take spicy food \nMost of the dishes including entrees , main courses were all spicy. I had no choice but to choose the chicken but it was very creamy. I don‚Äôt take cheese or creams very well so even the pizzas were out for me. \n\nI wish they had more options for those who cannot take spices.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1139, 'Tasneem J', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r1010821677-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Huge disappointment!', 'Meaning to try this place for quite awhile now so decided to go there for an early dinner. To be fair, the milkshakes were okay but the food was mediocre to say the least. The establishment I think has lost focus on the quality of food and the way it should be presented, no value for the price you pay. I got a few sorry looking refried chips and a burger, no joy for the eyes nor the taste buds. If eating for you is just to fill full then this is the place for you. But if you eat to enjoy and delight your taste buds then there are better places out there. Don\'t waste your time and money at Nairobi street kitchen.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1140, 'moe', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r1001778901-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'SI senor Excellent Mexican food', 'thanks to @Chef Wycliffe for the incredible Taco Pollo and Al Pastor ‚Äì absolute mouthwatering delicacies! The flavors were rich, authentic, and unforgettable.Can‚Äôt wait to come back for more!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(1141, 'SEB06000', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r994408689-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Nice place for music', 'I went to Nairobi Street Kitchen on a Thursday night with my girlfriend, and I loved it. Although I didn‚Äôt eat there, the atmosphere was great. It attracts a very cosmopolitan crowd and has a lovely setting. It‚Äôs perfect for dancing outside on Thursday nights to African music. The prices are reasonable too. I definitely recommend it for a fun night out.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1142, 'Traveler06115066386', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r994346838-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent', 'Very nice place and my friends were happy.\nWe enjoyed the service and the friendly staff\nWe will truly come back especially on Thursday when we visited. It was busy and liked the crowd.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1143, 'Jason Mburu', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r983707698-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'I got the gist of enjoyment', 'This is a nice spot for day or night out with buddies, family and friends. Best meals, friendly staff, very fast waiters and waitress', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1144, 'Pauline Mlotswa', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r982061821-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing night', 'Very clean place with enough space.very many food options.Good music,friendly staff.if you love music this is the place .', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1145, 'Shemina S', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r980383561-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'NSK', 'Variety of food available. \nGood seating area.\nüç∏ üç∑ Alcohol also served.\nParking next door at a fee.\nClean.\nGood service.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1146, 'Shayna W', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r966900401-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Nice Experience', 'My friend and I came to Nairobi Street Kitchen on our first night in Nairobi.  We wanted good food and drinks in a lively atmosphere and received just that.  We loved that we could order from all of the different food vendors at our outdoor table through the wait staff.  We came a little before 9pm, and a few of the dishes we ordered were sold out, but everything else was delicious.  One of the bartenders stopped by our table to suggest some of the drink specials and they were delightful.  Afterwards we moved to the inside bar area where there was a DJ spinning Afrobeats and other lively genres.  It was a great night out!', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1147, 'emmachoo', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r963976333-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden Gem', 'Great spot for casual dinner with a choice of multiple eateries, so lots of different menu choices. Thai noodles were great and very big portions. Burgers were also delicious and my daughter enjoyed her pizza.\nIt felt a bit tricky to find in the dark as the street light levels in Nairobi are a bit low and it can feel a little unsafe walking there but definitely worth finding and perhaps getting a taxi or hotel driver to do door to door.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1148, 'west1983', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r963059538-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Good spot', 'I like the interior design, very open and clean. Lots of space for the several different cuisines they have on offer. Have been a couple fo times. I especially enjoyed the Indian mean I had, and the Thai one was okay. Both times the service was really good. It\'s well priced for what it offers, Will return.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1149, 'Helena P', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r962039772-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Very good!', 'Highly recommend! There is lots of choices for food options. The staff is very nice and the music is good! Enjoyed both Indian food with friend and burger in my own!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1150, 'Asif Hash', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r956647404-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Fantastic/Amazing', 'Arranged a birthday Party for a friend at NSK for about 60+ People on 23rd June 2014.\n\nSpecial thanks to lead NSK Manager Ms. Ann Oloo and Head of Dining Mr. Cosmos. Both these staff are amazing and helped us a great deal. Their communication, their punctuality, their precision in ordering, planning, executing and to top it all, a Big Smile and their Pleasant personalities helped by going an extra mile to make our event a success and absolutely world class Fantastic.\n\nOverall Great food, great team, great sound system, lighting and wooden dance floor, ample parking, awesome location and decor, top class customer experience made our event a memorable one. Birthday Girl was delighted and all the guests loved the event.\n\nThank you once again, Ann, Cosmos and Mr. Yasir Hussain, you guys are amaizngüëçüèΩüôèüèΩ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1151, 'Qiwai', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r953143669-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen is Fantastic!!!!', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen is an absolute gem for anyone seeking a vibrant and eclectic dining experience. The food is outstanding, with a mouthwatering selection that includes perfectly grilled nyama choma, succulent kuku choma, and flavorful tacos that will transport your taste buds on a culinary journey.\n\nBut it\'s not just about the food here. The lively atmosphere is infectious, with the sounds of salsa music filling the air and patrons often breaking into spontaneous dance. The fusion of Kenyan and international flavors creates a unique and twisted cuisine that keeps you coming back for more.\n\nWhether you\'re a food lover or just looking for a fun night out, Nairobi Street Kitchen delivers on all fronts. Highly recommended!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1152, 'Namdah Tour Safaris', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r953140434-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Nairobi Nightlife. ', 'Good music, went straight to the upstairs bar, good ventilation and enough space for dance. A good spot if you\'re into music and dance. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
