(1154, 'Robert O', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r932358931-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'New Year\'s Eve in Nairobi \'street kitchen\'', 'The name street kitchen got me off on the wrong foot. I thought street food (simple quality, good price) would be on offer, but the concept is very much that of an ordinary restaurant be it that a variety of dishes from different culture areas are on the menu. I had \"pescado\" from the Mexican sub menu. Tiny portions of fish served on mediocre quality tacos (900 Kes). Amarula (very small quantity in a big glass - 400 Kes). I can\'t say I was impressed.\n\nService was good. We were a group of twelve people (twelve different nationalities) and every individual paid for his/her own bill. Chapeau for the waiter who pulled it off.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1155, 'Kemoy L', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r929070346-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Yummy food', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen is a foodie haven with so many restaurant choices! Tried Spilt Milk, and my taste buds did a happy dance with their awesome vegan option. It\'s a place that truly caters to everyone\'s cravings. Highly recommend for a tasty and personalized culinary journey!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1156, 'Trevor M', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r925244685-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Thursdaze Soiree', 'Experience  \'A\' amazing.\nWas served by Helena, did I just forget to say how she is all-smiles.\nGreat service from her, full of energy and professional.\nI had pork-noodle, shoutout to the Chef at nood who made my dish. Ma-utamu tu! That\'s what we say back here at home when you have no words to food.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1157, 'saida k', 'Mpaka Rd Opposite Posta Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nairobi Street Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d23484428-r924976449-Nairobi_Street_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'So much HYPE', 'Had so much hype online about it visiting from Tanzania decide to check it out was dissapointed the meal I wanted sirloin steak they didn\'t have it! Nice decor different food courts to eat.  Still don\'t get why so much hype üòÇ it\'s ok would say teenagers may enjoy it more! Tried  a new cider drink Kenyan brand tasted fresh and crispyüòâ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
