(1305, 'LaetitiaMarais', 'Kijabe Street Longonot Place, Nairobi Kenya', 'Mawimbi Seafood Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d20151172-r1004187814-Mawimbi_Seafood_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Business dinner. Not so great.', 'We went to Mawimbi last night, took business partners from Germany and Ethiopia for dinner. \nWe\'ve been here before so our expectations were high. Unfortunately, this time round, it was very dissapointing. We ordered a variety of dishes and it was all around very underwhelming and not what we used to at Mawimbi.\nThe Tuna Tartare was extremely bland and the avo had hardly any taste. The chicken mains was very dry. I had the prawns and calamari and the prawns were so tiny, the 4 that came on the plate, dry and overcooked and very oily. \nThe calamari was just ok, the batter around it thick and too doughy. \nThe Carribean Mixed Seafood was such a small portion with mostly just calamari and octopus, hardly any shrimp and lobster.\nThere were also a couple of catch of the day orders which the fillet was quite small. Almost every one mentioned the food was cold. Especially the fries. The waiter was friendly and attentive and did a good job but unfortunately the kitchen and the chef let him down. We didn\'t want to make a scene infront of the guests so we just left it and called it a night. Unfortunately this was not a good experience food wise and definitely not worth the price or the drive there for that matter. Hope it will improve again. Especially for return customers like us, that travel to get there.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1306, 'Patricia N', 'Kijabe Street Longonot Place, Nairobi Kenya', 'Mawimbi Seafood Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d20151172-r1003510110-Mawimbi_Seafood_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great evening and surprise birthday celebration', 'We had a wonderful experience; right from the reception by the maitre d‚Äôhotel, the excellent food and great wine list.\n\nThe server for the night Brigid Wamuga was exceptional, went beyond call of duty. She demonstrated great knowledge of the menu and her recommendations were wonderful. I greatly appreciate her organizing for the band and staff to celebrate my birthday.\n\nWe had a memorable evening and will surely be back', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1307, 'arthur m', 'Kijabe Street Longonot Place, Nairobi Kenya', 'Mawimbi Seafood Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d20151172-r1003321079-Mawimbi_Seafood_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'The best in a long time. Bridget made it much better', 'The serene atmosphere and Bridget\'s service was excellent üëåThe food was top notch and tasty. On top of that Bridget organized a cake for my birthday making the experience surreal. Thanks a lot', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
