(1362, 'Felix R', 'Kijabe Street Longonot Place, Nairobi Kenya', 'Mawimbi Seafood Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d20151172-r998244321-Mawimbi_Seafood_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Satisfied customer', '\"I was at Mawimbi yesterday, and that place is amazing! The hostess‚Äîthough I can\'t remember her name‚Äîwas wearing glasses and was really friendly. You could see her smile from afar! She welcomed us warmly, showed us around, and gave us the best spot.\n\nKibira was our server, and she was amazing! The food‚Äîwow! You have to try Mawimbi. And their birthday celebrations? Unbelievable! You‚Äôll feel like celebrating your birthday every day.\n\nIt‚Äôs a 10/10 for me and my family!\"', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1363, 'Da B', 'Kijabe Street Longonot Place, Nairobi Kenya', 'Mawimbi Seafood Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d20151172-r998241017-Mawimbi_Seafood_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Happy client', '\"Yesterday, my friends and I went to Mawimbi for the first time, and we were truly impressed with everything. The reception was very welcoming, the ambience was great, and the food was incredibly tasty and fresh. They also had a live band, which I would rate a 10 out of 10!\"', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1364, 'Ravinder S', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r847487847-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Really fresh', 'Wow, loved the quality of the sushi and sashimi. In fact all the dishes we ordered were of high quality and the service was amazing. Really enjoyed our family dinner, washed down with some lovely sake. Staff were very friendly.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(1365, 'Jeff C', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r839736448-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Awesome Food!', 'Awesome food and wonderful service!  Elegant atmosphere with very attentive staff.  All of the food was perfect.  Going back soon.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1366, 'Lox', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r837448545-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Slowly sliding ...', 'We\'ve come here from the time they opened, about eight years ago, on a very regular basis.\nThe food is fairly consistent, but portions are smaller and more expensive, the wonderful practice of a clean, hot towel before the meal gone.\nTheir complimentary fresh salad is now basic to the core, its dressing made with fake vinegar.\nSushi and sashimi platters look the same, but the tuna is now more pink than red and the salmon fattier, meaning both are of a cheaper, lesser quality.\nService can go either way, sometimes excellent, now and again chaotic.\nAfter all this time the owner still acts as if he\'s never seen us before, so he is either very rude or needs better glasses ...', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1367, 'ash', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r834049526-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely authentic Japanese!', 'Wonderful! \nThe sushi and sashimi was excellent as were the sizzlers and the teriyaki with crispy fresh vegetables. \nService was without any fault and very good. \nA good and decently priced wine selection to enjoy with your meal. This should be a must at all restaurants. \nHighly recommend this restaurant. \nWill define be back!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1368, 'Anthony C', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r833581757-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Car Broken into and everything stolen while we dined', 'We have been regular customers of Haru for years, the food and service is always excellent.\nSadly though, last Thursday I parked my car where I always do in front of three security guards.  In the 28 minutes that I was in the restaurant, my car was broken into and they took everything of value.  When I got back to the car I saw straight away that my door lock had been jammed open with a screw driver and the CC TV camera inside the compound was also conveniently aimed up at the sky.\nI reported this to the management but there was little sympathy.  I was told not to park outside the compound (where you have to park as there is never parking inside).\nI personally feel that the staff in the compound were a part of this as it happened right in front of them in broad day light.\nIt would be wonderful if  Haru could do something about this and I can have my equipment returned.\nI gather that this is a regular occurrence and cars often have spare wheels taken too....\nAs I said before the food and service in great, but I would suggest taking your own security to ensure that your belongings are not stolen.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1369, 'JRubadiri', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r827137934-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Rude customer service agent Dennis', 'We love the food at Haru and usually order for deliveries and we also love to eat in person at the restaurant.\nToday Dennis was extremely rude, refused to even listen to the location which is 3-4 minutes from the restaurant. He only heard langata road and immediately said NO they don‚Äôt deliver to langata toad. Even after explaining to him the langata toad touches ngong road at Karen roundabout and goes all the way to TMall. The location was before Karen hospital but Dennis still said no! What was worse is his attitude, lack of listening and then ended up hanging up the phone on us. How many other clients has he done this to? He wouldn‚Äôt even apologize for rejecting an order before hearing the location. It was easier for him to bang the phone. The management needs to warm him and get him out of the customer service desk as he doesn‚Äôt understand what that is at all. Haru just lost a sale because of a rude staff member.\nJanette', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1370, 'Ketan', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r827032636-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Tepanyaki', 'Had booked a table for tepanyaki on the 5th to be told it‚Äôs all booked . We come here to be told that there is somebody on the table. The explanation we are given is that somebody else is sitting on our booking. What‚Äôs the point of booking a day in advance and everything confirmed. That is really not good customer service. And the worse thing is that there is no explanation given to why our table has been given to someone else. Really disappointed.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1371, 'Susan', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r823597554-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'price has raised up, portion got msaller', 'Before corona started prices were much better for sushi and portions were like double size with what is now. Even the portion of wasabi on plate became smaller. \nPortions are half size what I experienced before corona started, including any kind of sushi.\nThe other meals i do not have an experience.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1372, 'Patrick W', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r819565902-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Racist/Arrogant Staff with the exception of Steve', 'Went for a dinner date with my gf and we waited 30min to get served. Some white girls arrived and got served immediately. We told off the guy that was serving them but he didn‚Äôt concerned. We made a decision to go but on the way out Steve got to chat with us and was personable and gave us exceptional service. Staff ought to be trained to be better and stop perceiving white people as superior. It is sad that at this day and age we still have racist mentality. Kudos Steve. Won‚Äôt recommend this restaurant.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1373, 'Connie Kibui', 'Karen Professional Centre Karen Road, Nairobi 24168 Kenya', 'Haru Japanese Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d4540736-r819565325-Haru_Japanese_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'RACISM', 'Sad that we had to wait for 30minutes to get a waiter whereas a couple of white ladies were served immediately they got there and it was after us. However Steve the waiter was able to curb the situation while we were leaving. Kudos Steve!..But in general, racism is a disgusting behavior so change your ways. Would not recommend', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1374, 'Sunita B', 'Lower Kabete Road, Highridge, Nairobi 20117 Kenya', 'Rift Valley Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8734695-r978898287-Rift_Valley_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing experience', 'Great service by our waiter Billy. Also great ribs. Also they had a nice small indoor playarea for our kids which helped entertain them.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1375, 'Margaret N', 'Lower Kabete Road, Highridge, Nairobi 20117 Kenya', 'Rift Valley Spur', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8734695-r978377295-Rift_Valley_Spur-Nairobi.html', 'Bill the G...t!', 'The ambience, mocktails and food were good. The service from Bill was even better. I would recommend the place to anyone who is looking for a chill place.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
