(1417, 'katha91_01', 'General Mathenge Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'Asmara Restaurant, Westlands', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d6276115-r780003159-Asmara_Restaurant_Westlands-Nairobi.html', 'Fantastic Eritrean food in Nairobi! ', 'The place is beautiful, nice seating in the garden. The food was plenty and very flavourful, and the service. It\'s a little bit \"fancier\" so the food is not served on injera bread and you\'ll get cutlery (unlike in many other ethiopian/eritrean places). ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1418, 'Anne M', 'General Mathenge Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'Asmara Restaurant, Westlands', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d6276115-r757510217-Asmara_Restaurant_Westlands-Nairobi.html', 'Once a gem, never again!', 'We have been die hard Asmara diners for years now. Its a great space for kids as well,. Theirs is the  passion cosmo I will drink in Nairobi . A couple of weeks into the shutdown, we decided to support our fave local restaurant by ordering in. We ordered one chicken dish, one fish and injera.  On opening the chicken dish, it looked like someone had eaten the entire piece and left a backbone immersed in the gravy. I took it up with management the next day(as they were closed), who said they would follow up. I haven\'t heard a squeak from them since.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1419, 'sdmmb', 'General Mathenge Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'Asmara Restaurant, Westlands', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d6276115-r755310655-Asmara_Restaurant_Westlands-Nairobi.html', 'One of the few restaurants', 'One of the few restaurants open for dining in with social distancing.  Excellent food and nice setting with spacious terrace garden.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1420, 'sdmmb', 'General Mathenge Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'Asmara Restaurant, Westlands', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d6276115-r748440742-Asmara_Restaurant_Westlands-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent food and service.', 'Excellent food and service.   Ethiopian/Eritrean food.  Good meat and vegetarian options and nice setting', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1421, 'Talampakan', 'General Mathenge Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'Asmara Restaurant, Westlands', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d6276115-r747030511-Asmara_Restaurant_Westlands-Nairobi.html', 'A revelation', 'A friend who lived in the neighbourhood recommended this place. We had a lovely lunch out in the garden on a Sunday afternoon. Some of us had meat and others had fish. The fish dish that I ordered was superb, although there was too much injera (Eritrean/Ethiopian bread). Coffee was also a great treat after the heavy meal.\n\nService was friendly and efficient. Apart from outdoor seating there is a huge indoor facility that could be used for larger gatherings. Parking spaces are plentiful.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1422, '–ú–∞—Ä–∞—Ç –ê', 'General Mathenge Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'Asmara Restaurant, Westlands', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d6276115-r745537675-Asmara_Restaurant_Westlands-Nairobi.html', 'Place of good surprises ', 'Have found Asmara Restaurant on internet, but was not sure that it serves Ethiopian food. Place is very easy to find as restaurant is located in a walking distance from the popular Sarit Mall and is located in a nice and extremely safe area of Nairobi. Entering the restaurant you have a feeling of coming to a botanic garden as it has so many trees and very green and nicely managed. You have a choose to stay indoor or outside and be surrounded by trees with birds which is quite exotic. \n\nVariety of food is quite large that starts from very simple Ethiopian snacks continues with more comprehensive stuff. The taste of food is unbelievably delicious and so yummy!! You could also get Ethiopian coffee made of fire. If you are close to Sarit Center don‚Äôt lose an opportunity to enjoy Asmara restaurant, and it will allow you unforgettable atmosphere combined with delicious food.\n\nGood luck and share your opinion with others', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1423, 'MPMKM', 'General Mathenge Lane, Nairobi Kenya', 'Asmara Restaurant, Westlands', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d6276115-r740765545-Asmara_Restaurant_Westlands-Nairobi.html', 'Great Food ', 'This is one of my favorite restaurants in Nairobi.  The food is Eritrean/ Ethiopian.  Fantastic.  The beef tips are the best.  Everything is fresh, well seasoned and delicious.  ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(1424, 'Theresa H', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r1036227959-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great authentic food and enjoyable place to dine.', 'What an amazing  venue. Service is awesome, food is delicious and the atmosphere was delightful. The view is to die for. Definitely on my list for a return visit.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1425, 'Naureen K', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r995243567-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Good', 'The ambiance here was lovely! The food was not that great, though. Muted flavours and not the softest meat. I would go to a more local place; this place seemed to make it \"more palatable\" for more Western diets.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1426, 'John N', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r976490732-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'African cuisine  place', 'Very great place and clarity of the environment,good and delicious  samosas and a healthy coctail soup of the day.Not forgetting  big smilers the waitres n waitress. My muzungu was impressed  by the good and well prepared food.great place to bring guest for African cuisine. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1427, 'Marilyn T', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r972089443-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great food and even BETTER service.', 'We had a delicious meal but even better service during our visit. The Ingokho Isiche (or smoked chicken) was falling-off-the-bone tender and delicious. I loved the green chill condiment that was served alongside. Lovely that there are vegetarian offerings that are sumptuous too! The Obwoba (mushroom) dish was packed with woodsy flavor of fungi and I love the story about the foraging given in the menu. Should I return to Nairobi and repeat visit would definitely be in the plans.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1428, 'Xaver W', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r971290008-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Kenyan Introduction to cuisine', 'Great Kenyan food, great intro to the cuisine. Great service and atmosphere. Enjoyed it a lot on a casual tuesday night.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1429, 'Martin W', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r968311715-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great Dinner in a Great Location.', 'We enjoyed a seven-course meal of traditional Kenyan food from all around the nation.  We enjoyed chicken, beef, fish, fruit, and many vegetable dishes.   The food was amazing and the atmosphere was beautiful.   It was a visit on our last evening in Kenya and it was well worth the money and the time.   Highly recommend this restaurant.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1430, 'Ursula K', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r967567746-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'A SAFARI FOOD EXPERIENCE NOT TO BE MISSED', 'The food was fantastic, and the service made it even better!!\nWithout a doubt we will come back to Amaica.\nWe had just finished 2 weeks safari and for the last night in Nairobi we booked this restaurant for dinner We were a total of 20 people, from Italy, from the US and from Kenya. We truly enjoy the Kenyan traditional tasting menu. The highlights were the chicken, the black ugali, the beef and surprisingly the fried termites. Also, we they had a fantastic Cab. Frankly we found the price to be really good considering the variety of food and the quality of it, it was really a food safari!!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1431, 'Debayan', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r967396381-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great food and ambiance', 'Great food. \nWe tried the rabbit and the tilapia. Rabbit was a bit overdone. But the fish in the coconut curry was so subtle and delicious. \n\nHighly recommend the place for the atmosphere as well.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1432, 'Gareth P', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r967197631-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely laid back afternoon meal', 'Lovely restaurant and super friendly staff who gave me great advice on choosing my meal which was excellent (pigeon pea stew)! \nLaid back venue with lovely view of the forest. \nIf I‚Äôm back in Nairobi I‚Äôll certainly be here again.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1433, 'Jummib√§r', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r941544302-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Super Service, sch√∂ne Lage und sehr gutes Essen!', 'Super Service und eine sehr ansprechende Auswahl ! Ich habe mich f√ºr die ger√∂steten Termiten, ja wirklich! Termiten als Vorspeise entschieden. Sehr gut, viel besser als gedacht, dazu brauchte ich aber einen Dipp der mit dazu gereicht wurde. Als Hauptspeise habe ich den Hasen gew√§hlt mit Beilagen. Das Restaurant ist am Waldrand und man ist ein wenig abseits der Stra√üe. Sehr sch√∂n und sauber. Ich kann es uneingeschr√§nkt empfehlen.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(1434, 'Liz H', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r915515612-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Best Restaurant in Africa', 'We have travelled to over 100 countries and have just been in Africa for the last 6 weeks and this is by far the best authentic African food we have had combined with friendly, enthusiastic staff.\n\nWe had previously ate ar their Airport restaurant in 2019 and throughly enjoyed our food and experience. On this trip faced with a change in Tanzania or going via Nairobi we opted to go via Nairobi so we could have ‚Äòdinner‚Äô here again at our favourite African restaurant and it definitely didn‚Äôt disappoint.\n\nThe service was amazing and everyone was smiling and very keen to help. We met Pamela who is the manager who is passionate about authentic Kenyan food and this shows in the menu and the food itself.\n\nWe had three courses paired with great wine over 3 hours‚Ä¶. And it was better than we remembered‚Ä¶ we will definitely be back.. hopefully before another 4 years passes‚Ä¶\n\nThank you to everyone‚Ä¶üòéüôèüôèüôè', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1435, 'Journey18435461134', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r912883760-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Serene location with great waitstaff but tasteless food', 'I had been looking forward to dining at Amaica for authentic Kenyan food especially the Luhya cuisine but it turned out very disappointing. The atmosphere is serene and beautiful and the staff very friendly and professional. However, the place is  quite and can get boring. Imagine, we were the only guests in the entire restaurant on a Friday evening; which is strange in Nairobi especially in a busy area like Westlands. People flood restaurants with great food on Friday evenings. So this deserted environment was strange.\n\nI Must admit that I liked how the waitstaff welcomed us pleasantly and served  us drinks of our choice. However, the main meal was far from delicious. I don\'t know how they prepare their food but there is something about the taste of food that just isn\'t right. The taste is off. Also, their pries are insanely expensive that we were shocked when the waitstaff presented us with the bill. \n\nI would go back for the environment, if there is some music to spice up things. But as for the food, it\'s a NO for me.  ', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1436, 'Jakano', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r898948996-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Relaxed ambience and great food', 'Amaica never disappoints me each time I visit. The relaxed ambience and great Kenyan cuisine that is very well presented. \n\nThe staff is responsive and knowledgeable about the different dishes. On the day we were there, the owner of the restaurant gave us a warm reception. \n\nDefinitely a place to visit for a true gastronomical experience of well-prepared Kenyan dishes.\n\nHighly recommended!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]');
