(1476, 'Expat2Globetrotter', 'Kenyatta Avenue Westminster House, Nairobi Kenya', 'Artcaffe Westminster', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19795523-r874288784-Artcaffe_Westminster-Nairobi.html', 'Indulge yourself in a breathtaking 1928 architecture with excellent service!', 'Friendly service in a breathtaking spacey architectural flair from 1928!\n\nAfter our order, we even got a free cake on a plate with chocolate letters wishing us ‚ÄúSafe skies Carlo and Robert‚Äù!!! What a personal touch!\n\nHighly recommendable!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1477, 'Shemina S', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r1034756106-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Nargis', '*Nargis Restaurant* is a long-standing, beloved culinary institution in Nairobi. Renowned for its truly *delicious barbeque* , the menu offers a tempting array of expertly grilled dishes, ranging from smoky starters to generous main courses. Every plate is served with fresh side salads and *signature sauces* , perfectly complementing the main event. While the prices at Nargis are undoubtedly *steep* , the consensus remains that the exceptional quality and memorable flavour deliver *value well worth the investment.*', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1478, 'Jasmine A', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r948135399-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Classic Nairobi experience', 'Lower your expectations in regard to \'atmosphere\' - you go to this restaurant for the DELICIOUS spicy bbq meat. I wouldn\'t really recommend it for a vegetarian - the menu is very limited but basically if you like meat cooked desi BBQ style and feel like you don\'t need to eat it with alcohol (which is not served here) then this is the place for you. This restaurant has been around for for decades and is still run by the original family who set it up, they don\'t take reservations and every time I\'ve been it\'s been packed, mainly with people from the Kenyan Asian community - because the food is SO GOOD. The mushkaki fresh off the BBQ is unbeatable, the chicken tikka is delicious, the kebabs are so good...the kulfi was also amazing and they have a paan-walla on site so you can get your fix after your meal. During Ramadan I often ordered the iftar boxes from them (2k for a family sized portion of mixed grill) as they really hit the spot. It\'s a very simple, old building and has a very relaxed casual family atmosphere. Staff were great and responded to our requests very quickly.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1479, 'Nimish Hadole', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r913183127-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'A simple restaurant for some great Indian Barbeque', 'Despite average ambience and customer service, the delicious food more than compensates. A top choice in Nairobi, offering tasty options in a simple yet beautiful outdoor setting.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1480, 'OnAir61460187516', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r893825293-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'worst place', 'it used to be my favourite joint but my last experience was really bad.Useless food.The naans were pathetic and the food is ridiculously overpriced.The worst place and rude people. Especially sajjad. please dont waste your time and money.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1481, 'Adil S', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r891169809-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Useless service', 'AVOID AT ALL COST CAALLED AT 730 SPOKE TO SAJJAD 2 HOURS LATER HE NEVER ANSWER CALLS USELESS WORTHLESS CANT WAIT FOR HASHMI ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(1482, 'Leylahni', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r847479872-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Below average', 'We were a big group and booked in advance however the team was not coordinated well at all. Our food came out in bits with some of waiting for ages for our drinks. One of us gave up altogether \n. Shame really as we went here quite often as kids and this experience was marred.\n\nThe food itself tasted ok. Nothing to write home about. Kebabs tiny. Will not be returning.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1483, 'B.R', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r816062804-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Authentic ', 'Nargis has been around for decades and one thing they specialise on is consistency.\nWith recent refurbishments it looks much more refreshed. At night the ambience is amazing.\nFierce competitors with haashmi (now closed) they have chartered their own market share with good bbq food.\nThe chicken is definitely more tasty (u can\'t taste the cheap fat /oil that other establishments use), well spiced and marinated. Sadly during rush hour u may get issues with the orders.\nPortions are definitely smaller than most other places.\nThe paneer tikka is amazing and so is the fish tikka.\nThe nans are average and tend to dry out fairly quickly.\nService is usually on point.\nIf you want authentic chicken tikka its definitely the place to be (they cook to order not pre cook like others & they avoid msg) so it is worth visiting.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1484, 'Hitan P', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r784048937-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Perfected tikka in Nairobi ', 'I have been eating at Nargis for over 10 years till today the taste is still the same.\nThe kebabs are amazing too.\n', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(1485, 'Shabnaam qureishi', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r757067260-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Nice tikka', 'Nice tikka and good prices abit differnet than most places however they seem to be good with their services and taste . The place is abit old but that doesn‚Äôt matter as the food does up for what the eyes see', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1486, 'Ashraf A', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r734457115-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Family dinner in Nairobi.', 'A very busy outlet in the Westlands area of Nairobi. Had a late dinner with family on arrival from Kampala.Th emplacement was a beehive of activity with the aroma of the various meats penetrating the air.We ordered our starters of mushkaki, shami kababs.The chicken tikka was out of this world and Nargis lives up to its expectation of excellent food.The Butter nans were well prepared,not forgetting the Vimeo Specials.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1487, 'Srikanta P', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r723865669-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'A meeting with a food at perfect place', 'I came here by a friends invitation and heard about the Chiken Tikka. The food was awesome. Taste is superb. Service is fast. The staffs attend to multiple tables and do justice to each table on service.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(1488, 'Hitan P', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r723446142-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Take out as good as always ', 'We normally do a take out from nargis the chicken tikka and Mushkaki are truly the best in town. Their vegetable paneer chapatis are also good not to forget their poussin chips simply mouth watering', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(1489, 'Khalid', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r723400980-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Delicious Chicken Tikka, stark atmosphere. ', 'Pros- their Chicken Tikka was the best I have ever had in East Africa. The serving staff was one of the hardest working and sweetest servers I have I ever seen. Despite them seeming unhappy working there. In addition, I was so impressed by their service I gave them a handsome tip. They made sure I understood why my frustration was with their menu and made sure my order came quick and were very polite. \n\nCons- Their menu is every limited they only offer curries on specific days. Also their Passion fruit juice was less than appetizing. It tasted off both my friend and I couldn\'t finish it. It was outright disgusting sorry to say. Also the atmosphere was stark and tacky. No music and no mood. \n\nConclusion- I Would come back for the chicken Tikka. Take away. ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1490, 'Juzer K', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r713941685-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Tantalising food', 'Very tasty food chicken chooza paneer nan all food is very tasty what they really need to improve is service sometimes when you want order something it\'s very difficult to get hold of a waiter that is very disappointing', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(1491, 'Chandni', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r704614098-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great Indian Barbecue', 'They have great Indian barbecue in Nairobi. They offer all types of meat (beef, mutton and chicken) and vegetarian options too. For vegetarians it is mainly paneer options - which they do a great job with (it is certainly not saltless or tasteless paneer). \n\nThis is a family style restaurant - and it always helps to reserve if you are many. \n\nThe restaurant itself is not very pleasing to the eye - but the food does all the justice. I haven\'t tired going to this place for years now. I highly recommend it for fresh, spicy, Indian barbecue. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1492, 'Madame_Trey', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r679031676-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great chicken Tikka ', 'Visited Nargis to settle an argument: what\'s the number 1 spot for Indian grilled meat in Nairobi.\nI am team Hashmi. My friend is team Nargis.\n\nThe restaurant is hidden in a quiet road in Westlands. I have driven by for several years and didn\'t even know the house was a restaurant.\n\nThere is adequate seating inside but it\'s much more enjoyable to sit outside in the courtyard.\n\nFood was quick and service efficient.   We ordered the standard array: chicken Tikka, kebabs, masala and regular chips, wings, samosa. Spice levels were just right, tempered by yogurt sauce and crisp salad.\n\nThe food was sincerely great..... HOWEVER Hashmi flavor lingers in my mouth much longer and drool has often woken me up in the middle of the night at the thought of the mixed grill platter.\n\nGive it to try yourself.... ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1493, 'HNC1980', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r664793038-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great Food', 'I have been to this place severally and their food is consistently good. Their prices are also very reasonable. The outside sitting atmosphere is very enjoyable especially in the evenings.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1494, 'moha m', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r664626044-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Only issue is Food Quantity and Car Parking', 'The restaurant is good, prices are moderate but the quantity is disappointing, try ordering their \'mshkaki\' it will remind you of the Mr.Bean Christmas Scene. They also have problems with parking especially if you go there on a weekend.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(1495, 'WW Traveler', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r647190541-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Average ', 'Average barbecue restaurant with very limited choice. For sure there are better places around in town ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(1496, 'Qasim K', 'School Lane Westlands, Nairobi Kenya', 'Nargis Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3685476-r634462745-Nargis_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Wonderful Food!!!!', 'Wonderful place to go food is the most delicious food ever!!!! Staff is really friendly and the owners are always at your service best food.It might be a bit old fashioned but that is what makes it special!!!!.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1497, 'Guillaume D', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r823698091-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Great Experience ', 'A wonderful experience on new year eve which completed a nice Kenyan tour : the \"Gourmet Safari Across Kenya\" menu was just the perfect end to our holidays\n\nWaiters were very kind !\n\n', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1498, 'klgdvm', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r816904736-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Interesting food selection', 'We had lunch here on our last day in Nairobi. The menu had many interesting options, East African food instead of the continental fare we had much of the trip. I had Athola, which I thought was quite tasty. The staff was friendly, and helpful, as I decided which dish to order. The service was slow by American standards, but we are not in the US. We had time to relax and visit with friends without the pressure to leave the table. Covid precautions were taken- temperature check on arrival, hand sanitizer, tables spaced, open dining area. A very enjoyable lunch experience.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1499, 'TraceyFogarty', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r720255748-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Authentic Kenyan Food...', 'We lunched here and were pleasantly surprised with the food. Our guide suggested and we were not disappointed. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1500, 'Karari Kariuki', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r711805258-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Phenomenalüòã', 'I would easily call this an undiscovered place. Everything about it was just amazing. The food, the ambience, the staff... I honestly don\'t know what they can improve on (the portions maybe?ü§î). If you haven\'t been here yet, you don\'t know what you\'re missing. Especially if you\'re looking for a relaxed place, with everything good, and little traffic.\nGive Amaica a visit. You won\'t regret it. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1501, 'Angella c', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r704950030-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Kenyan cuisine', 'I had their brown ugali and rabbit meat which was divine! I would definitely take guests visiting Nairobi to Amaica for a meal.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(1502, 'Angelique F', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r686443096-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Kenyan cuisine fresh and tasty', 'Just wanted to taste Kenyan cuisine. You have the barbecue but you also have a s√©rie of side dishes and stew which are delicious and spicy. Spicy sauce is served  in a separate bowl, the restaurant has a nice terrasse and it‚Äôs overlooking the nearby forest. A good address.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1503, 'Mukuma', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r640540240-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Staff great but not food', 'We had breakfast here whilst on transit to London.\nThe staff were excellent but the food was very poorly prepared.\nWe had the light breakfast with pancakes.\nThe bacon was doggy and underdone. The pancakes were underdone too and very thick.\nA quick word is needed with the chef to improve the cooking.\nOtherwise, a lovely atmosphere and the usual lovely Kenyan hospitality.\n', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1504, 'misssamanthalouise', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r619774789-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Fantastic food, great service and atmosphere.', 'We dined late, they kept the band playing for our arrival. Comfortable couches, well decorated, great atmosphere. Peanut soup, fish and curry were delicious and we were too full to try dessert. Next time, we definitely will go back it was the best dinner we had in Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1505, 'Latonia G', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r617117951-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'My first meal in Nairobi and it did not disappoint', 'On my first night in Nairobi, I decided to take a taxi from my hotel to the famed Amaica.  It was a Monday evening and understandably slow - there were only a few patrons in the restaurant when I arrived but the food was simply fantastic.  I ordered the lamb and had it with sauteed spinach.  The entire meal was great, the lamb was flavorful and tender and the sauteed spinach had a smoky flavor that was fabulous.  I met the chef and promptly asked for the recipe and he was kind enough to tell me how to make it.  Chef Dennis, thank you so much!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(1506, 'SNM', 'Getathuru Garden Off Peponi Road, Westlands, Nairobi, Nairobi 00100 Kenya', 'Amaica The Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d3581892-r610272637-Amaica_The_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'A poor choice for our last night in Kenya', 'We are on our honeymoon and had the opportunity to spend one night in Nairobi before flying back home. They served interesting food which was tasty and all went well with each other. Our server was also kind enough to help us order the right dishes. We were a bit nervous coming into an empty restaurant at 8pm on a Saturday night, but she told us ‚Äúthey are coming!‚Äù And 2 other couples showed up shortly after we placed our order. Both the chicken and beef that arrived were far too tough and other reviews say it‚Äôs because it was all precooked. But it took them almost 40 minutes to deliver our order so I don‚Äôt know what took them so long to bring out. And lastly, the credit card machine couldn‚Äôt accept my card. We agreed to pay 50 usd (a bill that I had in my wallet) and I asked for 1000 KES back since the conversion rate on google was 5,039 KES for 50 usd. But then she came back saying the rate her boss asked for was 80 KES, meaning it would be exactly the 50 usd and they got the total of 1000 KES marked up. Super rude, We had no choice to accept and we just didn‚Äôt give a tip anymore. Kenya has been so good to us, in meru, the masai Mara and Nairobi... it‚Äôs such a shame that they had to low key ruin our last night with such a sour taste in our mouths.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"portion_size\", \"delivery_takeout\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1507, 'Amy W', 'Harry Thuku Rd Fairmont The Norfolk, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'TATU RESTAURANT', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1910873-r1029882935-TATU_RESTAURANT-Nairobi.html', 'Top 10 dinners I\'ve ever had', 'A memorable experience.  In the top 10 best dinners I\'ve ever had.  The staff,  Joy, Eunice, Tandy and Micheal were attentive and professional. Top top service.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1508, 'Joy S', 'Harry Thuku Rd Fairmont The Norfolk, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'TATU RESTAURANT', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1910873-r1029755934-TATU_RESTAURANT-Nairobi.html', 'I was so touched by one of the waiter a really gentleman by the name Tevin. He is amazing, he made our terrific.', 'It was an amazing evening, excellent service, good food, so serine environment. Every one was so friendly n helpful. Which made us feel comfortable and homely. Tevin was our waiter tonight and I can say much in so many words he\'s amazing.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1509, 'Obinna Benjamin C', 'Harry Thuku Rd Fairmont The Norfolk, Nairobi 00200 Kenya', 'TATU RESTAURANT', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1910873-r1028947673-TATU_RESTAURANT-Nairobi.html', 'Stupendous Dinner at Tari', 'Service was awesome and the waiters are so nice. Had a very welcoming reception from Florence and Joy.\nThe food is also great.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]');
