(1608, 'Dips D', 'The Mall Shopping Centre Ring Rd Westlands, Westlands, Nairobi 00800 Kenya', 'Haandi Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d802603-r821601976-Haandi_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'PLEASE DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY ON HAANDI @ WESTGATE MALL!', 'We went to Haandi restaurant to have Indian food, since the menu looks so interesting.. We ordered variety of dishes plus Tadka Daal without spices, tomatoes & chillies since my hubby has acid reflux issue.. \nThe Daal arrived full of turmeric that u can actually taste raw turmeric rather than the daal + chillies!! We requested the waiter to change it, poor guy goes to the chef and the chef WITHOUT tasting it, insists there are no chillies, we sent him back again and the chef tasted and said \"OK TELL THEM WE CAN NOT MAKE MORE THAN THIS FOR YOU\" & refused to prepare another daal.. Is this the service of Indian restaurants in Nairobi? Is that how these namely restaurants treat their customers?? \nThe other dishes were idli/vada, chole bhature, butter masala dosa, paapad, French fries, sweet & mango Lassi.. Their food does not have authentic Indian taste.. \nFor best experience of Indian food in Nairobi, I will rather recommend Cinnamon, Bhagwanji and Giriraj restaurants. \nPLEASE DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY ON HAANDI @ WESTGATE MALL!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
