(1691, 'Ruby362', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r929112219-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Has been way better.', 'Let\'s hope that this otherwise incredible restaurant was having an \'off\' day because our experience yesterday was really poor. Food took forever, items not available, service was very pleasant but far too busy. Even parking was a disaster. Not a great experience. Expected way more.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1692, 'Relax621409', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r927727301-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Thai Chi Westlands Nairobi', 'We were stopping at the Sarova Stanley hotel in Nairobi. This was the attached restaurant for which I‚Äôd read some super reviews. However, it is currently under renovation. The reception staff told me that they had a standalone branch situated in the Westlands area and they kindly arranged complimentary transportation if we wanted to make a reservation. We did and what a wonderful experience, seating both indoors and outdoors. We chose a spot not far from the open bifold doors so we got a shared setting, a cracking vibe to the place. Maryanne our waitress couldn‚Äôt have been more helpful and assured in her role, thank you again. The food was fabulous, we chose five different dishes and all were super. If you are in Nairobi and want to experience a nice Thai restaurant, I‚Äôd recommend this place whole heartedly.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1693, 'Rachel P', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r927333449-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Huge (and expensive) disappointment!', 'We had high expectations when we arrived for dinner last night, alas none of those expectations were met.  Our waiter, Ivan, while a lovely person, was thoroughly unfamiliar with the menu. We had to ask multiple time and in different ways what things meant (example, \"what does Thai style tempura mean? ...it is the style it is prepared. Uh, yes, but what is that style/ how is it prepared?\" the response were blank eyes. When asked about putting a chili sauce on the side, he assured us they would - and when the dish came it was covered, covered, in chili sauce - and for the one of our party who ordered it - inedible.\n\nWe finally got a different waitstaff, MaryAnne, who was much more switched on - unfortunately, her good service couldn\'t make up for the food. We ordered udon noodles w/ chicken and got rice noodles with chicken (apparently there were no udon noodles, but no one told us that, and BTW, the primary order was for udon noodles (with which a guest could add chicken or prawns, or whatever).  The misnamed Udon noodles with chicken dish was indistinguishable from the Pad Thai with chicken.  The satay was good and we could recommend that. We ordered chicken wings, which came as deep-fried chicken mince (ground chicken) stuffed into a wing and breaded and deep-fried - interesting, but tasting like fried breading mostly. The dessert, the sticky toffee pudding, tasted rather bland, almost overdone.  Another disappointment. \n\nAt the end of the dinner, we waited for a long time for our check, understandable we saw it was busy, but we also waited and waited and waited for the left-overs in the take-away containers, too.\n\nThe food is fair, but it is not particularly thai, and the initial service was appallingly poor.  I might take a business lunch there and order the satay, but we left the restaurant feeling very let down by the whole experience.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1694, 'Linda R', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r926449119-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'friday Dinnr at the lavington branch', 'Thai Chi Lavington, service was amazing, the food was really goo, nothing to complain about and the mocktails were decent too, its worth a try, got seated even though they were fully booked on booking, hope they keep up the standards, worth a revisit', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(1695, 'Amu', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r921894779-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Disgusting ', 'The new Thai Chi in Lavington is horrible. I had the worst dinner I have ever had. I used to go to the old one in town. The Stanley. It was amazing. When i heard there\'s a new one, I said why not. The food is overpriced. The quality is horrendous. The mocktails are good, my kids enjoyed, but the food is very very bad. We ordered the prawns dumpling, salmon, chicken yogurt ( turned out to be a bun very disguring), beef, seafood salad. The seafood wa stale. The prawns had a bad bad taste. Then dumplings are soggy bad flavor. The seafood salad was spicy, so hold back the bad taste of seafood. The chicken was bland and wrong. The salmon wasn\'t seasoned. The only thing good was the plain rice for dessert. We got fortune cookies. Which was a good touch, and it wasn\'t bad. I was expecting the same kind of food I used to get in Stanley, but I was shocked and throughly disappointed. I\'m never visiting this place again, and I highly don\'t recommend this place. Service was OK. ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1696, 'Wanderlust', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r916932195-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Avoid it at all costs!', 'Decided to try the new location in Lavington for a birthday dinner. Their original location was an old favourite many years ago, so this seemed like a good idea. First impressions were positive; the place was full. The rest went downhill rapidly from there. It took forever to get a server\'s attention and even get a drinks order in. We placed the food order at the same time as it had taken so long already. The server repeated the order about five times. When it arrived much later, the food was appalling. Cold, flavourless, and overpriced for the portion sizes, there was nothing to salvage this bad experience. The staff were confused, still managing to place the wrong orders, not sure what to do when I complained and sent the food back. They were not expecting honesty when they came for the routine \"so how\'s your meal\" banter. This is the worst Thai food I\'ve had in Nairobi in a long, long time. Unfortunately there is no rating below 1 star on this. It\'s a trainwreck.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1697, 'caroline5018', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r908499608-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent food and lovely staff and service', 'I decided to treat myself on the last night of my wonderful visit to Kenya, and I wasn‚Äôt disappointed. The food was excellent ‚Ä¶authentic Thai cuisine, which I love. The service from the staff was also excellent, especially from my lovely waitress Njeri. I will definitely return next time I am in the city. Thank you!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1698, 'black_velvet', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r906271106-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent Thai cuisine in Nairobi ', 'One of the best Thai restaurants I\'ve ever been to (and I travel a lot...). This venue offers a relaxing and classy environment. The food was above my best expectations. The service is also excellent, thanks to the kindness of Njeri.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1699, 'Micke A', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r881227630-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Stay here while in Nairobi', 'Great Thai restaurant at a really interesting Hotel. \nThe food and service was outstanding. \nThe restaurant is located in  the Stanley Hotel which originally was built in 1902', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(1700, 'Jackline N', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1019897874-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Great experience', 'This is a great place for a date night. The ambience is very good. The food is also delicious. I had chicken wings as a starter and they were the best I have ever had.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1701, 'DeLonne E', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1019524949-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Chef‚Äôs kiss', 'A magical experience. Amazing flavors, outstanding menus, wonderful staff, and everything is grown right there. You must tour the farm. So good we ate there multiple times, and will be going once more before we leave back to America. A must visit when in Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1702, 'Victoire V', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1019243404-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Absolutely amazing.  Best lunch ever . Amazing staff supper efficient and amazingly friendly. The food was incredible,', 'Amazing experience \nThe most delicious food ever . Light , a bit spicy but just right . Some crab meal forgot the title, but shared with my friend . Delicious wine', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1703, 'gawahoo', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1018969694-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'our favorite meal in Nairobi', 'All six of our group loved the service, experience, and meal. Two of our party said the Kobe burger was the best burger ther\'d ever had -- and ordered another. Was a great experience!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1704, 'Michelle O', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1016966653-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Great place to grab dinner or lunch in Nairobi. Don\'t miss this experience!', 'First-- the  ease of seeing menu and being able to reserve online is a big perk. \n\nSecond-- was able to change time of reservation on our day with no issue. \n\nThird-- was in a location easily known by our uber drivers\n\nFourth--the decor and atmosphere was perfect. Excellent service throughout our meal-- start to finish. \n\nFifth-- the food was simply fantastic. Easily could be a place you would find in NYC or Miami or Philadelphia-- with a Kenyan twist. Appreciated by locals and travelers alike. \n\nThis place is five stars in our book for sure.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1705, 'constablegal', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1015271728-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Karen\'s Fabulous Restaurant', 'When we first stayed in Nairobi on our way to Safari, our host recommended this restaurant. We were able to stop there for lunch on our last day before heading to the airport. What a terrific place! It is divided into several attractive sections, and we ate in one of them. The food is delicious, and the recommendation was spot on. Fish tacos, cauliflower, french fries - just to name a few of the pescatarian and vegetarian options - were excellent. It\'s located in a section called Karen.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1706, 'Joyce A', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1013548764-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Loved it!', 'Amazing terrace space with NYC level cocktails and shared plates. Everything was delicious! And open early enough that we grabbed dinner before our evening flight out of Nairobi', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1707, 'Anthony D', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1012651485-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Great Nairobi experience', 'It‚Äôs a trek from Nairobi unless you‚Äôre in the Karen area, however, the trek is worth it! The restaurant is beautiful, the service attentive, friendly and professional, and the food is outstanding.  A lot of choices are offered in terms of protein based and vegetarian dishes, and everything was very well thought out and executed.  We‚Äôre already thinking of when and how we go back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1708, 'Michela M', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1010771383-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'A Perfect Ending to Our Nairobi Adventure', 'After a game drive in Nairobi National Park with some friends who were visiting the city, we went to Cultiva for lunch. It was the perfect way to conclude our experience and showcase what Nairobi has to offer. The food was excellent, and the staff were incredibly welcoming and well-prepared. There were six of us, and we wanted to try several dishes, yet all of the meals were served within ten minutes! We had an amazing experience at what might be the best restaurant in the city, noting more to add.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1709, 'Carrie V', 'Pofu Road, Nairobi 00502 Kenya', 'Cultiva Farm Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d19292723-r1010691759-Cultiva_Farm_Kenya-Nairobi.html', 'Creative use of local ingredients with knowlegeable,friendly service.', 'Fun, lively restaurant with open kitchen. They grow much of their own produce and connect with local farms to supplement. Creative uses of vegetables. Broad selection of menu items all tightly executed under chef\'s watchful eye.  Educated, service oriented front of house staff.  Very pleasant experience. I would go again.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1710, 'Subhash Modi', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r876760675-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'BRILLIANT VEGETARIAN THAI FOOD WITH IMPRESSIVE SERVICE AT THAI CHI RESTAURANT,NEW STANLEY HOTEL', 'My Family had a wonderful dinner celebrating my wife\'s 75th. Birthday at the top class Thai Chi Restaurant thanks mainly to the The Management and Staff of New Stanley Hotel. Our special thanks go to the Thai Chef Ms. Nelius for preparing delicious  and heart winning Thai Vegetarian dishes . The food was simply brilliant and so was the impressive service by Ms. Maryanne Wambui. We enjoyed Thod Man koa Pd , Som Tam Thai Jee, PhadToa Makluw,Kao Phad Egg, Gang I ew jee and Chocolate Coconut Cake. The ambience and surrounding atmosphere was eye catching. According to us, Thai Chi is one of the best and the finest Thai  Restaurants in East Africa. We look forward to visit this top class Thai Restaurant again in future.  Great Value for Money.                             Subhash Modi - Former International Cricket Umpire..', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1711, 'Scarlets M', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r861518286-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Best Nairobi Hotel', 'Wild Race Africa Safari booked us here and we loved the facility.\nThe rooms are so specious and the staffs are very friendly.\nWe like the thorns tree cafe a lot.\nI will definitely get back here in the near future.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(1712, 'Alicia R', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r854693861-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing dinner', 'It was the perfect restaurant for our first night honey moon. \nThe place is really beautiful, romantic and calm, with a real Tailand decoration, the attention is amazing, the waiter Alex was really kind, and after tree months living in Thailand I can say that they cook delicious Thailand food.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1713, 'Felipe P', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r846798720-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Bead food and service in Nairobi', 'Best food we had in Nairobi. Service is really excellent and out waiter Alex was amazing and super kind and attentive. 100 % recommended for anyone traveling to Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1714, 'Andrea Torres', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r845311245-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Delicious & amazing service', 'We had such a delicious meal, the waiter made such amazing recommendations, we had fantastic food, good wine, and a very friendly and attentive staff', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1715, 'AustralianHelen', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r844975186-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'What a huge disappointment', 'As a lover of Thai food, I was looking forward to eating at the Thai Chi. It was so disappointing.\n\nThe menu doesn\'t indicate what dishes are gluten free. So my friends and I ordered some dishes and the waitress said she would check with chef if they were suitable. It took 45 minutes for the waitress to come back and tell us that we couldn\'t have two of the dishes. We then choose alternatives. A beef Penang that only had chewy beef and no vegetables; a prawn dish and then a plate of boring, steamed vegetables as we we told we couldn\'t have sir fried vegetables. If this is the best Thai restaurant in Nairobi, I am sad for the rest.   \n\nThai cookery is really good for those who follow a gluten-free diet and so it is unforgiveable that this restaurant doesn\'t cater for us and the food was so poor.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1716, 'Kada C', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r833190769-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Good stuff', 'The food was excellent.. Favorite dish the duck, pork and chicken...Great service from Alex.\nLovely ambience...', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1717, 'Vulcainvgb', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r806191367-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Enfants non autoris√©s ??! ', 'Quelle d√©ception suite a une pr√©c√©dente exp√©rience il y a trois ans en couple nous avions d√©cid√© d\'y retourner avec nos enfants. Malheureusement les enfants de moins de 12 ans ( les notres on 8 et 10) ne sont pas autoris√©s apparemment dans ce \"fine dining restaurant\". Pourtant ce n\'√©tait pas la foule ce jour et je sais que certaines tables sont isol√©es dans des alc√¥ves.\nJe tiens a pr√©ciser que notre exp√©rience il y a trois ans √©tait absolument parfaite et que la nourriture y √©tait excellente. \nDommage noys ne reviendrons plus !', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(1718, 'yellowhaus', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r798072206-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Nice Thai place in business area', 'Went to have a drink and dinner after work.  The bar is very nice.  The restaurant an very good Thai food. Sadly due to the curfew we were the only people having dinner.  The staff was very nice and friendly. \n\nThe curry good and the appetizer very tasty.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(1719, 'Gituma', 'Kenyatta Avenue & Kimathi Street, Nairobi Kenya', 'Thai Chi Restaurant - The Stanley Hotel', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d1104866-r750874520-Thai_Chi_Restaurant_The_Stanley_Hotel-Nairobi.html', 'Great food and memorable experience', 'We went to this restaurant for a dinner on our second anniversary and it was a memorable experience.\nWhen we go there they had set up the table well with rose petals but we decided to eat sitting down. The service was excellent form our waiter Wilson who was always on hand and took very good care of us.\nThe starters were tasty in good portions and I enjoyed the corn fritters and chicken skewers. The main course of beef and particularly the tilapia was delicious with just the right amount of spice and sweet. These came served with Jasmine rice.\n\nThe desert and fruits were great too especially the friend ice cream\n\nAll in all a memorable night', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(1720, 'Kristine H', 'Silos Road Nyali, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'Tamarind Mombasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d1214217-r1037461548-Tamarind_Mombasa-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Amazing place and view', 'Very kind staff and very good food. Amazing view of the water and over to Mombasa Island. We had nachos, vegetarian sushi and Swahili lobster.', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(1721, 'Rachel S', 'Silos Road Nyali, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'Tamarind Mombasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d1214217-r1036942598-Tamarind_Mombasa-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'The perfect place to visit when in the coastal area.', 'The location is fantastic.Fish was very delicious ad fresh,the service was friendly ad very welcoming.\nI will definetly visit once more.', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
