(1779, 'Haider S', 'Kaunda Avenue Fidelity Insurance Building, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'MNKafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d3902895-r847447553-MNKafe-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Amazing', 'This is an amazing cafe. Absolutely brilliant. I\'ve tried everything on my return to Mombasa and this is literally the only place which has retained its high quality.  We visited on Friday night and we ordered the pousine chicken & fries, peri peri fries, chicken fritters, beef burgers, hot dog for my kids, karak chai and the waffles. Everything was super, all of us loved it ! Their waffles are hands down the best I have had in my life and I\'ve been to places like Milan, Vancouver, Sydney, Brussels and Paris. I say we\'re going back soon, very very soon !!!', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1780, 'Navigator04379778284', 'Kaunda Avenue Fidelity Insurance Building, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'MNKafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d3902895-r845702385-MNKafe-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'High tea', 'My wife and I had the newly introduced three tiered high tea at the cafe which runs from Thursday to Sunday 4-6 pm. There are various sweet and savory items for 2 persons that was well presented and delicious.There is a 48 hrs booking duration in order that all the ingredients are fresh and prepared to be served on the day/time you decide to go.\nDefinitely a place to go for high tea in Mombasa;highly recommended.\nRashid', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1781, 'Noah Schwarz', 'Kaunda Avenue Fidelity Insurance Building, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'MNKafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d3902895-r839879656-MNKafe-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'A mixture of Africa and Europe!', 'During my longer stay near Mombasa, I visited the caf√© several times because you get good food and delicious drinks for relatively reasonable prices (from a European point of view).\nThe caf√© is very centrally located and in an area where you feel very comfortable even on foot.\nHighly recommended!', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(1782, 'Franklin H', 'Kaunda Avenue Fidelity Insurance Building, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'MNKafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d3902895-r804656879-MNKafe-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Excellent Oasis in Mombasa', 'I had the falafel (very spicy), buffalo fries, rosemary chicken sandwich and an iced latte (excellent expresso, really enjoyed it!) Staff is professional, and prices are very reasonable for an upscale cafe. I will visit often when I am in Mombasa.', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
