(1789, 'Nia', 'Cement Road English Point Marina, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'The Deck Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d12592401-r661896953-The_Deck_Kenya-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Best Restaurant in English Point', 'Such great ambience! I had the chip and fish and I think it was probably the best I ever had. Be patient as food takes a little long but definitely worth the wait. Food is delicious. My friend ordered traditional Kenyan food and she also loved it.', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(1790, 'tjthefoodie', 'Cement Road English Point Marina, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'The Deck Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d12592401-r607847203-The_Deck_Kenya-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'STAY AWAY', 'My friend and I were looking for place to chill after dinner so we decided to give the place a go and have some coffee. First, it took some frantic waving (which was ignored) and actually going up to one of the waitstaff to get any service. Then, it took 45min to get our coffee (in a restaurant that had only one other customer)\nTo cap it all off- they brought one of the coffees in a dirty cup (dried coffee and lipstick stained!!!!) When we complained- the server brought us a sponge (the flat kind they use to wipe down tables that smelled pungent) and told me to \"wipe it\" with such a couldn\'t care less attitude that I felt really sorry for whoever had the misfortune of hiring him.\nNeedless to say- we did not drink that coffee (lord only knows the state of their kitchen if thats what they felt comfortable displaying to their customers) nor will we return. \nMy advice- give the place a wide berth and avoid it (unless you\'re ok with some food poisoning)', 1, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(1791, 'Sukesha D', 'Cement Road English Point Marina, Mombasa 80100 Kenya', 'The Deck Kenya', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d12592401-r530180382-The_Deck_Kenya-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'CHILLING ZONE', 'Fantastic place to spend your evenings and see sunsets and stars along with the varied skyline of mombasa city. Beautiful enviornment set out on the Deck overlooking the creek and the light house facing the Indian Ocean.  Varied seating available, with steps, and bean bags and tables and chairs as you enjoy coffee, bites, wine or shisha as the breeze blows back your hair', 4, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
