(2027, 'Pooja Khetia', 'Kipkenyo, Kenyatta St, Eldoret, Kenya', 'Sunjeel Palace Ltd', 'https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2sxeWEzVnZaalYzVkVSZlRWbENjVU5HTFU1cGFYYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x5351585f89b367ea!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOk1ya3VvZjV3VERfTVlCcUNGLU5paXc%7C0cbbLJnhFjZ%7C?hl=en', '', 'Sunjeel Restaurant in Eldoret is honestly one of the best dining experiences I‚Äôve ever had. From the moment you step in, the atmosphere is cozy, welcoming, and just perfect ‚Äî it feels like a hidden gem where every detail has been thoughtfully put together. What I absolutely love is how the kitchen is visible through a glass wall right as you walk in. You get to watch the chefs in action, making everything fresh, especially the naan being baked in the traditional naan oven. There‚Äôs something so satisfying about seeing your food being prepared with such skill and authenticity ‚Äî it just adds to the excitement and trust in the food.\nNow, let‚Äôs talk about the taste ‚Äî it‚Äôs truly five stars! Every dish is packed with bold, rich flavor, but the pousin chips are on another level. I ordered them with garlic sauce and pousin sauce, and I swear I was transported to another planet. The combination was out of this world ‚Äî crispy, spicy, tangy, and absolutely addictive. I genuinely cannot get enough. The portions are generous, and everything tastes so fresh and perfectly spiced.\nI‚Äôm honestly in love with this restaurant. From the food to the vibe to the open kitchen ‚Äî Sunjeel is a must-visit. ELDORET IS SO DAMN LUCKY TO HAVE IT!!!!!!!!!!!', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
