(2752, 'Kaufman Kigame', '1649 Mburu Gichua Road, Kenya', 'The Legacy Hotel & Conference Centre, Nakuru', 'https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xWUFFVdHFWbTlyTUVSRmNUSk9SRXBsTURSbllYYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xd43677865f089266!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlVPQUtqVm9rMERFcTJOREplMDRnYXc%7C0cme0eDxF4A%7C?hl=en', '', 'The Legacy Hotel & Conference Centre in Nakuru strikes a fine balance between elegance and comfort from the moment you step inside. Located on Maralal Road, it is well placed for both business travellers and tourists wanting proximity to the city‚Äôs highlights yet not far from nature.\n\nWelcome & Reception\nWhat stands out immediately is the warm, genuine welcome. Guests frequently comment on the reception staff‚Äôs friendliness and professionalism‚Äîhow they greet you, help with your luggage, explain options, and ensure you feel immediately at ease.  The front desk seems to go beyond just checking in: there‚Äôs a sense of being cared for, with staff attentive to your needs.\n\nService & Assistance\nThroughout one‚Äôs stay, the assistance provided is consistent. Whether assistance means guiding you to nearby sights, helping with room requests, or ensuring meals suit dietary preferences, the staff do well. Reviewers often note how prompt and helpful personnel are.  The restaurant service also gets praise‚Äînot just for the food, but for how service staff attend with courtesy and sometimes go the extra mile (special requests, setting up for events, etc.).\n\nFacilities & Ambience\nRooms are described as spacious, clean, and decently equipped. The fitness centre, conference halls, free parking, and lift amenities add to the overall comfort.  The hotel‚Äôs ambience is calm and polished despite being in a busy area, which helps guests relax.', 5, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
