(2764, 'THESILENTITCH HONESTY', 'Nakuru, Kenya', 'Pwani Flavor restaurant', 'https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pZMFlteE1VVjlJV2poS05EVm5ZVFJ6WlMxNFUwRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xfad842f95c994558!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjY0YmxMUV9IWjhKNDVnYTRzZS14U0E%7C0cf6MMvLIOz%7C?hl=en', '', 'If minus zero were an option, this place would already have it framed on the wall. In my personal experience, the food tasted exhausted, like it had done a few rounds before ever reaching my plate. The only diners who seemed satisfied were the flies, buzzing around like VIP regulars.\nMy stomach signed itself up for a demolition derby and I am still dealing with the wreckage. When I raised it, the response I got, which sounded like a ChatGPT auto-reply, was that they have ‚Äúnever had complaints.‚Äù Maybe that is true and I am just the unlucky pioneer, the first explorer planting a flag in Complaint Land.\nAs for service, I might as well have sent a fly to place my order and it would have done a better job.\nFor me, this was a mistake I will not repeat. If you want to test your luck or your health insurance, go ahead. Personally, I am tempted to invite the Health Minister here for lunch just so someone official can share the experience.', 1, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-09 12:44:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
