(3106, 'Angela M wangi', '58 Muthaiga Rd, Muthaiga', 'Royal 58 Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d32909468-r1032622750-Royal_58_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'Memorable Birthday Lunch at Royal 58', 'I went to Royal 58 Restaurant in Muthaiga for a birthday lunch with a friend, and it turned out to be such a special experience. The restaurant itself is classy and elegant, with a warm and welcoming atmosphere. The food was absolutely delicious ‚Äî every dish was beautifully prepared and full of flavor.\n\nWhat really touched me was the surprise from the team: they brought out a small dessert with Happy Birthday and even provided a lovely photo frame to take pictures with. It was such a thoughtful gesture that made the day unforgettable.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-10 19:07:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3107, 'Gladys', '58 Muthaiga Rd, Muthaiga', 'Royal 58 Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d32909468-r1031762532-Royal_58_Restaurant-Nairobi.html', 'We were informed that the hotel has a \'\'no birthdays\'\' policy', 'To begin with the positives, the venue itself is absolutely beautiful. Furthermore, our waiter, David, provided excellent service throughout our afternoon visit.\n\nHowever, beyond David‚Äôs attentiveness and the venue‚Äôs aesthetics, the overall experience was a series of significant letdowns. To start, I had to follow up with the front desk multiple times just to secure a reservation. I was eventually informed that a prepayment of 5,000 per guest was required, as they do not accept walk-ins. I complied and specifically requested that a particular table be reserved, as I was hosting a birthday lunch. Yet, when my guests arrived, there was no reserved table, and they were told it was free seating.\n\nThe food, unfortunately, was remarkably bland‚Äîevery guest at our table immediately requested salt and pepper upon its arrival.\n\nThe most egregious issue, however, was the mishandling of my birthday celebration. As is customary in many restaurants, the live band sang \"Happy Birthday\" to guests at two other tables. Despite my friends‚Äô repeated requests, our table was completely ignored‚Äîeven though we were seated directly in front of the band (the closest table to the band). This blatant oversight wasn‚Äôt just rude‚Äîit was deeply embarrassing.\n\nWhen we brought this to the manager‚Äôs attention, we were met with a frustrating and disjointed series of excuses. First, he claimed the band must have simply forgotten. Then he said our request came too late because the band was already packing up‚Äîdespite our request being made before the second birthday celebration. He then attempted to distance the restaurant from the situation by claiming the band wasn‚Äôt part of their staff. Finally, he cited a supposed hotel ‚Äúpolicy‚Äù against birthday celebrations‚Äîa claim clearly contradicted by the earlier performances for other guests.\n\nWe confronted the manager, who‚Äîrather than offering a sincere apology or addressing the issue with his team‚Äîchose to deflect responsibility at every turn. It was only after we asked for the final bill and mentioned we‚Äôd be leaving an honest review that he rushed to the kitchen. Shortly afterward, the staff returned singing \"Happy Birthday\" and presented a compensatory slice of cake. Surprisingly, they also brought out a hotel-branded birthday photo booth frame‚Äîdespite their earlier insistence on a ‚Äúno birthday celebration‚Äù policy.\n\nWe chose to be polite to the staff, most of whom had not witnessed the earlier mistreatment. However, we still insisted on paying the bill, declined the belated gesture, and left them to enjoy their slice of cake. \n\nPerhaps they have a certain profile of guests they prefer to host.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-10 19:07:19', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
