(3494, 'roberteR6817SY', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r504944580-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'As good as it gets in Nakuru', 'I used to live in Kenya and shop for supplies in Gilani\'s and get a meal upstairs.  Although it is not what you would expect in Europe or the US, it is perfectly fine and a reasonable cost.  In particular, the bathrooms are reliably operational and they maintain a level of cleanliness that might be acceptable.  Not awesome, better than most you\'ll find except full \'tourist\' places.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(3495, 'WashBigs', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r486885770-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Good business meeting point', 'Has normal cafe setting with options of local and Indian cuisines. Prices are affordable and is located right next to a supermarket. \n\nHas unique pub and private meeting rooms. ', 3, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3496, 'Katherine C', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r480205552-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Popular upstairs cafeteria', 'Fast service, plenty of waiters and waitresses. Indian and Chinese on the menu are praised, but I haven\'t tried any of those dishes. \n', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3497, 'Dr Glen', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r463706633-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'good range of food with friendly service', 'Convenient and well located above the shops, has a good range of food with relatively prompt friendly service, especially from Naftalie (hope I spelt his name correctly). And there\'s always a tuk tuk at the door waiting to take you to the next place...', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3498, 'Jim V', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r459635225-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'An old standby', 'I\'ve been going to Gilani\'s Restaurant for over 30 years, and seen it through several decor and menu changes. It\'s basically good dependable food in an OK environment. Took a group there recently and preparation of food was exceptionally slow. One guest got her food (a steak) about 20 minutes before everyone else. The rest of us ordered various Indian choices: Prawns masala was OK but very small prawns; Matar paneer was nicely spiced, but paneer had been fried a bit too long and was a bit chewy. \nVery friendly staff as always. Place was clean and not very crowded for a Sunday afternoon. Same old cabbage salad starters they\'ve had for 30 years.\nSo, if you want predicability, and are willing to wait for it sometimes, Gilani\'s is the place to go. Reasonable prices as well!', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(3499, 'evalynek2015', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r458175511-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'wow!!!', 'nice place to visit.... good food, nice service and the location is findable!!! we always go there with my family when i visit home...', 5, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3500, 'KK', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r456663470-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Good food, very good service.', 'We came for lunch several times, and the food was always good. The Indian manager was very friendly and treated us like special guests. Compared to Java or KFC in Nakuru, gilanis is much cheaper with equal quality.', 5, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(3501, 'Sinza', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r455434281-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Simple but busy restaurant!', 'Located at city center, very busy, same building as a supermarket hosting it thus busy. The restaurant has two sides: one looks like gen pop and the other proper restaurant. The food was good....seems they focus in Indian dishes, service was great!', 3, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3502, 'Abdi M', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r445780857-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Nice food , disgusting bathroom ', 'My wife and first time  Kenya visitor, enjoyed her chicken Tikka.The food was delicious and very wait staff were very professional and service was great.The negative thing that was disappointing was horrible and filthy bathrooms. ', 3, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3503, 'Steve F', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r443028499-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'The Go To place in Nakuru for REAL Indian food', 'Given Nakurus long history with the Asian community (they built the Kenyan Railway and Nakuru was a major stop), it is surprising that there is not more good asian food but if you ask the locals and Nairobi Asians - they all recommend Gilani\'s.  We have found going on a Sunday we get more \"authentic\" Indian and given that you are usually surrounded by Asians, you know they must think its good too.\n\nWe often use it as a \"take away\" as we live about an hour away and often not all of the family make the trip to Nakuru. \n\nThe service is incredibly friendly and they treat you like Kings.', 5, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3504, 'Jill P', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r441500446-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Nice Indian food', 'Go up the stairs past the grocery store, past the bar, into the cafeteria and on the left you\'ll find a very nice Indian restaurant.  The staff were great and the food was good. Great option for vegetarians.  Worth a visit if you\'re in Nakuru.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(3505, 'YOTraveller', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r438203947-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Delicious Indian food', 'The restaurant is a bit hidden, but in an  elegant room and the food is delicious, at least the Indian cuisine! The staff is kind and the manager as well. We went with a local person and she recommend it as one of the best places with always fresh food.\nGreat experience ', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3506, 'uclatraveler9', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r438192272-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'decent place', 'We got food for takeaway here before going to Lake Nakuru.  They were able to do burgers, curries, samosas, and chips in individual takeaway containers. I had a veggie burger, which was pretty good.  It was Indian style and pretty spicy.  Every enjoyed their food, and they were kind enough to give us little packets of tomato sauce and salt.  \nConvenient if you\'re in town.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(3507, 'Ashly J', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r433111473-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Ashly Jacob', 'Gilani\'s s the place to go for Indian Food in Nakuru. Whenever myselfand family  passes through Nakuru, Its a must for us to dine at Gilani\'s.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3508, 'T8737HOchristianr', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r427901211-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'first time - last time', 'u dont necessarily get what you ordered. Food bad to middle, Drinks very bad. Restaurant is not worth the Prices. atmosphere is anything else than nice. like the Cafeteria from the Supermarket. Extra room extremely conservative and old fashioned. definitely a no go.', 1, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3509, 'Aaruna Aaruna', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r426468882-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Late Lunch', 'The place is cool and clean but the food stays too long before being served. The pub is just perfect and hook up place. Guys my girls love the place though... ', 5, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3510, 'Triple A', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r425801649-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Fabulous chicken curry and naan', 'Just what the doctor ordered.  Great curry, nice buttered naan, good service. Certainly a place to visit while in nakuru.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3511, 'AliC', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r416924579-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'excellent restaurant', 'The choice is extensive, the food is delicious, the portions are generous and the service is attentive.', 5, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(3512, 'Maggie C', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r411861587-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'good meal, cold drinks', 'went here for a work lunch. there are 2 restaurant areas - one open public one and a more private one (more expensive and different menu).  I had a good meal, buffet of fresh salads and bread roll are included in whatever you order.  it was a good central place for a work meeting in the middle of town.  not fancy but quite reasonable.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3513, 'kiamasimon', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r387499447-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'eating place in Nakuru town', 'very strategic located. ample parking for your car. warm welcome from their qualified  staff. very specious restaurant. a welcoming mango juice glass in the warm afternoon.\nvery fast wifi as i waited for the lunch to get ready. i enjoyed a freshness of nicely grilled chicken with fries. sweet and mild salad.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3514, 'Mwende Nyatuka', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r381597883-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'okay', 'Its an okay place.You may have to wait a little bit but the fried foods are good.Want to take the kids out for lunch in town,this is the place to go.The management could do better.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3515, 'Dennis O', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r380781185-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Overall good food', 'The atmosphere is meh. But the food is quite good for its value in money. They serve quick too. They have a bit of lag time over some evenings with many clients but that is to be expected', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3516, 'Peter B', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r359793441-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Erg lekker Indiaas eten', '√â√©n van de betere restaurants in Nakuru is zeker Gilani\'s. De Indiase keuken blijft mij altijd weer verassen. ', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[]'),
(3517, 'A T', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r355527544-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Gilanis - good value', 'Whenever I\'m in Kenya, I come here at least twice during my visits with friends. It\'s cheap for a \"muzungu\" (non African) and a nice treat for Kenyans who have a bit more money than your average local ie you wouldn\'t see locals who don\'t have good paying jobs in here, it would be too expensive. \n\nThe menu is a mix of Kenyan, Indian and Western food. An average selection of burgers, sandwiches, chicken, curries, hot chips, desserts are also available. But bear in mind, hot chips (or fries) in Africa just don\'t taste the same as in Western countries, and neither does the tomato sauce which is a weird looking fake red colour). The problem with the chips is the oil that they are cooked in probably hasn\'t been changed (fully) likely never, ok at a push maybe last year. To a westerner raised in Australia, New Zealand and the US, these chips just wouldn\'t rate at all. Most of us would chuck it out but can\'t because we\'re in Africa! But the chips aren\'t inedible. If you\'re really hungry and don\'t mind them being beyond greasy and not so flash looking, these are fine. But whatever you do, don\'t grumble about their hot chips or food, Africans love them, and there\'s plenty of hungry kids and adults alike outside on the pavement who may never had a chip in their life. \n\nBut I digress. Gilani\'s is situated above a supermarket by the same name. It is opposite to an entrance to one of the town\'s central clothing markets (ie it\'s not the only one). At the entrance to the building on the street level, you will be checked by a security guard waving an detector paddle over your body, and/or checking your bag/s - as is the case all over Kenya. Note: if you haven\'t noticed this already only female guards are permitted to check female visitors/patrons. It is a matter of decency. \n\nThere are some stairs to climb, and it will be a problem only if you\'re truly unfit. Once at the top, the open cafe/restaurant area looks like one of those lunch places from the 60s and 70s. It has lots of plastic covered tables and plastic chairs,with plastic covered menus. Not flash, but not horrible. The main thing is that it is clean and doesn\'t smell bad or anything like that. To the left is the entrance into the bar area and another entrance into the private dining area. I\'ve eaten in both the open dining area and the private area, whatever takes my fancy at the time. If I\'m feeling a bit grumpy I\'ll head into the private space. And when I say private, I mean that it\'s got cloths on the tables, the chairs are more comfy and I think the floor is carpeted, and you\'re not surrounded by lots and lots of people. In the open dining area, there isn\'t any carpet, and it\'s more of a casual affair. \n\nThe wait staff are always pleasant, much more pleasant than some of the other establishments I\'ve been to. They don\'t really lounge around which I always like, and seem to have a better sense of urgency than other places. Having said that - the food can at times take forever. This happens quite a lot. So if you have children with you and the food is running late, insist they bring out hot chips for the children quickly and make it clear it isn\'t an option. But bear in mind, the food may be running late because they\'ve had to send someone out to buy more supplies or the gas isn\'t working, or whatever. Their issues tend to take longer to fix than ours would, so have a heart and try not to get angry about it, and don\'t take it out on the wait staff. \n\nThere is a good selection of juices (although on menus around Kenya they say it is freshly squeezed, they are actually from a box), the Kenyan favourites tend to be Mango or Passion (pronounced \"pash-shon\") both of which are highly sweet but pleasant enough. Sodas, water, tea and coffee are also available. \n\nThe clientele seem to be a mix of travelling business men, office workers, students and boyfriend/girlfriends out on dates. It\'s safe in there, you\'ll have no problems with beggars coming in off the streets.\n\nThe cutlery and plates seem clean enough, I\'ve yet to see a dirty one. And the food comes in quite large portions, so if you\'re ordering chicken and chips, you\'ll probably have leftovers unless you like to eat a lot. Ask to take any left over food away. If you don\'t want it for yourself for later, then give it to one of the kids outside or one of the vendors selling their wares on the street (I always do this, so I\'ll ask for an extra plate so that I can put what I want to eat onto the second plate and eat from there so as not to put my germs onto whatever food I\'m giving away). \n\nDon\'t expect gluten free, vegan, low FODMAP, preservative or paleo to be catered for. They have no idea what that is. It is your responsibility to check the menu and figure out what you can have. \n\nI like coming here not only because the food is a good price, but because I feel I can relax in here especially in the private area - it\'s a great place to catch up with my friends. Everyone just minds their own business.  \nFor myself and one extra person, I\'d pay around 1,200 - 2,000 ksh, and this includes drinks, but it also depends on what we order. I\'m a vegetarian and I find I\'m easily catered for.\n\nAlthough I do caution the drinkers, if normally hot chips and burgers are your go to when you have a bad hangover, then just order water, fruit and juice if you can manage it. The burgers and chips are too greasy for your queasy tummy.\n\nNote: I have been coming to Gilanis since 2013. I come in either for lunch or dinner, and I\'ve never been sick from the food. I\'ve rated it mid-range food but note it is considered pretty good in Kenya. I wouldn\'t go near a restaurant like this back home, but it\'s great for what it is.', 3, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3518, 'Nathan R', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r347351368-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Good food, waited too long, needs a facelift', 'Had a good lunch today. The naan was excellent! Chicken curry, roast chicken, and chicken fingers were all good. The veggie pizza was OK. Had to wait over 30 minutes for the meal. Tables need to be redone without twisted, warped wood.', 3, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(3519, 'Alf M', 'Club Road Gilanis Supermarket Building', 'Gilani\'s', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d8012579-r316988096-Gilani_s-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Great supermarket', 'Excellent value and variety supermarket.\n\nStaff offer good service and seem to know their products.\n\nEverything from dry foods, meat, hardware, furniture and even fireworks and cold drinks.\n\nSituated right in the middle of the bustling city of Nakuru.\n\nBe careful crossing the road as you leave & enter the front door as it is hectic.\n\nReasonable prices', 5, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:52:51', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
