(3532, 'Tony C', 'Kenyatta Avenue', 'Merica Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d2416748-r679057650-Merica_Hotel_Restaurant-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Merica- sad and tired with dreadful service', 'The rooms have always been overpriced and utilitarian the one saving grace has been the pool and it‚Äôs environs. It‚Äôs pretty, it‚Äôs well landscaped too; but, the service is absolutely dreadful. You sit and wait to be noticed by the staff engaging in their own conversations, nobody seems to know what the bar stocks or the menu means. Getting a refill involves the same hand waving and calling out you did for the first drink, it‚Äôs almost as if they don‚Äôt want your custom. I‚Äôd like to say it‚Äôs gotten better but sadly no, it is a nice pool and if my friends did not like to swim here I would never enter this place again. But I‚Äôm wiser now, I eat somewhere else and only have the patience to stay for one drink to meet my friends. They all complain about the service but until another nice pool arrives in Nakuru they don‚Äôt feel they have an option.', 1, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:57:19', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3533, 'ronjey', 'Kenyatta Avenue', 'Merica Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d2416748-r672725739-Merica_Hotel_Restaurant-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'cool vibes', 'Merica is the place you go to for dinner and wine before a night out, or for a polite evening without too much party commotion.\nThey have a bar, lobby, rooms, patios and all amenities of a good hotel.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:57:19', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3534, 'PastorT3', 'Kenyatta Avenue', 'Merica Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d2416748-r655838006-Merica_Hotel_Restaurant-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Home Away from America', 'In February 2019 I made my way to Nakuru-Kenya. I was taken to the Merica Hotel. Upon entering this facility I felt the warm of the staff of Miriam  and Joseph at the front desk, the contemporary look of the bedrooms with doors bells ,  the beautiful clean pool, and the food including pizzas made we feel at home. I had a chance to meet the General Manager of the Merica Hotel on several occasions, Mr. Joseph Ndunda. He made me feel at home. This facility has a barber shop, spa and a gym.Thanks to Steve in the barbershop for the two haircuts, other staff Ronah and David. Waiting to return with a smile.', 5, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:57:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3535, 'EKamaara', 'Kenyatta Avenue', 'Merica Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d2416748-r650017494-Merica_Hotel_Restaurant-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Good location with fresh food', 'The location is great if you have business right in town or if you want to do business in the hotel. But they could improve on service. ', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:57:19', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3536, 'Githugo', 'Kenyatta Avenue', 'Merica Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g1015946-d2416748-r647512804-Merica_Hotel_Restaurant-Nakuru_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'SERENE ENVIRONMENT FOR WORKSHOPS AND CONFERENCES', 'I was one of the organizers of a small conference at this hotel in October 2018 and all i can say is that it was a very enjoyable experience. The meeting rooms are comfortable, with natural daylight and tastefully decorated. They have a plentiful supply of charging sockets, comfortable chairs and tables for delegates. Quality coffee, tea and food. I would recommend the hotel as a very good conference venue.', 4, 'Nakuru', '2025-11-10 19:57:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
