(3738, 'EKamaara', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r612381319-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Relaxing ambience', 'I didnt know that this hotel in in Eldoret town until our daughter took me to The Well Irish Pub and Restaurant last weekend.  The hotel has a relaxing ambience and great food. Try their pork chops  or whole fish! Delicious!', 4, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3739, 'jamesghennessy', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r590667787-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Excellent experience', 'I have visited both the Well in Eldoret town and the new one in Rupas Mall and in both places thoroughly enjoyed myself.The menu is varied and the food excellent. It is also very reasonable. The selection of beers is very impressive and considering there are so many foreign beers the prices are again very reasonable.\nThe staff are very friendly and really courteous. \nIf you like sport this is an excellent location as they don\'t just show football. When I was there two screens were showing rugby. The music is varied and not too loud. You can still have a conversation. One of the best pub(s) I\'ve been to in Kenya. Would highly recommend both establishments.', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3740, 'kimathi007', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r589088961-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Felt like I was in Ireland', 'Great Ambience. Good food and drinks. A bit slow in customer service but it\'s worth the wait. Great service though. Definitely going back there more than once\n Cheers', 4, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3741, 'Sergoit2016', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r567214950-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Great bar and restaurant', 'Topclass place. High class finish to furnishings and facilities. Great food and drinks. Lots of tv for sports and great staff too', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3742, 'gregory k', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r564356348-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Slow', 'The staff are slow and unresponsive. I was seated for at least fifteen minutes without any member of staff attending to me', 3, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(3743, 'Victor K', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r550166325-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Ambiance', 'Located in the heart of eldoret town. A nice restaurant for having dinner with your family and friends. It is also perfect for dates, trust me. \nThe staff are clean, friendly and welcoming.\nFood is very delicious, you have to wait about 20 mins for the food to be prepared. \n\nHave your meal with soft rock music in the background. \nThere is also a bar where you have various drinks from beers to whiskys.', 4, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3744, 'Jerry Y', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r548026104-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Ambiance & Class', 'I have a had chance of dining at so many esteemed restaurants, but I must say at this particular eatery, I have been able to get out the best in terms of the Food. I love their food, well cooked plus their culinary skills are out of this world. In terms of music, it is calm and soothing no unnecessary, loud banging music. It is my favorite hangout in Eldoret, Uasin Gishu County, Kenya. I highly recommend, that anyone who visits Eldoret Town should make a point to pay them a visit.', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3745, 'Cynthia M', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r547888841-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Amazing ', 'Great service. Good food. Way too awesome music and ambience. Attended an event here recently and really enjoyed myself. It has surpassed my expectation of an Irish Pub... home away from home', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3746, 'ANGELA M', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r545826160-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'üòÅüòÅüòÅüëåüèΩüëåüèΩ', 'Really cool place to hang out.. good food affordable price. The pub atmosphere was very inviting with a very friendly bartender. I‚Äôll definitely be here again and again.', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3747, 'KimberlyShemi', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r545823911-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'EVERYDAY!!', 'Great ambience.Music üíØ service üíØ foodüíØ drinksüíØ Eldoret this is the place to be.Anyday everydayüñíüñí', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3748, 'Allan B', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r544406094-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'All Day Everyday ', 'As I entered the place I was welcomed by a magnificent setting  and a delightful marriage of ambience and the luxuries of modernity. The place offered comfortable bar sitting area  as well a cosy lounge with aged leather chairs and dazzling art pieces displayed on the walls. The menu offered a wide variety of mouth watering starters. The meal was well prepared, served on time and was extremely delicious and the dessert was to die for... The service was commendable and welcoming as we exchanged pleasantries all the while. I had a pleasant dining experience with food of the most exquisite flavours. The choice of music really captivated me as well as the personalized client service. For this reason I recommend The Well Irish Pub and Restaurant as my most preferred pub and restaurant in Eldoret, Kenya.', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"delivery_takeout\", \"events_entertainment\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3749, 'Zack A', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r541607567-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Visit', 'Nice place with cool ambiet music....very favourable for conversation/chat....nice service, tasty meals and wide variety of drinks, ', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3750, 'Lisa D', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r516387337-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Absolutely Terrible.', 'Booked a tabke for 13 people. Arriving at 1930. We were all pretty hungry, and ordered pretty quickly after sitting down.  Two hours later we were still waiting for our meals! We questioned the staff. Eventually some of the food arrived.  Not even hot.  Not to mention nothing like the menu description.  We questioned the staff multiple times, and some of our food didn\'t even arrive.   We had enough of waiting. \nWe were practically the on table in the place. Awful experience.', 2, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3751, 'Zana G', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r507271941-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'NIce music, great ambience', 'ambience is great, music is awesome but needs to improve on variety of drinks and bar waiter needs to be customer frienly', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3752, 'Kblessing254', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r471586290-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Anytime, All time ', 'The best of the best if you need good food, music, ambience and drinks. I will not hesitate to recommend anyone ', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3753, 'simongoveyausuk', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r464532264-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'The Well Irish Pub', 'Well  I went there for lunch today. There is no parking and it is not easy to find. I ordered a simple dish which took nearly an hour which was far too long and was nearly cold. Despite these things I can see that this place would be fun. A good sports pub and good music. I will return for a fun night out but not to eat.', 3, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3754, 'Isaac D', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r448795671-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Just food ', 'We waited a long time to get cold food. And the waitress mixed up our order. The location is a bit hard to find, but would probably be a nice place to watch sports.', 2, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3755, 'skhimasia', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r443016505-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Nice food and atmosphere ', 'Stopped over for a bite. Nice bar/ lounge where the music is not too loud. Food is surprisingly good. Had a pizza which was a good size and flavour, the coconut chicken which is unusual but very good and the Irish stew which again is amazing. The atmosphere is slightly dark but pleasant. The staff are nice and they have a great drinks menu with cocktails. ', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3756, 'Madsope', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r439772025-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Prima bar, veel ruimte en veel keus', 'Een behoorlijke drank lijst en alles voor een goede prijs. Toen ik er was was het wat leegjes maar het is echt een goede plek voor wat drankjes.', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[]'),
(3757, 'uclatraveler9', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r438188444-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'So fun!', 'We came here to watch some soccer and have some food and drinks on a mid-week evening.  The place was packed!  Luckily we were able to find some space at the bar.  We had so much fun!  We definitely did not expect to find such a lively pub in Eldoret.  What I especially loved was that it was mostly locals.  They have an excellent selection of beer from all over the world.  I was happy because they had Nile Special from Uganda :)  Some of my colleagues ordered food, and everything was good.  They got lamb stew, fish and chips, and some really yummy smothered chips- thing.  The only thing we didn\'t really care for was the carrot-ginger soup, as it was very bland.  We would recommend everything else, though, and the prices were good!  They accept credit cards.  The only negative is that it was pretty smoky inside.\n\nIt\'s a bit hard to find.  If you see the signs for medical office, don\'t get thrown off!  The Well is on one of the upper floors.', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3758, 'Kevin L', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r429012312-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Nice place to drink again!', 'I enjoyed the Music over there. Wifi and drinks not bad. There food is also ok. Forgot to add that there KEG is the best in town.', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3759, 'Foxychiri88', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r417082082-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Delightful', 'Very tasty fish & chips, adequate food portions! Great service and fairly good ambience. Decent place to watch sports over a drink. Definitely coming back next time I\'m in Eldoret.', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3760, 'Brian K', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r393863283-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'HOME', 'Awesome service, Awesome ambience, the cocktails are amazing,What can I say about Wells apart from THAT\'S HOME AWAY FROM HOME!!!!!!!', 5, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3761, 'Winter c', 'Cheruiyot Street Saito Centre 1st Floor', 'The Well Irish Pub & Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g681265-d3675400-r389684682-The_Well_Irish_Pub_Restaurant-Eldoret_Rift_Valley_Province.html', 'Classy bar and restaurant', 'A cool Irish bar and restaurant to enjoy a drink with friends over a football match. It can also be a nice place to have dinner. The ambience is great!', 4, 'Eldoret', '2025-11-10 20:12:54', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3762, 'Wombler', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r982845563-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good food and views, if you have plenty of time.', 'Great location at the lake victoria. It was not very busy, but for some reason everything took looooong time. Staff seemed confused they have visitors. Staff took long time to get the order for drinks. Then food order. Then food serving etc. Whole process took about 3 hours, which was for my taste too long for Lunch. \nPositive: Food was great, staff was friendly when they were around. \n\nYou need to pay for food separately from drinks and the membership fee. Don\'t understand why this can\'t be waived when you consume at their premise, but these are the rules. \n\nIf you look for good indian food on a nice setting and have plenty of time, this is certainly a possibility in Kisumu.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(3763, 'Khadija M. Awadh', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r981543933-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Kisumu Yatch club', 'My family and I were around for the weekend and sidelined to pass by for lunch. Beautiful set under scenery by the lake, privacy ensured by gazebo set up. Lunch was sima samaki greens and kachumbari. Soul food the Kisumu way....we enjoyed ourselves immensely. Looking forward to going back when I am next in Kisumu', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3764, 'Shemina S', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r941191661-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Kisumu yacht club', 'Great ambience .\nGreat food üòã üëå. Yummy fish and chicken \nGood service. Ample parking\nView of the lake, breezy.\nPocket friendly bar prices', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3765, 'Gary J', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r930952299-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great food & a great experience ', 'My family was invited to the yacht club by a family friend who is a member.  From the time we arrived the staff was very attentive.  My wife and I ordered two of our favorite dishes, Chicken Kiev & Chicken Cordon Bleu which we shared.  The food was outstanding!  We had a wonderful time with our friends.  I definitely want to come back here again.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(3766, 'Tom D', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r885929769-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice but pricey if not a member', 'First, if you are not a member, you pay 750 kes just to enter the property.  The food was good, not the best in Kisumu, I rate it #2 for Indian. The atmosphere is the best in Kisumu. The 8 or so ramadas are very nice and right at the waters edge of Lake Victoria. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3767, 'jarednyangira59', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r778444268-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The best refreshment site', 'No proper words to describe the excellent services I received here, I would recommend it to friend any time any day.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"overall_experience\"]'),
(3768, 'Kenneth Skovgaard', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r745719906-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Okay..', 'It was a nice place, nothing out of the ordinary except the view over the lake, that is Beautiful especially during the sunset.. You have to pay for a membership at least to use the restaurant, but the food was then cheaper then I see many other places..', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3769, 'Triple A', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r707815936-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Unwind while in Kisumu', 'The Yatch Club is a great place to unwind after a tough week or day in Kisumu .  Had dinner at the Club with friends after a tough day out on a project.  The food was finger licking, the service from Baraza and Ouma was warm and the ambiance was just right for conversation and laughter late into the night, while enjoying the calming swash of the lake behind us. \nThere is a temporary membership fee of 500/- for non members which is well worth it.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3770, 'Jay A', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r695831982-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'lunch by the lake', 'if you are not a club member, then you must pay 500ks temp membership fee in order to eat lunch. Tables are outside next to the lake, great ambiance. Restrooms are clean, food is good. They say that they don\'t take credit cards, but they will if you negotiate ahead of time for this bonus service. MPesa is preferred and very easy.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3771, 'Jacqueline J', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r693646964-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Wonderful Views of the Lake', 'The Kisumu Yacht Club is a Members Only Club that grants day membership to non-members for 500KES. The lawns are well maintained, they have gazebos right by the lake side and they have a play area for the children. The service was so-so because the staff struggled to communicate to us about the food and to answer our questions. \n\nMy friend ordered a Magherita Pizza and I ordered a Chicken and Sweet Corn soup. The soup was tasty with a bit of a kick from the Tabasco Sauce but the use of brown coriander leaves as garnish was not appreciated. The Margherita pizza was quite dry and lacked the gooey goodness that comes with mozzarella cheese. Sightings of hippos and my friend\'s child catching a fish was delightful though.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3772, 'WMLth', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r682624477-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'So Relaxing ', 'Dropped by just after walking around the Wildlife Park and across to Hippo Point. I was the only customer and was happy to pay the KES500 temporary membership fee if only to relax in the garden area overlooking Lake Victoria. A 500ml cold Tusker was an affordable KES 200. The menu is reasonably extensive with very moderate prices. I believe cash only and the bar and restaurant have a separate billing system. I certainly would return and recommend to one and all. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3773, 'Mwenje123', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r673750248-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Awesomeness', 'A good place,nice environment the gazebos next to the lake just breath taking.good get away for the whole family anytime', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3774, 'crookhamcommon', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r671905477-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Members only ....', '... but a day-membership can be bought for 500KES. Excellent coffee in elegant lake-side grounds. A five minute taxi-ride from downtown but very peaceful.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3775, 'Lisa F', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r654998772-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lovely, but bring cash!', 'I stopped here for a glass of wine and, I hoped dinner. Beautiful place. Staff were friendly and attentive. Menu looked great--but they are a cash-only place, (and I ATM) so I couldn\'t stay, alas. In this day and age, no credit cards accepted?', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3776, 'Paul C', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r648190865-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Very good food with stunning views', 'We visited the yacht club several times last week as guests of our family and we never got fed up with the views across the lake, the stunning sunsets and the lovely cool breeze.\n\nThe food was excellent, the butterfish and the chicken saag get special mentions.\n\nThe ice cold Tusker lager was brilliant and to cap it all, one night there were two hippos grazing in the garden, (I did see them before drinking, honest!).\n\nThat\'s something that you will never see in an English pub beer garden!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3777, 'Linda M', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r645437167-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Awesome lunch ', 'Was taken to lunch and the food was great . I‚Äôm dreaming about more and soon !! Quiet and peaceful with a nice view of the lake covered with water hyacinth . Beautiful !', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3778, 'sydneyannem', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r640308549-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lake Victoria ', 'The yacht club has the best location to food ratio. The food is very good, and you are sitting right on the edge of lake Victoria. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3779, 'Ngina M', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r639992363-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Menus Price different from billing price', 'This is a members only club, but can have day membership at kes 500.\nIt is right by the lakeside with a scenic view.\nHowever, the food takes way too long.\nThe fish price on the menue was kes 600 but when the bill came, it was at kes 1000. Upon enquiring we were informed the fish we were served was bigger than their usual serving hence the increase price. Ridiculous! How do you increase the price by over 50 percent and not inform clients in advance especially since we were ordering about 6. What if we had no money? The staff were nonchalant and unapologetic about the inconvinence.\nThe experience left a bitter taste. Honestly the stars are just for the view.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3780, 'michaelO3124AE', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r624141859-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Amazing Lake Side Site!', 'Great Indian food, and the view of the lake from here is stunning, really to die 4! Cover charge for non members. Take the tables/bandas outside great place to have lazy lunch, by the lake!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3781, '424abida', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r598311188-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lunch', 'Nice location with great views overlooking Lake Victoria. This venue offers open air seating and good service as well as great food. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3782, 'Byron78', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r588218568-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Catching the breeze.', 'Lots of work over the last few years,from cabro parking to immaculate lawns and bandas perched above the waters edge.The ambience is remarkable and the seating options make it even better,with a large terrace above the main bar being a wonderful setting.The views out over the lake are scenic and refreshing ,not to mention the breeze that reduces the Ksm heat.\n  The food was fresh and fairly quick though there were few tables around.Service was much improved and overall a lovely setting with delicious food.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3783, 'Carly K', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r584060253-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lovely sunset and views', 'We headed over from Kiboko Bay to the yacht club for dinner and sunset. The sunset and views were beautiful. Dinner was okay, although the butter chicken was quite disgusting and not like any butter chicken I have ever had .Staff were friendly and helpful. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(3784, 'Shawn G', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r568197661-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great spot but only downside is Cash or Mpesa only. ', 'Everything was fantastic here and I‚Äôd super rate this place well because the food and service was excellent but only taking cash or Mpesa in this day and age is not 5 stars worthy so giving it 4 stars only. Definitely go and bring oodles of cash though, it‚Äôs a great spot!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3785, 'Meera183', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r567653175-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Sunsets over Victoria', 'Breezy open place where you can enjoy a sun-downer and a good meal.\nThe best sunset views over Lake Victoria!\nKids can enjoy too..', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3786, 'wayne y', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r550591419-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Beautiful!!', 'This is a great place to enjoy the sunset over your evening meal.  The kitchen does not open until 6 or 630 for the evening meal.  There is a nice little play area for the children while you wait for your meal.  ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(3787, 'rosie313', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r532122777-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Poetry on Lake Victoria', 'Due to protests in Kisumu, our visit to do poetry in the city was canceled.  We ended up spending the afternoon at the Yacht Club doing poetry by the lake.  The food was excellent, the staff was very attentive and the view of Lake Victoria was amazing.  There were tons of dragonflies flitting about.  They didn\'t bother us and were quite a good addition to the grounds.  I can only imagine how beautiful this place would be at night.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3788, 'Abi M', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r500776962-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Ok experience', 'We ate here as a large group, and were rather disappointed with our experience. The service was slow, considering we were pretty much the only people in the restaurant.\n\nHaving now read previous reviews, it looks like Indian food is the better way to go. We had a mixture off the more typical western menu and it was just terrible. The pizzas were soggy, and the burgers disappointing. It is cheap but our food was almost inedible so not worth the trip.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3789, 'John S', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r479496378-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Quality Restaurant', 'A fine restaurant on the lake.  I like that the tables are on individual verandas over the lake.  There is a lot of privacy that way and a great view of the lake and the city.  It sits so that you can watch the sunset over the water.\n\nThe food that we got was good.  Indian food is the way to go here - I understand that they have a chef well-trained in Indian food.  The Afghan Chicken was a treat, as were several of the curry dishes like traditional chicken tikka masala and butter chicken.  The butter chicken especially was very good.  Naans are all good.  They also have more traditional Kenyan dishes.\n\nPrices are surprisingly good for such a nice restaurant - it\'s about the same as what you\'d pay at a comparable restaurant in town.  The view and beautiful grounds are bonus.  Pay Ksh500 per person to sit down, except on Wednesdays, when it\'s \"open\" night and you only pay Ksh100 per person.  We did notice that service was slow.  Probably dishes that are all cooked individually from scratch.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(3790, 'jthollywood', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r467183517-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Beautiful view...but that is about it', 'Well located for a beautiful view over the lake, especially at suset. Service was attentive, if a little slow, even though we were the only ones there. Food is very cheap, but absolutely terrible. On the plus side, it is fun to say you are a member of a yacht club! (just don\'t tell anyone it cost only Ksh500 and was only for he night...)', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3791, 'RazSunshine', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r451380981-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Business catchup', 'A good place to meet with people and talk business\nMembers and friends access\nLocated by the lake, quite, reclusive and established\nGood service, excellent staff and good food and drinks\n', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3792, 'Brian M', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r446702809-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Just amazing', 'What a lovely place to watch the sunset while having a cold beverage and a bite to eat.The view is just breath taking and you\'re simply drawn to always going back.The service is very welcoming right from the gate to the kitchen and bar.The food is a mixture of African,Indian and barbecue all in one depending on ones taste buds.An area that can accomodate functions,parties and kids facilities are also available.Try it you will love it.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3793, 'JANETACHAYO T', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r436603146-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'variety of menu offers with very friendly staff', 'the foods are mouth watering, very spacious and clean rooms with speedy wifi. the rates are relatively fair and very welcoming staffs.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3794, 'alkenya', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r389668361-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Food and Ambience > Service', 'We were a big group of people (around 20) having lunch at the Yacht Club. The scenery is amazing due to the lakeside location of the club. I have been here a number of times and nothing much seems to have changed over time (for better or for worse). The food is excellent - I would highly recommend the butter chicken and freshly made chapatis. The service, on the other hand, is terrible. I don\'t know where the waiters disappear to - it took us at least 15 minutes to locate a waiter to order our meal after he brought us our beverages. Another 10 or so minutes to locate him once again so we could order more chapatis... and it went on until like this until we paid the bill. I guess the food and the ambience make up for the lack of good service.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3795, 'VC009', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r385999317-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Beautiful lakeside eatery', 'One of the best kept secrets in Kisumu. Situated a short walk from impala park on well manicured gardens with overhanging bandas on the lake. Variety on the menu with poor service, but all this is forgiven due to the beauty of the place. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]');
INSERT INTO `restaurant_reviews` (`id`, `author_name`, `place_address`, `place_name`, `review_url`, `review_title`, `review_text`, `review_rating`, `location`, `created_at`, `predicted_sentiment`, `predicted_aspects`) VALUES
(3796, 'pooja02', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r385213868-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice place ', 'We went here regularly to have lunch and dinner and must say well maintained and this club is really good.\nMy young kids loved the place and went out on the lake which was also very good as seen some hippos as well.\nAlso visited the old harbour place and history was quite interested.\nLoved it as peaceful.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3797, 'Odhiambo O', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r369007206-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good sight', 'My wife and I visited this place for a refreshing weekend by the lake. And despite not being members we were allowed to access the premises and enjoy the services.  However, the restaurant from the way things were handled seemed poorly managed. The workers didn\'t seem motivated and the services we required or good food was not to the expected standards. But I would recommend the location and the lake view for those interested in those.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3798, 'rudyvoller', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r356076605-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nonexistent Yatching, eating and drinking only.', 'This is a members club Andover can get in by  paying $5 as temporary membership. The yatch club has an enviable location and we guessed with the number of bridal groups that it\'s a popular location for wedding photo shoot.\nThe food is average and not pricey, if you have a chance order the dhania chicken, it wasn\'t bad at all.\nThe biggest disappointment was that the toilets were locked for non members, where would we go.\nBeing called Yatch Club we thought that we would find substantial sporting activities on the lake, sadly this is just an ordinary eating and drinking joint.', 1, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3799, 'Dirk D', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r345161896-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Yacht club Kisumu', 'Gelegen aan het meer,maar alleen for members.Behalve op zondag dan mag iedereen er binnen.\nIk was er niet geweest maar dit als info voor jullie', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[]'),
(3800, 'Marco P', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r344803862-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'eigentlich ein toller platz, leider auf dem absteigenden ast', 'wir waren √ºber jahre immer gern dort. seit 2 jahren ist allerdings der eintritt erh√∂ht und die k√ºche klar schlechter geworden. ich habe mir beim essen vom fisch den magen f√ºr 4 tage verdorben. der kellner fragte, ob ich wirklich den fisch m√∂chte, ohne mir klar davon abzuraten. als ich beim n√§chsten besuch von dem eklatanten misstand berichtete, hat dies dort keinen interressiert! der ausblick ist toll und wenn sie h√§hnchen bestellen, sind sie sicher.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[]'),
(3801, 'MrsSimbaonsafari', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r337941195-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lunch with a view! ', 'Every year that we visit Kisumu, we definitely go have a meal at Yacht club. It\'s on Lake Victoria and very scenic. Sunsets are a must there! \n\nIt\'s good value for money and good vegetarian choices. I like the \"kawaida\" snack there. \n\nService can be quite slow so make sure you keep chasing them. \n', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3802, 'Heidi W', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r314698849-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'High Style!', 'A great place to visit for lunch or dinner! A beautiful view of Lake Victoris, with the occasional hippo grazing experience! Delicious service, bar, billiards, boating!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3803, 'mavrick63', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r283444485-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'BKM team were hosted by Kisumu Lions club for an elegant banquet', 'Excellent service combined with vibrant, fresh, selections of vegetarian and meat dishes expertly prepared and presented. The shore of Lake Victoria, the second largest freshwater lake in the world provides a soothing environment. Day memberships are available. Hippo sightings optional.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3804, 'Kyle M', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r257220100-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Wednesday sunset spot ', 'I went with a member, but here on Wednesdays anyone can go. Great spot to have a cold drink or some solid Indian food along the lake. Time it just right and the sunset will most definitely impress. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3805, 'Kari S', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r255727974-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'You should know....', 'As I sit in this beautiful lakeside location, awaiting the lunch that we have already ordered, I am met by the manager who informs me that there is a cover fee for non members... 500 shillings.... EACH!!!!!\n\nFirst we spoke with the guard as we came in, then we were met at our car and escorted to a table, then not one, but two very courteous waiters stood table side for the twenty minutes as we relaxed and paroosed the menu. \n\nAFTER we ordered drinks and received them, AFTER we ordered our lunch... THEN we were informed of this cover fee.  No signage at the gate, no signage as we were escorted in, nothing mentioned on the menu and nothing spoken. \n\nSo, I asked the manager who after I said, \"No thank you, we will leave\", she \'graciously\' reduced the cover charge to 100 shillings.  With GREAT reluctance and only because we are visiting Kisumu with guests... And we are hungry.... We are staying.  But this VERY POOR and most unhospitable action, which if ONLY presented upon arrival could have been a game changer... Has convinced me that... I WILL NOT BE BACK!!!', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3806, 'Mohamed K', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r250295043-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lunch by the lake. ', 'Had a business lunch here. The most amazing part is the cool breeze from the lake accompanied by the calming and relaxing sound of the water splashing against your Banda. The environment is very clean. Their menu is numbered from 1 and goes to 100\'s so they practically have all sorts of dishes. Give the poussin fish a try. Make sure to have your meal quickly as the breeze from the lake cools down your food in no time. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3807, 'Irene-van-Laarhoven', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r232188171-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'wonderful view and breeze', 'great view, nice bhajia\'s friendly service and a laidback atmosphere. We go here regularly and have not been disappointed', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3808, 'hnyamori', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r227888832-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Beautiful views, but just that!', 'Beautiful views of the lake Victoria (when it\'s not covered with hyacinth), magical sunsets and refreshing breeze. Apart from the bar area, it\'s generally dull, the food terrible and service wanting. Then there are these ugly, injured cats (need treatment or putting down) that won\'t stop begging for scraps', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3809, 'Helen L', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r205695892-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Beautiful but boring', 'We read about the yacht club and decided to visit after enjoying the sunset at hippo point.\nThe 500 shilling \"temporary membership\" fee was very steep\nalthough the grounds are really beautiful.\nThe atmosphere was non existent although it was early, but by 9 pm it was still only us and 2 other people !\nThe food was plentiful, in fact, far too much and of mediocre quality.\nWe enjoyed the tandoori mushrooms as a starter, but the pork chops were bad quality meat to start with and then overcooked and served tepid. The potato bahji were yummy ! and the mixed vegetable curry was okay. The rice and naan were fine.\nService was very friendly although food took for ever to arrive.\nThis would be a lovely place to spend a weekend afternoon, enjoying the surroundings and the view having a couple of drinks and some snacks.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3810, 'JAYANTH87', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r196022319-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice place to spend a evening', 'It is one of the best places to spend your evening. This is a members club and it houses the most affluent customers in Kisumu. The place is calm and you could thoroughly enjoy the dinner with your family while always enjoying the scenic view of Lake Victoria.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3811, 'Wa Ritho', 'Harambee Road', 'Kisumu Yacht Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214126-r188968337-Kisumu_Yacht_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'December 2013', 'They have redone it  and now you get to sit in fairly ok bands that are right over the lake edge. the lawn is good. The view, especially the sunset is magical. Food takes forever to come. it is ok - you will not get sick but nothing to write home about. The road there is appalling. has a good place to sit and enjoy the evening - one of the best in Kisumu.', 1, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:18:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3812, 'WAH711', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r997992692-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Methi chicken', 'Great location for dinner. Outstanding helpful staff. My Methi chicken was very generous in size and good if I had wanted butter chicken. The chef must have been short of fenugreek. I wish he had been honest instead of serving something which was not what I ordered!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:37', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(3813, 'Kjell', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r952009955-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lovely place', 'Lovely place, friendly staff, delicious food and Great views.\nWe had a lovely time at Accacia and their rooftoprestaurant with a pool.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:37', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3814, 'Wamukhula', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r915934454-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Losing its previous standards', 'Check in was nice and easy. When I got to my room, I called room service to order a cup of tea. No one picked the room service line and I had to redial again and again before it was picked.  It then took a whole hour for me to get the tea.   The shower did not have hot water.  It\'s disappointing that  the standards at this hotel are going down.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:37', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
