(3850, 'KenyanStarfish', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r437408893-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great food, Good Ambiance in the middle of Kisumu Hotel', 'Acacia hotel is relatively new in Kisumu and is located in the centre of the city. The pool side dinning area is on the second/ third floor and has a great deck. The food is very well prepared, and the staff could do with a bit more training in responding to customers. A word of advice: At night there are a lot of mosquitoes and other insects because the seating area is outside. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3851, 'AdhiamboC', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r436396001-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Kisumu\'s finest', 'I love Acacia. I love the hospitality that the hotel gives, the way in which the staff know and welcome me every time I\'m there - from the doorman to the waiters to the front office manager, the chef - they strive to ensure I feel welcome when I stay there. \nThe rooms are great, spacious and well decorated. Food is really good. Service is personalized. The pool and gym facilities are awesome. \nYou wouldn\'t regret staying at Acacia. \n', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3852, 'Winifred A', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r429095949-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Jewel of Kisumu', 'Totally impressed with the effort that went into creating this masterpiece. Bedrooms are FIRST CLASS. However, they need to expand their menu to cater to different tastes. ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"menu_variety\"]'),
(3853, 'WattaOnTheGo', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r412869349-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'A weekend at Acacia Premier', 'My brother and I recently took a flight down to Kisumu and chose to stay at Acacia Premier because it suited our needs on this particular trip. I had a brief chat with the concierge who after finding out what our interests were, came up with a fantastic itinerary to ensure we didn‚Äôt miss out on any wonders the lakeside had to offer. They even had hotel transfers complete with a chauffeur hence we wouldn‚Äôt have to worry about getting around town.\n\nWe stayed at the Bay Suite on the fourth level. It has a bedroom, dining area and living room along with the usual trappings of 5 star hotels. Walking out onto the balcony, we were treated to an unmarred view of a slice of the city as well as the magnificent Lake Victoria further beyond. After a short workout at the gym followed by a one-hour classic massage at the treatment room, I was ready to take on the city!\nFood is always such an integral part of any hotel for me and the menus didn\'t dissapoint. I chatted up the barista at the coffee lounge on the ground floor as he fixed me a cup while I marveled at his latte art. We had daiquiris at Aqua Pool Bar & Grill and toasted to good health while watching the stunning sunset! For supper, we tucked into butter naan and lamb Rogan Josh- settling for Indian despite the Pan Asian, Italian and African options available. Over all great experience. \n\n', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3854, 'daniellenijsten', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r409866098-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Very good food centrally located in Kisumu', 'Very good restaurant with wide range of dishes. Many Indian and Italian dishes but also local tilapia. From European perspective the place is very cheap as a main course wil cost you around 9 euros. Services could from time to time be better as they do not always pay close attention.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3855, 'Gregory O', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r405964936-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Business Luxury', 'Right in the city, and conveniently situated for other amenities. Just the right place for business travel accommodation. Don\'t go without a deep pocket.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(3856, 'Cleo8101', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r398666132-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Fabulous', 'Have had a meal here and the preparation was excellent, the waiting staff was also nice. Ask to sit at the swimming pool area at the edge to enjoy wonderful views of Kisumu city', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3857, 'kenolly2016', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r389235203-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Very good', 'Very well organized good staffs but not friendly they look like they are a fraid of their work am looking forward to see some changes to this ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(3858, 'VC009', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r385998043-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'new establishment thats already loosing character', 'Went there for a meal to join guests who were staying there. Disinterested wait staff and slow service messed my experience. The guests also complained of poor and overpriced stay.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3859, 'r0dneylc', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r384149917-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good food and wine', 'Both the main restaurant and the rooftop grill offer full menus of reasonably-priced and very good food.  The view from the rooftop is quite nice as well.  The wine here is definitely the best in town BUT alcoholic beverages are quite pricey by local standards.  The service is also excellent!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3860, 'Odhiambo O', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r369008102-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good and wonderful', 'Acacia premier offers exemplary services in the heart of Kisumu. It\'s a world class with regard to its rooms and restaurants both at the rooftop and those located inside. I would highly recommend for those visiting Kisumu and are interested in excellent conditions. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"overall_experience\"]'),
(3861, 'Fred O', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Acacia Premier Hotel, West End Mall Next To The Central Bank Of Kenya', 'Acacia', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d8537654-r366482283-Acacia-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'NGO', 'Wonderful lovely and friendly staff  from the recption room service and dinning.... one of the staff called Dada was  excellent. Keep it up', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:24:38', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(3862, 'Dyan Kola', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r972985816-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lake view ', 'Dunga Hill Camp is situated at the shores of Lake Victoria.It a Serene location good for spending the weekend.Its suitable for the whole family.You can enjoy the great taste of food and drinks,take a boat ride or listen to the live band that plays especially in the afternoon.Its easily accessible from the CBD by Tuk Tuk,boda Boda or private means of transportation.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3863, 'KeduKudzi', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r889867302-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Pleasant!', 'Very pleasant and natural place to hang out with friends or solo, enjoy drinks and food and watch the sunset. Lake views are fabulous', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3864, 'Mary-jane B', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r886888574-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Pleasant.... ', 'Pleasant with nice views of the lake. Bit basic with limited food and drinks. But staff try and breeze plus views good.. ', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3865, 'Francois L', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r877439409-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Hugely pleasant place, but only to be visited in the evening', 'We arrived around 10:30 am for a brunch. Most of the staff was obviously barely waking up. We had our first piece of food at 12:30.\nThat being said, the place is uniquely set with 180¬∞ view at lake Victoria. Best go there early evening and enjoy the sunset.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3866, 'Byron78', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r843206895-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lakeside breeze', 'Much developed. Huge stage. Various music genres across the weekend. Service and food has improved. Secure parking. Sufficient seating.Boat rides. Amazing views right on the lake.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3867, 'Great Horizon Trails', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r768732385-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'A glimpse of the sunset', 'Offers the best opportunity to capture the glimpse of the sunset due to its location on the shores of Lake Victoria. It  is set to change the unwinding objectives in Kisumu City', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(3868, 'Pauline O', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r749409455-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'It is an amazing place. excellent to go in the afternoon and stay there until the sunset', 'The place is rustic, nothing fancy, but cool and relaxing. Enjoying a sunset there is a unique experience. It is breathtaking. Not only tourists go there. It is also full of locals. If you have the chance to go there do not hesitate and do it. It is also close from downtown.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3869, 'Jacqueline J', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r745166103-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Relaxing Place... Meh Food', 'We went for Valentines day lunch because it was on the Trip Advisor list of romantic places in Kisumu but there was no valentine funfare. The layout is really nice, I love how the tables were strategically placed under the trees for shade. The lovely views of the lake make you feel so relaxed and at peace. We had wet fry pork with bhajia and a burger with bacon and cheese with garlic fries. The Wet fry pork was in a sweet tomato sauce, but there were too many bones. The bhajia was a bit bland but the accompanying sauce was a delight. At first instance, I couldn\'t see the bacon in the burger so I asked the waitress to confirm if it was really there. Turns out there were some small pieces of bacon in there but because they were minuscule, they did not deliver the flavour you would expect bacon to lend to a burger and the beef patty was lacking in flavour and it was a bit chewy. The garlic fries were okay though my date was disappointed in them.\n\n Would I try it again? Yes, for the ambience and I hope next time the food will redeem the place.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3870, 'Fekuchand', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r717550947-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lakeside best ', 'Great place to spend your idle day in Kisumu,  the booze is pocket friendly,  the food is passable but the view and ambiance is superb.  Great Value for Money,  until something better comes up.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]');
INSERT INTO `restaurant_reviews` (`id`, `author_name`, `place_address`, `place_name`, `review_url`, `review_title`, `review_text`, `review_rating`, `location`, `created_at`, `predicted_sentiment`, `predicted_aspects`) VALUES
(3871, 'Canny Trekkers', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r710581624-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Food overpriced ', 'I had the crumbed fish, it was really good and fresh, I asked what does it come with? They said NOTHING so I ordered masala chips which came out cold so we didn‚Äôt touch them.\nMy husband ordered a burger which was fine, again comes with NOTHING.\nEven a slither of something might have made us less pissed off.\nWe went for the entertainment which started at 5 pm and it was meant to start at 3.30. After a heavy rain after the first song the music was abandoned and we left.\n\nDunga Hill Camp needs to go to hospitality school!\n', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3872, 'Thomson74', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r703527865-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Peaceful Afternoon', 'We had lunch here on a Sunday afternoon. It was lovely and peaceful with stunning views of Lake Victoria. The food was good value and the service was reasonably quick. The staff seemed friendly and helpful. Would recommend a visit if you are in the area.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3873, 'PNMO', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r695429728-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Very slow service', 'Was there on Monday 28th July 2019 and the view is pleasant for an outdoor experience, but the food ordered took too long on a Monday, yet there were few people at the place.  The waiter had told us it would take half an hour, but it took over more than an hour.  And one plate ordered arrived 15 minutes much later after the other food.  We had almost forgotten about it.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3874, 'Samwel Owino J', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r657107939-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best sundowner', 'Best sun set view sitting on the rocks closer to the lake shore. Fanta stick place for birding with the papyrus swamp adjacent to it. The management should improve on waste disposal.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3875, 'Jonas O', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r654154760-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Camping on the shore of Lake Victoria ', 'This is a wonderful place run by friendly and welcoming people. Simple camping for just 500 KSh, with a cool restaurant and bar. There was no reason to leave, but since I was there all day the owner suggested a nice 1km walk to the fishing village of Dunga, which you can also see from the camp.\n\nI especially appreciated Amos, the manager and bartender, who made sure I was all set up and also scheduled a tuk-tuk to take me back to town the following morning, since I had to leave early.\n\nThe restaurant is good and fairly cheap. I think this should actually be rated as a $ rather than $$-$$$.  500 KSh for most full meals, less for snacks. Perhaps a Kisumu $$, but most travelers will appreciate it as a $.\n\nI only spent two nights I Kisumu, and I wish I had spent them both here.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3876, 'Olive C', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r652490062-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Linga Longa at Dunga', 'This is just a beautiful location overlooking Lake Victoria with virtually guaranteed spectacular sunsets...as the sun retreats diners leave their tables to try and capture the best picture ever...this places hugely popular with locals which ,as a tourist, gives you a more authentic restaurant experience...having said that the food can only be described as average but I would still recommend it as a must do if in Kisumu.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3877, 'Sande Olocho', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r637785631-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lakeside Great Outdoors', 'The first thing that hits you at Dunga Hill Camp is the fresh cool breeze and open space. It is very popular for campers and picnics. The food is very good and the views stunning.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3878, 'MrsK-J149', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r626066696-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Beautiful spot', 'Really lovely place to view Lake Victoria, picnic site and cafe and glorious views. Is popular with locals at the weekend but on a Friday morning we had the place to ourselves. Peaceful haven on the outskirts of insanely busy Kisumu.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(3879, 'michaelO3124AE', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r624142573-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Stunning Sunsets 365 Days a Year!', 'Kid you not no where in Kenya has the best sunsets like Lake Victoria. This is one of the many locations you can see one, any day of the year! The only place that serves Sukuma Wiki Pizza! Must try and have, this a local vegetable that has been added as one of the toppings on Pizza, however be patient the service can be slow when its full, good variety of food on offer and fresh.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3880, 'Annelot T', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r618829641-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Super fijne plek om te chillen na een dag de toerist uithangen :-)', 'Geweldig uitzicht over het Victoriameer. Heerlijke drankjes, lekker eten(Traditionelere gerechten en meer westers georienteerd. Voor ieder wat wils) en geweldige gastvrije staf.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[]'),
(3881, 'Byron78', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r591320782-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Tusker baridi with lake views.', 'Located down a murram road past the Impala Sanctuary with a signboard indicating the turn.Bar set on a small hillock with fabulous views.Boat rides and other activities occur on a regular basis with regular band days also.\nPleasant place to while away a weekend.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(3882, 'sam N N', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r548558541-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'NICE', 'Nice cool breeze with an Africa touch.Out of the busy noisy CBD.Good relaxation.Fish well done.I enjoyed.Soothing music in the background.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\"]'),
(3883, 'Istvan G', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r530566942-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Dinner', 'The food is good, but the Service is slow and non attentive! Order the telapia to be served sooner ;)', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(3884, 'Alfredo Carannante', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r524209390-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Il meraviglioso tramonto sul lago Vittoria e una buona cena locale', 'I tavoli sono in un prato panoramicissimo sulla cima di un promontorio verde sul lago Vittoria. La cameriera gentilissima porta birra fredda  mentre il sole africano tramonta incendiando il lago di colori meravigliosi... gi√† questo basterebbe... ma la cena √® ottima con il tipico pesce di lago la tilapia fritta condita con stufato di pomodori e peperoncini dolci e accompagnata da banane al vapore e ugali tipica polenta di mais bianco. Consigliatissimo ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[]'),
(3885, 'collins Otieno Oyoo', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r510402674-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The sun sets here.', 'The yellow, sunshine sets magnificently on the shores of the great Lake Victoria. Out in the fields, on a hill just on the shores of lake the largest fresh water lake, is the Dunga Hill Camp, referred to as the DHC. Its is structured in the country style. Sit on the hill overlooking the sun setting yellowly and enjoy your favourite drink.Everything is perfect here', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3886, 'SophyCathy', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r501252105-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Dunga Hill', 'The service there is great, with great live music and other guest are very kind and talkative. It is quite good to socialize and I enjoyed every minute there. The view from Dunga Hill is awesome, especially during sunset. Thanks for this great experience.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(3887, 'NaipaulJ', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r499735192-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great camping location, even better atmosphere', 'Camped here for two nights with a friend. Felt welcome from the first moment. Not only is the location absolutely stunning (those sunsets!), the staff is also helpful and friendly. Also, the atmosphere gets super on the weekends, the food is great and decently priced and the owners are awesome. Highly recommended, either for a dinner, drinks or camping overnight (or, ideally, all three!).', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(3888, 'Mandla T', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r490642820-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The Ultimate Weekend Afternoon Plan', 'The place offers an amazing view of the lake and beyond. Good service and an awesome crowd to kickstart your relaxation.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3889, 'Sharon O', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r486749358-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'soul lifting', 'loud music,nice food and friendly staff.loved the view of sunset and the soul lifting breeze from the lake.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3890, 'pifi2017', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r485033086-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice sunny place', 'a bit too load music but family friendly place. The food is nice and the service is quite correct. I recommand to go at sunset when its going dark.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:32', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3891, 'anneharmon', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r479675858-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Sunset', 'On a dirt road in Dunga. Food was fine and cheaper than most other places. Make sure to take bug spray.\nInteresting gift shop that was closed.\nWill visit again.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3892, 'Danielle J', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r479238012-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Amazing view!', 'The food was wonderful and the sunset is the best in the city. Friendly staff, great grounds! All around amazing place. 10/10 will visit again', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3893, 'Phil G', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r474529557-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'little bit of heaven', 'Dunga Hill Camp is fantastic! Went there with some friends for sunset drinks this weekend. Rain and lightning off on the horizon, a gentle breeze and 75¬∫ perfect temperature, overlooking the lake as the sun went down, with inexpensive cold beers to nurture great conversation. Tough to ask for anything more perfect.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(3894, 'Greta K', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r471320530-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Most beautiful place to watch the sunset', 'Dunga Hill Camp is one of my favorite places in Kisumu. I love to go there, having a drink and watch the sunset over the lake. Especially on the weekends it\'s always a good place to meet your friends and enjoying the sunset together. \nAlso on weekdays its a really lovely place to relax and enjoying the view over Kisumu and the lake. \nMy favorite dish is the Chips Masala, you should definitely try them when you are going!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3895, 'Crystal O', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r470227744-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Beautiful scenery', 'Dunga hill camp has an amazing view of the lake as you sip your favorite drink. The ambience is peaceful; a place i would definitely go back just to unwind.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3896, 'Jamie', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r465998262-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great location, nice food, Laughably bad service ', 'Absolutely idyllic location overlooking lake Victoria - perfect for sundowner drinks. Very lively at the weekends with lots of locals and tourists mingling. Food is tasty but the staff are beyond disinterested. The barman (seemed to always be the same guy) makes you feel like you\'ve offended his entire family when you try order, and we waited over 2 hours for our meals another time (there were 5 tables in!). ', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3897, 'Maryanne N', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r463937951-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The Killer view!', 'Sun downers at Hill Camp ! My my! The place is nice and chill! Crowd as well. But the view! My word! ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3898, 'sjoerd', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r452928001-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Prachtig uitzicht', 'Prachtig uitzicht op deze plek, aan het victoriameer. Eten is ook lekker, pizza\'s zijn alleen te dun om als volledige maaltijd te dienen. Aan te raden biertje: Nile Special', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(3899, 'Buyo‚Ñ¢', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r443273169-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Awesome vieuwpoint Victoria Lake Sunset', 'We had some tasty finger food, as in somosas and sausages along with a few Gin & Tonic on ice which tasted perfect! The waiter was ever so polite and the view of the sunset over the lake is superb!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3900, 'Charles K', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r439971554-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'PASCAL:Fraudulent Waiter', 'So I went out for dinner with my colleagues from work & the final bill was brought to me for finalization. Going through the bill (25,150 Kes) I became curious on the breakdown. We were 13 staff and quick math revealed that he had charged us for 16 plates.. Digging further revealed that he had also inflated the bill on drinks. Quick forward - The bill was actually 18,680 Kes - This is 7,000 Kes less than what he had initially charged us.\n\nThings got heated & even the bar tender denied supplying the drinks that the waiter PASCAL claimed we took. I told him to his face that I will share this information on trip advisor so that people are aware about his fradulent ways in advance. Guys enjoy the place is great, but if your waiter is PASCAL Please double check your bill!!!', 1, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3901, 'Bramwell B', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r437296151-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Dunga Hill Kisumu', 'On the shores of lake Victoria. Awesome views. Boat cruise available. Nice food. Alcoholic beverages are available. Nice music. Service is abit slow. About a kilometre of gravel road to get here.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(3902, 'Joris T', 'Dunga Road 300m Past Kiboko Bay Junction', 'Dunga Hill Camp', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10769731-r436520734-Dunga_Hill_Camp-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'quiet and peacefull', 'Great bar, perfect place to see the sunset at Lake Victoria. You can drink beers, wine, sodas and the house speciality: DelMonte, 1 litre of passionjuce! ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-10 20:29:33', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(4003, 'Thomas K', 'Junction of Kionange & Biashara Streets and The Village Market CJ\'s Building', 'CJ\'s Koinange', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d14008730-r1039511241-CJ_s_Koinange-Nairobi.html', 'Big menu, every one can find something they would like to try.', 'Great chain of restaurants with a big  menu to choose from. Perfect for groups, everyone can find a dish they would like to try. I was here at least 6 times, tried their breakfast, lunch and dinner. My favorite was their salads and their mexican food. Also have great local dishes and indian food. Loved their Santa Fe salad and their tacos. Their specials are good too. Always good service. Will be back.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:43:57', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(4004, 'Wouter', 'Junction of Kionange & Biashara Streets and The Village Market CJ\'s Building', 'CJ\'s Koinange', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d14008730-r1037749843-CJ_s_Koinange-Nairobi.html', 'Tasty food but with mediocre service', 'Enjoyed the chicken chipotle and beef curry tonight. Especially the use of sauce and garnishing was well done.\n\nAs for the service, I didn‚Äôt feel much at home. It could be a Nairobi thing, but once again the service felt distant and inattentive.\n\nI‚Äôd say the restaurant is in the somewhat safer and prettier part of town (CBD). Furthermore, I liked the stylish interior, large windows and the cleanliness of the toilets.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:43:57', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(4005, 'catline safaris', 'Junction of Kionange & Biashara Streets and The Village Market CJ\'s Building', 'CJ\'s Koinange', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d14008730-r1032781684-CJ_s_Koinange-Nairobi.html', 'Taste Coffee with a difference!', 'We visited the restaurant for evening coffee and cake. It was excellent! The coffee aroma will be memorable and the    black forest cake tasted very fresh.  We were given one big table with 6 comfortable seats, the waiter was so friendly.  Please try this place for evening coffee or dinner.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:43:57', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(4006, 'Milly N', 'Junction of Kionange & Biashara Streets and The Village Market CJ\'s Building', 'CJ\'s Koinange', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d14008730-r1024889398-CJ_s_Koinange-Nairobi.html', 'Very bad experience üòï', 'It\'s unfortunate that l ordered my food on 16 of August 2025 in the evening and after paying for the food ,they were supposed to deliver it,but No it\'s so bad especially in a hospitality industry like that they kept my order for good 4hours and I had already paid them.and after keeping me for long they ended up cancelling my order.They have my money and they are not willing to send it back it\'s a bad experience with the CJS restaurant koinange street so üòûüòîüòû', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:43:57', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"delivery_takeout\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4007, 'CORNY C', 'Junction of Kionange & Biashara Streets and The Village Market CJ\'s Building', 'CJ\'s Koinange', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d14008730-r1024046044-CJ_s_Koinange-Nairobi.html', 'WHOA!!', 'Who would ever imagine A 5 star restaurant at the heart of cbd!!..spacious airy  and clean.the staff are very very professional...the floor manger does not rest..always walking around ensuring everything is tip top.\nThe food is yummy n clean and the portions very generous!\nThe decor...wow!! The whole set up is intimidatingly perfect.\n\nPlease do not lower your standards coz I will definitely be back!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:43:57', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(4008, 'Peter S', 'Junction of Kionange & Biashara Streets and The Village Market CJ\'s Building', 'CJ\'s Koinange', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d14008730-r1023423146-CJ_s_Koinange-Nairobi.html', 'O.K., but rather impersonal.', 'Clearly the place to be seen at in this area, and always busy. Good choice of food, efficient staff - but because of how busy it is, and how they cram people in, the place really does feel impersonal.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:43:57', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
