(4038, 'Molly N', 'Junction of Kionange & Biashara Streets and The Village Market CJ\'s Building', 'CJ\'s Koinange', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d14008730-r937954911-CJ_s_Koinange-Nairobi.html', 'Delicious Chicken and Large portions', 'This a great spot for casual dining with family and friends. We had the honey glazed chicken wings with fries and plantains.  The food was delicious and the portion was large. Best chicken, I have had in a while. \n\nCons\n-The guacamole and masala fries were  subpar. The guacamole was watery and tasteless. The masala fries were not rusty and too soft.\n\n-The service was average. Our waiter came to our table only once to check if everything was fine. I asked another waiter to bring me some ice and he seemed irritated. He did bring the ice  and he didn‚Äôt say a word. \n\n-You have to buy water. I wish they would offer free water. \n\n- They brought my aunt hot herbal tea instead of cold.  The waiter wouldn‚Äôt  return it even though she said it was not what she wanted and she hadn‚Äôt touched it.\n\nTotal expense for three people was Ksh 7,800', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:43:57', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
