(4081, 'sdmmb', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r748438293-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great setting.    Very good', 'Great setting.    Very good selection of salads both as a main course and as an accompaniment to the main courses of offer.  Good for kids and to combine with trip out to Karen.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(4082, 'Amber D', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r746139112-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden gem', 'Stopped in fir lunch after a day of sight seeing with a friend in Karen abd ur was the perfect light lunch. The fresh salads fir sides was the best part of the meal. It‚Äôs quiet and has nice ambiance, def worth checking out.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(4083, 'Megan Joy', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r741682358-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'An unexpected find! ', 'An unexpected find! We ordered a vegan sandwich, and while they brought us the wrong sandwich, it was still very good. Bonus that sandwich order comes with a salad bar offering a variety of fresh & healthy salads. Lovely setting on a bright  patio surrounded by the shops. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(4084, 'Gill d', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r739628539-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great lunch', 'Set amongst the stalls of the craft market, this cafe is a great place to eat lunch.  Lovely selection of salads and healthy drinks - try the turmeric latte!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(4085, 'MarieR', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r737882195-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'So and so....', 'I actually really like this place and have been a couple of times. The Otto Lenghi Style salads are delicious and the food is overall really good. However, it is a little beyond the shabby chic and just looks plain dirty in some places. Also, at our last visit we came with our toddler who can\'t eat solid food. We asked for some well cooked vegetables so we could mash them for the baby. The waitress said they had no vegetables which is rather surprising. We asked for just plain cooked potatoes to which the waitress again said, there were no potatoes.... standing next to a potato salad. So we finally managed to order an avocado which was so hard once it arrived we were unable to mash it for the baby. The whole thing just felt like the waitress was in a bad mood and didn\'t feel like being helpful or accommodating. For a restaurant this is not ideal.... ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4086, 'Cleo', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r734869740-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Awful food!', 'We had a terrible experience at the Tin Roof Cafe. The sandwiches were overpriced and badly cooked. Never going back', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'negative', '[\"overall_experience\"]'),
(4087, 'Felino', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r729721634-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great Time!', 'We went there to celebrate our daughter first year birthday, just something spontaneous nothing prepared in advance\n\nWe invited a couple of friends to join us and we ordered by menu, we did also bring our own wines and we were just charged KES 500 for cork fee\n\nFood was goooooood maybe because we were during pizza week we did had cheap bill (around 12K for 10 people) and we did had good time with drinks, foods, coffees....\n\nTeam was fantastic they were very helpful at the time to put balloons and decorate a bit\n\nHighly recommended, cozy, cute, fresh, foodie....', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(4088, 'Glyn12', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r727962843-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'What a super surprise for a lovely casual lunch. Highly Reommneded', 'The Tin Roof Cafe is situated amongst a haphazard cluster of boho shops selling furnishings, jewellery and clothing as well as a second hand shop with a wide array of wares. The Tin Roof is VERY simple and therefore the excellent service small but eclectic menu of very tasty and well presented food is a great surprise in a sylvan environment. Highly recommended. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(4089, 'Ramona Lea', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r724300400-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A pretty, quiet place to relax amongst the garden and birds', 'We visited here on a Sunday afternoon and it was thankfully not overcrowded. Staff were pleasant and the environment was a mix of romantic/shabby chic/country cottage decor in a pretty garden environment. The garden attracted birds and squirrels, which we also enjoyed. The menu featured many ingredients (such as quinoa) and dishes (cauliflower rice, breakfast bowls) which I do not see commonly in other cafes and restaurants. Also there were dishes on the menu to cater for dietary requirements (such as gluten-free). The prices were also fair and I will definitely recommend this venue to others! I audit restaurants for work in Australia and am hard to impress but I enjoyed my visit to this venue!', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4090, 'Jon T', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r693145829-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Perfect healthy food!', 'I would highly recommend this restaurant if you like freshly cooked food that is both healthy and tasty. The accompanying salads are especially good. This was a good place to eat after visiting the giraffe sanctuary.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4091, 'tris798', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r690624823-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great find for Vegetarians!', 'This restaurant is located in the middle of a small town shop. It is very quaint and even has books you can read. My husband and I ordered a few items each to share. I had a delicious chai latte. Their smashed avocado toast and smoothie bowl were phenomenal. We also shared their pancakes, which were delicious crepes with sugar and lemon. I would definitely come back again. Highly recommend. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4092, 'daniel m', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r690369662-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'HEALTHY AND LOVELY', 'Lovely corner of Karen for a nice healthy bite. The freshness and tastiness of the food is very refreshing. simple, nice, fun, health conscious! ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(4093, 'Roger S', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r689959405-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Another adorable gem of a spot!', 'Settled in behind some very nice shops, is the tin roof cafe. A storage container turned into cafe, they deal out some very fresh and tasty treats! Between my wife and I, we indulged a but and got the pancake, avocado toast, smoothie bowl and bacon sandwich for which they had a more elegant name but I forget it. Everything was great! Some of the best avocado we\'ve had and the smoothie bowl was just yum! The bacon sandwich was bit lacking but nothing worth a demerit on this review. Definitely give this a shot!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4094, 'Joe Teflon', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r689677796-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Tin roof cafe ', 'A hidden gem away from all the city noise. A nice place to take your family. Nice clean atmosphere but has that old western feeling. ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(4095, 'Josee_nd', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r688927494-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Loved the food and the experience to the Karen branch', 'My family & I really enjoyed a nice relaxed and healthy meal on Sunday at the Tin Roof cafe. Kids enjoyed the nice simple playground set up. We shall be back. The food was amazing!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(4096, 'Spear', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r686760956-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'ambience', 'good ambience and climate, fabulous shopping experience, is on the same property, which makes this an obvious place to combine lunch and shopping.\n', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4097, 'Escape-overseas', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r678295098-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Nice setting within the Langata Link Complex', 'Nice setting within the Langata Link Complex, hidden among the nich shops. Good service, refreshing milk shakes, coffees and smoothies.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(4098, 'Finnegan', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r674456455-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A peaceful haven with a fantastic salad bar', 'This Tin Roof Cafe is hidden in a treed location which makes it a great secluded getaway for a light and tasty lunch.   The cafe has a quaint patio and the inside has a bright and fresh decor.  The all you can eat salad bar is my favorite with a variety of options and flavours to suit any palate. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(4099, 'sharp shi', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r673659498-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Loved the ambiance but hated the quality of pizza', 'now -\nI took my friends there from the look we expected high and positive turn out. to our surprise the coffee was of quality but the pizza we ordered for was not pizza but a burnt butter naan something that is not worth paying for. the waiter instead of apology all he could say is \"and the way our customers like it?\". ...this was not the way to answer neither did he even advice or rather use suggestive idea of how the pizza could not even meet a one person\'s want... I was embarrass by the service as well and even ashamed to face my friends. I personally can\'t recommend anyone to such a place its a total waste of time. not all glitters is gold ', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4100, 'rejoicing', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r666342008-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'I love this place!', 'I have been here many times and always leave very satisfied! Their menu has many things to offer, but I prefer their salad bar. There are always beautiful and delicious salads available, that are also extremely healthy. You can chose from a variety of tables at which to sit, most of which are outdoors in a nice atmosphere. Even the service is excellent!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(4101, 'melissa k', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r666313770-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Home away from home!', 'I love love love it here! They use fresh produce and make clean food like back home. Their feta and cheese crepe was amazing but their salad even more so! I ordered their juice and it came with a paper straw. I love environmentally friendly cafes and restaurants. It is situated away from the main road and has a little garden on the side if you want to have lunch among greenery. I highly recommend anything on their menu and just to bring a book to read there over coffee or a juice.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4102, '950Julie16', 'Dagoretti Road Opposite The Hub Karen. Approx 200m from Karen Roundabout', 'Tin Roof Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5561344-r666237163-Tin_Roof_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'morning coffee', 'tucked away but a great find, all freshly prepared and organic produce. highly recommend a visit for breakfast, not had lunch as yet, but menu looks lovely.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:46:19', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
