(4311, 'beryn A', 'Chiromo Lane JW Marriott Hotel Nairobi', 'Hudson Tavern Bar & Grill', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d33219451-r1031865039-Hudson_Tavern_Bar_Grill-Nairobi.html', 'Unacceptable profiling and bad Attitude at Hudson Tervan Nairobi', 'I visited Hudson Tavern at JW Marriott Nairobi on 10th September, and unfortunately, my experience was very disappointing. My cousin and I ordered food and tried to order wine, only to be told by one waitress(Molly) that it was only sold by the bottle. Another waitress gave me a conflicting information (not sure if it‚Äôs her name),to say we had to spend a minimum of 5,000 KES per head before being served.\n\nThis did not make sense, especially as I saw other guests around me being served wine, beers and whiskey by the glass without such restrictions. Even a friend of mine who had been there earlier that evening confirmed she had only ordered a glass without issue. It felt like a case of profiling and discrimination, which was very upsetting.\n\nWhen I asked to speak to a manager, the waitress was extremely rude. The manager later tried to justify the ‚Äúpolicy,‚Äù but it did not match what I observed with other guests. Having worked within the Marriott brand myself around the world , I was shocked at how far this fell below the standards of service and respect Marriott is known for.\n\nNo guest should ever feel judged or profiled when dining in a Marriott property. I hope management takes this seriously and improves both training and attitude among the staff.\n\nIn addition, I must highlight that Molly‚Äôs attitude throughout the interaction was extremely rude and unprofessional. She made us feel as though we could not afford our meals and, worse, as though we were being profiled as having inappropriate intentions simply for being women dining at the property. Such behavior is unacceptable and goes against the very principles of hospitality that Marriott upholds. Molly should be reminded that not every woman who visits a Marriott property deserves such treatment, and I strongly recommend that she undergo retraining in Marriott‚Äôs policies and service standards!!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:56:37', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4312, 'Brenda B', 'Chiromo Lane JW Marriott Hotel Nairobi', 'Hudson Tavern Bar & Grill', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d33219451-r1031824275-Hudson_Tavern_Bar_Grill-Nairobi.html', 'A Refined Escape in Nairobi‚Äôs JW Marriott', 'Hudson Tavern at JW Marriott Nairobi is a gem. I went for a solo date, and everything from the ambience to the service felt effortlessly refined. The space is modern, warm, and perfect for photos‚Äîideal for dinner dates, birthdays, or a chic night out. The cocktail was an easy 9/10, but the fish and chips stole the show‚Äîhands down a 10/10. Service was impeccable; Andrew made the experience seamless, attentive without being overbearing. It‚Äôs quiet, stylish, and welcoming, with pricing that feels fair for the quality. A spot I‚Äôd recommend wholeheartedly, and one I‚Äôll definitely return to.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 17:56:37', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
