(4461, 'Hafsa O', 'Runda,Northern Bypass Glee Nairobi', 'The Peacock Restaurant & Bar', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d33273987-r1031001376-The_Peacock_Restaurant_Bar-Nairobi.html', 'It was fantastic', 'Had an awesome time there. From the moment we walked into the restaurant, the atmosphere had us ‚Äî warm lighting, low jazz in the background, the scent of garlic, rosemary, and something grilled in the air. We were greeted with genuine smiles and seated by the window, where the city lights flickered like stars just for us.\nThe menu? A dream. Every dish sounded like a love letter to flavor. We started with crispy calamari and truffle fries ‚Äî perfectly golden and impossible to stop eating. Our mains arrived like artwork: seared salmon on a bed of creamy risotto for me, and a thick, juicy ribeye for my friend, grilled to absolute perfection.\n\nThe conversation flowed as smoothly as the wine ‚Äî a bold red that seemed to melt away the week‚Äôs stress with every sip. Laughter echoed across the table as we shared stories, made new memories, and let the vibe of the place carry us.\n\nAnd just when we thought it couldn‚Äôt get better: dessert. A molten chocolate cake with vanilla bean ice cream that should be illegal, and a cr√®me br√ªl√©e with that perfect sugar crack on top.\n\nWe stayed longer than we planned, not wanting to break the magic. It wasn‚Äôt just the food ‚Äî it was the whole experience. The kind of night that reminds you life is made of moments like these: good food, great company, and a little sparkle in the air.\n\nWould you like it more tailored ‚Äî like with a specific cuisine, a romantic vibe, a funny group dinner, or a solo self-care night?', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 18:01:56', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
