(4597, 'Paul1410', 'Shanzu, Serena Road Serena Beach Resort & Spa', 'The Jahazi Grill by Serena Beach', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d15887310-r1031146581-The_Jahazi_Grill_by_Serena_Beach-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Awesome food, great quality and friendly staff', 'We stayed at the Serena Beach Hotel and Spa in Mombasa for two weeks for our holiday abroad.\n\nA must go to seafood restaurant in Mombasa is The Tamarind, it‚Äôs been there for decades and is famous certainly in Kenya if not beyond. We both had lobster at The Tamerind as our main course whilst it was lovely we then went to The Jahazi Grill.\n\nThe service was great, the staff really friendly and the lobster excellent. We actually went back again!\n\nI would rate our experience at the Jahazi Grill as well as the quality of the food better than that at The Tamerind.\n\nBy the way - it‚Äôs cheaper than the Tamerind as well.\n\nWell done to the management and staff - hope to visit you again on holiday next year!', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:11:05', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4598, 'Toney K', 'Shanzu, Serena Road Serena Beach Resort & Spa', 'The Jahazi Grill by Serena Beach', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d15887310-r1030149588-The_Jahazi_Grill_by_Serena_Beach-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Outstanding dinner experience', 'Very professional staff, a great culinary experience and wonderful atmosphere. \nKeep up the great job you are doing. \nThoroughly enjoyed the charm in the service and entertaining saxophonist.', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:11:05', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
