(4684, 'Christine M', 'Nyali road, Inside City Mall, Nyali', 'Cultura Mombasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d27253415-r945998163-Cultura_Mombasa-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Excellent service', 'The ambience and aesthetic i would rate: 10/10\nThe service is topnotch, the reception is good and welcoming, we were served by a waitress called Ms.Swabra, i would recommend her she is the best she offered us the best service making the stay more excellent and worth spending.\nThank you Ms. Swabra', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:12:43', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4685, 'Max B', 'Nyali road, Inside City Mall, Nyali', 'Cultura Mombasa', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d27253415-r944614110-Cultura_Mombasa-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'So much potential but the steaks are consistently bad', 'I want so much to love this restaurant.  The front of house team are really very good, the dining room is beautiful, the wine list is excellent.  All this is however what one should expect given the prices, but one can never be sure as we are in East Africa.  The coffee and deserts are as one would expect from Cafisserie‚Äôs sister excellent.  The fish is good, as is the sushi - although quality inconsistent on the two times I was there - excellent the first and ok the second.  The problem, and where all this falls apart for me is the meat, and this is sold as a meat restaurant.    If spending ksh 16,000 on a bottle of wine as is easily achievable on that wine list one expects to pair it with a very good steak.  Sadly, twice now, in a row, as a small group,  we have been served what can only be described as rubbish.  A good steak restaurant will show the cut to the customer before cooking.  Marbling should be evident, and it should be unfrozen.  I had sadly not seen the tomahawk, sirloin or rib eye before cooking, and they arrived at the table without any fat, steamed, unseared, overcooked, unseasoned, tough and tasteless.  They were returned and replaced with apparently fresh local t-bones from a delivery that morning.  These were to be fair better, but they were not in any way special.  If they can get a good new meat supplier and the chefs can learn to prepare and cook the meat properly - look at the photo from my review of Cut - this could be a fantastic restaurant.  Until they figure that out it will not be..', 3, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:12:43', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
