(4847, 'Abdirahman H', 'Nyerere Avenue Ralli House, Opposite Shell Petrol Station', 'Qaffee Point', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d16739335-r986473871-Qaffee_Point-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Amazing Sea Food and Fantastic Ambiance.', 'I recently tried the seafood platter, and it was absolutely fantastic! Everything tasted so fresh, from the prawns to the fish fillets. The calamari was perfectly cooked‚Äîcrispy on the outside and tender inside. The flavors were spot on, and the sauces added a nice touch without overpowering the seafood. The portion was generous, and it was perfect for sharing. If you‚Äôre a seafood lover, this is a must-try! I‚Äôll definitely be back for more.', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:23:30', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(4848, 'joan o', 'Nyerere Avenue Ralli House, Opposite Shell Petrol Station', 'Qaffee Point', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d16739335-r923913432-Qaffee_Point-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Excellent service from Betty, and very tasty mojitos.', 'The food was amazing and worth the money. \nBetty was a great waitress.\nThe mocktails were very tasty, especially the mojito.', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:23:30', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(4849, 'Hesmailji', 'Nyerere Avenue Ralli House, Opposite Shell Petrol Station', 'Qaffee Point', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d16739335-r922388120-Qaffee_Point-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Good Place in the CBD', 'This cafe is in the CBD near Biashara Bank building. The place looks small from the outside but once you go in they have a huge basement seating. Fully air-conditioned so once you get seated you already feeling nice after the Mombasa heat outside. \n\nThey have a really extended menu. From grills to curry to rice dishes to continental. Its got a fairly good cake selections too. \n\nWe been here twice so that itself shows the food is good. \n\nOver our both visits we had ordered \nBurger, humus, biryani, butter chicken, Poussin chicken, mix grill platter, \n\nAll the above foods were good apart from the Poussin. I wouldn\'t order that again. It wasn\'t Poussin chicken was more like a cereal or bread crumb coated chicken with some tangy sauce. \nOther stuff were to the mark. \n\nService was good. Staff are very friendly. Reasonably priced restaurant. Definitely a place to dine at when in Mombasa. ', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:23:30', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(4850, 'Ngowa M', 'Nyerere Avenue Ralli House, Opposite Shell Petrol Station', 'Qaffee Point', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d16739335-r867895554-Qaffee_Point-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Best food in Mombasa CBD', 'Perfect food,perfect quantities.\nAmazing flavors .Good for business meetings,family outings at affordable prices', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:23:30', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(4851, 'mjs786', 'Nyerere Avenue Ralli House, Opposite Shell Petrol Station', 'Qaffee Point', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d16739335-r854648401-Qaffee_Point-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Very Very Good Eatery', 'I have visited this restaurant few days I was in Mombasa the food is absolutely delicious I have tried different dishes and I really liked  them all apart from one dish PIza I don‚Äôt know why but is not near the Piza I have used to before but that‚Äôs minor issue I will recommend this clean and awesome restaurant in the heart of Mombasa CBD', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:23:30', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4852, 'Circumnavigator', 'Nyerere Avenue Ralli House, Opposite Shell Petrol Station', 'Qaffee Point', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d16739335-r805850267-Qaffee_Point-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Good food but ground zero for potential Corona infection', 'This restaurant has good to excellent food and has very friendly and helpful staff. The place is family friendly.\n\nUnfortunately these excellent characteristics are completely annihilated by the total lack of staff discipline in wearing mouth masks. The obligatory hand wash and temperature check before entering is just to keep up appearances but inside it seems there is a policy of the managing and serving staff to wear mouth masks below the chin. Occasionally there is a staff member wearing the mouth mask correctly but most others apparently never heard of the Covid-19 pandemic. So I gladly informed them it was a reality. Even when explained, memory loss occurred after approximately 5 minutes.\n\nRather than the potential of being the best bistro in town, they are now exploiting the potential of being ground zero if the Covid-19 virus ever decides to invade in the country. So sad.', 2, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:23:30', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(4853, 'WYN', 'Nyerere Avenue Ralli House, Opposite Shell Petrol Station', 'Qaffee Point', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294210-d16739335-r784204273-Qaffee_Point-Mombasa_Coast_Province.html', 'Excellent food', 'Tasty food, nice people & ambience, excellent service & staff, attractive presentation .. I enjoyed a wonderful Lobster with a special sauce yummy', 5, 'Mombasa', '2025-11-24 18:23:30', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
