(5049, 'Joseph M', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r365114748-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'I want to eat here again.', '3 of us went to dinner here on evening. The food is amazing and the potions are huge.  This is the best place in town to eat.  If you visit Kisumu you owe it to yourself to come here and eat dinner.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5050, 'Mayur N', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r337828063-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Excellent food', 'This place makes you feel you are in CHINA the ambiance is fantastic, their service is good, food is made fresh and very authentic chines taste, price is fairly reasonable and the portions are big. A place not to be missed when in Kisumu city.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5051, 'EAZG', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r327150558-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Just OK, but they deliver!', 'The menu has about what you\'d guess for predictable Chinese food in a medium size town in Africa. But it is predictable, and it it\'s OK, and--on a wet and (relatively) cold Kisumu night--the Oriental is one of the few places in Kisumu that actually delivers. And in containers that don\'t spill all over. I do wish they had spicy Chinese mustard however :)', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5052, 'Katherine S', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r316853904-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Tasty food', 'The wait staff aren\'t always great but the food is quite good. The food is definitely a \'toned-down\' version of Chinese food, so don\'t come here looking for authentic dishes but in terms of eating in Kisumu, this is definitely one of the better lunch or dinner places to go.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(5053, 'John S', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r278300993-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'A long-standing classic hidden away in Kisumu', 'Come up to the second floor of Al-Imran plaza, and you\'ll be treated to a nook of oriental cuisine in Kisumu.  It\'s not the most authentic Chinese food, but then again you\'re in Kenya.  The restaurant is like a stalwart in the middle of Kisumu - I\'m not sure a single thing has changed about the place since I started coming in 2006.  I always order the sweet & sour chicken, sauce on the side - it\'s usually a substantial portion but their sauce is too overwhelming.  The fried rice comes at a good price as well and is an enormous heaping serving - definitely enough for 2 people to share.  They have sodas and a bar.  They also have ice cubes if you ask for them.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5054, 'Ruth M', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r237922325-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great  Chinese dishes', 'I don`t know if  it is my soft spot for Chinese food but i could eat all my day`s  meals at this restaurant.The staff are always available and prompt in preparing the meals too.\nI feel they however  need to improve on their  their restrooms though', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5055, 'Herbert D', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r236703191-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Oriental Restaurant in Kisumu', 'The food and services are good and very affordable.  A nice place to get oriental food while visiting Kisumu', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5056, 'Irene-van-Laarhoven', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r232190249-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'nice food but unhygienic toilets', 'The food is nice, thoughnot exceptional. The location is ok, but the restaurant shares its toilets with other businesses in the building and has a problem with water. So if your stomach is sensitive don\'t go there. ', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5057, 'sally l', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r208141527-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'the BEST', 'I would miss out on a meal at the Oriental.. its my favorite place to eat in Kisumu.. the meals are fresh, lots of good food and the service is awesome... I take my friends there for the best feed each year i travel to the Orphanage.. it beats cooking one night as well...', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5058, 'Mohamed V', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r193616711-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Allright, Not the best', 'Apparently, the only oriental restaurant in Kisumu. Service was very poor; food was not all so good. Nothing to rave about. ', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(5059, 'Alis0n_90', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r187248947-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good asian food..and lots of it!', 'Staff were helpful and friendly and the food was really nice with absolutely huge portions. Great if you have a big appetite. \nSeemed to be relatively busy, with westerners and locals which is a good sign!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5060, 'Sunrise364', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r184629118-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Average', 'Went there for lunch a couple times. With the general lack of variety in the city, it is an option I appreciate having whenever I pass through Kisumu. The owner is cold and looks a bit mean, but the waiters are friendly. The service is excellent. However, the bathrooms could be kept more clean. I once used them and the stench of urine was so invading that I never went back.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5061, 'Byron78', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r181582300-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Doing the basics better', 'Went on a Friday night quite late 9.30 and it was pleasantly not full.Ordered spring rolls and wings as starters and was tasty and a very good portion.Waitress was also attentive.Mains were veg of which they only had a half portion left and a pork and chicken dish each.The portions were again very good and the food had a fresh delicious taste quite unlike the london chinatown places.Hard to fault anything about the meal and the experience.Leftovers packaged quickly.A nice change to the last time i was here a few months ago.Nice enjoyable tasty meal.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"delivery_takeout\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5062, 'Ginny442', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r175650441-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Wow great food', 'Well that\'s it, great food in a place I didn\'t expect it. It cost a family of 6 under KSE5000 to eat a huge meal. The choice was great, the price was fantastic and the service amazing, we could even have a glass of wine. We went a few times and will go back again when I am there next.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5063, 'Hong S', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r157522983-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'It filled an emotional hole...', 'Food portions are massive! Vegetable fried rice was OK, they agreed to add egg to it free of charge, but having grated cabbage and carrot wasn\'t what I was expecting, but perhaps I shouldn\'t have had such high hopes!  The fried dumplings were OK, again, filled an emotional hole.  Sizzling pork was OK, a bit tough, the chicken and chilli onion wasn\'t too chilli, but was certainly oniony.  Both of the two main dishes had that kind of distinct \'brown\' shade of sauce, but actually tasted a bit different. Not a bad restaurant, but not amazing either.  It certainly feels an emotional hole if you\'ve been craving it. ', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5064, 'Serena K', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r155757392-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best and Only Chinese in Kisumu', 'The asian couple that owns this restaurant are very nice, and make mostly westernized chinese dishes.  You aren\'t able to order everything on the plate all of the time- a typical issue in Kisumu restaurants and infrastructure issues in Kenya in general.  That said, after living on lentils and rice for the past 6 months - this place made my day! ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(5065, 'Tina B', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r140460053-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great steamed pork dumplings!!', 'Good as any basic chinese you would get around the world. Prices can be higher than most other options around town, but it is consistent,  and service is good. Worth a visit if you are craving chinese.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5066, 'MissTravelFiend', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r133095123-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice food', 'If you like Chinese food then this place is great. It\'s also the only Chinese restaurant in Kisumu, which is probably why I enjoyed it so much.\n\nThe atmosphere is decent despite the fact that it\'s located within a mall type building. Service was adequate and the prices are not bad either.\n\nAside from Chinese you can also order local food like tilapia etc. They even have chips (fries) on the menu, which I thought was funny (because who eats chips with Chinese???) until a group of Americans came in and ordered a bunch of Chinese food with chips :)\n\nIn any case, it\'s nothing spectacular but the food is nice, and I will certainly be going back next time I\'m craving Chinese food.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5067, 'Chotu P', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r124700974-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'ORIENTAL RESTAURANT', 'Situated in center of town. Outside sitting area , one can enjoy fresh air. Service is excellent .The menu is Chinese and Thai lovely dishes.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5068, 'Alsacienne', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r124548292-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good food and service, generous portions', 'We visited on a very quiet evening when the inside of the restaurant was empty but the tables outside on the \'veranda\'  were all taken.\n\nNot all the dishes on the menu were known to us, but we had generous portions - particularly the dim sum dumplings - and great service.  Not particularly cheap but we felt that we had had good value for money and attentive service.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5069, 'Byron78', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r122398560-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Average food,rubbish service.', 'Good food and terrible service.Found a table,waited 20 mins for service in this small restaurant.Service did improve,though the owner kept pretending she did not speak English and then directed the waiters in English.Not a pleasant woman at all.The waiters did improve but overall not a great experience.The food couldnt be faulted and was appetising and tasty when it came in stops and starts.So a hit and miss place.Sad thing is,it is the only oriental restaurant in the city so you cant go anywhere else.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5070, 'Denise R', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r122355181-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Just okay', 'It has just ordinary Chinese food. There is nothing special except it is the only Chinese restaurant in Kisumu.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5071, 'adventurersKisumu', 'Oginga Odinga Rd, Kisumu', 'Oriental Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214119-r121755568-Oriental_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Oriental Chinese', 'Food is good and portions quite big....Waiter service is average but the cooks are very fast (maybe some of it could be pre-pepared!)and the food is served very fast too...', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:50:29', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(5072, 'Judith A', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r780841462-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Cold lunch, rude chef', 'Bad experience, order messed up, cold food and a chef who walked out on us and told said ‚Äú Roan can do without your money‚Äù while we were trying to discuss the issue with him.\nOverall service- poor', 1, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5073, 'Shiku', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r776748941-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', '1 hour for a bland pizza', 'Service is soooo slow. Hardly more than 7 guests in the whole place and it still took 1 hour for a bland tasting pizza. Eat somewhere else', 1, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5074, 'Ouma Oluoko', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r712496434-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The magic of the evening', 'Interestingly named after the noblest and yet the unforgiving Roan Antelope, The Roan Bar and Restaurant is the place for those who see opportunities in life and go for them. Make a date with them and achieve your ambitions.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5075, 'Toto Joy :-)', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r691303376-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great Saturday night vibes and pizza Tuesdays!', 'Cool place in downtown Kisumu. Great place to hang on the weekends, even though very crowded. Overall good vibes and they\'ve got special pizza days during the week and the pizza is great!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5076, 'Alex1970', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r669172914-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Enjoyable chill', 'Great place to pass time watching life below pass by.  Wonderful value for money. Sometimes can be loud which may say more about my age. Good, safe option is staying at the Imperial Express opposite ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5077, 'Kate', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r655587241-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Delicious meals!', 'Finger-licking food. Will be eating at Roan rooftop hotel whenever in Kisumu. Professional staffs. Keep on the good services.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(5078, 'sydneyannem', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r640308260-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Weekly date spot', 'My husband and I have started getting away together once a week, and this has become our favorite spot. We have ordered something different from the menu each time. It has all been good, and it is our favorite place to eat in Kisumu. They also happen to have a better bar selection than most places. We have only been during odd hours and havent made it at the regular nightlife time, so cannot attest to that. The food, however, is on point. The local food menu is great, and they have the best kuku choma. The pizzas are as good as any we\'ve had in kenya, and they do take away. ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5079, 'michaelO3124AE', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r624141642-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice View of the Lake', 'Place to chill, grab a drink and catch up, I like the view of the \"aerial view\" of the lake and like to go there for a late lunch and gaze at the lake from a distance. Night time is too loud for me and crowded I prefer late afternoon visit.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5080, 'budgetlust', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r617667854-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Night Spot', 'This was a go-to spot for the group I was with. The food is decent (although can be a long wait), they offer a good variety as well. Late afternoon and early evenings are pretty quite and a nice time to go. Nights and weekends it gets packed, sometimes to the point of not being able to move or find a seat, but still a fun time. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5081, 'Byron78', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r615712408-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Apex Bar', 'Leading entertainment venue in Kisumu.Located up a flight of stairs in the cbd,the kitenge roofed lounge with comfortable seating and bar stools has fabulous views over the neat green city centre and view of the distant hills and lake.For those seeking privacy,there is a large private room for parties.\n  The menu is a combination of continental dishes with the highlight being a seafood slant with squid,lobster et al bringing a pleasant change to the Kisumu scene.As night falls the place morphs into a bar like atmosphere with various nights including karaoke,quiz and Fri onwards a dj plays various afro house and other beats.Service is fairly good when it is not too busy with attentive staff,they have lunch offers too which are surprisingly very good.\n Avoid the bars that have rain pouring through their cloth roof and enjoy a night of revelry at this joint.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"events_entertainment\"]'),
(5082, 'Victor R', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r568145867-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good food', 'This is a nice eatery in Kisumu that prepares delicious Africa food. The restaurant gives you a good view of the city', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5083, 'Samantha C', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r560984838-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The go to place ', 'The food is always absolutely wonderful,from seafood to BBQ\'s to pizza, quite a lot of variety to choose from and from preparation to presentation, very pleasing. Not to forget the amazing cocktails,great Ambience and fun club nights.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5084, 'Byron78', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r553122710-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Main street rooftop fun.', 'Located on the main street with views of the cbd,this is on the 3rd floor of the buildfing.\nHas a wide varied menu including seafood and pizza and a well stocked bar.\nHas various events during the week and the weekends are generally packed out.\nGreat addition to the Ksm scene for entertainment and varied menu.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5085, 'Gabuo2018', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r549644925-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Tamp down the racism and shameful PR that follows!', 'Supposed decent ambiance and good service utterly sullied by allegations of blatant racism and discrimination of locals with none too subtle preference for white clientele. ', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5086, 'anneharmon', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r548659516-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Long climb up to resturant', 'We had lunch and dinner. Seafood on menu!! Even lobster\nIn the evening mostly a young crowd with loud  music (don\'t sit near the speakers)', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5087, 'Cthitu', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r544452186-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Dinner at the Rooftop ', 'We got a recommendation to have dinner from Imperial Express and was skeptical at first but the meal was sumptuous and well presented.  The Chef came for reviews. Had their fish, tasted their chicken and they were very good and tasty. \nWould have preferred a quite corner.  We\'re accompanied by an elderly gentleman.  ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5088, 'jdaws478', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r499217911-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Between a Pub and Club is very accurate', 'The review below for \"somewhere between a pub and a club\" is extremely accurate! The wait time for food is actually absurd ~expect about a one hour wait for dinner. I ordered the fish curry and it was very good food that was quite yummy. My friends ordered the tilipia helicopter which apparently means fish head, she did not enjoy her dish and ended up eating half of mine. My other friend got the a roast chicken dish that was just ok. If you go here, definitely order the fish curry and prepare to wait. The view is nice and I would try to get here before sunset. The music is on a loop but they are classic R&B and pop hits that you forgot how much you loved a long time ago.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5089, 'BeOnen', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r492610213-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The place to be.', 'It\'s such a pleasure to have a classy and fun joint to go to any night of the week in Kisumu. The location in the middle of town is spot on. Nice ambience, upbeat atmosphere, great food (including seafood) and music that covers every genre. There\'s no dance floor but that doesn\'t stop punters getting down on the Friday and Saturday nights. \n\nHarold the owner is personable and fun and his staff are awesome.\n\nPS: You have to try the Flaming Lamborghini', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5090, 'lifeinthetopbunk', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r468246710-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Somewhere between a pub and a club.', 'I went on a Friday night; security scanned my bag on the way in.  The DJ was fantastic - playing lots of 90s hip hop and R&B, as well as some good mash-ups (there\'s no dance floor, however).  The drinks here seem cheap, but the single shot jigger they use is really small - maybe 3/4 ounce?  Beer is a cheaper option, but they do make a proper cocktail and have a wide selection of single malt scotch, which impressed me!  There\'s lots of room and a mix of locals, expats, and tourists.  Nice bar staff / busy on weekends; located above Choppies.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5091, 'Vidiri', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r453396878-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'NICE AMBIENCE', 'Roan rooftop is a welcome establishment in kisumu. The ambience and decor are really nice. The food is not to be bad. As a hangout spot it is quite nice and the music is good. Just need to improve on service when the place is packed especially on the weekend nights', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5092, 'Ratimo A', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r441475997-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The best evening hang out in Kisumu any day of the week', 'Been here a few times. Its at the top of a building in the center of town at the end of a rather long and dingy staircase. But worry not. Its worth the climb. The customer service at this facility is the best in Kisumu. Yet to have an unpleasant experience with the wait staff. They do not have female wait staff either.The food is top notch if a little pricey but definitely worth it. The quality of food is very good. Its not overdone. Simple and well done.The pizza is frankly the best pizza I have had in Kisumu. I would dare say in Kenya maybe. Its really good. The live band on Thursdays is great. And the its fairly open so you can get a feeling of the lake breeze. Its just the perfect place for an evening out with friends or a date or just plain alone time.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5093, 'EdT1117', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r436284501-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'At the roan', 'Definitely the ultimate experience for dinning and a night out when in Kisumu. Lovely ambience, superb service, good food and fantastic view.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5094, 'kochieng12', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r432333986-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'curious', 'Its my first time to night am going to The Roan Rooftop i hope i will have a good time... expecting to see view of the place drinks n delicacy', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5095, 'dinahogeto', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r406918684-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Place to be that accomodates the needs of all.', 'Roan roof top cares for the needs of all people both vegetarians and non-vegetarians with their wonderful food.They also have non-alcoholic drinks for the customers who don\'t drink beer.It is a wonderful place that really impressed me.If you pass-by Kisumu and you are looking for a place to eat or drink,go ROAN ROOF TOP.Their prices are pocket friendly.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5096, 'Ominde', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r405510003-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great food at Roan Rooftop', 'If you are looking for a place to eat amazing food within the Kisumu CBD then Roan Rooftop is definitely the place. Mostly know for it\'s night life, very few people actually know that it\'s in fact a restaurant that turns into a night club a couple of nights a week.\n\nThey can possibly whip out anything you dream of from their kitchen. Their menu ranges from traditional Kenyan delicacies to dishes you would find in American or Asian restaurants.\n\nIt\'s one thing to make amazing meals and totally another to present it well, that is one thing that the guys at Roan have mastered.\n\nThe fresh breeze on the third floor establishment just add to one of the reasons why you should have your meals here.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5097, 'dennis j', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r403152883-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best thing that happened to the lake side city of Kisumu!', 'What makes a good restaurant?\n\nAtmosphere of the utmost importance. It‚Äôs very key. The lighting has to be right. And table settings have to as well. It‚Äôs about trying to space tables out nicely so you have that atmosphere no matter how busy the place is. That in combination with good music, food, drinks (and you should see the whiskey collection) gives you The Roan rooftop! Check it out!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5098, 'Eric O', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r397134464-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best hangout in Kisumu Cty, Anytime, Anyday!', 'I am a local at the roan, I come here to work, dine, dance and party. The wifi is the best you can find in Kisumu city and in the day, it has the perfect ambience for writing over a few beers. I have hosted a few office partys as well, really good service and great food for such occassions. And on any Thur, Fri and Sat, its the perfect place to hang out and drink.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5099, 'muchuih', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r397124284-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Roan - Mwisho wa mawazo', 'Great hosts, lead by the Team leader, Harold, the staff make you feel home. They preempt your needs and treat you like loyalty. \n\nBeautiful ambiance, finger licking food and the choice of music is simply awesome!!!\n\nWhether you live in or around Kisumu or you are a traveler, this is a must tick Roan in your bucket list of must visit places.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5100, 'James U', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r390685444-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice food.', 'Quite some nice food, staff taking time though to attend to customers.\n\nGreat ambiance though.\n\nIn the CBD, could probably check on time taken to attend to customers.\n\nNice live bands by the way.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5101, 'Winter c', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r386841499-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Beautiful interior and delicious food!', 'The wet fried fish was delicious and filling. I loved the interior decor as well... The beautiful fabric on the ceiling, the dark wood tables and the open windows all round that bring in a cool breeze!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5102, 'r0dneylc', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r384150081-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best seafood in town', 'We went here for our anniversary and really enjoyed the experience.  The only downside was that the music was too loud for us to easily talk to one another, but the food and the view made up for it.  The wine was also quite good!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5103, 'Paul E', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r380292173-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice Food Long Climb', 'We visited yesterday evening and had a nice meal. My husband had some snapper and I had peri peri prawns, the snapper was delicious, both meals were served with rice and vegetables. The staff were friendly and helpful and sitting at one of the tables by the open windows you get not only a good view of the town and some of the lake, but you get a refreshing breeze too.  The downside is the long climb up a very dingy staircase, with no signage to let you know if your in the right place or heading the right way That said we both agreed we would return', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5104, 'Tonny O', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r376000971-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nothing beats the lake view and food  from the Roan Rooftop', 'dropped by for a quick lunch and was impressed.fabulous food and service.Great view of the lake and what a whiskey collection.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(5105, 'Michael D', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r375092969-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice Place', 'Good food, good prices, good service. They have wi-fi and a nice view over one of the busier streets in Kisumu, with the lake in the distance. It\'s right across the street from the Imperial Express Hotel. The wife and l each had fish, which was fresh and tasted good.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5106, 'mcooley31', 'Lolwe Drive, Milimani, Kisumu', 'The Roan Garden Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d10179506-r370049494-The_Roan_Garden_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great place to eat, drink, and hang out!', 'The seafood at The Roan is Excellent, but that is only part of the experience!  This rooftop bar also offers an amazing whiskey selection, great views of Kisumu city and the Lake Victoria sunset!  The wrap around open windows also allow for a nice cool lake breeze, no matter how hot it is outside!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:52:27', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5107, 'harunani k', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r813577691-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Too expensive', 'Good ambience but too expensive food.taste of food is good but quantity little.they have a good style of keeping customers- salad comes immediately so you can\'t run away without ordering main meal.Youll enjoy your meal only if you are rich.for average guys like us, difficult to return here', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5108, 'Byron78', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r739782436-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Solid classic', 'Reliable lunch and dinner venue with a massive new conference hall which houses a new gym venue too.\nBuffet on friday with a wide range of veg and non veg at a fair price.Restuarant still does a variety of indian and continental dishes that are quite superb.Open 7 days a week and they do outside catering too.Ample parking and security allow lots of privacy too.\nGo enjoy.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5109, 'Dinesh S', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r720499309-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Excellent Cuisine, really lovely food', 'The cuisine is predominantly indian. The food served was excellent. A trip to kisumu would be incomplete without a visit to the place. Well done Raj and team.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5110, 'Triple A', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r707817166-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good Value for money', 'The Friday Buffet is good value for money in a laid back open atmosphere.  The live cooking station was the highlight of the evening with the freshly made Naan and stir fry chicken going down well with drinks and laughter.\nThe wine list is very limited, so don\'t carry too much expectation there.  Prices are very fair.  \nThe place is called Simba club but signage says Sikh Union - confusing for out of towners who do not know Kisumu well.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5111, 'harunani k', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r668160025-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Always wanting more', 'A trip to kisumu without dining at simba club/sikh union club is not called a trip.this is the best buffet place in kenya iv been to.they serve both veg and non veg which are amazing.plus they serve desert too .the only disadvantage is that buffet is only on friday night.and 1k per person for v.delicious and variety of food is v.afordable.keep up the excellent job.lookin forward to dining there again', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5112, 'Byron78', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r617916097-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Exquisite', 'This is a sports club with an restaurant that does predominantly Indian food with a smattering of continental dishes.Located on the main  Ksm-Kakamega highway opposite Ksm girls with a further entrance at the back just opposite Khetias.\n Large parking area at the front and back and there is a very large new hall that has been constructed away from the main building.\nWalking through the arch,one enters a quaint courtyard with tables set in the bandas and the open air hall.\nService is attentive and pleasant with Chef Raaj in full control,ensuring each dish passes his scrutiny before dispatch to ones table,One can also order and pick uo your dishes.\nOn friday the reasonably priced famous buffet is still on and has a wide variety of non veg and veg dishes.\nThis is a unique place worth checking out.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5113, '424abida', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r598311480-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Marriage of Simran Chatte', 'A lovely historic venue. Grand Hall, great searing area. Lunch was served consisting of a great variety of Indian food. Most tasty. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5114, 'romanholiday28', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r552002046-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Fantastic', 'Went with a friend who lives in Kisumu and really enjoyed the food. Chef Raj is a delightful chap and we had a memorable evening, The Rajoli kebab was the best iv eaten anywhere and lemon prawns were divine.. I mean I was wary ordering prawns 600 km from the coast,  but they were fresh, flavourful and perfectly cooked. Highly recommended! A must if in Kisumu', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5115, 'nabiebayoh', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r541666678-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'All that you can eat Indian food on Friday nights in Kisumu', 'A good selection of Indian cuisines, best for group dinning - friends, colleagues, family. Avoid getting there late, else some of the best will be out and you may be in a long queue (though the queue is worth it!)', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5116, 'Byron78', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r515098896-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Tasty,wholesome food.', 'During the post election period not many establishments were open,here however they are always open and good food appears to be a guarantee.\n  A small group of us sat in the large dining banda.The menu covers Indian,continental and some chinese dishes too.We ordered a smattering of Chinese dishes and relaxed.Being fairly spacious the tables are not jammed up next to each other so conversation is comfortable.The waiters are a friendly bunch and swiftly brought our starters of chicken wings and fish fingers.Our mains followed,good wholesome dishes though the rice dishes were a tad small.\n Quick service,good food in small town kisumu,one cant go wrong in visiting this place.The mall next door is a few metres away too for tuks tuks and boda bodas.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5117, 'neil d', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r467142851-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Simba of Indian food in Town', 'This place is where you go if  you want proper indian cuisine thy the Chicken al Simba  or the buffet every Friday highly recommended ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5118, 'Elizakwamboka', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r449269161-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great Friday Night Indian buffet', 'Great Friday night buffet of Indian cuisine for a good price.  Have been many times over many years. The breads are particularly delicious from the clay pot.  Lots of choice. Always a colourful affair as many residents are wearing their sparkling outfits.  It does start quite late though.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5119, 'Valerio M', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r433667237-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Caratteristico ', 'Bel pub, buone le birre artigianali. Stiamo sempre parlando dell\'Africa e a mio avviso non pensavo avessero delle birre cos√¨ buone. Musica locale bella e piacevole. Quando si ritorna a casa si ha sempre nostalgia dell\'Africa e del suo caratteristico \"mal d\'Africa\"! Beh anche i loro pub hanno il loro perch√© e questo potrebbe essere un punto pi√π per tornarci! ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'negative', '[]'),
(5120, 'spanner48', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r413504375-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Quite \"Indian Colonial\" in feel. But good food.', 'Tucked away down a back street, but very large, once you get through the gates.  There\'s almost a maidan, between the walls, with tables set out round the edges, outside, but under cover.\n\nFood is mostly Indian [mostly north Indian/Gujerati] plus Chinese. Nothing exceptional, but good and reliable.\n\nService was a little slow, but friendly.  \n\nDoesn\'t take credit cards.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5121, 'Ratimo A', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r396285514-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Delicious Indian cuisine buffet', 'I have been here a couple of times for their Friday night buffet. Begins at 9pm. Costs Ksh750 which isn\'t exactly cheap but for what you get, you would pay a lot more at a restaurant. Its all you can eat buffet so get there early and get in the queue. If you are late you mght find that some of the buffet options are finished.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]');
INSERT INTO `restaurant_reviews` (`id`, `author_name`, `place_address`, `place_name`, `review_url`, `review_title`, `review_text`, `review_rating`, `location`, `created_at`, `predicted_sentiment`, `predicted_aspects`) VALUES
(5122, 'Skip B', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r361359047-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Luxury', 'Great food, and not too pricy. It\'s normally the home base for a rotary club. The staff is nice, and the atmosphere is more formal than other restaurants.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5123, 'Shreyash P', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r356471706-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'lovely food', 'Owner has a string of hotels and restaurants, food is always consistent and good, staff are friendly ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(5124, 'Katherine S', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r317140641-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Odd venue but good selection of well made food', 'The Simba Club is a venue large venue -perfect for parties- but is pretty heavy on the concrete and lacking charm. That being said, they have a great selection of Indian and local food that are well prepared and usually not very slow, either. Note that it can be hard to find a piki-piki (motorcycle taxi) outside on the road, so come prepared with the name and number of someone to pick you up at the end of the night or be prepared to walk 10-15mins South (turn left when exiting) until you reach Tusky\'s supermarket to find a piki-piki.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5125, 'TrvlBlue', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r312589369-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'spacious , relaxed open air  location  for group event', 'nice place to have a good food and good time. the service is excellent , very efficient service. polite and swift staff . enjoyed the evening thoroughly ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5126, 'Kyle M', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r257219097-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great Indian food ', 'The Friday night buffet for 750 Ksh will be good for your stomach and your sole. Some of the best Indian food I\'ve had in Kisumu! Haven\'t been on any other night yet though. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(5127, 'annegwynn', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r243792122-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Don\'t Miss the Friday Night Buffets', 'Go on Friday nights at 9 pm for the most amazing Indian buffet! There is a huge variety of food, all for only 750 KSH. Go very, very hungry!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5128, 'hnyamori', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r227985962-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good for buffet on Friday nights...', 'Located between United Mall and main bus park, Simba club is a members establishment that allows temporary membership to diners. Friday nights buffets are the main attraction to non-members with tasty Indian cuisine. The menu is well balanced, ambience average, service good. It looks  obscure during the day but comes alive in the evening, colorful, breezy. Yum..!!', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5129, 'olung39ati', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r219709077-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Famliy night out', 'The food is amazing and the indians make customers feel at home.The food and hospitality makes one feel at home,the location make sit easy to access.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5130, 'Serena K', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r155757724-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Friday Night Buffet', 'The word on the street is that the past owner of the Club use to serve dinner to the public every Friday night, and the new owner has continued this tradition.  This is buffet style Indian food (and some Italian- which never made sense to me) at a good price- I want to say approx 1200KSH + drinks.  The food was okay- but at all you can eat, with a nice mix of local Indians and ExPats, it\'s a good time!  Drinks are extra, service is good, outdoor seating, watch out for the mosquitos.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5131, 'ReneeML88', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r152690373-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'YUM!', 'a little over priced, but nice and relaxing sitting in an open air restaurant and the food was awesome!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5132, 'coyot9', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r149934369-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'All you can eat Fridays', 'They have a huge buffet on Fridays. You pay 750 shillings (jacked up from 500, might change again) and you get amazing Indian food. They have some vegetarian options. You get ice cream at the end. It\'s pretty magical.\n\nThey get you on drinks. A beer is expensive for Kisumu, something like two-fifty bob, and they gut you if you order a water, like a hundred shillings.\n\nIt\'s a cool setup. The seating is semi-open air, underneath the first floor. If it pours down rain, no one gets wet. They also have fully-open air seating. Kisumu never gets cold, its usually very pleasant in the evening.\n\nIt starts a little after the sun goes down, maybe around 19:30. You might want to check first. You shouldn\'t need to make reservations, just show up.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5133, 'dudiegirl', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r136096287-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'basic decoration and atmosphere but good food.', 'the food here was really tasty, however the tables were all outside resulting in a ridiculous amount of mozzies attacking you while trying to enjoy dinner. the staff were all lovely as well and were more then happy to call taxi\'s etc. ', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5134, 'DEV', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r128317232-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'must visit place in kisumu', 'simba club offer lots of facilities like games, restaurants, family get togethers, and other social ceremonies.. this club is for club members only. food quality is good with a fanatic look of lake victoria. you can drink and dine majestically at outdoor garden restaurant. nice place.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5135, 'Denise R', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r122355312-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great for late dinner Friday evenings.', 'My first taste of Kenyan Indian cuisine and it is delicious. A large variety of dishes to choose from and the price is right (about $6.00 USD for all you can eat!)', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5136, 'adventurersKisumu', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r121754602-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'simba club- pub n restaurant', 'food very good and the friday nite buffet a must to try...', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(5137, 'cmeliw', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r121556144-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'A feast', 'Simba has a friday night dinner that is open to the public.  Amazing Indian food.  Fresh Naan Bread.  Clean tables/dishes.  \n\nExcellent!  Cost 500 kes per person.   Worth it!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5138, 'Ceboyer', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r120406912-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Excellent Indian Buffet on Fridays', 'Friday nights, starting at 9pm (late I know, but worth it), there is an Indian buffet held here. This is a favorite of ex-pats and NGO workers. Food is amazing and all you can eat, including dessert!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5139, 'KendalVisayas', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r119031059-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good taste and value, friendly and helpful service', 'Don\'t get me wrong, this is no palace, it is open air eating near to the hockey pitch on Jomo Kenyatta Highway. It is not a private club; anyone can eat there. There are very few good eating establishments in Kisumu; only three I have personal knowledge of. Simba Club is probably the best value and has a varied menu of mainly Indian Food with all the accompanying rices and breads, cooked to the heat you prefer. You get a generous portion of fresh, tasty and free salad while you wait for your orders. The waiters are very friendly and will accommodate any reasonable food requests. Since I temporarily reside in the area, I usually order about three times what I can eat and take out the rest for later, which serves another couple of meals (about $15 for all). I particularly like the spicy mushroom starter, veg patties, Chicken Kadai and Chicken Tikka (though they give it a different name).', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5140, 'Byron78', 'Jomo Kenyatta Highway Its the big walled compound next to United mall', 'Simba Club', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d2170653-r113778416-Simba_Club-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Quality,Cheap and great waiters', 'Visited this place in June with friends from overseas.We had heard of the Friday buffet which was available for ¬£5.The dining area is a large hall plus they have bandas around the edges of the courtyard.The waiters are a friendly bunch and quite happy to help out with different dietary requirements.The buffet was a mixture of veg and non veg plus dessert of ice cream ,fruit and cake.Apparently this was buffet was an old custom and the current owners had to carry on this tradition.We came back the following day to try the a la carte which was mostly asian food with some western choices thrown in.The pork chops were superb as was the Tikka and other asian dishes we ordered.The bill came to under ¬£30 or 3000 kshs for 3 of us.\n   Apparently the Simba Club has a hockey team that plays in the National League and were the leading team for decades,so watching a hockey match followed by dinner is the next plan.They have a seperate sports bar which looked under utilised when we popped our heads in.Maybe good to catch the rugby WC there.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:54:17', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5141, 'Rahul Amin', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r689469909-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The meat...', 'All the meat dishes are wicked. Mishkaki chicken> lamb. Tandori chicken breast> leg. Sheek kebabs are top. Naans are crisp and buttery. Ice cream to cool off at the end', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(5142, 'Byron78', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r683944399-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Tandoori outdoors', 'Located in swan/sansora mall.Have the grills out the front in the evening.Wide menu of biryani,samosas,kebabs  etc.Grilled meats done freshly ,tasty and hits the spot.Not the cheapest place but the service is pleasant and easy going and cleanliness appears to be a good trait.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5143, 'wayne y', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r670455192-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Amazing Chicken Mushikaki!!', 'We visited Al Noor last evening for dinner.  The tandoori oven and the grills are outside which is unique.  Last evening we were interrupted by a rain storm which delayed our meal a little and forced us to move inside.  They have a good sized menu of vegetarian and non vegetarian choices. My wife ate the chili paneer and I ate the chicken mushikaki.  The chili paneer was good but not exceptional (The best chili paneer in town is at Laughing Bhudda).  The chicken mushikaki was excellent.  The flavor was very good and the chicken cubes were moist and not dried out like chicken breast is sometimes.  I ordered it spicy (hot) and it was, but it was delicious.  If you are sensitive to spice tell your waiter.  Even their mild spice can be quite hot.  Our waiter went missing for awhile and did not check up on us after the initial service, though he did a good job with that.  Their prices may be a little higher than some similar places in Kisumu.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5144, 'budgetlust', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r584368198-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Outdoor Seating, Decent Food', 'I had the veggie samosa and a pineapple pizza. The veggie samosa was pretty good, but was spicy which I could have done without. (priced around 70 ksh, I believe). \nThe pineapple pizza was less than satisfying. The cheese in Kenya in general is not the cheese I\'m used to in America. It\'s flavorless and has a weird texture to it, which throws everything else off. The pizza was around 500 ksh, I would not get it again. Menu has a decent variety to chose from but service is very slow, they even state on the menu to expect a long wait on evening entrees. It is all or almost all outdoor seating, which is nicer than being cooped up inside.', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5145, 'Al-Karim Mitha', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r567628765-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best chicken tika in town ', 'I always go to Al noors cafeteria for my weekly doze of their amazing chicken tika and naan .. \nthe service  is great the chutneys are amazing... i highly recommend their milk shakes and fresh juices to wash down their usually spicy food ( medium is the way to order) \ncan‚Äôt wait to go back next week .. keep it up and see you soon ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5146, 'Ali K', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r471917316-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'WOSRT FOOD AND SERVICE', 'Pathetic service, the waiter doesn\'t even get the orders right, less than average food, very bland. Horrible experience. I\'m never ever going back to this place!!!!!! Keep off.', 1, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5147, 'nabiebayoh', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r469582350-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Al-Noor Cafe best for chicken tikka in Kisumu', 'Sit outdoors, order chicken tikka and nan bread, dont forget to indicate how not so spicy you like your food. While you are waiting try some cheese kima chapati!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(5148, 'ENTHALPHY', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r460707075-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'A LOVELY DINNER', 'Excellent food ,classic ambiance and swarming with people after dusk ,it is a favorite with the ex pats ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5149, 'bobbymoore13', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r458476832-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'oh the nan at this place is amazing...', 'i really could just make a meal from the nan, but all the food is great.  the staff is helpful and it\'s a great place to enjoy a meal.  don\'t miss this spot.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5150, 'pankaj537', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r458436562-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Modest Price Great Food !', 'Its a modest place very conveniently situated on the main road near Swan Centre in Kisumu. Operated by a 3rd Generation Owner, always smiling , very courteous and polite. \nThe place was recommended to us by a friend, and we were not disappointed. Excellent quality of food, especially the Tilapia Fish especially recommended by the Owner as a must try ! \nIts a town on Lake Victoria, the catch of the day is fresh ! \nAnd for those who love the \'indian paan\' , the Owner takes pride in making a great one since the leaves are sourced from the markets in India  ! \nAsk for a \'sweet variety one\'. \nAt night the Owner sets up a BBQ and one can see cars driving up after ordering on the phone ! \nWe enjoyed our late night dinner meal and all of the interesting chat with a 3rd Generation Kenyan Citizen.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5151, 'Kalie G', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r454527762-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'One of my favorites in Kisumu.  Yes, get the tikka specials!', 'Al Noor is in my top three for Kisumu.  The chicken tikka is amazing, be aware that they start cooking it fresh at 7:30 pm or so in the evening!  Also the poussin paneer (I recommend spicy) is addictive.  The family that runs Al Noor is also incredibly kind and they care a great deal about their food!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5152, 'Allan O', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r393841732-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great Food, Great Price', 'I had the best fish masala ever in my life at this joint. The location and ambience can be deceiving but the food didn\'t disappoint. Could do with better service though.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5153, 'MissTravelFiend', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r349035591-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Tasty BBQ dishes -- good for takeaway food', 'The food here is very good and the portions are huge (especially the biriani), although the menu is super confusing. The tables are out on the sidewalk and the atmosphere is very laid back, which is why I was a bit surprised at how pricey it is. Another downside is that they do not serve any alcohol. With this in mind, I would recommend it for takeaways, but not so much for sit-down dining.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5154, 'Ciku', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r339220551-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'not fancy but the food is worth it', 'based on previous review, my hubby and i went here. I was unimpressed by the ambience but all that was compensated for when they brought the chicken tikka (YUM!!) Watch out, though, their version of mildly spicy is the average person\'s moderately spicy. I had to have a cold drink with my Tikka. I saw 2 grown men struggle to finish one serving of biryani hahaha!! there was literally a mountain of food on that plate! \nPlease note that they close on Tuesdays, I was so disappointed \n:(', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5155, 'Herbert D', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r293949763-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nice barbecue Chicken in Kisumu', 'If you want some good barbecued chicken in Kisumu then try this place.  The restaurant offers both indoor and outdoor seating on the pavement.  Very popular in the evening with takeaways and sitting customers.  ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5156, 'Vinicius0392', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r291148100-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Gostei da Alnoor Cafeteria', 'Gostei bastante da alnoor cafeteria. Tem um excelente expresso e boa variedade de comidas para se tomar um bom breakfast', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[]'),
(5157, 'Ratimo A', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r288774618-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The biriani is top notch', 'I love this restauarant!!Been here quite a number of times. The chicken biriani here is top notch. A tad pricey but for what you get its totally worth it. And its enough for like five people. So value for money actually. The service is quie good as well. And the food is served to order so you have to wait a little bit. A great place for an evening date. You can sit in their outdoor area and get the lake breeze.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5158, 'vivekrajdev81', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r282891272-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best food ', 'This is the best place to have chicken tikka, and everything else on the menu\n\nFood is made fresh and trust me you will want to eat there every aine say\n\nIn my opinion this is the best place to eat tikka in East Africa, it is worth taking a flight or driving down to Kisimu for. ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5159, 'Ayush N', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r260786412-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best Chicken Tikka EVER..!', 'Being a Kisumu Resident Al Noor is a fortnightly ordeal. When I was away for University , the one thing I missed most about home was Al Noor\'s Tikka. Goes great with the Butter Naan. Meatlovers should add some Mushkaki.\n\nKisumu is still evolving and so is Al Noor but the the Tikka better not change..!!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[]'),
(5160, 'Kyle M', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r257409813-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Chicken Tika!! ', 'Some of the best chicken I\'ve ever had! But this is definitely a dinner spot. Curries etc are all right but they fire up the outdoor grill after dark and grill your chicken tika right in front of you!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5161, 'EAZG', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r255995688-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great chicken tikka', 'My family loves the chicken tikka (one of my favorite things in Kisumu) -- pili pili and very flavorful, and good naan.The grilled items are the best but know that dinner fromthe grill starts late (often after 8 or later). A plate of pilau is huge. Ice cream shakes not super, but they have nicely frozen ice cream to choose from (not once-melted) . Also pan for after dinner (ask for an explanation). Note that no alcohol is served or allowed. . ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"speed_wait\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5162, 'MichaelSabry', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r242389431-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'One of the best restaurants in town', 'It\'s one of the best restaurants in Kisumu. the only problem that all the grilled meals/food are done after 6 PM. I tried many dishes and meals and was never disappointed. the service is good and the place is clean. as we stay near Kisumu we usually take our friends their for the BBQ. the desserts are not v.good. the menu is big and has many varieties. By the way no alcoholic drinks are served.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5163, 'Charity H', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r237675271-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great meals!', 'Great place to have Indian food. The waiting time can be a bit long especially if its a busy weekend. Generally the food is good, tried the Biryani which is fairly priced and serves 3-we had to do a take away! Drinks are also quite fresh, hope to have milkshake in my next visit.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5164, 'Ruth M', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r236500672-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Very Nice Vegeterian dishes', 'I love the fact that it is a vegetarian restaurant within Kisumu Town and they can offer you some alcohol if you need some.\nI Dislike it when they have parties though,it gets too loud and spoils the whole dinner experience', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5165, 'Michael M', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r232695114-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best chicken in Kisumu', 'When you want to have some Indian BBQ tandoori chicken, this is the place. They also have a lot of other great menu items, most of which are BBQ items. Their milkshakes are also fantastic -- I recommend one of these three flavors: saffron (for a hot afternoon), espresso (for a mid-morning wake-up jolt) and faloodah kesar baddam (for post-BBQ dessert). \n\nOn days/nights when they aren\'t doing the tandoori oven, the main dishes are genuinely subpar and I would recommend going across the street to Gopala or next door to Laughing Buddha. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5166, 'Byron78', 'Swan Centre, Kisumu', 'Alnoor Cafeteria', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d4473604-r209243808-Alnoor_Cafeteria-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Grilled meat', 'Nice place located at Swan centre.Has the grill outside and does a varierty of foods,like tikkas,kebabs,mushkaki,etc the aroma around the area is enticing to say the least.\n There are many tables on the sidewalk  which they share with the vegetarian restaurant next door.The service is quick and efficent though the Friday night i went,they were chock full and the food was not all great,the tikka was over burnt but im assured this was due to the rush of orders,the rest of our food was tender and well done and delicious.The costs are average,we paid 2000/- for two people and it is  apleasant place,just try avoiding it when very busy.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:56:28', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
