(5168, 'nabiebayoh', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r539499773-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Best place for Ethiopian cuisine', 'A quiet place that is good for conversation and a finger licking Ethiopian style sauces both vegetarian and non-vegetarian. Good idea to call and order the meal ahead of your visit if you want their signature Ethiopian meal, preparation can take a long while.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5169, 'Bas Jan K', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r513278189-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Amazing restaurant and hotel ', 'Nice atmosphere and a beautiful garden.  We had a lovely time in the hotel and had some good meals! I recommend the Ethiopian coffee experience.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5170, 'NaipaulJ', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r499734024-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Excellent food, little out of the way', 'Had dinner here with a friend. The food is excellent and decently priced. Service is quite friendly. The location is a little bit out of the way but worth the trip.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5171, 'Alyse', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r477942287-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Fantastic service and food!!!', 'This place was amazing. The staff were so nice and I loveddddd all the delicious food! The coffee room is just lovely, and the ambiance is very welcoming.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5172, 'md a', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r456638423-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Delicious food', 'Was ther with few local friends. Their foods, exspecially meat was yummy. Near and vegetable ate with one kind of rooti. That rooti little bit saure, I wish it\'s serve without saure.\nEnvironment was awesome, there are many forwigners was there to have dinner.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5173, 'Ratimo A', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r453512993-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Not sure I would go back', 'Decided to try out this restaurant one evening while with a friend. I have had Ethiopian Injera before and thought maybe I should scope out the place. Its hidden in a residential neigborhood away from town. I had heard good things about their food but was sorely disappointed. The tables and chairs are so dated and dusty I wasn\'t sure whether the place was operational any more. The young lady whom served us was disinterested to say the least. The menu was a tad overpriced. We had coffee, juice and popcorn. Nothing to write home about. We had to wait forever for our change and basically had ot go into the kitchen to get it. Seemed to me that they are understaffed and we were the only customers in view. In the current state definitely would not venture here again anytime soon', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5174, 'Karen N', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r437446842-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Sad decline', 'We first visited this restaurant a couple of years ago. The waiters were all smiles and we really enjoyed our coffee and popcorn: typical Ethiopian snack, as well as some samosas and sausage. Last month we went back hoping for a repeat experience. The tables are so dusty with the varnish dry and faded, and the smiling waiters were gone. There was just one girl who looked so bored or disillusioned and half hardheartedly wiped our table. The only thing available on the menu was the coffee and popcorn, no other snacks. I was afraid to ask for food because I would not be sure it was fresh. We just left.', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5175, 'gw472016', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r417829884-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Not any more what it was', 'With change of Management this once fine ethiopian restaurant became horrible!\nIndschera horrible\nTibbes horrible\n\nAlthough the service is still friendly no place to go for ethiopian food anymore', 1, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5176, 'Roger W', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r406884765-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Amazing food, beautiful location', 'The food is really delicious. The restaurant is situated a little outside of the crowded town but you can reach the centre in 5-10 minutes. The garden is beautiful and the staff is incredibly helpful and friendly. You should check out there guest rooms as well. Perfect stay, thank you so much, will definitely be back soon.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5177, 'Bas Jan K', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r401679044-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great restaurant', 'We ate lovely Ethiopian food and had a great time eating in the beautiful garden. Michael the manager is an amazing host and greets you with a smile. Besides eating it also is a great place to sleep.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5178, 'Lana W', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r399592197-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Traditional experience, fantastic service', 'I booked for a large group, and the owner Michael was so accommodating for all our needs, calling me several times to confirm the menu and our seating preferences... the food tasted great and it was a very traditional experience, everyone in the group wanted to go back! They were also bringing out a new indian menu to go along side the ethiopian stuff!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5179, 'Bernie R', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r391246318-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Not a fan but good service', 'Didn\'t enjoy the food but that\'s just my  taste! Excellent service and loved the coffee and popcorn! Catered well for our group of 12', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\"]'),
(5180, 'BetinaTravels8', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r366337938-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'NOT GOOD ENOUGH ', 'We were not  able to eat any of the food that we ordered for. And the packaging of food is way below average ,although they have a nice garden. ', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"delivery_takeout\"]'),
(5181, 'J G', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r361432303-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Amazing food experience, quiet garden ', 'I have visited Habesha twice, and both times were great. Ask the manager for advice. I love the white round ethiopian \'bread\' with several sauces of meat or beans. \nThe Garden is a very lovely place to sit quitely outside. ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5182, 'EdenMariet', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r361103957-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Quiet nice garden, good food', 'Quiet nice garden, helpfull staff and amazing food. The experience of eating ethiopian food is one you should not miss out on!', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5183, 'hnyamori', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r346045571-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'A good attempt at Ethiopian cuisine', 'Tucked in  a peaceful garden, Habesha offers a wonderful relaxed culinary experience to residents and visitors to the lakeside city of Kisumu. The food is tasty, service polite but slow; the food pales a bit compared to other Ethiopian restaurants I have visited - it\'s like they have not put their heart to it, or some ingredients are missing.m I would have loved more variety, say \"Kitfo\", or \" Shiro- wot\" for example. Could they consider \"theft\" for the \"injera\" bread?The coffee (buna) was good, the ambience good, the price affordable. It is a good attempt at Ethiopian cuisine, a good addition to Kisumu\'s culinary landscape.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5184, 'Mark_S_1957', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r336519917-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'The garden setting is beautiful!', 'The food was fantastic; there was lots of it and it was well-prepared. I ate there my first full day in Kisumu and it helped set the tone for the rest of my 2.5 weeks there. Sitting under a tree, eating at a leisurely pace and chatting with my daughter, her partner and one of their friends was a perfect cure for jet-lag. It is a little out of the way but worth hunting it down.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5185, 'Jan J', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r334031704-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Little Paradise ', 'The house and its garden are amazing. Perfect place to spend a relaxed afternoon. It took a while till the meal was served. This place is not for people in a hurry. The food was good even though the mixed vegetarian plate was with less veggies than in other ethiopian restaurants. The ethiopian coffee is worth to try. The service was very competent and friendly. Habesha is a good and affordable choice.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5186, 'Raappu', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r331590274-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Relaxing and tasty', 'Habesha is set in a peaceful garden and the staff there will make you feel at ease. It\'s an ideal place to relax and take a break from the city.\n\nPrices are also affordable (400-500 shilling per dish) and the food is also good. However, the main thing, which will bring me back to Habesha is the atmosphere. Furthermore, the Ethiopian coffee is excellent!', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5187, 'MissTravelFiend', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r331546073-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Lovely Ethiopian cuisine', 'It\'s a little bit out of the way and hard to find if you don\'t have your own vehicle but I love the food here -- Delicious. The service is friendly and quick and the little garden is lovely to sit in. Altogether a great dining experience. Do visit if you get a chance. ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5188, 'Katherine S', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r316855953-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Hard to find but wonderful food!', 'The food here is really fantastic and it\'s the only place to get Ethiopian in Kisumu. You dine in a lovely garden setting. The location is very difficult to find and a little far north in the city. My best advice is to follow Jomo Kenyatta Highway (heading North) until you\'ve just passed Marie Stopes on you left. You\'ll then see a sign on your left for Habesha. Continue following the signs, even when you\'re heading down a semi-circular dirt road that doesn\'t seem to end and you start doubting yourself because there are no more signs...the restaurant will finally appear on your right hand side. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5189, '·ûò·üâ·üÇ·ûì ·ûü', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r295490480-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Will be back', 'I went with friends to this restaurant, a nice tea and dinner is done, is shaped and helps to eat, we will be back.', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"drinks\"]'),
(5190, 'Pranav Shah', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r291522654-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Not good for food', 'The place is good as to the location though hard to locate. Green sorounding really good specially if u r from the concrete city. But not worth taking the pain if u r only going for food. The taste is not good at all.', 2, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5191, 'Kyle M', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r257219648-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'A garden paradise a little outside the city ', 'Hard to find, but once you do you\'ll be glad you did. I\'d recommend going during the day, it\'s a nice place to cool down from sweltering heat. Cold beer and very solid Ethiopian food. The best I\'ve found in the short time I\'ve been living in Kisumu. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5192, 'MichaelSabry', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r252853898-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good Ethiopian food in Kisumu !', 'I visited this restaurant like 3 or 4 times and i was introduced to it by a work colleague. I love Ethiopian food and my experience here wasn\'t that bad. Sharing the same name with another Ethiopian restaurant in Nairobi but i believe they are not related. Well,the food was OK not as good as the Ethiopian restaurants in Nairobi,prices are fair and the service is good. it\'s located in a a very interior place so you should know the directions before heading there.I always hear cars moving around the wall so i guess they are close to a main road and I believe if they managed to create a gate on that main road they would get more customers as i believe many people don\'t know there\'s an Ethiopian restaurant in town. they should do more concerning marketing and cleanliness of toilets.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5193, 'Joe O', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r250435658-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good food', 'Habesha is located in Tom Mboya estate in Kisumu.  It is in a secure area serving very good food at reasonable prices for food and drinks.  It is well worth a visit for the food and a good drink.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]');
