(5194, 'Ruth M', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r236498451-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Very deserted place', 'Directions  to the place not clearly marked,place is very deserted and need to improve on their delicacies especially the Injera', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'negative', '[\"location_access\"]'),
(5195, 'clone1969', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r234834171-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'mangiare con le mani ,un esperienza da rifare', 'mi sono recato con amici in questo ristorante ,il posto √® piccolo colori vivaci molto semplice ,la birra etiope √® buona gli antipasti saporiti e speziati ma il piatto forte deve ancora arrivare ecco un grosso vassoio pieno di carne al sugo, patate ,ortaggi in varie preparazioni e tutto si mangia con l\'engera un pane tipo focaccia che si modella e aiuta a mangiare ,un bel the e la cena √® fatta,ci torner√≤ .', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[]'),
(5196, 'Michael M', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r232693805-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'One of Kisumu\'s best restaurants', 'Good food; friendly service; cold beer and nice Ethiopian coffee. I have been here about 10 times and always had consistently positive experiences. \n\nThis place is not mind-blowing, but if you are addicted to Ethiopian food like most of humanity and you are in Kisumu, you won\'t be disappointed. Just don\'t have too high expectations -- if this place was in Ethiopia, DC or Oakland, it would get 3 stars. But come on, it is in Kisumu and in all honesty it is one of the city\'s finest eateries.', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5197, 'Crystall22', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r183232793-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Homey', 'It was a bit difficult to find but overall, we had a good experience.The dish I orded (Key Wot) was good and reasonably priced. ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5198, 'Byron78', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r181592726-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Nondescript', 'Shares a name with a Nairobi Ethiopian restaurant but from wht we were told ,have no connection with them and truly it shows.Its located in the middle of a residential estate on the outskirts of town.Not much signage indicating directions.\n Arrived and im guessing due to the lack of visitors,the staff that emerged were quite surprised.There is a bungalow with rooms to the side of it with a path leading to the back bandas.Ordered the injera and platter of mixed dishes.Pleasant place to sit.Food arrived and really the tastes of Ethiopia were lost somewhere along the way.The piquant taste for some dishes was non existent,basically a bland medley of dishes which then makes the injera a waste.\nHope things do improve as Kisumu does need a variety of cuisines and Habesha has become a byword for good food.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5199, '', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r170807842-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'good exprience', 'I like Ethiopian food and have been to a fair number of Ethiopian restaurants outside Ethiopia. \n\nThe food here was good, though there was nothing outstanding about it. Tibs we ordered were good. \n\nWe had an pleasant experience at the end of the meal.\n\nI\'m sure I\'d go back or recommend this place to friends.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5200, 'laansa', 'Off Indusi Road - Tom Mboya Estate, Kisumu', 'Habesha - Ethiopian Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d3846239-r162380772-Habesha_Ethiopian_Restaurant_in_Kisumu-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Great coffee, indifferent food', 'Nice location in colonial bungalow and garden setting. Worth going just for the coffee which is brewed in the traditional Ethiopian way. Sit outside.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:58:07', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5201, 'Jacqueline J', 'Gor Mahia Rd, Kisumu', 'New Victoria Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214111-r693641325-New_Victoria_Hotel_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Average eatery but good value', 'This place is good for a no frills quick bite. It gets packed so be prepared to share a table with complete strangers. \n\nMy date and I ordered the mutton biryani and fish biryani.  The biryani flavours were spot and the mutton biryani portions was huge! The fish was a bit small and not very fleshy but the tasty biryani sauce made up for it. The service is okay.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:59:47', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5202, 'Rowan', 'Gor Mahia Rd, Kisumu', 'New Victoria Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214111-r649776225-New_Victoria_Hotel_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Good Food Good Price ', 'This restaurant is pretty large with a large menu. The masala fish with chapati is very good & very affordable. They also have samosas. The service is usually decent & they split checks for a large group which was great. ', 5, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:59:47', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5203, 'brianzach8', 'Gor Mahia Rd, Kisumu', 'New Victoria Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214111-r550165694-New_Victoria_Hotel_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'slow service and customer care', 'wait staff are confused and not welcoming they lack proper training on customer care, the food we ordered took long and was served cold after a long wait and no wait staff on the floor to check on the guest, they  don\'t smile and very rude to the guests...i don\'t want to say more  but all in all they NEED PROPER TRAINING AND KINDLY WORK ON THAT and they should know that 1st come 1st serve the service was just poor', 1, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:59:47', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5204, 'Dorthe M', 'Gor Mahia Rd, Kisumu', 'New Victoria Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214111-r487852072-New_Victoria_Hotel_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Hyggeligt sted', 'Dejligt sted ved siden af poolen p√• Vic new hotel. Der kommer ogs√• mange lokale og om fredagen oplevede vi super musik, 4 mands orkester ', 4, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:59:47', 'positive', '[]'),
(5205, 'Karen N', 'Gor Mahia Rd, Kisumu', 'New Victoria Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214111-r437448764-New_Victoria_Hotel_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Love the biriyani', 'This has always been a popular spot for a meal and/or tea. They have plenty of variety from junk food to wholesome meals. We asked for a platter of chicken biriyani; the portion was large enough for two. The rice was good quality,well cooked. the chicken was a roadrunner therefore a bit tough. I would have preferred it cooked longer but it was tasty. Finished off with masala tea which is always good. You can ask for extra masala in your tea if you like it really spicy. Just don\'t order sausage here. They use a strange tasting halal brand\n', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:59:47', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5206, 'ankeet_sinha', 'Gor Mahia Rd, Kisumu', 'New Victoria Hotel Restaurant', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g317064-d1214111-r394981422-New_Victoria_Hotel_Restaurant-Kisumu_Nyanza_Province.html', 'Average hotel but best one which is clean and spacy', 'It is an average hotel located in the heart of Kisumu. The food options are good but they run short of several items on many occasions. Good value for money though and it has a good clean and spacious ambience.', 3, 'Kisumu', '2025-11-24 18:59:47', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
