(5334, 'Heather', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r1017759040-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Beautiful grounds ', 'I had an avocado and tomato panini with chips (french fries). The sandwich was bland, but filling. The staff were nice and the grounds were pretty, with both indoor and outdoor seating (in tents with heaters if necessary). There is an art gallery onsite as well, with beautiful pieces.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5335, 'Huzefa H', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r969829727-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Terrible to the core', 'Most racist restaurant in nairobi, the rude staff only are trained to serve whites n they literally ignore other diners ,action should be taken againts them for being of colonial mentality in this age. BOYCOTT MATBRONZE', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'negative', '[\"service\"]'),
(5336, 'Dakley', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r960719331-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great spot for lunch', 'We had the opportunity to go for lunch at Matbronze Cafe.  We had told our driver, Max that we would like to have lunch in Nairobi and this was where he took us to.  It is beautifully located, although down a rather rough and bumpy road to get to, but a serene oasis once you arrive.  The dining tables are located outdoor on the grounds of the restaurant under dining tent/gazebos.  The menu was vast and the food we ordered was tasty.  The gallery that is attached to the restaurant is beautiful with some unique pieces.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5337, 'seventyeight enterprise', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r953155746-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Best place to enjoy dinner ', 'Very cute nice staff and secure place good place to be . Soon I will be back to be there\nI also like the management for open hearted ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5338, 'Walter A', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r939374192-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Urban Paradise', 'I was referred to Matbronze as a lunch spot after going to the Nairobi National Park. What a surpise.! This is a cool place. I will  not comment on the art because I was focused on getting food, but the art was beautiful. \n\nSeveral Nairobi restaurants incorporate the outdoors, but Matbronze was unique.  It felt like a full nature park. The tables are in small tents, which provide privacy.\n\nThe food was very good and at a fair price. The wings had a vibrant flavor. I had spinach and feta samosas, which were excellent.  We got pork ribs that had a unique flavor that reflected the Kenyan palate. I would return just for that. \n\nI loved it. Matbronze was a perfect retreat.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5339, 'MichiganLaurena', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r939062096-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent lunch while enjoying activities in Karen.', 'In the past, while visiting the sculpture area, I\'ve had just coffee and other beverages. This time I had lunch and it was especially good.  I had a cheeseburger and the salad bar.  Portions are generous and reasonably priced.  Servers are excellent.  It\'s a really nice place to have lunch in the shade and relax from the long flights while visiting other sites in the area like the Sheldrick elephants and the Galleria Mall for some shopping. My driver for the day enjoyed it as well.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5340, 'Abeda H', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r936502478-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great ambience', 'A really nice place with such calming ambience . The birds and butterflies give it a serene touch . Food is good . A good place to go relax over lunch or coffee', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5341, 'Divasco C', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r936499839-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Don\'t bring guests here as a driver', 'This is the last place I will ever bring guests as a driver who specialises in Airport Transfers and Excursions.\nNo water for the driver or even lunch after a long drive trying to bring them guests.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5342, 'Henrietta', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r935232600-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Perfect calm time. ', 'Privacy is top notch and the serenity as well.Friendly staff and quick services. \nLoved the art gallery experience üòç and jewellery. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5343, 'Francine S', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r927851565-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Private, great ambiance, serene and cozy', 'The dining experience was fab. We used one of the tented space and it was quite an experience and the heavy drizzle added to the wonderful experience.\n\nWe had the mega breakfast which was great. Excellent service from our waiter. Food presentation was off-the-chain and quite tasty and filling. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5344, 'Benbuzz', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r918518955-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Functional and secluded, peaceful cafe experience ', 'Off the beaten track, secluded cafe suitable for easy inexpensive decent lunch. Food was tasty but service slowish. The ambience was comfortable and gentle. The washing facilities clean. Adjoining the cafe is an art gallery of paintings and bronze animal statues, which all appeared of high quality and prices to match.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5345, 'Suzanne2303', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r911694461-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely place to have lunch after visiting the gallery', 'Good food and service at this lovely cafe set in the gardens surrounding the gallery. We enjoyed a coffee and lunch. My Thai noodles stir fry was delicious and so big I couldn‚Äôt finish it. Very reasonable prices too.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5346, 'Mr P', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r885754148-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'It\'s definitely worth a visit, or more', 'Perfect way to while away a sunny day. Everything from the tree-lined breezy location to the bronze sculptures and jewellery hints at a great time. Excellent food and drink choices, attentive service without being overbearing, and amenities that cater to adults, children, groups, solo, and couple diners. A definite hit.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5347, 'fiamma11', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r868611890-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Delicious in Beautiful Surroundings', 'My son and I had lunch here and enjoyed it so much. I had a sandwich which turned out to be so good; I saved room for dessert because the meringue called to me. The service was excellent and the environs so pleasant. The sculptures were an additional treat. Wish this oasis was near where I live; we would frequent it for certain.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(5348, 'Sally Z', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r862036415-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great Lunch & Amazing Art', 'Wonderfully innovative dishes or a sandwich & chips(fries).  Dine out in the gardens then stroll through the artwork for sale inside.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(5349, 'MMJLM', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r856497356-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely spot for lunch', 'We visited to see the bronze sculptures and then had a very pleasant lunch in the garden (gorgeous resident sunbirds). The strawberry and banana milkshake is out of this world. Friendly and efficient service.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(5350, 'Wilfred Thompson', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r850549326-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great Food and Great Art', 'Top quality burgers - the mega burger especially! The addition of avocado is awesome. Not only is it a fine establishment to sit and eat lunch or have a coffee (must acknowledge that a cold Tusker is cheaper than the most essential ingredient of life itself), but the bronze artwork is spectacular. A Nairobi classic.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5351, 'Oiltraveller', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r849189593-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Nice garden setting', 'Lovely setting in the garden, impressive Elephant head sculpture that is the icon of the sculptor / owner. \n\nHad several meals here and each one was good, quick service and the BBQ buffet is also a good option. \n\nThe added advantage is that you can walk through the studio and browse through the bronze items for sale\n\nPeaceful setting and good service', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5352, 'CossyWombat', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r832742191-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'The food was good and we really enjoyed the exhibition of fine bronzes', 'This was my first visit to this cafe and we enjoyed a lovely lunch in the gardens.  The bronze displays in the two areas was really a nice surprise.  They are of international standard and priced accordingly.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"price_value\"]'),
(5353, 'julie B', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r828315978-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Nice lunch', 'stopped here for lunch at the recommendation of our guide after the elephant orphanage. Certainly a nice quiet spot for it. Food was very nice and if you so wished, visit the lovely bronze art afterwards', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5354, 'Khatidja Dhala-Seyoum', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r793464740-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Lunch after visiting Elephants', 'This was the perfect stop after visiting the Elephants, we had lunch here and walked around. Make sure you give yourself enough time to walk around, it\'s all very casual and outdoor garden seating.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5355, 'Fred M', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r792333848-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Sunday afternoon family out.', 'The quality of the hotel is simply amazing! The food is great and the price is unbelievable! 1,500 per person for buffet. The value you get is worth it.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5356, 'Samantha Greenwood', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r784057980-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Socially distant quiz night', 'Thanks Matbronze for an awesome quiz. Social distancing rules carefully adhered to and quiz brilliantly pitched to be entertaining and challenging. Great service and another memorable night. See you next time!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(5357, 'ChristinaSLacey', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r770578902-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Perfect little place for brunch, lunch or a coffee', 'Lovely gardens, set outside the main bronze gallery.  Small enough menu that it\'s not too difficult to choose from but big enough to satisfy everyone.  We regularly have brunch here on Sundays and have also tried the weekend currys, which are great. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5358, 'Kirsty L', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r768320352-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely place to visit', 'Lovely environment in very well kept gardens. Staff were very polite and food was great! There are scultptures around the gardens and in a gallery which we spent time looking at whilst we waited for our food to be ready. All in, a very nice visit.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5359, 'Foxes99', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r761515043-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'We go to Matbronze often -', 'We go to Matbronze often - relaxing and just really really nice! Great service and prices are not too bad. We can take the dog which is great. Open during these COVID times and fully recommended.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5360, 'Gareth H', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r761039306-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely gardens, art & food. Great service', 'We have been here numerous times and came again post re-opening. All COVID safety measures have been implemented. The food is lovely and it is such a peaceful setting. We can always bring our dog too, which is quite unique. Service is always excellent.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5361, 'Ellen P', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r749204006-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great for a family lunch ', 'Our guide and driver suggested this place for lunch during a busy day of sightseeing and it was a real hit. Very calm and relaxing atmosphere. Good food - with a kids menu for our kids to choose from. Great experience, warmly recommended. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5362, 'Amy Elizabeth', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r748928212-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Highly recommend', 'I loved my visit here. All the little details make such a big difference. I liked how there was a paw print on the hot drinks and a little animal chocolate which looked handmade. The toilet signs of male and female lion were also a nice touch. Garden area is beautiful and some lovely sculptures. I also left my coat and cardigan behind but I phoned and the lady saved it for me to collect at a later date. Prices very reasonable.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5363, 'Cathy Fraser', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r748905365-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Peaceful garden .', 'Lovely peaceful  place to relax and enjoy lunch. Guinea Fowl roaming around. Reasonably priced drinks. Delicious food. Highly recommend.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5364, 'sdmmb', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r748438586-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Beautiful setting in magnificent', 'Beautiful setting in magnificent garden.  Varied choice of food including salads,meat, fish and pasta.  Good quality and reasonably priced. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5365, 'Gogs', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r744988562-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'My favourite lunch place', 'Relaxed garden setting with guinea fowl running around. Close to the giraffe sanctuary and Daphne\'s elephants. Limited menu but the food is good with a great ottolengi (spelling??) salad selection. Good to eat or just for a coffee', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5366, 'Aleksandra B', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r743423421-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Chill and enjoy', 'Lovely place. Hidden jewel. Never too crowdy. The menu is not massive but all the food is really nice.\nI love their burgers and chocolate mousse BUT the only problem is that most of the time they ran out of it.\nThe only reason why I sometimes avoid to go there is.......I can\'t get resist going to the bronze art gallery and buying something.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5367, 'ummul j', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r740047249-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'ambience', 'this place was the perfect place to take my family visiting from the uk. they really were able to take in the true beauty of kenya.\n\nthe food is so tasty, and the portions are just right. we ordered the cheese and tomatoe panini and drink was lovely.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5368, 'Glyn12', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r727960687-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Ideal relaxed location for an informal snack lunch', 'Matbronze is not easy to find and the cafe is an adjunct to an art gallery, which is the main activity. As a result the cafe was very quiet when we visited for a late lunch midweek. Nevertheless the service was excellent, the location is very peaceful and attractive and the mainly outside seating very comfortable. Very tasty food and drinks.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5369, 'Srikanta P', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r723869023-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Average', 'My second visit. Took family along with. Not disappointed, but not excited like first time either. We ordred the Hot Chocolate with Cinnamon flavour and mint flavour. Both are Okay. Crepes were very ordinary. Starwberry shake was also average.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5370, 'Alykhan2014', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r720374860-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Simple but excellent food in a gorgeous setting!', 'Having recently re visited Matbronze, I had to write another review, the place has made some lovely additions to the terrance area, and the gardens are more beautiful than ever.\nThe food surpassed my expectations, being a public holiday, and the service was great and the food served in record time.\nWe enjoyed the chefs special mushroom soup and the pate to start with - delectable!\nThe mains consisted of several pizzas, flame grilled chicken breast and the grilled chicken sandwich with the homemade pesto.There is a great salad bar to choose from.  It was great to see that among the bread offering, there was a great rye, which I opted for with both the pate and the sandwich\nThis is a must visit place for a meal, and the proximity of the gallery is an added attraction, whether one is just browsing or out to do some shopping, it is a unique and truly wonderful gallery to see!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5371, 'Srikanta P', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r712701839-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent place to visit, buy, see, drink, eat', 'One place, where you can see the bronze made wildlife souvenirs, nuy them, get them couriered to your overseas address, send some as gift. Not only this, you can visit the garden here, which is too well kept. Now there are food and beverage services as well which you can have there and enjoy the complete round trip nicely.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5372, 'etbtravelphotography', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r708820456-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Nice Gallery and Garden, Food Average', 'I understand the coffee, pate and soup are great, but the sandwiches are fair.  The gallery, however, features paintings, bronzes, photos and more.  Visit my TA Nairobi trips page for more detailed information @etbtravelphotography', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"drinks\"]'),
(5373, 'Karenjo G', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r700487048-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Grounds are like a secret garden', 'Our guide brought us to the enchanted location behind a metal entry gate.  The gardens are lovely with outdoor tables and a charming indoor cafe.  The food is good (perhaps not imaginative but the quality is tasty) and the service was very good.  The galleries adjacent to the cafe are showcases for amazing bronze pieces as well as drawings and paintings by various artists.  This is a great spot for a wide variety of folks including families with children or business acquaintances - it is just a terrific spot to enjoy the sights, sounds, tastes, and \"feel\" of a special moment in Nairobi.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5374, 'Beatrix', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r689522462-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden gem in Nairobi', 'Our favourite coffeee spot in Nairobi. We went there only for coffee, but the breakfast and lunch options also look good. The place is simply amazing, set in in a beautiful garden where you can spend your day and let the kids play around. You can also enjoy the exhibition of bronze statues. \nThe coffee is quite good, European standard. I particularly enjoyed and appreciated the paw shape decoration on the milk foam. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5375, 'Grace K', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r670681482-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', '\"Who said gold is no 1 bronze is kingüòÅ\"', 'Appreciated the bronze workmanship at the gallery......amazing, unique pieces. You can not leave without buying something. Prices vary depending on the item. The staff are very helpful....\nüö∂‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èCrossover to the cafe where the ambience is exquisite, the staff are warm and frienldy, service is fast and the food portions are generous and tasty. \nThis review doesn\'t do the place justice you have to visit the place to experience it. \n‚ô•Ô∏è Bronzed out', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5376, 'Escape-overseas', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r668141871-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Combining lunch with bronze art, whilst enjoying the sun. ', 'Combining the opportunity for lunch in the sun, surrounded by bronze sculptures, and the opportunity to purchase artwork from the indoor gallery. Lunch is consistently good, and Matbronze is always on our list of places to visit whenever we are in a Nairobi. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[]'),
(5377, 'Catherine', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r665884130-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Afternoon lunch in the sun', 'Came to Matt bronZe for a family lunch. Upon arrival the atmosphere is so gorgeous, lots of vegitation  and gorgeous scupltures to look at. We all had Tuskers and a range of burgers. I can honestly say that these are the best burgers I have ever tasted. They are served with avacado, red onion relish, toasted cheese bun and this beautiful fall apart beef burger. One of the best lunches in the best place for me. 10/10', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5378, 'Deadpan0', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r665015161-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Wonderful experience!', 'Nestled up a dirt track in the famous Karen district of Nairobi, this is a fantastic family restaurant. We (two couples three kids 6-12) had lunch here after seeing the rescued elephants at Daphne Sheldrick. Kids loved the milkshakes, pizzas and the chips (\"heaven\" to the 12 yr old). A more sophisticated selection of Sandwiches for the grown ups. Chicken pesto was divine. Beautiful location, tasty food and amazing Kenyan service. Couldn\'t ask for more. Plus a look around the gallery was a fascinating bonus.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5379, 'Simon Watoro', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r664403084-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Definitely recommend', 'The service delivery is excellent. Waiters are polite and professional and the food is just superb. I recommend.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5380, 'OceanPalmer', '#2 Kifaru Lane', 'Matbronze Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8580248-r660748595-Matbronze_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Nice cafe in a beautiful setting', 'Matbronze is fun to visit on its own; and having a quality cafe on the grounds makes it easy to relax and enjoy a beautiful blend of art and ambience. \n', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:29:16', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\"]'),
(5381, 'AlexSwallow', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r1022601054-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'A solid option in the area', 'We stayed in this area for a bit and enjoyed this place. Some of the food was exceptional, some merely good, but all was tasty. Liked the decor, the breakfast smoothies and the fact they had local beer.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5382, 'ETT', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r1007418362-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'I was looking forward to this but remained disappointed.', 'I had visited Nairobi a year or two ago and this was my favorite place.  Salads/ poke bowls and healthy options were rich with flavor. New menu not working ‚Ä¶ tried twice. Second visit was what did it for me. Lacked flavor, my home made spaghetti sauce had more flavor‚Ä¶ Tex-mix had a leaf or cilantro ‚Ä¶ Mexican food is reach with flavor and at the least have zest this was incredibly bland and the bowl was not crunchy more soggy. The steak sandwich and few little strips and had too much ketchup. I felt like I was having a child‚Äôs meal. The place was also not as full as it used to be during lunch. All too 30-45 minutes wasn‚Äôt even crowded. Change back.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5383, 'AnnK78', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r973468335-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Loved it! The avokado toast is addictive.', 'The perfect lunsj, brunch and breakfast place! I‚Äôts avokado toast is addictiv. We trird tree dishes and loved them all. A lot of food. \n\nLoved the fact that the cafe is a bit hard to find‚Ä¶but the street is a hiddeb gem in a safe aerea in Nairobi. \n\nThe store at 2.floor had reasonable prices that we did not want to bargain about. Very nice produkts and souvinirs that was not mass produced (we felt at least so).', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5384, '_shivona_tavares', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r970614284-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Probably not worth going for a concert after hours', 'Went for a concert that started at 7pm.  A friend came at 9pm and paid the full amount for 5 minutes. After paying the bill (15,000/=), then ordering a bottle of wine, we got the same bill again plu the bottle of wine (18,500/=).  When we queried it, the bill was 3,500/=.  No sooner had we sorted that out, we were asked to leave by the staff.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5385, 'beanu B', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r902446119-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'delicious food and lovely atmosphere', 'It‚Äôs  lovely with a great atmosphere and the food is DELICIOUS! Will definitely be going back soon!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5386, 'Badgersabroad', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r870906632-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'A Regular Breakfast Haunt', 'It is interesting reading the reviews for this place - they are so varied and it is hard to understand why. I come here regularly for breakfast and I find it a great place to start the day. The menu is different and I love that it isn‚Äôt the usual fare. The service is good, the ambiance enjoyable and the food interesting and good value. What‚Äôs not to like? It is what it claims to be - nothing fancy but out of the ordinary. The only possibility I can think of as to why it gets such mixed reviews is that it may depend on the time of day you visit. All I know is that it is a great midweek breakfast joint.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5387, 'Rodney Likaku', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r826285863-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'If You Haven\'t Had Brunch here Do You Even Live in Nairobi?', 'Great service, great ambiance for a hangout with friends, amazing food, good vibes, chilled--we are definitely coming back.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5388, 'SONIA P', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r811962932-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Worst Meal i have had', 'I ordered a takeaway from wasp and sprout yesterday , the description on the menu sounded lovely ( The Bali Box:\nChicken Satay, with coconut rice, egg omelette, cucumber, sambal oelek & roasted peanuts).  What I actually got was a bland dish of boiled rice and chicken with nuts. I could hardly find the omelette and there was less than a teaspoon of sambal, if that. I have attached a photo of what i got ( less one chicken skewer and some rice).  Extremely disappointing.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5389, 'Talampakan', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r801097146-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Great find', 'I had second thoughts about going to this place after reading the recent bad reviews. However, I am glad that I took my chances.\n\nI overshot the road where the caf√© is located as I could not believe that my navigator was telling me to turn to that road. It is best not to try to get all the way into the narrow road but to turn right into the parking area and walk a few meters.\n\nThe menu included traditional breakfast fare and a few surprising entries from Asia and Latin America. My Latin American friends were quite happy with their Cuban and Mexican breakfasts. We all enjoyed the freshly-squeezed orange juice and the coffee.\n\nService was friendly and efficient, and we did not have to wait very long for anything that we ordered. Now I just have to find another excuse to go there again and try other dishes on the menu.\n\nThe place is very simple and informal, so do not expect anything fancy.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5390, 'David O', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r796559161-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'TOTAL CRAP', 'Waited over an hour for our food we came for breakfast at 1030 by 12 we still had no food.. we left hungry with no food ever given to us 1 star not worth the effort', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5391, 'SafariQueenNairobi', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r791380022-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Getting by on a bygone reputation?', 'This was a terrible brunch. I wouldn‚Äôt go again if I could possibly avoid it! Dirty, ugly, unappetising food, slow, and I was brought a dish I hadn‚Äôt ordered! I can‚Äôt understand why people like it?? This was described as ‚ÄúSouthern slaw‚Äù but it was red cabbage, with cheap mayonnaise stirred in üò¨', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(5392, 'Aleks on the Road', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r744408450-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Restaurant in the designer shopping district', 'Laid back atmosphere, colorfully designed interior, a place to chill out with friends during the day.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5393, 'Rogers Tiger', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r732029898-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Chilled ', 'Chilled coffee shop with a very beautiful garden. Charming service and fresh and healthy food options. Great base in Nairobi. Wish they would serve dinner too. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5394, 'Akinyi Adongo', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r729732905-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Breakfast Time!', 'The Eggs Benedict was delicious! My friend enjoyed his omelette too. I also had the cold pressed Orange Juice üòçü§§ ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]');
INSERT INTO `restaurant_reviews` (`id`, `author_name`, `place_address`, `place_name`, `review_url`, `review_title`, `review_text`, `review_rating`, `location`, `created_at`, `predicted_sentiment`, `predicted_aspects`) VALUES
(5395, 'HmanG', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r719445786-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Dangerous and unsafe', 'Be careful while visiting this restaurant. I had heard of some burglaries in the area but never thought it would happen to me. My car was broken into and all my valuables were stolen while i was at the restaurant. When i reported this to the manager, his exact words were \"thats unfortunate, theres a police station down the road\". When i asked why they dont have security watching the cars, i was told they dont keep security because its city council land, even if its the designated area for their customers to park. No empathy shown, he clearly just wanted us to leave and move on.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5396, 'Maria', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r709985447-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Horrible service on a Sunday brunch', 'Nice location, interesting healthy menu but horrible service. We were served after 1,5 hour and we were not the only disappointed clients that day.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5397, 'niknpatel', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r705216337-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Horrendous service...let\'s hope the food is ok!!! ', 'I\'m actually writing this as I sit here waiting for our food (ours been 1 hour and 45 mins so far!!! )\n\nWe\'re here with two young children who are starving...and the staff keep just saying \"sorry...it\'s coming! \"\n\nSigh', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\"]'),
(5398, 'Amber D', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r702560672-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden gem', 'This place is definitely a hidden gem and hard to find if you don‚Äôt know where you are going but it is so worth it. The chicken and waffles are some of the best I had and the blueberry and ricotta pancakes are perfect. The ambiance is lovely as well. I have eaten here many times and I have only been disappointed once and that waswith the waffles which were pre-cooked and then re-heated when I ordered them and they were just meh.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5399, 'Puja J', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r696188160-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Quick and pleasant service', 'Visited this hide-away eatery late on a Sunday afternoon in the nick of closing time. The server was attentive and suggested dishes we couls try from the menu.  All products used are organic and made to order. \n\nFood arrived well portioned and presented - both to the eye and the stomach! \n\nThis eatery offers lots of gluten free and vegetarian options. \n\nThe naked falafel was a delight - served with Mango and Avo salsa. Delicious though a little dry. The Southern Chicken Burger was ginormous, accompanied by red cabbage slaw and chips- the portion was enough for 2 to share. The Salted Caramel milkshake a tad too sweet for me though absolutely delicious.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5400, 'armantheman', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r695641974-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Urban chic settting. Average food. ', 'Stick to the basics here. Have a coffee and maybe some plain eggs. Anything else and you\'ll likely be disappointed. The food is either overseasoned or overly cheesy or greasy. It\'s a shame as it is one of the most unique settings for brunch in all of Nairobi. ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5401, 'CatherineO1970', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r695545507-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Decent prices and good ambiance', 'After being disappointed with the high prices at Utamanduni I looked for some alternative shops selling Kenyan crafts and found this shop and cafe in Loresho, north west of the city centre. The prices here are much more realistic in the shop (than those at Utamanduni). I didn‚Äôt have time to visit the cafe but it looked lovely and seems to cater for locals, ex pats and tourists. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"overall_experience\"]'),
(5402, 'hitzdun', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r695202016-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Great Vegetarian food', 'Definitely recommend. Great sitting area and meeting place. Friendly staff. Geat vegan options available ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5403, 'isra khawaja', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r694371178-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Brunch spot!', 'Lovely ambience with friendly staff, amazing food - catering for both vegetarians and vegans too! Food quality is excellent, portions are filling. \nGood place to spend have a delicious brunch!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5404, 'Amu', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r675221703-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Great place. ', 'We heard about this place from a friend. We never heard about it before not seen it as there aren\'t any advertisements and or sign board to tell you where its located. We had heard good reviews about the place so decided to try this place. I must say. An amazing place. The location isn\'t that best as its hidden in a small corner. The area isn\'t that big. But it has a small play area for kids and the tables seem bit close to others. However the food there is awesome!!!  The menu is limited which is good as it allows them to perfect every dish that comes out. Our last visit there was just yesterday. The place was packed beyond anything. I guess word of mouth is spreading really quick. Anyway. The service was slow this time compared to the other times we have been there. The coffee is really really good so are the fresh juices. The food wow. I had the all American. A weird mix of sweet, salty and tangy but really really awesome. My wife had the Benedict and that was great as well. We try and visit once in 2 months and so far the dishes have always been spot ok and consistent. I insist everyone should visit this place. At times it does get noisy but it\'s worth the noise and at times the waiting game. I wish they could be somewhere else as well as in they should expand. Love it and will always visit. Keep it guys üëç', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5405, 'Alexander D', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r673462584-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Great menu', 'Really unique and delicious menu. I basically wanted to eat it all! And it was as tasty as it sounded. Really lovely decor with handmade furniture and African wax cushions all around. Friendly service and a lively croud. Excellent brunch destination with a cool little shop upstairs. Will be back ASAP. Put a sign outside and on the road so we don\'t have to wander around confused! ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5406, 'milleniatraveltip', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r672183594-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'It was okay', 'Pros\nHave made a good effort with the ambience, excellent service and a warm cosy atmosphere.\n\nCons\nThe grandiose description on the menus creates a bigger expectation than what was delivered.\n\nI had the Burger, seemed quite basic and underseasoned, nothing outstanding.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5407, 'Carl M', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r670231536-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Great place for breakfast and lunch ', 'In Loresho you only have a few options and this is by far the best one! Chris managed to find a great place that has an identity of its own and really stands out in the otherwise rather average Nairobi food scene. There is no place like W&S, we enjoy more to go for a lazy Sunday breakfast with the kids. Apart from a very very nice breakfast for the parents (Baghdad eggs, YUM!), they also have a kids corner where they have a great time while the parents can sip their lattes. Also weekdays, really recommend it for lunch. I love to go there and do some work while enjoying a superb salad, burger or sandwich. Top tip, check out the store upstairs, they have some great stuff you don‚Äôt find at every bargain box/bizarre bazaar fair!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5408, 'Rebecca Vedova', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r657983750-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Sunday brunch ', 'I was at wasp and sprout for brunch last weekend. I ordered a veggie and feta bowl made of grilled aubergines, red & yellow peppers, hummus, lettuce, cherry tomatoes, olives, feta and onions. The person I was with had the southern friend chicken on waffles with red coleslaw and syrup. I really enjoyed my bowl, I was looking for something healthy and tasty to eat. My friend enjoyed the chicken and waffles. He did however find the chicken a bit dry and had to ask for some more syrup. I found his plate a bit too empty and simple. Just the chicken on the waffle. I think something should be added on the side wether it‚Äôs some fruit with a nice coulis or fries or veggies. It didn‚Äôt look exciting at all. \nI like wasp and sprout. It has a nice vibe to it and the food and drinks are usually very good. ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5409, 'john B', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r656194797-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Unique in Kenya', 'it seems that most coffee, cafe venues around try to compete, be the same, copy, overall one is much the same as the other. Not here. What a breath of fresh air! How someone has carved out a unique place, out of the general business area, away from other eating houses and be so busy is fantastic. I don\'t know any other cafe around where you do need to book a table, here it is! But if you want every day, same same menu, generic substance like everywhere else, don\'t bother coming, it\'s not for you. Congratulations Wasp & Sprout for giving us this great experience and a little touch of home.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5410, 'nyarmama', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r645164875-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Left with No Intention to Return!!', 'I was very disappointed and embarassed at the crass behavior of the wait staff and I do not intend to return.\n\nWe chose to sit outside - all the tables were un-occupied and we purposely picked one that did not have a \"Reserved\" plaque (paper in this case).\n\nAn hour or so later our table was cleared and one of the staff asked us to leave the table because the 6:15 reservation for the table had arrived. Note at no point for the entire hour we were there did anyone let us know the table was reserved. The patrons at the other tables, including the ones not reserved, were not asked the same. Not being Caucasian may have influenced their decision to target my friend and I. \n\nAdditional note: the pizza we ordered had no seasoning!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5411, 'Mukui M', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r641527630-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'A unique spot', 'Really liked the ambiance! \nThe burger I had was ok, but the earl grey milkshake was terrific!\n\nI would definitely recommend it for your looking for a quiet lunch or tea with friends.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5412, 'Sam W', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r639930647-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Nice', 'A beautiful but busy place. Breakfast choices are good and creative. The service is excellent. Great coffee.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5413, 'George Kinuthia', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r631521879-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Unique', 'I stumbled in to this unique placed perched in Loresho area, the other day. The decor is very creative and the staff very pleasant. For someone who is adventurous and would like to experience a more relaxed and less formal atmosphere, unlike the conventional very serious business approach this would be the place. Sadly they only operate during the day if I got the working hours correctly.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5414, 'Sheffield-MR', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r627381903-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'It‚Äôs Africa', 'As the title suggests it‚Äôs Africa bit qurcky, bit different but really nice. Yes you don‚Äôt have to be in a rush but our food was worth the wait, especially for something different try the Dowa.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5415, 'M P', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r623390544-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Great..except the smoke!', 'I love Wasp & Sprout. I got there often with my family because service and food are excellent. \n\nMy biggest problem with the place is that they allow smoking near the indoor seating. So, if you are sitting inside, you will likely be inhaling a lot of smoke with your meal. It is really disgusting given it seems to market itself as a family friend environment with the kids corner. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5416, 'Sukesha D', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r618560582-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'BRUNCH WITH A STING', 'A rustic chilled out nonchalant place having a menu with a different kind of a sting.... \nFriendly and efficient staff and the food was very well presented and absolutely fresh. \nA lot of healthy options available and suitable for the vegetarians and Vegans as well.\nI would suggest a Name Board of the cafe to be installed.. as many were driving around in circles looking for the place.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5417, 'Leah M', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r618054588-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Nice and lovely', 'I looked up top places for brunch in Nairobi and came across this one. It lived up to its reputation. Very nice food, both veg and non-vegetarian. Only issue was in billing which took rather long! It\'s a hidden gem and I\'d definitely go back.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(5418, 'Lyiia', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r608248216-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely atmosphere but..', 'The place is lovely to hang out, and have coffee. The staff is very nice too. However It takes a while to get food (1 hour and 10 minutes last time we visited, from the moment we arrived and the moment we got our food), so you must go knowing that you will be there a while, which is fine as long as you are aware of it. But the food has been really disappointing during our last visits. I am very allergic to wheat, which is usually ok to eat out as people understand and try to accommodate it. But there, there is no effort to accommodate this what so ever. I asked if it was possible to not put the wheat salad on the plate explaining my case, and I was told that it was not possible (this is just one example of several). So either I have to pick in the side list (a side of poach eggs with a side of plain spinach..again, not very tasty and pretty bland), or one of the very few wheat free dishes available, even though it would not be too hard for them to not put an ingredient on a plate to make it gluten free and it would make the menu much more appealing.\nOn the Sunday morning brunch, I can have a single dish (two actually if I count the coconut milk fruit salad). I had it and it was not great. No seasoning, no dressing, the falafel were super dry and very bland. I guess it is just bad luck that it is all I can have, as some of their dishes look quite tasty. \nTo their defense, it does say no alteration to the dishes, but then it may just mean that this is not a place for people like me to eat!\nI will probably go back since it is a lovely place but I won\'t order food again!', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5419, 'Shailja P', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r607536179-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely space, weird kitchen logistics', 'Love the decor, friendliness, and neighbourhood cafe vibe. \n\nBut it\'s frustrating that even the simplest food order takes much longer to arrive than it should. The kitchen is located outside the cafe, and the chain of communication seems to be erratic.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5420, 'Evaristontour', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r607533020-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Healthy or naughty, you choose', 'Best brunch in Nairobi with surprising and unique menu. A lot of vegan and vegetarian super tasty and original options - you can go back a thousand times without getting tired of it. Relaxed spot perfect to go with friends or alone with a book. Enjoy it! ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5421, 'Ithinkiatetoomuch', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r602423763-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'so worth it', 'Yum, it is a bit hidden, it is on the side and near the back, there is no sign. The food was delicious and the drinks were strong and we had a great time. I had the sweet potato waffle. \nthe atmosphere was good and the service was good too. Not very expensive either. Fun!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5422, 'RSG17', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r591380677-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Best brunch in Kenya!', 'Lovely bistro located in a remote part of Nairobi. The breakfast and brunches are excellent and cooked to a very high standard. My favourites are the eggs benedict which were cooked to perfection and the fresh oysters! Highly recommended if you are visiting Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5423, 'romanholiday28', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r588339912-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Simply brilliant!', 'Im glad the dodgy looking building didnt put me off going in.. Inside the set up is refreshingly bohemian and the menu simple yet creative. Eggs Benedict were done perfectly, i cant remember the last time i said that, and we had fresh oysters - For breakfast! The rest of the menu is begging to be explored and i shall definately be back. So glad that that there now is a sprinkling of such independent establishments in Nairobi amongst the drudgery of your chain Javas and Art caffes! They shut by 2 pm on weekends by the way.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5424, '25wanderlings', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r588053042-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Great breakfast', 'Very tasty breakfast, good coffee, good juice selection.  This place is a little tucked away, but popular, so you might have to wait but it\'s worth it.  Cosy little place with interesting decor and some art and crafts for sale inside.  Definitely worth it for breakfast.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5425, 'Julieknuckles', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r585254014-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Great atmosphere, amazing brunch!', 'This place has a lovely cozy outdoor garden seating area and the indoors area is nice too. Coffee is fantastic and the baked eggs. wow. I\'ve been here for brunch and lunch and would have to say this place really shines for breakfast/brunch.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5426, 'Lama K', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r585018641-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Nice and cosy', 'A great little coffee shop for working and just meeting up for food and drinks. Came twice while i was in Nairobi. Mt brother lives close by and came the first time on my own to work and the 2nd time to have a bite. Coffee is great and meal portions are good. The internet was down the first time was there and was unable to do any online work but managed to edit my papers!', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5427, 'Han2234', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r584811738-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Cute cafe with a relaxed atmosphere', 'Great place to have breakfast or brunch.  Slightly difficult to find if you aren‚Äôt with a local but the food was really great so it is well worth hunting it down.  Lovely shop on site too.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5428, 'Daniel R', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r579778753-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Tastiest breackfast in Nairobi ', 'This is the breackfast Or brunch in Nairbi. They change the menu constantly and each dish they have is amazing. Beside delicious food and coffe tehy also have kids activity corner, where they look after your kids while kids play and draw.\nThe place is not easy to find, but once you are there there is no better place for a relaxing brunch.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5429, 'c4wley', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r575557567-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Comfortable local feel, with delicious healthy bites', 'Wasp & Sprout is one of those spots I always go back to for the delicious food and relaxed atmosphere. They make a gorgeous Sweet Potato Waffle with almond butter, mint, and raspberries. Definitely worth stopping for a bite', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5430, 'FarahinDubai', 'Loresho Shopping Centre Loresho Ridge', 'Wasp and Sprout', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d10082726-r574261263-Wasp_and_Sprout-Nairobi.html', 'Quaint brunch place in Loresho', 'Great vegan and non-traditional options such as sweet potato waffles! Good coffee and tea, great decor.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:31:06', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5431, 'Nikki C', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r1016790066-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'An absolute must in Nairobi', 'This place is amazing. Such a treat. The staff are lovely and food amazing. I ate way too much pizza but it was hard to stop. Shout out to the team for helping us with a US dollar situation. Garden area stunning. Toilets clean. Hot chocolate was awesome', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5432, 'Lisa G', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r1016321187-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Favorite breakfast after 3 weeks in Kenya', 'Best breakfast in Kenya! Our family came on our last day looking for better gluten free options. They had wonderfully fluffy gluten free pancakes which the entire family (not all gf) loved. We also had crepes, breakfast sandwiches and coffee. All were excellent, delicious and served hot. Vegan options as well \n\nStaff was amazing. No need to know any sign language to go and easy to communicate. My kids really liked the experience to learn a few signs and wished we had a cafe like this back in Seattle. Joked about not leaving after breakfast and staying for lunch. So good. You‚Äôll be glad you visited. \n\nShops adjacent were great as well if you want to find something more unique', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5433, 'UWE S', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r995062665-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Beautiful expirience', 'We come since years here for breakfast and still in love of the atmosphere, the friendly service and the very good relation between price and quality.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5434, 'Thanveer M', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r981670013-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Bad experiance and food', 'Very bad experience. The staff there are ignorant even the mallus. Initially food was good now they serve packet porotas and cold. I was the only customer there and waited for almost an hour to be attaneded by staffs. I went again the following day as my kid like their playground but unfortunately  they dont seem caring for customers. Always i see staffs moving here and there. Dont understand those movements without serving the customers.\n\nLooks like they are spoiling the mallu authentic food culture and taste.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5435, 'Beatrice K', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r969828835-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Bad food', 'The food took a while to come and k expected it to be warm on arrival. It was extremely cold - every single dish we ordered apart from the fries. \n30min after leaving we all have experienced a bad tummy .', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'negative', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5436, 'lizmcd2', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r941687427-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing hidden gem', 'We visited the branch on galu beach. Amazing place where most of the  employees are deaf so you can learn sign language whilst enjoying the atmosphere and view of the beach. \nStaff were very helpful and order us a tuk tuk when we were ready to go. \n A good walk from Diani beach but definitely worth it .\nSun loungers are available as right on the beach so can spend all day there', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5437, 'Zeena K', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r940934073-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing work environment, breath-taking setting, gluten free pizza, incredible food and differently-abled service', 'Such an incredible place I am from the US working remotely in Nairobi for 6 months and spend almost everyday here working! The atmosphere is amazing, good stable wifi (hard to find), the ambiance/greenery is breath taking, the food is so great (only place I could find with gluten free pizza and brownies) and the place is very inclusive staffed with differently-abled deaf waiters and waitresses, and the service was phenomenal! A must-go cafe in Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5438, 'Tom', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r928266175-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A very pleasant outside eating experience, to pass time, eat with friends, or business  have lunches', 'This is a very interesting up market restaurant / cafe what gives deaf people an opportunity to work, and the waiters do not have hearing. The restaurant is managed by an experienced operator, with many years experience in another coffee bar chain called Java.The waiters were charming and gentle, and the restaurant was managed with tender loving care. It is situated in a large nurtured and partly covered back garden in Lavington.  The menu is wide ranging, including pizza - freshly cooked in a clay oven, and hummus, and many other interesting dishes. I went there several times, and enjoyed time there on both occasions, and would go again. There is wifi. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5439, 'Tracy', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r897782392-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Sunday lunch', 'Ate some great food, there is a fabulous garden atmosphere, the apple pie was delicious! Staff great, loved the Guinea pigs!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5440, 'Chandni', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r893838227-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'It\'s A Vibe', 'I like the ambiance and I enjoy the outdoor seating under the sun. The thoughtful details on the potted plants, colors, and art make me happy every time I am there. I also like the fact that the place is airy and the tables are distanced well. I keep going back, but not primarily for the food. \n\nI recommend their breakfast options since they are straightforward and I also like their chicken wings and chicken tacos. \n\nI am not a big fan of most of their heavier meals and combos because those have been hit-or-miss for me. I also don\'t like their fries and their choice of ketchup, so that holds me back from ordering the sandwiches, wraps, burgers, etc again. I hope they can invest in good ketchup and work on sourcing good potatoes/fries that cook well. \n\nService tends to be a bit slow, so it is a good place to go when you want to chill, take your time, enjoy conversations with someone, and get tucked away in a corner away from the hustle and bustle of the city. The team is very friendly and welcoming. They are patient with clients who forget or struggle with communicating in sign language. They constantly check on customers to ensure good service. Overall, it\'s a good place. I keep going back for one-on-one brunch dates with my girlfriends and it\'s a vibe. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5441, 'Benjamin T', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r877227540-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Super d√©couverte', 'Parfait! \nTr√®s bon service, la nourriture est bonne et bien pr√©par√©e.\nLe cadre est relaxant‚Ä¶\nAllez y les yeux ferm√©s!!!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"service\"]'),
(5442, 'Mattias K', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r873869904-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Underbart caf√©!', 'Underbart litet caf√© i gr√∂nskan. Toppen mat - vill s√§rskilt tipsa om den fina frukosten. En oas i Nairobi. S√• v√§nlig personal som kommer med filtar och eldfat n√§r det √§r kyligt.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'negative', '[]'),
(5443, 'Mzungubabe', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r871362542-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Relaxed outdoor dining space', 'Visited with a group of friends for lunch. Waiter Edwin was super friendly and really appreciative of our poor attempts to communicate in sign language. Food was very good and well priced. I will definitely be back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5444, 'Tony M', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r857156714-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'GALU BEACH - New!', 'Whilst we were in Galu we found this cafe on the beach and visited twice whilst in the area. I think its new as I couldn\'t find the actual one we visited on TripAdvisor, but this one in Nairobi is part of the group. Their policy of employing deaf people is most admirable, and we felt that we had to support it. If you are looking for this along the beach then you need to look carefully for the painted handsigns on the wall of the building which is set back and not easy to see. What they need is a sign on the beach, or you can walk past, like we did first time.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5445, 'Dara G', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r853281991-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Best Food in Nairobi with amazing decor and ambience', 'The Pallet Caf√© is an amazing find in Nairobi.  We ate as two families with teenagers plus some friends, a mixture of Kenyans and Europeans.  The location is excellent, parking very convenient.  The ambiance and decor captures you immediately.  Beautiful gardens, seating made from drums covered with modern kitenge patterns, a vibrant and dynamic indoor/ outdoor restaurant.  The teenagers loved the atmosphere.  The food is outstanding, the pizzas are as good as if not better than  any you would find in Italy. The gourmet burgers are mouthwatering - I recommend the mango chilli sauce-just delicious. The zucchini noodles were fabulous.  Top class food, superbly presented at very good prices. The best thing however is the staff who were so attentive, prompt and organised. We were a big group and were served piping hot food together. The concept is incredible-a community based caf√© to integrate hearing impaired workers.  We really enjoyed learning new signs and practising some old ones. Our only regret is that we discovered the Pallet Caf√© at the end of our holiday. Next time we will be there on the first night.  If you are in Nairobi, you cannot miss this amazing place. Asante Sana for a wonderful dinner.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5446, 'CharlotteUBG', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r850015551-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Highly recommend', 'We absolutely loved our visit to the Pallet Cafe. The staff were friendly, the garden was beautiful and the food was great. Would definitely recommend.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5447, 'Eyama E', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r841422141-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A lovely and empowering restaurant', 'Pallet has an amazing staff who are deaf yet so lovely! The food itself is first class and priced reasonably! It was such an amazing experience to eat in their scenic garden and enjoy the ambience, excellent food and service.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5448, 'Jasmine A', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r835986219-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely atmosphere, chilled surroundings', 'There is something magical for all age groups about this place - sitting outside surrounded by the lush greenery, sweet animals (guinea pigs & a massive tortoise, dogs in the drive way) and simple pallet furniture with bright kitenge fabrics on them, there is a lot to look at, a lot of space for kids to play, and that\'s before you order the food. The coffees and drinks are delicious - I usually go for an iced latte or a lemonade. The food is good too - I would recommend the eggs Benedict or the feta samosas. Not a fan of the burgers here as I found them too garlicky but overall the food is good. We go back to this place all the time because it\'s in our neighborhood and the staff are lovely and caring too.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5449, 'hcb81', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r804291134-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Will be back', 'Loved our visit here. Service was fantastic, food excellent, atmosphere relaxing and great for children (garden, play areas). Super coffee too. The fact it also supports a good cause just made it even more enjoyable. We\'ve just moved to the area and will definitely be back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5450, 'Ambassador737604', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r788756896-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing experience', 'My friends and I really enjoyed the ambience of the restaurant. It was calm, serene and beautiful and we instantly felt right at home. A tortoise was eating and walking near where we sat and there were some bunnies we could see from a distance which added a nice touch.\n\nThe servers were amazing. It was a first experience with deaf servers-they were lovely and warm, accommodating, wrote some things down when we struggled with sign language and they made us laugh. They were the best servers we‚Äôve ever experienced so far.\n\nThe food was great and affordable and the servers kept checking in to see if we enjoying our food. I would highly recommend their pizzas. My friends raved about them.\n\nThere‚Äôs something about this place that will make you want to go back again. I‚Äôll definitely do and would recommend it to anyone who wants a beautiful, calm place to eat and catch up with family or friends.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5451, 'Kat', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r782510565-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Lovely Cafe', 'This is a fave for a quick bite, working lunch or a nice afternoon with friends. The service is great and the food is tasty. Just don\'t wave around your chicken wings if sitting out in the garden because the hawks have an eye out for the tasty food as well.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(5452, 'Jet409788', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r778445067-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent service, delicious coffee and food', 'This was my first time here for dinner (I had previously only been for lunch). The service by the waiters/waitresses is excellent as always, better than most hearing waiters in my experience. Even though they are deaf we were able to communicate quite easily through gestures and I ordered by pointing at items on the menu.\n\nThe food is good, I had a beef burger with red capsicum mayonnaise accompanied by garlic fries, it was tasty and filling. My vanilla latte drink was delicious!\n \nSeating is outdoors under a roof so it can be cold, but the cold is easily beaten by the warm charcoal fire the staff are happy to provide you upon request.\n\nThe evening ambience is cosy, with the pizza oven in one corner and a garden surrounding the dining area. Whilst the comforting buzz of nightime Lavington can be heard in the background.\n\nAn overall lovely, cosy night out with the family.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5453, 'OneStrayTexan', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r775754463-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent Dinner Experience', 'Wonderful restaurant that hires hearing impaired individuals. The chicken wrap, peri peri chicken, and kids fish sticks were excellent.  Service has always been outstanding and the restaurant is adjacent to a park where many local festivities occur.  If it is a warm day, I suggest sitting away from the brick pizza oven.  The margarita pizza has a strong herb influence, good but can be a bit much for some.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5454, 'ileadntr o', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r758881799-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'perfect', 'The pallet cafe is one of the best places to take your family for a weekend. They have variety of dishes.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"menu_variety\"]'),
(5455, 'africanman_840', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r750790362-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'It is still a great place', 'I recently visited the Pallet and have to say that I enjoyed it as much as ever. The menu is still varied, and the service continues to be excellent.  I can\'t wait to return.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5456, 'Usha Harish', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r746232333-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Cafe with a difference', 'What a little hidden gem at the heart of Lavington. No-one can imagine such a coffee shop exists amid green lush surroundings. The staff are very courteous and always smiling. Food and ambience is very good. A place to unwind after being in Nairobi traffic. I loved the hashtag in every staff T-shirt #Iamdeaf and thats what makes the difference...Thank you for hosting.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5457, 'Triple A', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r741710379-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A refreshing change to the restaurant scene in Nairobi', 'Had afternoon tea here with friends. The ambiance is very warn and friendly. The food is awesome, certainly made with love. Love the mint tea, the fruit salad just hits the right spot. Great place for a business meeting and to hang out with friends on a sunny afternoon.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5458, 'Jet409788', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r740473730-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Awesome food, coffee, staff and experience', 'The food and coffee is delicious! I had a fish burger and a vanilla latte. The staff are very friendly and attentive. The cafe hires and trains disabled people and all the waiters are deaf. I was so happy to promote a business with a great social cause and have a great lunch at the same time. üòäüëç', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5459, 'Caitlin W', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r733556724-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Such a gem!', 'This place is such a gem in Nairobi. It is within a compound that not only has a delicious restaurant that is staffed by deaf workers (easy to communicate, so don\'t worry) but also has a shared workspace, a place to host yoga as well as a very cool art shop. My first though that came to mind was how this place could be a great beer garden, but they don\'t serve alcohol but they do serve delicious food (vegan options as well). It is not a seafood restaurant but there is fish available.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5460, 'Lorene F', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r731598639-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Love the food and atmosphere', 'I had the good fortune to work in an office adjacent to Pallet Cafe on a recent assignment in Nairobi. It was a delight to eat lunch here. Once I discovered it, I ate all my lunches at Pallet. Excellent food and espresso, great service, friendly staff, and spacious outdoor seating under a roof. I highly recommend it.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5461, 'Flora K', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r724393293-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great atmosphere', 'A lovely, garden cafe with good food and warm hospitality. I\'ve had the wings and one of the burgers before. I highly recommend. Awesome that they employ hearing impaired individuals. Shall be back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5462, 'Nirnc', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r720354524-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Wonderful place, the food', 'Wonderful place, the food was great, and also it was nice to seat outside; they hire handicapped people which is important and amazing. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"location_access\"]');
INSERT INTO `restaurant_reviews` (`id`, `author_name`, `place_address`, `place_name`, `review_url`, `review_title`, `review_text`, `review_rating`, `location`, `created_at`, `predicted_sentiment`, `predicted_aspects`) VALUES
(5463, 'khensa@gmail.com', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r716911950-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great coffee , Ambiance', 'A lovely place for coffee n a snack. A meeting outdoors .. \n\nThe staff are unique n very helpful \nThe only cafe which has employed , the deaf and dumb only . \n\nIt is great to see someone in Kenya offering good opportunities to such challenged people \nAnd they are doing an amazing job \n\nMuch love n  respect', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5464, 'ThierryPoussard', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r716431436-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A moment of grace', 'Pallet is a good restaurant, food is nice, but what I want to talk about is what is making it more than unique: a company hired people considered as handicapped (they cannot hear the customers, and cannot talk), and in Kenya, their chances to find a job is close to zero. These  people look happy in their job, dedicated, customer oriented, and have this touching way of making sure that the communication works well. My 11 years old daughter understood a lot during the time of a meal. And I advise anybody to go for a meal, or a breakfast, or even a simple coffee, and see how a company can contribute really in making the world a better place', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5465, 'Ros A', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r711665772-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Pallet Cafe Is a Nairobi Gem, delicious fresh food, excellent coffee, beautiful green setting and lovely staff.', 'Pallet Cafe Is a Nairobi Gem, delicious fresh food, excellent coffee, beautiful green setting and lovely staff. Most of the staff have a speech or hearing impairment and you have to order using sign language or paper and pen. Despite this they‚Äôll serve you with a smile on their face. combined with the friendly tortoise, local shop and other animals it‚Äôs fast becoming one of my favourite spots in Nairobi.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5466, 'Afro S', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r708173822-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Unexpectedly GOOD Sunday brunch!', 'We wanted to try a different place around Lavington mall and we pulled in Pallet. We did not know that the staff is deaf mute, what a wonderful idea to enable their integration into the market. Probably the best zoodles (zucchini noodles) I have had, lots of space for kids to run around and rabbit and Guinea pigs to keep them busy. We will go back. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5467, 'Aleksandra B', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r706947294-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'So special', 'This is the place you must visit but only if you carry positive vibes and you‚Äôre a positive person. \nThis place is all about that. Simplicity, originality, friendliness, happiness, modesty, togetherness, environment, humanity, art, peace and much more than that.\nYou must experience it to understand it. It is more than words can say.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5468, 'Ndux', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r703475220-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A hidden gem', 'We visited Pallet Cafe on a Sunday afternoon and it really was a pleasant surprise.  They hire Staff with Hearing Impairments and I hope this cafe grows and this concept spreads all over Nairobi. The service was excellent. We learnt some new sign language from the Sign Language books on the tables. Not only did they serve the best Chicken Wrap I have had in Nairobi so far but our boys had fun running around the yard and feeding some rabbits.  They loved the milkshakes too.\nWill be back to try their Breakfast menu.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5469, 'Mukami K', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r701783625-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great garden cafe!', 'This is such a lovely place to visit. I went on a cold morning and they were so kind to give me a jiko warmer, without my even asking. The staff are warm and welcoming plus the servers are amazing, differently abled individuals. Love it! The coffee was great and my omelette was good too. I\'ll be back. Keep it up.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5470, 'Davidgirlinguk', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r693130504-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Great social enterprise ran by deaf staff', 'This is a great cafe with excellent food and coffee. You can learn how to use sign language to order coffee with the illustrated menu. The waiting staff will help correct you if you go wrong. Really lovely food and a cool ambience!!! ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5471, 'Maryanne N', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r689761970-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Awesome ', 'The idea of a person employing disabled people is in itself is beautiful but meeting the staff who are beautiful people was the best part. My heart was warm the whole time. Ed our waiter, kept us laughing and giggling...helping us pick our food. The food was delicious!!!!! The art around, the colours and decor all playful. Perfect afternoon chill spot. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5472, 'khensa@gmail.com', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r688842268-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Pallet Cafe', 'Great Ambiance, the waiters are amazing .\nGood food at a good price .\nNice garden for the kids to run around\nLove their recycle look', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5473, 'africanman_840', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r688098372-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A Wonderful Cause', 'This a delightful cafe staffed largely by deaf and dumb employees. It felt wonderful to be helping them in such a delightful place. I enjoyed sitting outside in such a wonderful and enjoyable atmosphere. \n\nThe service and so was everything else. I will return.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5474, 'MoSande', 'James Gichuru Road', 'Pallet Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d17654764-r685196469-Pallet_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Delightful breakfast experience ', 'It wasn\'t my first time breakfasting at Pallet Caf√©, but it was a first in the cold season. To my delight, as soon as we were seated our server brought us a jiko for warmth. Not long after, I wore my jacket, silently wishing I\'d worn pants rather than a dress - my legs were so cold. Immediately, he brought me a blanket to cover my legs. I was touched by his mindfulness. And the food, as always, was delicious. I really like the meal portions- just enough and not too much. Pallet Caf√© is set to become my dining room away from home.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:33:35', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5475, 'Tessa F', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r924500011-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Bad acrid smoke filled experience', 'They were making waffles and the restaurant filled up with acrid smoke. Not a single wait or came round to apologise for the smoke. Was so bad some people including myself left. Not a good experience for a quiet coffee on a Saturday morning. My clothes stink if waffle oil. ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'negative', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
