(5495, 'Michael K', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r668136316-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Nice oasis away from it all.', 'Located in an office building and just off the main road, this was an incredibly peaceful retreat on a Sunday afternoon. Coffee is upscale and you have your choice of three types of brewing methods. There are two bean choices (dark/ medium roast); but a few single origins available for purchase as whole bean. It would be awesome if they had those available to drink there as well. Still, I like the place.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5496, 'Johan S', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r663996702-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Good coffee served with hipster-vibes', 'This sleek coffee-place offers a good space for a couple of hours of work, just off the main thoroughfare between city centre and Westlands.\nThe ambiance is spot on, and clientele an interesting mix of Kenyan students at the neighbouring university, expat young professionals, and ageing Indian business people.\nCoffee is the main focus on the menu with all the drip, press, and espresso varieties you can imagine. I\'ve had a few bad experiences with the foam on cappuccinos being thin and quick to dissolve. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
