(5503, 'wer0ny', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r606225235-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'The best coffee and pastries in town', 'Great ambiance, staff and the best coffee in Nairobi. Secure and in a great area of town i spent most of my mornings in Nairobi here.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5504, 'Sammy M', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r585818901-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Great coffee!', 'Peaceful location and ideal for brief business meetings. The service is fast and the coffee is amazing.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5505, '0504Traveller', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r574409433-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Good Coffee and Nice pastries, but slow service', 'Kenya is known for their coffee so I wanted to get some coffee to take home.  A lot of people had told me Connect Coffee was the best place so I went there.  Overall, they make good hot chocolate and the pastries are good, but the service is slow; REALLY SLOW.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5506, 'G1103BLchristinec', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r554106086-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Best coffee in Nairobi hands down', 'I have lived in Or around Nairobi for 5 years. I often work form coffee shops as my office is 45 minutes out of town. Connect has decent internet. Sometimes my computers does not want to connect right away but I somehow always get it. The five stars comes because not only is the environment great for either work or catching up with someone, but the coffee is amazing. It‚Äôs is the only good cold brew I have had in Nairobi and they have lots of options. I can‚Äôt recommend their coffee enough, get a bag of beans as well. I recommend the Romeo blend. This has been given to me as a present because it‚Äôs just that good!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5507, 'Miss Biwott', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r553606775-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing WAFFLES & perfect Ambiance.', 'With all the rave about this coffee joint, we { my sister & I had to give in}.\nDate: 13th Jan, 2018 \nFIRST IMPRESSION:\nWe walk in, and the smell of freshly brewed coffee woke up every sensory organ in us. I thought I could literary taste it on my tongue. We look around the, it\'s was almost 89% full. Believe us when we say, its a very small space - roughly it can fit comfortably about 20- 25 people from the original set up. I would say, this cafe would be great for a date, morning official meetings, discussion group, family time and parties.\nOver the counter, the list on the menu is right above the counter - with about 4 gentlemen each having a different task - I believe, and 1 lady by the far right of the counter, seriously and busy grinding the coffee beans into this huge coffee machine that is done in open space. We spotted empty seats at the right overlooking the parking lot, since the glass barrier is super clear with connect coffee stickers on it in a stripe formula, with raised bar stools - then settled there.\n\nThis being our first time there, these are the things to consider if you are a newbie:\n\n#1. Its\' a self service Environment.\n\nYou walk in, look around, spot a seat {Pray that no one takes it}, walk over the counter, place your order - pay, then back to your table and wait for food/drink.\n.\n#2. Professionalism & friendly staff\nIts\' such a breath of fresh air to receive the simplest gestures like a greeting from the staff and made to feel comfortable. That\'s what we were received with.\n.\n#3. You\'ve got to try out their WAFFLES!!! OMG - Amazing!!\nApart from the coffee, get yourself waffles. You definitely deserve it, because it\'s done so well, the plating, presentation and deliciousness is beyond words. AMAZING!!\n.\n#4. Is it worth the Money & Fuss? \nYES!! YES!! YES!! \nIts\' not expensive neither is it cheap. The waffles and Coffee is of pure quality. I totally recommend them. We actually had - waffles and Mocha Milkshake. Yum!!\n.\n#5. Why WIFI - why??\nYes, they have WIFI connectivity, and yes its absolutely free. The problem is, give or take every 8 to 12 mins of the first input of the password, it disables again and you have to input the password again. Who has that time?? It\'s annoying - FYI- when using a cell phone, not sure if using your laptop.\n.\n#6. Be watchful when buying bottled water.\nNot sure if this was just this particular bottle of water, but even before we removed the wrap and opened the bottle, we could see \"floating fishes\". White particles in the water. Disturbing as it may have seemed then, we alerted the waiters and they immediately took action and replace us with another clean bottled water. I\'m not brushing it completely, but be watchful!!\n.\n#7. Decor is Classy.\nPersonally, I am a super fan of classy decor, and they\'ve got it. Fresh but classy especially the design and lighting.\n.\nMy rate - 8/10\nI look forward to sample it\'s other list on the menu and enjoy that space with more friends and family.\n\n', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\", \"events_entertainment\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5508, 'worldtravelaur', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r549547135-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Best Aeropress in Kenya', 'When we arrived at Connect Coffee we saw that they recently won Kenya\'s National Aeropress Competition. The winning barista happened to be working that day and we were able to try it ourselves - one of the best cups of coffee I have ever tasted! The cafe has a great vibe and the staff were super warm, welcoming, and friendly. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5509, 'Nate D', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r549546984-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Wow! Amazing coffee!', 'This place was close to the hotel we stayed at, and we were so glad we made it here!\n\nThe shop has all of the coffee gadgets for sale that you expect at a premier coffee place like Chemexs, Aeropresses, etc. We were pumped to see that one of their baristas won the best Aeropress in Kenya! Obviously, we tried it and holy smokes! It was incredible.\n\nConnect Coffee has a couple of blends they do and some single origin beans. The coffees they brewed for us were about as good as those we\'ve had at Origin and Rosetta in Cape Town!\n\nWe bought bags of their Romeo blend and Juliet blend to take back home too. They were also awesome!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5510, 'Vivian S', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r538463244-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Best coffee in Nairobi ', 'Fantastic espresso and waffle. Probably the only cafe you can get proper coffee in Nairobi. Good for solo trips, business meetings and casual meet ups with friends. Serene location. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5511, 'Monica G', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r514452562-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Japanese coffee addiction', 'Connect is very conveniently located around the vicinity of the Chiromo Campus of the Nairobi University hence pulls the young customers opting for a place beyond their university yet close by. The coffee making is unique and served with personal attention. One could opt for their choice of the strength of either flavor of coffee they desire.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5512, 'Peter P', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r511278327-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Best coffee in Kenya', 'Best coffee in Kenya by far. Along with Puzzle Coffee in Zanzibar, the two best places to get coffee in east Africa outside of Ethiopia.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"drinks\"]'),
(5513, 'Yasmin M', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r506667262-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Delicious coffee', 'Did a quick takeout of a caramel macchiato and a Romeo blend long black - both were delicious. It was actually really good coffee and you rarely get that here! Service was good, ambience was great- looking forward to going back!\nMy only qualm is the naming of the coffee blends- Romeo is the strong blend, Juliet is the weaker blend (as the nice man at the counter explained to me) hmmmmm....', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5514, 'Elke', 'Riverside drive road Ground floor Riverfront building', 'Connect Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d12076406-r506473888-Connect_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Finally great coffee in Nairobi', 'Glad to have discovered Connect Coffee. A micro-roaster offering excellent coffee in Nairobi. Only good things - the coffee of course, but also the interior, the cups, etc  ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:35:40', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
