(5541, 'TravellingKE', 'Argwings Kodhek Road Timau Plaza', 'Kesh Kesh Coffee Roastery & Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d13505255-r621687394-Kesh_Kesh_Coffee_Roastery_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Brilliant ambience. Great food.  But visit when the owner is there.', 'The ambience is just fantastic, very chic, very rustic, lovely warm lighting that wants you to look around and experience the Eritrean coffee culture. The food is always delicious. I would just go at a time of day when they are busy (sounds counterintuitive) so the bread (injera) is not dried up and hard. The coffee - very sadly - despite the hype, fell short. Had a chat with the owner so will spare the details. But will leave you to experience this place objectively and hopefully enjoy it as I did my first time because my first visit there was just fantastic from friendly staff, to amazing food and a bill that was not arbitrary. But I have to add that the first time I went, the owner was present and I believe that made the whole difference. Based on that experience, I took a friend there another time and it was at best, \'a stressful lunch\' of many things going wrong. Overall, I remain optimistic and hope to return again if a little skeptical. Definitely let it make its impression on you and share your reviews.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:37:53', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5542, 'Shan B', 'Argwings Kodhek Road Timau Plaza', 'Kesh Kesh Coffee Roastery & Cafe', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d13505255-r592097832-Kesh_Kesh_Coffee_Roastery_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'A delightful find', 'I needed a quick, quiet place in Kilimani to have a lunch meeting and was asked to go to Subway in Timau Plaza.\n\nTo my delight T Plaza also has an Eritrean Cafe called Kesh Kesh.  Sunny, with a bar, and delicious cappucino, an indoor area, and outdoor verandah, this place is such a find!!!\n\nWe sat outside and ordered Zigne and Shiro (beef stew and lentil curry paste).. and it came with brown ijera \n\nThe airy, efficient ambiance makes the blending of Eritrean cuisine and modern cafe life quite a delightful change.  It is my new go to place for easy meetings :D', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:37:53', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"speed_wait\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
