(5589, 'Hermes_NL üá≥üá±', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r1000638269-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Great coffee after visiting Karen Blixen museum', 'Point Zero coffee is at the beautifully manicured site of the Karen Blixen museum. Great chance to relax and have a good quality coffee after the guided tour of the museum. Also cakes and lunch available.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5590, 'CDFBologna', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r991753121-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent, try the Italian roast', 'Very nice, superbly decorated caf√© with top quality beans in a wonderful parc. You can also have a couple of things to it and we saw some very cute cats.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[]'),
(5591, 'Aaron S', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r970996583-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'So good', 'After our 10 day safari, this was the best food we had!! The meal was full of flavor, the coffee was delicious and the service was friendly and fast', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"speed_wait\"]'),
(5592, 'Penny g', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r967758258-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Coffee is spot on', 'Super lovely people work here . Great coffee and you can purchase beans and they grind them for you. Which we did. The cakes are to be recommended.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5593, 'Tina R', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r858857781-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Great stop for coffee', 'Super cute coffee shop with extremely kind staff. The carrot cake and veggie pies are amazing. The staff carefully creates a variety of drinks including mochas and macchiatos. Check it out after your Blixen tour!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5594, 'nabeab', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r857610169-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Re-open!!!', 'We got to go the first day they were back and had a great experience!\nGo sip a cup of tea or anything like the butter croissants üòÄ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5595, 'thesheikhfromdubai', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r728742545-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden gem', 'Nyayo House is the place foreignors need to do their visa things. The ultimate fortress of bureaucracy. Try to avoid. If you can\'t you really need to visit Point Zero, the small, but very cizy coffee place. Small, but the staff is extremely friendly and customer focussed and there is a great vibe. I ordered my usual double espresso, but sadly the machine didn\'t work. To compensate I was offered a free brewed coffee instead. I happily ordered and will pay for a cold water instead. But the fact they offered is great. If you go there, try their chocolate Zuchinni bread. The ultimate chocolat experience. Not many coffee houses offer the same service and ambiance. It\'s located between Nyayo House and the museum.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5596, 'CM J', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r710901087-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Quiet Covered seating', 'Pleasant atmosphere to chill and relax before or after visiting the gallery. Enjoyed the dawa and lemon cake.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
(5597, 'Vanessa', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r682231410-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'funky spot to reflect on the Nairobi gallery', 'Loved the simple but fun space. I had a cappuccino and chocolate and courgette cake to rest up a bit after a long walk and absorbing view of the gallery - both were delicious! The whole of downtown seemed very expensive - this place is also pricey but the coffee and cake were really yum so worth it. Really a gem', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5598, 'Lyndsey M', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r652033727-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Super place to destress from Nyayo House!', 'I did not actually eat here but I had a very good coffee and some friends had a bite here yesterday and they said it was good.  It is really a very atmospheric little place and a super place to wait for someone who is tackling the queues at Nyayo house.  Wifi.  Clean loo and the museum is very sweet in a wonderful historic building.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5599, 'Laura', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r608851985-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Really quite place in the city center', 'Great place to escape the hectic of CBD! Really friendly and helpful staff and great coffee :)\nLittle bit hard to find, as it is in the ‚Äûfrontyard‚Äú of a big building (but signs outside will show, just enter through the big gate)', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5600, 'Mzungubabe', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r583223622-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden oasis in the city', 'This is a great place for either a quick coffee or a longer, more leisurely snack.  Safe, cheap parking is also available for customers.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"speed_wait\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5601, 'Nyobu', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r491484486-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Great coffee shop a hidden gem in Nairobi', 'I was pleasantly surprised to find this wonderful gem in Nairobi CBD located right next to Nyayo House which I could aptly describe as an archaic Government building where one can get almost every Government service imaginable. Pointzero coffee shop is located in the same compound as the Nairobi gallery which houses some great artwork and collectibles which define the history of this great country. The service (with a smile) was excellent. The Kenya AA Blue Mountain Coffee was superb and a great change from the usual coffee dredge we have grown accustomed to in Nairobi. I will definitely be back soon. Keep up the good work.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5602, 'Clement Waigwa', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r480420400-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'best coffee', 'The cafe at  the Nairobi gallery have good style of mixing their coffee i liked the taste of several i tried in a single day\nlovely waiters who always have a smile to welcome you to the venue \ni love their bites as well and by that i reference them to coffee lovers \nits a good joint for simple meetings or hook up', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5603, 'Osman Your Tour Guide', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r478065540-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Nice place inside Nairobi Gellery', 'I enjoyed some tea there, the service was very good and tea taste was very good as well but the price was little bit high.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\"]'),
(5604, 'Laughing Owl', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r469294197-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Best coffee shop in the cbd!!!!!!!!!!', 'This place is a gem. It is so beautiful was wishing it was empty so i could take pictures. The menu is limited enough to offer the essentials. Their coffee is amazing especially when you dont add sugar or syrup, you can really appreciate a good coffeee bean. The greengram samosas are a must try with their homemade kachumbari. Bar none the best coffee shop in town if not in Nairobi. Try it, you will not be disappointed.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5605, 'Nyam B', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r449825898-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'The Coffee Depot', 'The difference between coffee and coffee. Journey through the finest and rarest Kenya coffee options guided by the most hospitable best informed staff in Nairobi. Little gem in a bustling city next to an art gallery. Hideaway one doesn\'t want too many people to know about. The kind of place you want to be a part of. On top of that they have entwined literature and aroma labs into the mix. Oh the senses!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\"]'),
(5606, 'Tiger-Kenya', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r401782332-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Quirky & Artsy', 'Their Blue Mountain Kenyan Coffee was amazing; the staff were enthusiastic and is an oasis of peace in the midst of chaotic Nairobi. This is the true centre of Nairobi as all official distances from and to Nairobi are marked from this point (hence the name) set in the former Provincial Commisioner\'s Building (Now part of the National Museums of Kenya and called The Nairobi Gallery)', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5607, 'Brian O. M', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r387562898-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Serene, Quiet, Cool', 'A quiet cool place, ideal for various kinds of meetings, coffee dates. With zero artificial noises. Pocket friendly prices too', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5608, 'Valerie N', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r386949405-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Serene Environment', 'Despite being located in the City the Coffee shop provides a serene environment ideal for meeting with friends, business meetings and a space to do personal work as you enjoy the coffee. The service is excellent and the managers very friendly.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5609, 'IronManKenya', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r382689885-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'They have fresh food and tasty pastries to go with your coffee', 'This is a beautiful coffee house right in the Nairobi city centre. Fresh coffee, well trained staff and a location so refreshing its worth raving about.\nLocated right in the Nairobi city centre ( next to the Nairobi Gallery). The experience is like no other. Sounds of a busy city play quietly in the background to create a perfect ambience for a good  stress free cup of fresh coffee.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5610, 'Mel M', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r351816639-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Oasis in the middle of the city', 'Pointzero coffee is delicious so I was keen to visit the cafe. The space is cosy and quiet, providing a pleasant refreshment in the middle of the city. ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5611, 'Beth K', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r342160638-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent coffee in cute spot', 'Enjoyed a wonderfully smooth latte and carrot cake at this little known nook in Nairobi. Coffee was so good, bought a bag to go. The location also gave me the chance to step into The Nairobi Gallery to view the Murumbi African Heritage Collection. I have driven passed this place for years, and was glad I finally got to visit. I\'ll be back to enjoy more of the coffee and the exhibition.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"drinks\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5612, 'david_waweru', 'Karen Blixen Museum Karen Road', 'Pointzero Coffee', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d9229882-r330526193-Pointzero_Coffee-Nairobi.html', 'Pointzero Coffee stands out!', 'I know my coffee. I know what to look for in coffee. The smoothness. The complexity. The aroma. The flavor. Pointzero Coffee, the little restaurant located at The Nairobi Gallery gave me just that. And I was there long enough to have my favorite Mocha. And then brewed coffee with a delicious chicken pie. Then the proprietors asked if I could try their Espresso Macchiato... I did after a tour of the gallery next door. So I finally left feeling, eeerrrr... spoilt! Excellent.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:41:55', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"location_access\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5613, 'Peter S', 'Yalla Towers. 3rd flr, Junction of Koinange St. and Biashara St.', 'Valley Coffee Shake', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5570668-r1019217474-Valley_Coffee_Shake-Nairobi.html', 'Great alternative to the more well-known establishments.', 'Situated on the third floor of a small mall down a side street (Biashara Street), this is a great alternative to the more well-known and more expensive cafes on the main streets of central Nairobi.\nGood selection of food and drinks, friendly and efficient service - and, of course, competitive pricing. Great value for money, and worth seeking out.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:45:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\", \"menu_variety\", \"portion_size\"]'),
(5614, 'Peter S', 'Yalla Towers. 3rd flr, Junction of Koinange St. and Biashara St.', 'Valley Coffee Shake', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5570668-r982562729-Valley_Coffee_Shake-Nairobi.html', 'Good value, friendly service.', 'Our second visit, (previous one was six months ago), and we remain very happy with everything. A comprehensive menu, good value, good service and tasty food. I was particularly impressed with their speciality drinks.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:45:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"drinks\", \"service\", \"price_value\", \"menu_variety\", \"overall_experience\"]'),
(5615, 'Peter S', 'Yalla Towers. 3rd flr, Junction of Koinange St. and Biashara St.', 'Valley Coffee Shake', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5570668-r960024364-Valley_Coffee_Shake-Nairobi.html', 'Worth seeking out.', 'This is worth seeking out. Not far from CJs, much quieter, much better value for money. Food was plentiful, lots of it, good quality, and excellent value for money. Lots of space inside - tables are not on top of each other.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:45:15', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"price_value\", \"atmosphere\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5616, 'Maja Nielsen', 'Yalla Towers. 3rd flr, Junction of Koinange St. and Biashara St.', 'Valley Coffee Shake', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d5570668-r884234623-Valley_Coffee_Shake-Nairobi.html', 'Healthy & Delicious Breakfast', 'Had a delicious BREAKFAST - their \"Signature...\", all vegetarian + (Egg) Mexican omelet - everything was fresh and tasty, I especially liked the golden toast, buttered sublimely ;-) On the side I had a excellent double espresso, Arabica ‚òïÔ∏è', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:45:15', 'positive', '[\"food\"]');
