(5724, 'PinoCipolla', 'Ground Floor,The Rhapta Promenade Mall, Rhapta Road', 'La Terrazza Italian Restaurant & Caf√©', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15360946-r813008802-La_Terrazza_Italian_Restaurant_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'The soul of Murielle', 'When a person at the peak of his career decides to open a restaurant 10 hours far by plane from his native place, the greatest risk is to have to distort his own characteristics, to make his soul clear to the world, completely independent with respect to security of the parent company, let\'s call it that, and having to face a hard path away from its own references. This is what happened to the dynamic co-owner of La Terrazza, a shining star in the panorama of Italian restaurants around the world, Ms. Murielle, a Frenchwoman who is bursting with energy like a new star of the galaxy. An indefinable vital force that leads it to be the precious engine of this restaurant, and that gives it that \"sixth sense\" that women entrepreneurs are more gifted with than us men. Murielle makes use of many smart people, the nice Stefano, sommelier and administrative mind of the place, and the various collaborators that are worth mentioning: Makau, Said, Tunge, Didi, Gedion and the kitchen team: Thomas, Rafael and Stephan. Let\'s talk about the place: young but classic and colored by the paintings of the excellent Tomasi, all between elegance, style and class, with adequate and non-invasive background music. Let\'s talk about the menu: I chose an antipasto based on Cipriani carpaccio, followed by an excellent dish of ricotta and spinach ravioli, and a very fillet (the meat is really delicious), with a tiramisu as a worthy finish. And I must also say about the wine list because I have seen and studied it, I drank some excellent wine from the Lagrein Winery. Next time I will go to the bottom of the other wineries! The desserts are splendid, and - let me tell you - the bread basket assortment is incredibly good. The bread that Murielle makes is worth the trip alone! Impeccably cared for service, the bill absolutely justified by the quality, and in fact I will be back, indeed I thanked those who recommended La Terrazza to me, because I was really good and this place deserves the influx of Italians and real gourmets who are in Nairobi .\nIn conclusion: a very pleasant restaurant, one of those that deservedly end up on the front page of specialized newspapers, but above all, in our hearts, it goes and will remain.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:50:47', 'positive', '[\"service\", \"price_value\", \"location_access\"]'),
(5725, 'Man from Jumanji', 'Ground Floor,The Rhapta Promenade Mall, Rhapta Road', 'La Terrazza Italian Restaurant & Caf√©', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d15360946-r808575302-La_Terrazza_Italian_Restaurant_Cafe-Nairobi.html', 'Overall great experience.', 'The ambience and views from the terrace were amazing. We had pasta dish to die for and the pizza was authentic Italian. Great customer service and the art gallery had some great pieces.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 19:50:47', 'positive', '[\"food\", \"service\", \"atmosphere\"]'),
