(5964, 'Muadh A', 'Mombasa Road Mombasa Road', 'Drip Burgers', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d26486272-r916251161-Drip_Burgers-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing burgers', 'Really changed the burger game. The best in town I would say, plus they have a 50% of on every Wednesday.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-24 20:28:02', 'positive', '[\"food\"]'),
(5965, 'Adewale O', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r1024159002-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'The 3 course meal paired with wine was excellwnt', 'Best restaurant in Nairobi in my humble opinion. The chef Harold is a Michelin 5 star with experience in Los Angeles and New York. He really does know his stuff.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5966, 'Alex V', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r987682716-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Great but the 10% service charge doesn‚Äôt go to the waitstaff.', 'The food is delicious especially if you have the 4 course off the menu. Flavors are bold & hearty. Highly recommend \n\nHowever the reason why it‚Äôs NOT a 5 star ‚≠êÔ∏è is because they have a 10% service charge ABOVE  the 16% VAT & 2% catering levy that DOESN‚ÄôT go to the tipping jar. \n\nEssentially, without being aware, you‚Äôd leave thinking the 10%!additional goes to them but alas! It doesn‚Äôt. \nUncouth behavior from the owner.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5967, 'Hardsome O', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r968577528-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Fantastic location with everything one could want', 'I now consider 45 Degrees Kitchen to be my favorite restaurant in Nairobi after our fantastic four-course lunch there! Each course was very tasty, made with fresh ingredients, and well presented. The atmosphere of the restaurant is quaint, rustic, and unpretentious. And the staff are friendly. Overall, very good value for money. If you like good food, you will not be disappointed. We will attempt the wine pairing the next time.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5968, 'MRSlowLoris', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r965149891-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Among the very best food in Nairobi', 'Among the very best food that Nairobi has to offer. The location feels a bit far but its not that difficult to reach and a cozy garden setup. But the real star is the food, fresh tasty, creative. Good portion sizes. Get the set menu and combine it with the wine. We will go more regularly.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5969, 'N W', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r955123965-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Amazingly delicious!!', 'Just delicious  !!!! \nBeyond my expectations.  Service was excellent! Every meal was served with it\'s special wine/drink. \nWould recommend anytime !', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5970, 'Hans Erik H', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r937702767-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Gott, sera gott ', 'Gott, sera gott. Vit v√≥ru ein b√≥lkur vi√∞ 22 f√≥lkum, sum v√≥ru har til eina f√Ωrar√¶tta√∞a matskr√°. Vit kundu velja √≠millum nakrar ver√∞ar til hv√∏nn av r√¶ttunum. Men fyrst fingu vit √∏ll ein for-forr√¶tt, sum var brey√∞ vi√∞ onkrum gr√∏num √°. Til forr√¶tt fekk eg gr√∏nt salat vi√∞ millum anna√∞ parmesan og valn√∏tum. Tann n√¶st r√¶tturin var gnocchi vi√∞ millum anna√∞ aubergine. H√∏vu√∞sr√¶tturin var grilla√∞ur fiskur vi√∞ r√≠si og onkrum √∏√∞rum til. Oman√° fekk eg eina dessert vi√∞ saltkaramel og berjum. Afturvi√∞ v√≥ru ymisk sl√∏g av v√≠ni. V√¶lsmakkandi matur √≠ einum hugnaligum umhv√∏rvi. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5971, 'Diane D', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r888498031-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Great food & wine, amazing patio, I will be coming back. ', 'I love lamb and eat it where ever I go so I tried the Mongolian Lamb and was not disappointed.  It was a generous portion and the spices were perfect!  The wine the chef pared with it was a beautiful compliment. I was so happy to meet Chef Harold too. \nI came when it was raining so I was inside, which was really cozy and stylish.  I will be coming back though so I can experience this patio.  Just the place to relax with friends under a string of lights. One thing I enjoyed was the ride here and the quiet.  I can see why so many people have recommended the place. \nI come to Nairobi often for my work from San Francisco and enjoy fine food.  I will be coming to 45 Degrees again soon.  Highly recommended. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5972, 'Kemitooma', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r882149707-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Just like mama\'s cooking', 'There\'s something about the food that takes your taste buds back to childhood. How do I explain how my experience at 45¬∞ led me to a decision to go back home_ a place I hadn\'t been in years? There\'s an aura of peace and air so serene you might forget to go back home. And in case that happens you can spend the night and wake up to birds chirping and cows mooing. If you didnt grow up on a farm pay this place a visit to experience a beautiful morning. A warm reception, an over the top hospitality.\nKudos to Chef Harold!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5973, 'Kenyan Nomad', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r873419684-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing Food!', 'Fantastic Cuisine! \n\nI visited this restaurant on Christmas Day with my mom and had a FABULOUS Christmas lunch! We had a choice of 2 menus - 3 course & course - each accompanied by a glass of wine. We chose the 4-course menu at a slightly higher price but we were not disappointed. The portions were good and more importantly, fresh and creative! We even got a free aperitif. The entire culinary experience was quite heavenly even though service from the 2 waitresses on duty could have been better in terms of speed and friendliness. Nonetheless, the restaurant owner did indicate that they didn‚Äôt have such a high number of reservations to warrant having a bigger number of staff on this day.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5974, 'Kiley R', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r870006504-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing food + fantastic people', '45 degrees is more then a restaurant. It‚Äôs a community, a home, and a place that knows food! With their large menu they cater to many cravings and dietary needs. As a vegetarian I found they had many items on the menu to meet my needs and all so delicious. I rented the studio on the property for a few days so was able to try several of the dished from morning to night and all were satisfyingly delicious. Harold and his lovely staff all welcome you with smiles and are very kind and hospitable. I loved my time here and will definitely visit again the next time I‚Äôm in Nairobi!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5975, 'Kristina N', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r863674115-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing Food, Lovely Ambiance', 'We spent a sun-filled, peaceful afternoon at 45 Degrees. It was our first time eating at the restaurant and it was a wonderful experience. It\'s off the beaten path but easy to find. The food was delightful to look at and absolutely delicious. It was beautifully presented - purple and yellow cauliflower - and the flavors just burst in my mouth. We chose the 4-course meal and each dish that came was as delicious as the last. They also serve a glass of wine with each course - well-selected and all as part of the 4-course price. The whole experience was amazing and I\'ve already recommended the restaurant to several friends.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5976, 'holidaylover55', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r848357670-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden Gem', 'This restaurant is located in a house in a residential area. We decided to have the wine paired menu. The decor is shabby chic. When the food arrived we where not disappointed. The presentation was fantastic and the taste even better. The chef defiantly knows his craft. They have a great selection of wines and cocktails. The entire experience was amazing. One thing I might add is that it is quite pricy. Ideal for a special occasion.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5977, 'Rachel S', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r835310768-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'The Perfect Birthday Dinner', 'We landed in Nairobi on March 31st, my 52 birthday. This was the 2nd dinner party I had planned at 45 Degree Kitchen. The first, was for my 51st birthday, but unfortunately, the restaurant was closed due to COVID-19.\n\nThis year, we made it happen. A dinner party for 9 people on a beautiful evening!\n\nThe food was spectacular, from beginning to end. The service was unparalleled. \n\nWe had heard of this restaurant from the Afrikan Traveler, who is a native to Kenya and he spends his time learning about the different places and businesses in and around Kenya. When my husband and  I saw the episode at 45 Degree Kitchen, I knew I wanted to go and experience eating there.\n\nThank you Rose and Harold for the amazing dinner and experience!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5978, 'S S', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r834253985-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Totally overated', 'A friend had talked so much about this restaurant that I decided to give it a shot. I planned a special date there and was totally disappointed. The food looked good but was completely bland, no flavours. It was also ridiculously expensive and the place was intended to be rustic, except , there is a thin line between rustic and cheap. The seats were really uncomfortable. Very disappointed. Not worth all the hype unfortunately:(', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5979, 'Sandeep K', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r826169468-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Check whether the main chef is there before booking!', 'Went as a group of 6.. for a 4 course menu with wine pairing. \n\nThe food was very very average. Soups were served cold. The Risotto was a disaster, the desserts were okay at best.. the taste, the presentation left a lot to be desired  the meats were good .. but not great.\n\nThe wine pairing was a sham as all of us got the same wines irrespective of what we ordered..\n\nThat said.. my son had been to the restaurant and he swears by the great food. He had interacted with the Ghanian chef.. and the food that chef produced was masterclass. (I saw the photos). The learning is to check whether the chef is around.. before yiu book.\n\nThat said the service staff were good and tried their best. The food was served quickly.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5980, 'Thomas D', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r816066021-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Disappointing!', 'After hearing good reviews, we finally went to this place. The ambiance is nice, the accompanying wines are nice, but the rest was not. Definitely not a repeat visit from our end! \n\nThe place wants to portray itself as a \'gastronomic restaurant\', but tastes and dishes are fairly standard (agree, the plates are dressed up as if they come out of a Michelin book, but looks deceive). Soups were cold and blant, main dishes overloaded but OK. The deserts....we were given ice cream cake and some ice cream scoops. The ice cream scoops were from a very cheapo brand in Kenya (Diaryland), and the cake was likely from an even cheaper brand...Pure sugar and inedible junk. We were flabbergastered such a restaurant would serve us that and sell it as \'gastronomic\' food! We fell cheated, really, especially after paying such a hefty sum. Even ArtCafee or a similar chain restaurant serves waaay better deserts.', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5981, 'Curious_TravellerKE', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r766278449-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Masturdate spot', 'Perfect spot for a date with self or company. \nEnjoyed my meal as well. The ambience is quite relaxing and there is also a bit of rustic feel to the whole place. The place is a perfect hideout from the shenanigans of the city in the city üí¶\nI, however, felt the 10% service fee is deceiving; a lil bird whispered that it is not divided amongst those it is intended for. \nStarted with a bruschetta which was soooooooo fresh and tasted home made. \nThen had pepe soup which was a rip off; expectation was soooooooo high seeing as the place is owned by a West African national. The soup was basically beef soup full of royco and bit of pepper. \nThe main course was delish though; a sea food bowl üëçüèΩ I am a sea food lover so it ticked the hit box. \nFinished off with a tall glass of a mocktail made from grapes and berries; now that was an INSTANT HIT üèÜ', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5982, 'LanceNudd', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r741491127-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent Date Night', 'I have been to 45 Degrees several times and it has always been excellent. I usually get the four course menu with wine pairings which is about $60 (6,000 kes) per person. The first course was a wedge salad with a homemade caesar dressing. For the second course I had the Ahi Tartar and shared a shrimp taco with my partner. The shrimp taco has a teriyaki style sauce and a homemade hard tortilla shell and a nicely paired salad.\n\nFor the main course I had the wild mushroom risotto this time and my partner had the short ribs. The ribs were fall off the bone tender with creamy mashed potatoes and the veggies and mushrooms in the risotto were fresh and crisp.\n\nFor desert I always have the flourless chocolate cake which Chef Harold\'s is the best I have had.\n\nThere is a 10% service charge, but it goes to the staff there. I think that was put in place because there isn\'t much of a tipping culture in Kenya. I suggest on top of the service charge you tip another 5-10% to your server.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5983, 'Jonathan J', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r738687957-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Disappointed ', 'It has v cheap and poor interior. Food was good, but extremely expensive... But what was unacceptable was the owner (a Ghanaian) had in small letters on last page adds another 10% for service charge which does not go to the staff!!!!  When I said I did not wish to pay the service charge and I wanted to pay the staff directly, he was v rude and obstinate and then walked away. V poor behaviour.  ', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5984, 'Kevin G', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r734764151-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Christmas Buffet Feast', 'We visited 45 Degrees on Christmas Day and were treated to an amazing buffet made specially for the day. There was a wide variety of meat and vegetable dishes and delicious desserts. The setting is very peaceful and includes both outdoor and indoor sitting. Our server, Brian, was such a delight. Having worked tirelessly all day, he was still upbeat and eager to please during our early evening meal. He really enhanced our overall experience. All in all, a very special day.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5985, 'Angela Cohan', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r728922989-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'A memorable and beautiful culinary experience in Nairobi', 'Visiting 45 Degrees Kitchen and meeting Chef Harold Sena-Akoto was one of the culinary highlights of our trip to Kenya. The food was prepared using local produce. Chef Sena-Akoto graciously gave us a tour of his backyard, where he grows vegetables.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5986, 'Jess', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r723531410-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Unique fine dining experience in Nairobi ', 'Incredibly sophisticated and genuine place, a must if you are in Nairobi! The food is beyond expectations, fine dining using locally sourced ingredients. Very interesting menu and a beautifully relaxing atmosphere. The service is impeccable! The owner is a creative Ganean men, who lived for several years in the US, with his Kenyan wife who also grew up abroad, in Canada. Strongly recommended!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5987, 'David K', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r720778179-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Michelin comes to Nairobi', 'What a spectacular meal!   The ambiance is wonder.  We dined outside in the courtyard.   The staff was so warm and helpful.   We had the 4 course dinner which is an incredible value.  I enjoyed the wedge salad which was so fresh with an amazing dressing.  The crab cake was done perfectly.  Not too breaded and a delicious salsa on the side.   The prawn dish was wonderful.  I asked that it be served without shell and head and it was presented on a bed of the most delicious angle hair noodles.  The deserts are over the top fantastic.  I had the molten chocolate cake which could have been prepared by the best pastry chef in Europe.  We were lucky enough to meet Chef Harold for the USA who opened this restaurant a few years ago and Nairobi is so lucky to have him and his staff!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5988, '925katherine', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r705313657-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Anniversary special', 'Fantastic place. The service was amazing and the food was very very special. Harold the owner has done an amazing job. This place is a destination for our special occasions. What a find!! Every course was a signature dish. So impressive.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5989, 'Mary Wandia', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r695354717-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Best Food I Ever Had', 'My husband and I have been passing by this place everyday and we finally decided to pop in and see what it has to offer. Wow!!! We were pleasantly surprised. Ambiance is great but what was even more perfect was the food. Oh My Palate couldn‚Äôt even believe it, the food was amazing. We plan on going back very soon. \nLoved the menu too.... just know I‚Äôm coming back 45 degrees. I‚Äôm coming back.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', '');
INSERT INTO `restaurant_reviews` (`id`, `author_name`, `place_address`, `place_name`, `review_url`, `review_title`, `review_text`, `review_rating`, `location`, `created_at`, `predicted_sentiment`, `predicted_aspects`) VALUES
(5990, 'Madame_Trey', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r693695492-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Spectacular ', 'Those of you who follow my reviews, know I am very tempered in doling praise but 45 Degrees stands proudly as my favorite restaurant in Nairobi. \n\n45 Degrees starts off with a non descript gate, non descript parking and general laid back village feel.\nI was shocked and horrified and looked at my dining companion with distaste, thinking we were both foodies, yet he brings me to a place to which I can even feel the stomach cramps that are bound to torment me for the rest of the weekend. \n\nWalking into the dining area, the ambience is still casual rustic however the details start to pop out. Interesting art, creative chargers for the plates... \n\nThe first shock is when the simply typed menu is brought. Never in Kenya has a menu so thoroughly tantalized and excited me. Words cannot express the tingling feeling of the anticipation of a great meal (heightened in part by the unassuming arrival).\n\nWe opted for the 4 course food and wine pairing, perfect for a lazy, sunny Nairobi day. The food was INCREDIBLE. The best I\'ve ever had in Kenya and rivaling international heavy weights.\n\nThe wine selection for each course is unusual, not run of the mill and hand selected. Prices are on the higher side. \n\nWhen it comes to the food, each bite was lovingly thought out and expertly executed. The wine selections shocked and amazed, even for seasoned vinophiles such as ourselves. It\'s a great feeling to discover your next favorite wine.\n\nThere is something for everyone. The biggest challenge you will face is narrowing down your choices.\n\n45 Degrees is a special occasion dining option, not the type of noisy Sunday lunch place for kids with jumping castles and face painting.\n\nI can\'t wait to visit again. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5991, 'Cristi', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r692496471-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Has gone MASSIVELY down hill ', 'I have been here a few times over the years and I must say the food is now bordering terrible!!! We had my friend‚Äôs baby shower here today and there was 7 hungry ladies. We were the only people in the whole restaurant which isn‚Äôt a good sign. It started well with very helpful staff and the complementary bruschetta but it was a disaster from there.  \n\n2 of my pregnant girlfriends were served undercooked chicken! Food poisoning risk aside, their 2800 kes chicken Alfredo was also bland and tasteless. 2 of us ordered the so-called crab cake.  I‚Äôve had this here before and it was nice. But now it‚Äôs made from bright pink, salty imitation crab stick!!!  No real crab in site.  And for that price????!!! Really sad.  I don‚Äôt know if they have changed ownership or what but the food here is ridiculously overpriced terrible!!!!!!!!  \n\nLastly I tried to order a bottle of Prosecco form the list of 6 options. The waiter told me that unfortunately they were out of all but one! . Well the one that was available isn‚Äôt even Prosecco but a cheap sparking wine that costs 800-1200 KES  around town. The owner came out to (rudely) tell me he could give me a discount from 6000 kes to 5500 kes.   Thanks.  \n\nTo top it off we weren‚Äôt even offered an apology for the raw chicken and it remained on the bill. Please save yourself the disappointment and a don‚Äôt go here!!! \n', 2, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5992, 'Emma and Christ... L', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r668011169-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Culinary pleasure', 'The food and service is at the highest levels, and would get Michelin stars if it was located in Europe. Harold and his team delivers perfection and creativity from beginning to end with a focus on bringing out truly great flavors.\n\nThe modest but inviting courtyard of an old farm building is an appropriate setting for a restaurant and a chef who wants you to focus on the food, and delivers only the best with a quiet determination. The succulent and tasty meats are combined with vegetables that are so fresh and shining colorful that it is hard to believe, even when you know they are grown in the garden next to the house. The soups are packed with flavor and the desserts the perfect end. The wine pairing offered with the four course dinner (a bargain) was spectacular.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5993, 'Rebecca Vedova', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r653615751-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Fabulous Valentine\'s dinner', 'I was taken to 45 degrees for Valentine\'s day dinner. I was so excited because it was my second time there and I knew that once again, i\'d not only have a great time, but eat extremely well.\n\nI had the beef consomm√© as an entr√©e. I then had the dried tomato and sage (if I remember well) gnocchis, then the beef medallion with mash  and then the cheesecake. What a delight. I ate so well, I couldn\'t stop singing about it the following weekend. \nWhat I love about 45 degrees is their research for the menu. The dishes are original, delicious and very particular. I also love the ambiance, it is one of the prettiest places I\'ve been to and not pretentious at all. The staff is so kind and our waiter really took care of us. He also always made sure to fill our champagne glasses! Ha!\nI really think everyone should spoil themselves and go to 45 degrees at least once.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5994, 'viajar_boa', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r650032738-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Excellent experience form this hidden Nairobi gem', 'Food: The food was fresh, perfectly seasoned and well plated. Apart for the menu items we ordered, the chef was generous in offering us complimentary starters, appetizers and dessert.\n\nService: The service was A++. Our server was friendly,  attentive and  knowledgeable about the menu, helping guide us through the menu items. On our dinner visit here, we sat on outside veranda and were provided with blankets and insect repellent, which was a very thoughtful gesture. The chef/owner also took time out of his duties to introduce himself to us.\n \nAmbiance: The restaurant decor is simple and artsy. Good music.  \n\nValue: The prices can be viewed to be on the high side, but this is dependent on what one is willing to spend on eating out.\n\nSuggestions to management: Adding a few more plant features to provide some warm and liveliness to the space. Clarity on the  10% service charge added to the total cost; from previous dining experiences around Kenya my assumption is that, outside of VAT and catering and training levy, a service charge is at the discretion of the dinner.  \n\nOverall we had an amazing dining experience at 45 degrees.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5995, 'shauser2018', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r649338440-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Larger than a positive surprise', 'The gate hides everything, the surroundings indicate nothing. The layout is simple, spacious and well organized. The staff is very well trained, knowledgeable, polite and well humored. The menu is a bid long for a restaurant of this type but this is no negative aspect. The 4 course meal (my choice) was absolutely perfect. Main course grilled Ono (a fish) was announced to be either rare or medium rare (!) according to the waitress so I took the risk and do not regret. It was absolutely excellent.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5996, 'Sophie G', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r648688112-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing!', 'The place, the food, the people - amazing! Loved it so much and most of all the gnocchi with tomatoe sauce! I can highly recommend eating at 45 degrees in Nairobi! Btw dessert was amazing, too!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5997, 'Shenaz P', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r638465489-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Dinner at 45 Degree Kitchen', 'The best ever food . This place surprised me totally. Never thought of finding food of this caliber in Nairobi. Every dish fro start to finish was mouthwatering, and the presentation too was excellent. Well done Harold Sena-Akoto', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5998, 'Peter V', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r631268742-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Extensive, creative chef', 'This restaurant succeeds because of the close attention by its chef/owner.  The menu features several unique and creative offerings.  A three course menu is provided with excellent wine pairings.  Helpful service.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(5999, 'Joanna H', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r622832418-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Clean Plates ', 'Decided to try somewhere new. So glad we did. All five of us licked our plates clean. Waiting staff fabulous. Wine list enormous - but expensive. That‚Äôs the only issue we had. You need to visit this restaurant. ', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6000, 'Monica D', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r619078012-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Hidden Neighborhood Gem!', 'We went on a Tuesday night and had the whole place to ourself, regardless the service and food was damn good and the outdoor setting was impressive with local art work.  We got the wine pairing special (2 glasses) with three courses.  The wine offered was sub-par and the wine list was quit pricey even the local stuff was marked up quit a bit.  I\'m not sure if you can bring your own, I would opt fo r that next time.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6001, 'EVerghese', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r618447183-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Don‚Äôt judge this book by its cover', 'So, this is confusing - we travelled 45 mins through traffic (at the annoyance of my husband!) to get to this restaurant because of the good reviews. It took us quite a while to find as it‚Äôs on a residential road and in the dark, it‚Äôs quite unassuming. It was a very quiet day mid-week when we went and to be honest, my heart sank when I saw the decor! Very average - was feeling a bit cold so wanted to sit inside but it did not look very welcoming. The tablecloths were also drab looking. My heart sank a little further when I saw the menu - everything seemed very pricey. I finally settled on a fish stew, and my husband a fish dish. Then comes the magic...\nWe were essentially served a 4 course meal for the price of one course - some lovely bruschetta (with a small amount of prosecco), some surprisingly delicious cauliflower soup, our actual main course (which was excellent) and then a fantastic dessert - prior to that, the owner came out to greet us and we explained we had come from quite far and we were celebrating our anniversary. We were soon presented with a lovely plate of brownie and other small delights with a firework candle each - a lovely touch. \nBottom line - the decor doesn‚Äôt match the quality of service and food. It‚Äôs definitely an excellent restaurant and it‚Äôs worth paying the higher price for the quality of food. What I don‚Äôt understand is that upgrading the ambience wouldn‚Äôt cost much to rectify (e.g. put on some nice white table cloths) - if the owner reads this, I really hope he takes it on board. If we hadn‚Äôt travelled so far, we would have walked out before ordering. As it turns out, I‚Äôm glad we didn‚Äôt...\n\n5 stars for the food and service (rated 4 here because of the decor). ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6002, 'Krisje V', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r610515758-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Dinner & opera at a hidden gem', 'Spent an amazing night with friends, enjoying a wonderfull dinner. The great opera voices made it much more special. \nThe personal touch of chef Harold mades it      A unique place in Nairobi', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6003, 'Jackie M', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r601009298-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Rustic,Elegant restaurant', 'This is one of the best hidden gems in the city. The food is amazing,the owner pleasant and his wine selection is out of this world. Definitely the go to place with your boo for  Sunday afternoon brunch üòä.\nWorth the drive..\n', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6004, 'Foumi', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r596105910-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'The good, the bad, the ugly', 'The good\nI started with the good because clearly the food is to die for. Really tasty food. The owner came to discuss with us. It was my partners birthday and he loved the food very much.\n\nThe bad\nThe prices are out of this world. Jesus! You can\'t eat here regularly. Tooooooooo pricy. \n\nThe ugly\nClearly the owner intended the place to look like in a certain type of way. We were suprised when we found it.  it looked like an uncompleted house, really ugly! But it\'s a gem with great food. ', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6005, 'Deborah J', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r595478305-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Amazing organic and awesome delicious food.', 'never had a bad meal here ever and the staff are fantastic. The food is super healthy and made to perfection. Howard and Rose are amazing hosts and Howard is a super duper chef. They even do catering and do the most amazing job. My husbands 50th food every one raved about. Thank you 45 degrees for your divine food.', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6006, 'kathyhan1', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r588913120-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'If you can find it', 'The trip started already with the problem that one has to search for the place. There is a small sign - but hard to find.\nThe place looks fine, the food was ok (but not breathtaking) and in my opinion overpriced. Not value for money.\nThe waiters were a bit \"tip-hungry\"', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6007, 'gwere', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r587081120-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'A gem that keeps shining!', 'Never have I ever reviewed a restaurant twice. I have, however, visited restaurants and places more than once. 45 Degrees is a \'hidden\' gem that never disappoints! If the chef in this restaurant went to put her ( I just think it is a \'her\'!) culinary skills on the TV series \'Chopped\' they would carry the day, by a mile.\n\nThe menu here provides a wide variety of vegan, vegetarian and meat dishes. Each meal has an accompaniment of wines from Spain, Chile or SA. I went in for the crab cake as a second course after a nice hot and sweet bowl of butternut soup. The 3rd course was even better with a very well done and delicately served slice of salmon on a bed of avocado and asparagus. All this was accompanied by a sweetly scented and lavishly presented sparkling wine to \'clean the palate\' after each course.\nThe dessert was a flourless cake. And it was indeed. Nicely done and perfect! My friend went for the sirloin steak, medium rare and scallops on her third and second course respectively. It was a cold night, but the waiters provided us with a fire on a jiko and the chat and vibe was warm and very charming.\n\nI hope to visit the 45 degrees restaurant again for the third time. As they say: three times is always a charm!!', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6008, 'Keracare', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r586584684-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Rustic ambiance', 'The restaurant is hidden in a quiet suburb away from the hustle and bustle of city life. The interior and d√©cor is rustic. As we waited for our meal, the chef was very generous and offered us bitings and soup.\nThe food was superb the dessert exquisite.  The staff are welcoming.\nIn this cold Nairobi whether we were offered blankets to keep us warm.\nI will certainly go back.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6009, 'AdriAfrica', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r573041976-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Different and disappointing', 'We had heard a lot of good of this restaurant, but I am afraid we were not impressed.  We were there for lunch.  Perhaps it is a much nicer venue in the evenings.  The restaurant is located in an old farmhouse in a residential area.  During the day, everything looks very scruffy.  I suppose that is the look that is intended, but if you want to have a \"shabby chic\" place, the tablecloths, cutlery, plates and glasses must be immaculate and very attractive.  None of this.  Some tables had no tablecloths and those that did, did not even seem very clean.  Everything, or almost everything, happens outside (obviously try not to go there when it rains - though they do have some tables indoors).\nThe wines are very expensive.  Actually quite outrageously expensive, because they offer bottles that are available in wine shops in Nairobi and the prices are almost quadrupled.\nWe had the bisque.  It was ok, but really did not have much taste.\nThe steak was great and very tasty.  However the rice that accompanied it was tasteless.  I had the risotto with fish and prawns.  The fish was ok.  The risotto was absolutely terrible.  Actually it was the same as the rise accompanying the steak, so it was tasteless and full of mushrooms which really have nothing to do with the fish.  Perhaps a chef\'s speciality, but the mushrooms were not nice and I usually love them.\nWe had wine by the glass and our bill, for three people was over ksh20,000 which I believe is very high for the quality of food that we were served.  I am sorry, but I do not think we shall be returning soon.', 3, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6010, 'Mandevu', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r569800546-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Dinner', 'I had heard good things about this place and it did not disappoint.  The restaurant is located on 5 acres, with 2 bocci ball courts as well.  The atmosphere is vibrant with both indoor and out door seating.  The food was prepared to perfection.   Ask for Harold the owner who will stop by and visit with you!  Two Thumbs Up!\n', 5, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6011, 'Fantajan', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r561147986-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Special occasions deserve a special place', 'We chose Valentine\'s Day for our first visit to 45 Degrees. They were offering a four course dinner - with or without a wine pairing. You need to know upfront that this is not a budget friendly place. Come with a full wallet and an empty belly. That said, the food is incredibly fresh and well prepared. I really appreciated that there were at least two vegetarian options for every course. The meal started with complimentary bruschetta and  champagne. I had a really nice beet salad with a yogurt dressing - a flavor pairing I\'d never tried before. The artichoke and asparagus fritter was also quite nice. I was a little underwhelmed by the wild mushroom risotto which could have used a little more seasoning. The shared dessert plate was a nice end to the meal. The service was very good and attentive. And the venue is cozy, as if you were sitting on the patio of someone\'s farm house (which is precisely what it is). The owner/chef is affable and told us a bit about the history of the place. Definitely a gem in Nairobi but one that we\'ll likely reserve for special occasions given the price.', 4, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6012, 'greg7972018', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r557247137-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'BIGGEST RIP OFF IN THE WORLD', 'This is definitely the most expensive restaurant in the whole of Africa. The place is in a shack in the middle of no where. It is dusty and hot and dirty. Not worth the money!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6013, 'bhums18vansh', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r546164439-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Disgusting place. Unhygienic. Crazy high prices!', 'The food is average. But this is probably the dirtiest restaurant in Nairobi and probably in the top 3 most expensive restaurants in Africa. Kitchen is basic and looks filthy. The table cloths are stained and old. The parking lot is like a dusty dump yard. NOT worth a visit! Save your money and time!', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', ''),
(6014, 'Javed M', 'Marurui Road Garden Estate', '45 Degrees Kitchen', 'https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g294207-d8826537-r545875837-45_Degrees_Kitchen-Nairobi.html', 'Great food but poor ambience and super high prices', 'The food is very nice but would not pay that price for the whole experience - the place is not nice at all.The parking is dusty and the ambience that of a war zone. There are rags and flies everywhere. Feels like you have landed in a shack.', 1, 'Nairobi', '2025-11-25 08:31:59', '', '');
